impact: Austin burned the Giants for a 64-yard TD on the third play of the night. He had one catch after that, but added 15 yards on a reverse. Austin's touchdown was his first since 2016. Despite the big game, Austin should remain limited to a gadget role moving forward.
report: Tavon Austin caught two passes for 79 yards and a touchdown in Week 2 against the Giants.

impact: Incredibly, Austin has been on the receiving end of both of Dak Prescott's touchdown passes this year. Of course, we use the word "pass" very loosely as Prescott merely underhanded it to Austin for a three-yard pickup during garbage time. The 28-year-old has speed for days and can still be an entertaining gadget player, though he remains miles away from fantasy relevance.
report: Tavon Austin delivered three catches for two yards and a touchdown while gaining 18 yards on his lone carry Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 3 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: He was in and out of the game after coming down with a first-half shoulder injury. Austin seems to be okay, though obviously he wasn’t a factor on Sunday. The 28-year-old beat Darius Slay down the field on his lone target but dropped what should have been a relatively easy touchdown. Six years into his career, Austin still doesn’t have a real position. He’ll break off a big play here and there, but he’s not someone fantasy owners can count on for consistent production.
report: Tavon Austin failed to haul in his only target while adding a single carry for seven yards Sunday in Dallas’ Week 4 win over the Lions.

impact: Austin suffered a groin injury at the end of a third-quarter run and never returned. He is questionable for Week 7.
report: Tavon Austin corralled his only target for a five-yard gain while adding a pair of carries for 14 yards Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 6 win over the Jags.

impact: The Rams' tight ends are not usually involved in the offense, but that changed after both Brandin Cooks and Cooper Kupp left this game with concussions. Everett recorded all of his catches after Cooks left the game, and two of them came with Kupp out. He was also tackled at the one in the third quarter. If Cooks and Kupp are forced to sit, he could be a streaming option in deep two-tight end formats.
report: Gerald Everett hauled in all three of his targets for 24 yards in the Rams' Week 5 win over the Seahawks.

impact: The Rams' tight ends are not usually involved in the offense, but that changed after both Brandin Cooks and Cooper Kupp left this game with concussions. Everett recorded all of his catches after Cooks left the game, and two of them came with Kupp out. He was also tackled at the one in the third quarter. If Cooks and Kupp are forced to sit, he could be a streaming option in deep two-tight end formats.
report: Gerald Everett hauled in all three of his targets for 24 yards in the Rams' Week 5 win over the Seahawks.

impact: The Rams do not utilize their tight ends much, but both Everett and Tyler Higbee had solid games. Everett caught two passes to help set up a field goal just before halftime, and he converted a two-pointer to tie the game in the fourth quarter. This was Everett's first game with more than 25 yards this season. He is still only rosterable in Dynasty formats.
report: Gerald Everett hauled in 3-of-5 targets for 48 yards and a two-point conversion in the Rams' Week 9 loss to the Saints.

impact: The score was Everett's first of the year after he posted a season-high 48 yards in Week 9. He was actually out-produced by Tyler Higbee against the Seahawks. With Cooper Kupp (knee) potentially lost for the season, but Rams tight ends could be staring at bigger usage down the stretch.
report: Gerald Everett caught 2-of-2 targets for 15 yards and a touchdown in the Rams' Week 10 win over the Seahawks.

impact: Juszczyk was on the field for 68 of San Francisco's 98 offensive snaps. He showed well as a receiver, nabbing three catches for a team-leading 56 yards in the first half. This game was sort of a perfect storm for Juszczyk with Matt Breida (ankle) injured and the Niners playing from behind. Fullbacks have grown almost extinct in today's NFL but Juszczyk continues to play a prominent role both as a blocker and a pass-catcher. In fact, he may be the best receiving back the Niners have at the moment.
report: Kyle Juszczyk nabbed six catches for 75 yards on seven targets while adding one rush for 12 yards Sunday in San Francisco’s Week 5 loss to the Cardinals.

impact: Despite sitting out all of the fourth quarter due to cramps, Gurley did his fantasy backers right in the blowout win. He scored three times from short distance, and he backed up two of those scores with two-point conversions. Completely healthy -- Gurley was walking around the sidelines in the fourth and almost certainly would have reentered the game if not for the score -- Gurley will be the top overall running back option next week against the Chargers.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 19 times for 42 yards and three touchdowns and caught all three of his targets for 31 yards in the Rams' Week 2 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Gurley now has at least 19 carries in all three games. As he usually does, Gurley converted a goal line carry for his fourth touchdown of the year. With a 28-13 lead in the third quarter, Gurley was fed carries and the Chargers were unable to stop him. Through three games, Gurley is averaging 25.5 PPR points and will remain an elite RB1 against the Vikings on Thursday night.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 23 times for 105 yards and one touchdown and caught five passes for 51 yards in the Rams' Week 3 win over the Chargers.

impact: Gurley averaged just 3.5 yards per carry, but that does not matter on a day he scores three times. The first two came from two yards out, and the third was a five-yarder in the fourth quarter. Gurley almost had a fourth score, but he was ruled down at the one and then stuffed at the goal line on the next play in the second quarter. Gurley now had at least one score in every game and two three-touchdown performances in just five games. He will remain the overall RB1 next week in Denver.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 22 times for 77 yards and three touchdowns while catching 4-of-5 targets for 36 yards in the Rams' Week 5 win over the Seahawks.

impact: One week after Isaiah Crowell demolished the Broncos' crumbling run defense, Gurley wrecked it for a new career high in rushing yards. Gurley was ripping chunk gains essentially every time he touched the ball, averaging 7.42 yards per carry. For the season, Gurley's YPC now rests at 4.82, while he's scored 11 total touchdowns, putting him on pace for 29. Gurley should run all over the 49ers, who will be playing on a short week, in Week 7.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 28 times for 208 yards and a pair of touchdowns in the Rams' Week 6 win over the Broncos, adding two receptions for 17 additional yards.

impact: He scored a touchdown because that is what he does, but Gurley was mostly held in check in the first half. That changed in the third quarter when he went for nine and 18 yards on back-to-back carries, and he managed to find the end zone again from one yard out later that quarter. Following a long punt return, he ended his day and any doubt about the outcome of the game with a 12-yard touchdown catch on a screen pass in the fourth. That score gave Gurley 14 for the season and tied him with Priest Holmes for the most touchdowns through seven games in NFL history. He now has three games with three touchdowns this season and eight total the last three weeks. He will look to keep things going next week against the Packers.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 15 times for 63 yards and two touchdowns and caught 4-of-5 targets for 23 yards and another score in the Rams' Week 7 win over the 49ers.

impact: He scored a touchdown because that is what he does, but Gurley was mostly held in check in the first half. That changed in the third quarter when he went for nine and 18 yards on back-to-back carries, and he managed to find the end zone again from one yard out later that quarter. Following a long punt return, he ended his day and any doubt about the outcome of the game with a 12-yard touchdown catch on a screen pass in the fourth. That score gave Gurley 14 for the season and tied him with Priest Holmes for the most touchdowns through seven games in NFL history. He now has three games with three touchdowns this season and eight total the last three weeks. He will look to keep things going next week against the Packers.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 15 times for 63 yards and two touchdowns and caught 4-of-5 targets for 23 yards and another score in the Rams' Week 7 win over the 49ers.

impact: In a devastating moment for fantasy owners, Gurley passed up a 21-yard touchdown run on the Rams' game-sealing drive, opting instead to go down at the four so the Rams could run out the clock. It was unequivocally the right decision, though one Gurley might later regret as he pursues the single-season touchdown record. Gurley was often running into brick walls but still came out the other side with a 4.56 YPC. With the Pack doing an excellent job on Brandin Cooks and Robert Woods, Jared Goff kept targeting Gurley against S Jermaine Whitehead. Gurley has a tough Week 9 matchup in the Saints' lockdown run defense, but matchups do not matter for Sean McVay's primary touchdown scorer.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 25 times for 114 yards in the Rams' Week 8 win over the Packers, adding six receptions for 81 yards and a touchdown.

impact: Not to be outdone by Alvin Kamara’s fast start, Todd Gurley rumbled for a couple big plays on his opening drive including an eight-yard touchdown in which he beat the defense to the corner. He stalled a bit following that series, finishes the first half with "just" 34 total yards on nine touches. He got back on the right track on the second drive of the second half, making a good cut in the backfield to get loose for a 24-carry, but that was about it for the star back. This goes down as a "quiet" game by Gurley's standards, but he is still the RB11 heading into Sunday night, showing how ridiculously high he has set the bar. He will obviously be a must-start next week against the Seahawks.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 13 times for 68 yards and a touchdown and hauled in 6-of-7 targets for 11 yards in the Rams' Week 9 loss to the Saints.

impact: Running with a head of steam on a toss play, Gurley's 17-yard score was sprung by a big Robert Woods block. Gurley has now cleared 150 yards from scrimmage five times this season. He has 17 touchdowns in 10 games. He should threaten for 200 yards in next Monday's Mexico City showdown with the Chiefs.
report: Todd Gurley rushed 16 times for 120 yards and a touchdown in the Rams' Week 10 win over the Seahawks, adding three receptions for 40 additional yards.

impact: Dalvin Cook played every snap of the first two series before Murray opened the third series and then handled much of the clock-killing work in the fourth quarter.  Neither back found the end zone, while Murray wasn't targeted in the pass game.  Murray is little more than a handcuff to Cook owners.
report: Latavius Murray rushed 11 times for 42 yards in the Vikings' Week 1 win over the 49ers.

impact: Murray was stuck on two carries before Dalvin Cook left with a hamstring injury in overtime. That issue is reportedly minor -- Cook described it as a cramp -- but it is enough to keep Murray on fantasy rosters for now. That said, he is nothing more than a handcuff.
report: Latavius Murray rushed four times for 19 yards in the Vikings' Week 2 tie with the Packers.

impact: Oof. What initially appeared to be the perfect game script situation for Murray turned out to be an absolute nightmare for the Vikings' offense. Minnesota's offensive line was a travesty throughout the afternoon, allowing Kirk Cousins to be blindsided and fumble on the team's first two offensive possessions. By the time the Vikings got the ball back for their third possession, they were already staring down the barrel of a 17-0 deficit. Minnesota's backfield received a paltry four carries on the day, totaling 12 rushing yards (3.0 YPC). Murray's five catches fortunately salvaged what could've been an even bigger disaster of an outing. Dalvin Cook is expected to return on Thursday against the Rams.
report: Latavius Murray rushed two times for one yard and added five catches for 30 receiving yards in the Vikings' Week 3 loss to the Bills.

impact: It was yet another disappointing affair for a player who is now averaging 3.53 yards per carry. Ominously, Murray ceded both a red zone target and goal line carry to "Roc Thomas." If Dalvin Cook (hamstring) can ever get healthy, Murray might have a hard time carving out a role. For now, Cook seems unlikely to play in Week 6, leaving Murray in the desperation FLEX mix against the Cardinals.
report: Latavius Murray rushed 11 times for 42 yards in the Vikings' Week 5 win over the Eagles, adding two receptions for 14 additional yards.

impact: With Dalvin Cook out, Murray rebounded from his disappointing Week 5. He ripped the Cardinals for three 20-plus yard runs, with his touchdown coming on a highlight 21-yarder where he stiff-armed into the end-zone. Murray came into Sunday averaging just 3.5 YPC, but he made a case for a role when Dalvin Cook returns. Cook would be a plug-and-play RB2 if Cook isn't back for Week 7.
report: Latavius Murray rushed 24 times for 155 yards and a touchdown in the Vikings' Week 6 win over the Cardinals.

impact: He added two catches for 14 yards on a pair of targets.  Murray's first score was an 11-yard scamper up the middle, and the second was an untouched run through the left side from 38 yards away.  With Dalvin Cook still struggling to get healthy, Murray has emerged as a strong RB2 with reliable workloads.  If Cook sits again, Murray will again be in play Week 8 against the Saints.
report: Latavius Murray rushed 15 times for 69 yards and two touchdowns in the Vikings' Week 7 win over the Jets.

impact: He added two catches for 14 yards on a pair of targets.  Murray's first score was an 11-yard scamper up the middle, and the second was an untouched run through the left side from 38 yards away.  With Dalvin Cook still struggling to get healthy, Murray has emerged as a strong RB2 with reliable workloads.  If Cook sits again, Murray will again be in play Week 8 against the Saints.
report: Latavius Murray rushed 15 times for 69 yards and two touchdowns in the Vikings' Week 7 win over the Jets.

impact: Murray converted a goal-line carry after a pass interference set up first-and-goal from the one-yard line. He was stuffed on his only other goal-line chance. Murray didn't have much of a second half impact with the Saints dominating time of possession. He's scored a touchdown in three straight games with Dalvin Cook sidelined. Murray has played well enough to have a role even when Cook returns.
report: Latavius Murray had 13 carries for 56 yards and a touchdown and caught 5-of-6 targets for 39 yards in Week 8 against the Saints.

impact: He caught his lone target for 16 yards.  Murray made the start for the Vikings, but Dalvin Cook came in on third down the opening series and eventually ended up out-snapping and out-touching Murray.  Cook had a 70-yard run in his return from a hamstring injury and totaled 109 yards on 14 touches.  The Vikings are now headed into their bye, Cook is healthy, and Murray will now go back to 8-12 touches as the clear No. 2 back.  His RB1/2 days are over unless Cook gets hurt again.
report: Latavius Murray rushed 10 times for 31 yards and one touchdown in the Vikings' Week 9 win over the Lions.

impact: Murray took a backseat to a healthy Dalvin Cook this week. He had a few carries after Cook lost an early fumble, but wasn't able to do anything with his limited touches. Murray isn't more than a touchdown-dependent change-of-pace.
report: Latavius Murray rushed four times for five yards in Week 12 against Chicago.

impact: He led Buffalo in receiving in a game they only managed 107 yards. Jones saw more targets than Jeremy Kerley, but he remains off the fantasy radar.
report: Zay Jones caught 3-of-6 passes for 36 yards in Buffalo's Week 1 game against Baltimore.

impact: It's the second straight week Jones has led Buffalo in receiving. Jones got most of his yards on a 57-yard bomb from Josh Allen, but his role is trending up. Jones is worth an end-of-roster stash in dynasty leagues.
report: Zay Jones caught 2-of-3 passes for 63 yards in Buffalo's Week 2 loss to the Chargers.

impact: The 38 yards were Jones' second most of the season. The sophomore is on pace for 40/576/0. With Kelvin Benjamin fading toward oblivion, Jones could take on a bigger role the final 12 games of the season.
report: Zay Jones caught 4-of-7 targets for 38 yards in the Bills' Week 4 loss to the Packers.

impact: Jones had Buffalo's biggest play of the game when he got open in the back of the end zone for a touchdown which gave the Bills the lead, but that was about it for the second-round sophomore. This game aside, Jones has been more efficient this season, but there is no fantasy value to find in this passing game.
report: Zay Jones hauled in 3-of-8 targets for 35 yards and a touchdown in the Bills' Week 6 loss to the Texans.

impact: It was another quiet week for Jones and the Bills' destitute offense. The 2017 second-rounder has cleared 40 yards receiving in just one of his seven outings this year. Even with a favorable matchup next week against a soft Patriots secondary, the 23-year-old won't be a fantasy consideration.
report: Zay Jones snagged three catches for 27 yards on four targets Sunday in Buffalo’s Week 7 loss to the Colts.

impact: It was another quiet week for Jones and the Bills' destitute offense. The 2017 second-rounder has cleared 40 yards receiving in just one of his seven outings this year. Even with a favorable matchup next week against a soft Patriots secondary, the 23-year-old won't be a fantasy consideration.
report: Zay Jones snagged three catches for 27 yards on four targets Sunday in Buffalo’s Week 7 loss to the Colts.

impact: Jones plays a lot of snaps in Buffalo's offense but lacks fantasy value.
report: Zay Jones caught 4-of-6 targets for 18 yards in the Bills' Week 9 loss.

impact: You read that right.  Jones erupted with Matt Barkley quarterbacking, getting open at will against the Jets' leaky secondary and catching a pinpoint tight-window throw from Barkley on his red-zone score.  Unfortunately, the Bills are likely to turn back to erratic rookie Josh Allen (shoulder) following their Week 11 bye.  Jones isn't worth grabbing in 12- or 14-team leagues.
report: Zay Jones caught 8-of-11 targets for 93 yards and a touchdown in the Bills' Week 10 blowout win over the Jets.

impact: Powell got the start for the Jets, playing the first six snaps before ceding work to Isaiah Crowell, who answered in a big way with a 10-102-2 rushing line.  The two figure to split work pretty evenly for much of the season, but Powell would seem to be the favorite anytime the Jets are chasing points.  That wasn't the case tonight with New York winning by 31.  Powell will be on the RB3/FLEX map next week in the home opener against the Dolphins.
report: Bilal Powell rushed 12 times for 60 yards and caught 1-of-2 targets for five yards in the Jets' Week 1 win over the Lions.

impact: Powell was out-touched 14 to 10 by Isaiah Crowell in this one, but Powell's superior versatility resulted in a far superior fantasy day.  Crowell struggled as a rusher (12/35/0) and was targeted just three times in the passing game.  In a near-even timeshare, both backs will be Week 3 flex options at Cleveland.
report: Bilal Powell rushed five times for six yards, but caught 5-of-6 targets for 74 yards and a touchdown in the Jets' Week 2 loss to Miami.

impact: Powell failed to corral his lone target in the passing game. Powell managed to out-rush Isaiah Crowell 73-34 on two fewer carries, though Crowell converted a pair of goal-line looks for scores. There just isn't much separation here right now. Powell will be the preferred play against the Jaguars' daunting defense in Week 4 as the Jets look to counteract the Jags' pass rush with short throws.
report: Bilal Powell rushed 14 times for 73 yards in the Jets' Week 3 loss to the Browns.

impact: Powell continued to start over Isaiah Crowell and finished with more touches. The Jets abandoned the run early, so there wasn't much of a chance for him to get going on the ground. Powell's pass-game role has made him more matchup-proof than Crowell through the first month of the season. He's a low-end FLEX for Week 5's matchup with the Broncos.
report: Bilal Powell rushed eight times for 26 yards and caught 4-of-7 passes for 26 yards in Week 4 against the Jaguars.

impact: He out-touched Isaiah Crowell 20 to 16, although Crowell had a monster day with 231 yards from scrimmage and a touchdown.  The Jets remain committed to a near-even backfield committee.  Powell will be a decent RB2/flex option when Gang Green draws a plus matchup at home versus Indianapolis next.
report: Bilal Powell rushed 20 times for 99 yards in the Jets' Week 5 win over Denver.

impact: Powell out-touched Isaiah Crowell 16 to 15 in what remains a near-even backfield, although Powell had multiple chunk-yardage gains negated by penalties. Powell does have double-digit touches in 6-of-6 games.  He will be a low-end flex option when the Jets host the Vikings next.
report: Bilal Powell rushed 16 times for 59 yards and missed his lone target in the Jets' Week 6 win over the Colts.

impact: With Marquise Goodwin going down very early in the second quarter with a quad injury, Pettis was the next man up opposite Pierre Garcon with Trent Taylor in the slot.  Pettis scored the Niners' lone touchdown, making an over-the-shoulder catch from 22 yards out on an escape maneuver by Jimmy Garoppolo outside the pocket.  Pettis will be on the fantasy map if Goodwin misses time.
report: Dante Pettis caught 2-of-5 targets for 61 yards and one touchdown in the 49ers' Week 1 loss to the Vikings.

impact: Pettis dusted Teez Tabor for a 35-yard gain in the first quarter but wasn’t heard from again. The rookie was expected to play an important role with Marquise Goodwin (quad) sidelined this week, but obviously that didn’t come to fruition. Even with a likely shootout on tap next week at Kansas City, the rookie will be difficult to trust in fantasy.
report: Dante Pettis was limited to one catch for 35 yards on two targets Sunday in San Francisco’s Week 2 win over the Lions.

impact: With Marquise Goodwin healthy, Pettis disappeared from the game plan. He can be dropped in redraft leagues.
report: Dante Pettis was not targeted in the 49ers' Week 3 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: He added five carries for 19 yards on the ground. Prescott didn't turn the ball over, but he also didn't throw a single touchdown. It's the seventh time in his last nine games that Prescott has failed to eclipse the 200-yard mark. Although Dak shoulders the blame as quarterback, rookie LG Connor Williams was as advertised (and not in a good way) in pass-protection and OC Scott Linehan could not have taken a more vanilla approach to Sunday's gameplan. It's early, but Prescott's ceiling may be lower than initially thought if slot receiver Cole Beasley continues being his clear-cut target in the flats.
report: Dak Prescott completed 19-of-29 passes for 170 yards in the Cowboys' Week 1 loss to the Panthers.

impact: Prescott wasn't asked to do much with the Cowboys defense shutting down the Giants. His touchdown was a 64-yard catch and run by Tavon Austin on the third play of the night. Prescott managed the game after that, but he added 45 yards on seven rushes. Through two weeks, Prescott has looked like the quarterback he was in the second half of last year. He gets a matchup with Seattle in Week 3.
report: Dak Prescott completed 16-of-25 passes for 160 yards and a touchdown in Week 2 against the Giants.

impact: Dak took five sacks for a loss of 31 yards. Plagued by a patchwork receiving corps and a declining offensive line, Prescott limped to just 40 yards on 6-of-13 passing in the first half. He was only marginally better after the break and spent much of his day trying to escape Frank Clark, who dominated up front for Seattle. Prescott’s lone touchdown "pass" came on a shovel throw to Tavon Austin with 7:11 left in the fourth quarter. Any chance of a late comeback ended when Earl Thomas pulled in his second interception of the day on a pass intended for Blake Jarwin. Perhaps Prescott will fare better against an attackable Lions defense at home next week, but with the Cowboys’ offense struggling in all facets, Dak will be little more than a back-end QB2 in fantasy.
report: Dak Prescott completed 19-of-34 passes for 168 yards with a touchdown and two interceptions while adding 21 yards on two carries Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 3 loss to Seattle.

impact: Prescott lost 24 yards on three sacks in the victory. Sunday marked Dak's first 200-yard passing game since Week 15 of last season. He spread the wealth, targeting eight different receivers including Ezekiel Elliott, who led the way with 88 yards and a touchdown on four catches. Prescott's first touchdown of the afternoon came on a screen to Zeke, who took it 38 yards to the house late in the second quarter. Dak later found tight end Geoff Swaim for a one-yard touchdown off a play-action pass, which stretched the Cowboys lead to 10 with under three minutes to go in the third quarter. That lead would evaporate but Dak kept his poise down the stretch, leading a late-scoring drive keyed by a 34-yard completion to Elliott down the right sideline. This was easily Prescott's best outing of 2018, which admittedly wasn't a high bar to clear after struggling mightily in his first three games. We'll see if he can build off this performance next week at Houston.
report: Dak Prescott completed 17-of-27 passes for 255 yards and two touchdowns while adding two yards on three carries Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 4 victory over the Lions.

impact: Prescott’s struggles resurfaced coming off his best game in Week 5. Both of his interceptions were on dropped passes, but Prescott was off the mark on the throws.  Prescott somewhat salvaged his night with 36 yards rushing. He doesn't have much of a supporting cast, but it's clear Prescott has regressed from last year. Prescott will be a back-end QB2 for a tough Week 6 matchup with Jacksonville.
report: Dak Prescott completed 18-of-29 passes for 208 yards with a touchdown and two interceptions in the Cowboys' Week 5 loss to the Texans.

impact: He lost 11 yards on three sacks in the victory. Going against arguably the league's toughest defense, Dak didn't blink, making Jacksonville pay for ignoring slot receiver Cole Beasley (nine catches for 101 yards and two touchdowns). Prescott also had a good day running the football, breaking out for a career-high 82 yards with a long gain of 28 yards. He probably would have had a bigger day had the score been closer but with Dallas winning big, Prescott only attempted nine passes after halftime. Next the Cowboys head to Washington for a division showdown against the Redskins in Week 7.
report: Dak Prescott completed 17-of-27 passes for 183 yards and two touchdowns while adding 82 yards and another touchdown on 11 rushes Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 6 victory over Jacksonville.

impact: Prescott ate a shoulder pad directly to his helmet while sliding near the sideline early in the first half, which forced Dallas' training staff to bring out the blue medical tent. He was cleared soon after with what was comically declared as a 'hand' injury. Prescott did encouragingly keep to his running ways, though, recording six carries for the third consecutive game. He's now averaged 7.6 rushes, 49.6 rushing yards, and 0.6 rushing touchdowns in the last three games for Dallas. Prescott will return from the Cowboys' Week 8 bye as a sneaky streaming QB2 versus the Titans.
report: Dak Prescott completed 22-of-35 passes for 273 yards and one touchdown, chipping in another 33 yards and one score on the ground in the Cowboys' Week 7 loss to the Redskins.

impact: Prescott ate a shoulder pad directly to his helmet while sliding near the sideline early in the first half, which forced Dallas' training staff to bring out the blue medical tent. He was cleared soon after with what was comically declared as a 'hand' injury. Prescott did encouragingly keep to his running ways, though, recording six carries for the third consecutive game. He's now averaged 7.6 rushes, 49.6 rushing yards, and 0.6 rushing touchdowns in the last three games for Dallas. Prescott will return from the Cowboys' Week 8 bye as a sneaky streaming QB2 versus the Titans.
report: Dak Prescott completed 22-of-35 passes for 273 yards and one touchdown, chipping in another 33 yards and one score on the ground in the Cowboys' Week 7 loss to the Redskins.

impact: He rushed just twice for 11 yards.  The 243 yards passing were actually Prescott's third-most of the season, and it was just his fourth game with multiple touchdown passes.  The rushing numbers were disappointing, however, after Prescott had averaged over seven rushing attempts per game over the last three weeks.  He also lost a fumble on Monday night.  The Cowboys came out hot, as Prescott hit Amari Cooper for a four-yard score in the first quarter.  But Prescott then tried to force one to Cooper in the end zone later in the quarter and threw a horrible interception.  His other score was a 23-yarder to Allen Hurns, who roasted Malcolm Butler.  Prescott will be a middling QB2 next week when the Cowboys go on the road to Philly.
report: Dak Prescott completed 21-of-31 passes for 243 yards, two touchdowns, and one interception in the Cowboys' Week 9 loss to the Titans.

impact: He added nine yards on six carries, including a one-yard touchdown on a sneak before halftime. Prescott did enough to keep the Cowboys' playoff hopes alive in a must-win game. His only passing touchdown went to Ezekiel Elliott on a short red-zone throw, but Prescott continued to show good rapport with Amari Cooper, who had a team high 10 targets. Prescott has been trending up since the Cooper trade. He's on the streaming radar against the Falcons' bottom of the league secondary in Week 11.
report: Dak Prescott completed 26-of-36 passes for 270 yards and a touchdown in the Cowboys' Week 10 win over the Eagles.

impact: After not scoring a rushing touchdown the first five weeks, Prescott has four of them over the last five games.  His four-yard scamper was the first touchdown of the afternoon.  Ezekiel Elliott later added a 23-yarder and led the Cowboys with a 7-79 receiving line en route to 201 total yards.  Prescott gets the Redskins on Thanksgiving.  In Week 7, Prescott had 306 total yards and two scores in a road loss against Washington.  He'll be a borderline QB1 play.
report: Dak Prescott completed 22-of-32 passes for 208 scoreless yards in the Cowboys' Week 11 win over the Falcons, adding a four-yard rushing touchdown.

impact: Peterson failed to corral his lone target in the passing game. Although he was playing through knee, ankle and shoulder issues, Peterson looked no worse for the wear, routinely pushing the pile in a knock down, drag out game. Peterson's YPC is now up to 4.40. Provided he avoided setbacks with his various ailments, Peterson will be a low-end RB2 for next week's game with the Cowboys.
report: Adrian Peterson rushed 17 times for 97 yards in the Redskins' Week 6 win over the Panthers.

impact: Peterson again led Washington's backfield in carries by a healthy margin without Chris Thompson available for the second consecutive week. All Day out-carried third-down back Kapri Bibbs 24-2 on Sunday, now having out-carried the latter 41-4 in the Redskins' last two games. He's bulldozed his way to 196 yards (4.78 YPC) in that span, too. If Thompson remains out in Week 8 against the Giants, Peterson will again be a clear-cut usage-based RB2.
report: Adrian Peterson handled a team-high 24 carries for 99 yards in Washington's Week 7 victory over the Cowboys.

impact: Peterson again led Washington's backfield in carries by a healthy margin without Chris Thompson available for the second consecutive week. All Day out-carried third-down back Kapri Bibbs 24-2 on Sunday, now having out-carried the latter 41-4 in the Redskins' last two games. He's bulldozed his way to 196 yards (4.78 YPC) in that span, too. If Thompson remains out in Week 8 against the Giants, Peterson will again be a clear-cut usage-based RB2.
report: Adrian Peterson handled a team-high 24 carries for 99 yards in Washington's Week 7 victory over the Cowboys.

impact: Peterson got the scoring started with a 7-yard receiving TD, then landed a game-clinching haymaker on his 64-yard breakaway touchdown.  Peterson has now tied Barry Sanders for the most 50-plus-yard rushing TDs in league history (15).  Even at age 33, Peterson has settled in as the centerpiece of Washington's offense.  He will be a legitimate RB1 play in Week 9 against the Falcons.
report: Adrian Peterson rushed 26 times for 149 yards and a touchdown and caught a seven-yard score in Washington's Week 8 win over the Giants.

impact: Negative game script combined with more offensive line injuries doomed Peterson, who also got vultured on a three-yard rushing TD by Kapri Bibbs in the second half.  And Peterson's best run of the game was negated by a penalty.  The Skins are in danger of heading to Tampa Bay in Week 10 without LT Trent Williams (thumb surgery), LG Shawn Lauvao (knee), and RG Brandon Scherff (shoulder).
report: Adrian Peterson managed 17 yards on nine carries and caught 3-of-3 targets for 16 yards in Washington's Week 9 loss to Atlanta.

impact: He caught both of his targets for a gain of one yard.  It was nothing special in the box score, but getting the ball in Peterson's hands is the Redskins' preferred offense to salt away the clock and keep the ball away from the opponent.  It's a boring brand of ball, but it works for them right now.  Washington is averaging fewer than 20 points per game.  Peterson gets the Texans in Week 11.
report: Adrian Peterson rushed 19 times for 68 yards in the Redskins' Week 10 win over the Bucs.

impact: The scores saved his fantasy day because Peterson's rushing impact was otherwise minimal and he didn't draw a single passing-game target.  The downgrade from Alex Smith to Colt McCoy isn't as major as it'll be made out to be, and Washington's run-first approach won't be changing.  Peterson will remain a volume-based, touchdown-reliant RB2 on Thanksgiving against the Cowboys.
report: Adrian Peterson rushed 16 times for 51 yards and two touchdowns in Washington's Week 11 loss to Houston.

impact: Chris Carson got the start, but Penny ended up with the same number of carries and targets. He was much less efficient with his work, gaining just 43 total yards while Carson went for 79. Carson looks like the best option in the backfield right now, but it seems like the Seahawks will keep Penny involved. Even so, he cannot be trusted in fantasy lineups next week against the Bears.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed seven times for eight yards and hauled in 4-of-5 targets for 35 yards in the Seahawks' Week 1 loss to the Broncos.

impact: That rushing line led the team.  Penny's 10 carries were four more than Chris Carson and the 30 yards were six more than Carson.  Carson didn't touch the ball in the second half.  As a receiver, Penny wasn't any better on two targets, dropping one and being the target on a game-clinching pick-six on the other.  Penny has been dreadful through two games, rushing 17 times for 38 yards (2.24 YPC) behind an atrocious offensive line.  This rushing game is a clear avoid heading into Week 3 at home against the Cowboys.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed 10 times for 30 yards in the Seahawks' Week 2 loss to the Bears.

impact: The rookie botched a handoff from Russell Wilson during the first half, though luckily, he was able to fall on it. After sharing backfield work with Chris Carson in Weeks 1 and 2, Penny took a backseat in this one, seeing just three touches to Carson’s 34. All three of his carries came in the first half, which would suggest Pete Carroll was punishing Penny for his earlier fumble. With Carson emerging as the Seahawks’ workhorse, Penny can be avoided next week, even in a favorable matchup against the Cardinals.
report: Rashaad Penny managed just three yards on five carries Sunday in Seattle’s Week 3 victory over the Cowboys.

impact: Penny played behind Mike Davis was out-touched by Davis 25-to-9. Penny ran well with his opportunities, breaking of a long gain of 15 yards, but clearly has not gained the trust of the staff. Penny is at bet a bench stash at this stage of the season. The Seahawks host the Rams in Week 5.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed nine times for 49 yards in Sunday's Week 4 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Penny was used early in the game on a 24-yard reception, although the majority of his carries came as the game got out of hand.  The Seahawks wound up smashing Oakland 27-3.  Penny's role remains uncertain entering Seattle's Week 7 bye, but he is worth rostering in 14- and 16-team leagues.  Chris Carson had 14 touches in Sunday's victory.  Mike Davis surprisingly only logged seven.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed nine times for 43 yards and caught 2-of-2 targets for 27 yards in the Seahawks' Week 6 win over the Raiders.

impact: Penny's zero-touch day was somewhat surprising one week after he got the ball 11 times against the Raiders. Chris Carson had 27 handles in Detroit, while Mike Davis had 11. Penny will be off the radar for Week 9 against the Chargers.
report: Rashaad Penny did not touch the ball on offense in Seattle's Week 8 win over the Lions.

impact: Penny surprisingly touched the ball on the Seahawks' opening drive. More surprisingly, he was barely involved in the second half even though Chris Carson was missing with a thigh injury. It was all No. 2 Mike Davis for the Seahawks. If Carson cannot get cleared for Week 10 against the Rams, Penny would be a risky FLEX with a little bit of upside for what could be a high-scoring affair.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed four times for 11 yards in the Seahawks' Week 9 loss to the Chargers, adding three receptions for 13 additional yards.

impact: Penny was not targeted in the passing game, but he ended up out-carrying and out-gaining Mike Davis in Chris Carson's absence even though Davis won the touch battle (15-12). A struggler for much of the season, Penny looked like a player with a different gear today. His touchdown was an explosive 18-yarder on a read option. With the Seahawks playing on Thursday Night Football in Week 11, Penny will have major FLEX upside if Carson can't get cleared to face the Packers.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed 12 times for 108 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 10 loss to the Rams.

impact: 30 of Penny's yards came on a jaw-dropping first quarter carry when he ran into a dead end on the right side of the line of scrimmage before completely reversing fields to make something out of nothing. Unfortunately, he tweaked his ankle on the play. Penny returned to play through a "questionable" tag but never looked quite the same. Chris Carson once again operated as the Seahawks' clear-cut feature back. Penny will be a risky FLEX for Week 12 against the Panthers.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed eight times for 46 yards in the Seahawks' Week 11 win over the Packers.

impact: His seven targets tied for second most on the team.  Pascal's on-field play has been poor, but he has a real chance at a huge role in Week 7 versus Buffalo.  T.Y. Hilton (hamstring) and Jack Doyle (chest) haven't seemed close to returning, while Ryan Grant (ankle) and Marcus Johnson (undisclosed) exited Sunday's loss injured.  Pascal has seven or more targets in three straight games.
report: Colts WR Zach Pascal caught 5-of-7 targets for 35 yards in Sunday's Week 6 loss to the Jets.

impact: Active for only the second time this year, the injury-prone Parker was targeted just once, which resulted in an interception by quarterback Brock Osweiler. The 26-year-old has never delivered on his first-round hype and could be a goner at the trade deadline later this month. He's not fantasy relevant.
report: DeVante Parker couldn’t haul in his lone target Sunday in Miami’s Week 6 win over the Bears.

impact: A de facto healthy scratch the past few weeks, Parker was only forced into the lineup because of injuries to Albert Wilson and Kenny Stills. He responded by dominating targets and posting the most yards of his four-year career. 46 of them came on a fluke ball that hit off of Jakeem Grant's hands and then a helmet, but Parker was feasting even before that. It's now looking extremely unlikely that Parker is dealt ahead of next week's trade deadline. The Dolphins will be facing the Jets' banged up secondary in Week 9.
report: DeVante Parker caught 6-of-9 targets for 134 yards in the Dolphins' Week 8 loss to the Texans.

impact: A de facto healthy scratch the past few weeks, Parker was only forced into the lineup because of injuries to Albert Wilson and Kenny Stills. He responded by dominating targets and posting the most yards of his four-year career. 46 of them came on a fluke ball that hit off of Jakeem Grant's hands and then a helmet, but Parker was feasting even before that. It's now looking extremely unlikely that Parker is dealt ahead of next week's trade deadline. The Dolphins will be facing the Jets' banged up secondary in Week 9.
report: DeVante Parker caught 6-of-9 targets for 134 yards in the Dolphins' Week 8 loss to the Texans.

impact: Even with Kenny Stills back, Parker remained involved and could have had a better fantasy day. He had a solid gain on a screen pass brought back on a penalty, and Brock Osweiler threw behind him on what should have been a long gain. That said, this passing game is not very good, and he is now competing with another player for targets. Parker will be a risky FLEX option next week in Green Bay.
report: DeVante Parker hauled in 1-of-2 targets for eight yards in the Dolphins' Week 9 win over the Jets.

impact: Jakeem Grant (leg) noticeably struggled throughout the game with a limp before being carted off, opening the door for Parker to stick in three-wide sets with Danny Amendola (7/72) and Kenny Stills (2/26). Parker saw a team-high 11 targets, but managed to grasp only five thrown his way. Miami's offense inevitably appeared to finally hit a wall with Brock Osweiler under center. Parker will be an interesting second-half candidate if Ryan Tannehill is able to suit up once the Dolphins return from their bye in Week 12.
report: DeVante Parker hauled in 5-of-11 targets for 43 yards in Miami's Week 10 destruction from the Packers.

impact: Mullens came out of nowhere -- he wasn't even verified on Twitter before the game -- to throw three touchdowns while averaging 11.9 yards per attempt in his first NFL game. The 2017 undrafted quarterback out of Southern Miss found a wide open Pierre Garcon for his first career touchdown pass, but he then followed it up with darts to Kendrick Bourne and George Kittle for two more scores. Even if C.J. Beathard (wrist) is able to grip a football next week, it's fair to wonder if the 49ers stick with their secret weapon. San Francisco will have another easy matchup with the Giants on Monday Night Football in Week 10.
report: Nick Mullens completed 16-of-22 passes for 262 yards with three touchdowns in the 49ers' Week 9 win over the Raiders.

impact: Things didn't go nearly as swimmingly as they did for Mullens in his NFL debut last week against the Raiders.  The league got some tape on him, and the Giants, unlike the Raiders, got some pressure, even though Mullens wasn't sacked.  Both of Mullens' interceptions were on tipped balls by LB B.J. Goodson, so they weren't entirely the quarterback's fault.  He still was able to move the ball with decent success, but Matt Breida on the ground was the star of the offense in this one.  Mullens' score was an 11-yard hookup to Breida, who made a nice grab at the goal line.  The Niners head on their bye week and will host the Bucs in Week 12.  We'd guess it'll be Mullens again.
report: Nick Mullens completed 27-of-39 passes for 250 yards, one touchdown, and two interceptions in the 49ers' 27-23, Week 10 loss to the Giants.

impact: This year's Mr. Irrelevant, Quinn is a much better prospect than his draft status after dominating his senior season at SMU for a 114/1,236/13 receiving line.  He got the Week 11 start at slot receiver, replacing Jamison Crowder (ankle) with Maurice Harris moving outside.  Quinn will be an intriguing, low-cost DFS punt in Thanksgiving-Day lineups against the Cowboys.
report: Trey Quinn caught 4-of-4 targets for 49 yards in Washington's Week 11 loss to Houston.

impact: The Pats were dialing up some exotic runs but predictably could not get Patterson going as a pass catcher. No one can. Patterson isn't going to make a realistic push for fantasy value the final three weeks of Julian Edelman's suspension.
report: Cordarrelle Patterson rushed three times for 13 yards in the Patriots' Week 1 win over the Texans, adding a six-yard reception.

impact: Patterson set up the Bears’ first touchdown with a fumble on a kickoff return, but he made up for it in the second quarter. With the Patriots down 17-7, Patterson took a kickoff 95 yards to the house to close the deficit and turn the game around. Despite the big special teams play, he has no value in standard fantasy leagues.
report: Cordarrelle Patterson recorded a 95-yard kick-return touchdown in the Patriots' Week 7 win over the Bears.

impact: Patterson set up the Bears’ first touchdown with a fumble on a kickoff return, but he made up for it in the second quarter. With the Patriots down 17-7, Patterson took a kickoff 95 yards to the house to close the deficit and turn the game around. Despite the big special teams play, he has no value in standard fantasy leagues.
report: Cordarrelle Patterson recorded a 95-yard kick-return touchdown in the Patriots' Week 7 win over the Bears.

impact: With Sony Michel (knee) out and featherweights James White and Kenjon Barner as the only other true running backs on the roster, Patterson actually got the start in the backfield and led the team with his 10 carries and 38 yards on the ground.  Patterson was heavily involved in the backfield in his college days and is a natural with the ball in his hands.  He got a couple carries from inside the 10-yard line on the second series but looked a little out of sorts.  This was likely just a one-week deal unless Michel is unable to go next Sunday against the Packers.
report: Cordarrelle Patterson started at running back in the Week 8 win over the Bills and rushed 10 times for 38 yards.

impact: Patterson had a five carry, 50-yard drive after James White left with a leg injury. He didn't start but had just one fewer carry than White. Patterson has looked good at running back with Sony Michel out the last two weeks. He could have a Ty Montgomery role even when Michel returns.
report: Cordarrelle Patterson rushed 11 times for 61 yards and a touchdown and caught one pass for seven yards in the Patriots' Week 9 win over the Packers.

impact: Morris was cooking in the first half before stalling in the red zone when he had four carries from the five-yard line and in before losing a critical fumble on the fourth attempt at the two-yard line.  Morris looked to have a strong grip on ball-carrying duties before halftime, but with the Niners chasing in the second half, Matt Breida was the main back.  At the end of the day, Morris posted as 12-38 rushing line to Breida's 11-46 line while adding a five-yard catch.  Morris wasn't targeted in the pass game.  This figures to be a timeshare most weeks, though Morris should have chances for big workloads in games the Niners hold the lead.  The Lions come to town in Week 2.
report: Alfred Morris rushed 12 times for 38 yards in the 49ers' Week 1 loss to the Vikings.

impact: Morris held a slight edge in touches (16-14) but Matt Breida out-gained the veteran by a convincing margin. Not usually known for his pass-catching prowess, Alf logged his most receiving yards in a game since 2014. Morris took much better care of the ball this week after fumbling twice in last week’s opener. Averaging a mere 3.31 yards per carry through two games, the 29-year-old will just be an RB3 for next week’s game in KC.
report: Alfred Morris soaked up 48 yards on 14 carries while nabbing both of his targets for 32 yards Sunday in the 49ers’ Week 2 victory over the Lions.

impact: Morris only had four yards on three carries in the first half as the 49ers' offense was sabotaged by penalties, but he helped jump-start things in the second half with steady, consistent gains. He also confirmed his goal-line status with a three-yard score in the third quarter. Unfortunately, touchdowns might be more difficult to come by moving forward with Jimmy Garoppolo dealing with a potential ACL tear.
report: Alfred Morris rushed 14 times for 67 yards and a touchdown in the 49ers' Week 3 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Even though it didn't show up in the stat sheet, Morris was subbed in for Matt Breida on the goal line early in the game, but he failed to convert it for a touchdown. The Butler will need to convert his goal line opportunities if he's to have any fantasy value moving forward. Those opportunities could be few and far between with C.J. Beathard as the quarterback. Morris' fantasy owners are only hoping for a touchdown against the Cardinals next week.
report: Alfred Morris rushed four times for 14 scoreless yards in the 49ers' Week 4 loss to the Chargers.

impact: Morris took over as the lead ball-carrier after Matt Breida left with a sprained ankle. Alf didn't do anything particularly notable, though the five targets were surprising as the 29-year-old has never been much of a pass-catcher. Breida's ankle injury doesn't appear serious, though it could keep him from suiting up next week at Green Bay. Morris would be a volume-based RB2 if Breida can't get the green light.
report: Alfred Morris went for 61 yards on 18 carries while also securing three-of-five targets for 30 yards Sunday in the 49ers’ Week 5 loss to Arizona.

impact: Even with Raheem Mostert once again stacking big gains, Morris led the team with nine carries as Matt Breida struggled with his ankle injury. Mostert would seem to have earned an even bigger role moving forward, especially if Breida is forced to miss time, but it does not seem like Morris is going away. Even so, he is not a fantasy option right now.
report: Alfred Morris rushed nine times for 25 yards in the 49ers' Week 7 loss to the Rams.

impact: Even with Raheem Mostert once again stacking big gains, Morris led the team with nine carries as Matt Breida struggled with his ankle injury. Mostert would seem to have earned an even bigger role moving forward, especially if Breida is forced to miss time, but it does not seem like Morris is going away. Even so, he is not a fantasy option right now.
report: Alfred Morris rushed nine times for 25 yards in the 49ers' Week 7 loss to the Rams.

impact: For the first time since Week 6, Morris worked ahead of supposed backup Raheem Mostert, out-carrying the latter 6-2. Mostert's 9.0 YPC (albeit on only two touches) still led San Francisco's backfield. There's clearly no projecting who works behind Matt Breida (16/42) as the team's No. 2 when healthy. Mostert should remain stashed for his athleticism and pending opportunity, but can't be started at this time. Morris can still be cut bait from given his nonexistent run in the Niners' passing game.
report: Alfred Morris rushed six times for 28 yards in the Niners' Week 8 nail-biting loss to the Cardinals.

impact: Moncrief got the start and actually saw one more target than Keelan Cole, but he was easily the least productive member of the receiving corps. Moncrief should remain involved because of his red-zone ability, but it would not be surprising if Dede Westbrook jumped him on the depth chart.
report: Donte Moncrief hauled in 1-of-5 targets for 14 yards in the Jaguars' Week 1 win over the Giants.

impact: There's a Moncrief line if we've ever seen one. Moncrief's four-yard score was a nice grab against tight Stephon Gilmore coverage in the end zone. Moncrief was announced with a knee injury in the second half but ended up playing through it. Despite the team-leading nine targets, Moncrief was fourth in yardage. He's a touchdown-or-bust WR4 for fantasy purposes.
report: Donte Moncrief caught 4-of-9 targets for 34 yards and a touchdown in the Jaguars' Week 2 win over the Patriots.

impact: Moncrief is a rotational receiver on a run-first team with a highly inconsistent quarterback.  He is barely roster worthy in 12-team leagues.
report: Donte Moncrief caught 2-of-3 targets for 16 yards in the Jaguars' Week 3 loss to Tennessee.

impact: Moncrief got behind Jets CB Trumaine Johnson for a 67-yard TD. It was his only real highlight, though Moncrief saw the second most targets behind Dede Westbrook. Moncrief didn't have more than 34 yards in any game prior to this week. This will likely go down as one of his best games.
report: Donte Moncrief caught five passes for 109 yards and a touchdowin in Week 4 against the Jets.

impact: Moncrief led the team in receiving, but there was nothing particularly impactful about his performance. He had 15 yards at the half, and 25 of his yards came on a meaningless catch deep into garbage time. That said, he remains at worst the No. 2 option in a passing game which has created a lot of yardage with Leonard Fournette sidelined. He will be on the desperation WR4 map next week in Dallas.
report: Donte Moncrief hauled in 6-of-15 targets for 76 yards in the Jaguars' Week 5 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Moncrief entered Week 6 with 11 catches for 185 yards and a touchdown over his previous two outings, but that all went out the window against Dallas. The ex-Colt blew a fourth-down conversion with an ugly drop in the fourth quarter, not that it mattered much with Jacksonville getting boat-raced. Moncrief's goose egg Sunday serves as a reminder that he'll always be a boom-or-bust fantasy player. We'll see how he fares against Houston in Week 7.
report: Donte Moncrief came up empty on his three targets Sunday in Jacksonville’s Week 6 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: Moncrief led the team in targets and receiving in a game where Blake Bortles was benched for losing multiple fumbles, and Cody Kessler wound up attempting 30 passes in a half as the Jaguars played from behind. The week before, Moncrief went catch-less on three targets. Although Week 8 against the Eagles poses a favorable matchup, Moncrief’s wild week-to-week inconsistency will render him a boom-bust WR3/flex option.
report: Donte Moncrief caught 7-of-10 targets for 76 yards in the Jaguars’ Week 7 loss to the Texans.

impact: Moncrief was a non-factor in the first half, failing to see a target as Blake Bortles attempted just seven passes. Things quickly changed after the break. He caught a 24-yard pass on the opening drive of the second half, and he came down with two more passes on a touchdown drive the next time the offense was on the field. Moncrief has started to look like Jacksonville's No. 1 receiver, but that is not a high-upside job. He is not a must-hold through the bye.
report: Donte Moncrief hauled in 4-of-7 targets for 54 yards in the Jaguars' Week 8 loss to the Eagles.

impact: Moncrief made his presence known quickly against his former team, breaking the offense out of an early rut with an 80-yard touchdown in which he shed a couple defenders on his way to the end zone. That was basically it for him until the fourth quarter, when he came up with a big third-down conversion. Moncrief now has at least 75 yards in three of his last five games, but his matchup next week against the Steelers is not worth attacking.
report: Donte Moncrief hauled in 3-of-4 targets for 98 yards and a touchdown in the Jaguars' Week 10 loss to the Colts.

impact: Moncrief hauled in an 11-yard slant on the opening drive and then went dark the rest of the day as the Jaguars threw just 18 times on the day. Moncrief had at least 50 yards receiving in each of his previous three games and in five of the previous six. A boom-or-bust option, Moncrief is only an option for the deepest of leagues and will only be a WR4 option next week against the Bills.
report: Donte Moncrief caught 1-of-2 passes for 11 yards in Sunday's Week 11 loss to the Steelers.

impact: It was an improvement on the four touches Montgomery saw in Week 1, but he still has been mostly uninvolved through two weeks. More worryingly, Aaron Jones is due back from suspension in Week 3. Montgomery is not a must-roster player in standard scoring.
report: Ty Montgomery rushed five times for 31 yards and caught 1-of-2 targets for nine yards in the Packers' Week 2 tie with the Vikings.

report: Ty Montgomery rushed five times for 31 yards and caught 1-of-2 targets for nine yards in the Packers' Week 2 tie with the Vikings.

impact: With Aaron Rodgers' receivers struggling to make big plays, TyMont finally got involved as a pass catcher/outlet. Both his 10 touches and 64 yards led the Packers' three-man backfield. Especially with Randall Cobb struggling, the Pack figure to work on getting Montgomery more involved on a weekly basis. The Bills are an appetizing Week 4 matchup.
report: Ty Montgomery caught 6-of-7 targets for 48 yards in the Packers' Week 3 loss to the Redskins, adding four carries for 16 additional yards.

Especially with Randall Cobb struggling, the Pack figure to work on getting Montgomery more involved on a weekly basis. The Bills are an appetizing Week 4 matchup.
report: Ty Montgomery caught 6-of-7 targets for 48 yards in the Packers' Week 3 loss to the Redskins, adding four carries for 16 additional yards.

impact: Most of Montgomery's yardage came when he got a free release down the left sideline for a 43-yard catch in the first quarter. The Pack's backfield remained a three-man rotation this afternoon, with Aaron Jones winning both the touch and yardage battles. Montgomery will continue to struggle for value outside of PPR leagues.
report: Ty Montgomery caught 2-of-3 targets for 56 yards in the Packers' Week 4 win over the Bills, adding five rushes for 18 additional yards.

impact: Most of Montgomery's yardage came when he got a free release down the left sideline for a 43-yard catch in the first quarter. The Pack's backfield remained a three-man rotation this afternoon, with Aaron Jones winning both the touch and yardage battles. Montgomery will continue to struggle for value outside of PPR leagues.
report: Ty Montgomery caught 2-of-3 targets for 56 yards in the Packers' Week 4 win over the Bills, adding five rushes for 18 additional yards.

impact: Montgomery got a ton of playing time in the second half with the Packers in catchup mode.  He has no fantasy value outside of deeper PPR leagues.
report: Ty Montgomery rushed four times for 15 yards in the Packers' Week 5 loss to the Lions, adding a 23-yard catch on three targets.

impact: Montgomery got a ton of playing time in the second half with the Packers in catchup mode.  He has no fantasy value outside of deeper PPR leagues.
report: Ty Montgomery rushed four times for 15 yards in the Packers' Week 5 loss to the Lions, adding a 23-yard catch on three targets.

impact: Montgomery's presence was only felt on special teams, where he committed what amounted to a game-ending fumble on a late kick return. Montgomery has only 14 offensive touches over the Packers' past three games, removing him from the fantasy radar.
report: Ty Montgomery rushed twice for six yards in the Packers' Week 8 loss to the Rams, adding a two-yard reception.

impact: Buck Allen got one touch.  The Ravens took an extremely run-heavy approach and wound up settling on undrafted rookie Gus Edwards as their lead back.  Montgomery is unlikely to develop into a fantasy option down the stretch.
report: Ty Montgomery did not touch the ball in his Week 11 Ravens debut.

impact: Coach Ron Rivera promised more playing time for Moore entering Week 3, but he continued to play behind Devin Funchess, Jarius Wright, and Torrey Smith.  Carolina's coaching staff will have its Week 4 bye to consider increasing Moore's usage.  Moore remains barely roster worthy in 14-team leagues.
report: D.J. Moore managed one catch for three yards on two targets in the Panthers' Week 3 win over the Bengals.

impact: Moore made the most of his limited opportunities, especially after halftime when the rookie pulled in three catches for 45 yards. He flashed impressive wheels on his lone carry, chewing up 18 yards on a double reverse. Moore saw as many targets Sunday as he had in his first three games combined. He’s not fantasy-relevant yet, but he’s getting there.
report: D.J. Moore corralled each of his four targets for 49 yards while gaining 18 yards on his lone carry Sunday in the Panthers’ Week 5 win over the Giants.

impact: Moore is lucky he saw as many targets as he did, as his first half giveaways were the difference in the game. He muffed a punt that set the Redskins up at the Panthers' 22-yard line. The Redskins scored one play later. He then let the ball get "Peanut punched" out in the second quarter, setting up three more Redskins points. To coach Ron Rivera's credit, he did not bench his first-round pick and he was productive the rest of the game. Moore will be a boom/bust WR4/5 for Week 7 against the Eagles.
report: D.J. Moore caught 4-of-5 targets for 59 yards in the Panthers' Week 6 loss to the Redskins, adding 18 yards rushing while losing a pair of fumbles.

impact: Carolina’s first-round pick also committed a penalty and continues to struggle with mental errors, but Moore’s explosiveness on the field is evident. Moore could end up with more Week 8 playing time if Torrey Smith can’t go after requiring X-rays following Sunday’s thrilling comeback win. Either way, Moore won’t be a fantasy option against the Ravens. Moore is just a Dynasty and deep-league stash for now.
report: D.J. Moore caught 3-of-5 targets for 29 yards in the Panthers’ Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: Carolina’s first-round pick also committed a penalty and continues to struggle with mental errors, but Moore’s explosiveness on the field is evident. Moore could end up with more Week 8 playing time if Torrey Smith can’t go after requiring X-rays following Sunday’s thrilling comeback win. Either way, Moore won’t be a fantasy option against the Ravens. Moore is just a Dynasty and deep-league stash for now.
report: D.J. Moore caught 3-of-5 targets for 29 yards in the Panthers’ Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: Moore added 39 rushing yards on two attempts.  He recorded all seven of his touches in the first half, picking up 72 of his total yards on a second-quarter possession that ultimately ended with a six-yard touchdown catch for Christian McCaffrey.  With Torrey Smith (knee) out, Moore got the start and tied with McCaffrey for the team lead in targets.  The Panthers need to make the move permanent and boot Smith from the starter's group.  If Moore keeps the job, he'll very much be on the WR3/4 map next week at home against the Bucs.
report: D.J. Moore caught 5-of-6 targets for 90 yards in the Panthers' Week 8 win over the Ravens.

impact: Moore's rushing yardage came on a beautiful reverse. Like last week, Moore lost three touches to Curtis Samuel. Unlike last week, Samuel produced, finding the end zone twice. Although Torrey Smith (knee) will likely remain sidelined for Thursday's game against the Steelers, Moore will be a risky WR3 after Samuel's big Week 9.
report: D.J. Moore caught 1-of-2 targets for 16 yards in the Panthers' Week 9 win over the Bucs, adding a 32-yard rush.

impact: For the second-straight week, Moore was splitting looks with Curtis Samuel behind Devin Funchess. Moore has followed up his Week 8 blowup with just 73 total yards across two games. The big-play potential will always give Moore upside, but he's probably not going to tap into it all that often. He will be a WR5 for Week 11 against the Lions.
report: D.J. Moore caught 4-of-5 targets for 20 yards in the Panthers' Week 10 loss to the Steelers, adding a five-yard rush.

impact: Moore came out of the gates hot, catching two passes for 42 yards on the opening drive. He looked to be headed into the end zone on the second of those catches, but he was pulled down from behind inside the five. He did even better in the second half. With the Panthers facing a third-and-long deep in their own territory, Moore went up high along the sideline to pull in a pass and sprinted down the field for an 82-yard gain before being chased down. It is the third-longest play from scrimmage in the NFL the season and the longest non-scoring play so far. Moore finally found the end zone with a toe-tapping catch late in the fourth quarter to seemingly tie the game, but the Panthers made the questionable decision to go for two. Moore now has two big games sandwiched around two lackluster outings. Likely to be up-and-down all season, Moore will be a risk-reward FLEX play against the Seahawks.
report: D.J. Moore hauled in 7-of-8 targets for 157 yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 11 loss to the Lions.

impact: Mixon was held in check on the ground before ripping a 31-yard fourth quarter run. He caught an underthrown red-zone pass from Andy Dalton for the Bengals' only offensive touchdown. Mixon played a near every-down role despite concern over his workload and looked fully healthy. He'll remain an RB2 for Week 6 against the Steelers.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 22 times for 93 yards and caught 3-of-4 passes for 22 yards and a touchdown in the Bengals' Week 5 win over the Dolphins.

impact: He nabbed 4-of-7 targets for 20 yards in the pass game.  Mixon was cooking in the first half with 40 yards on five carries but just didn't get enough work.  The Bengals probably should have put the ball in his belly more instead of having Andy Dalton throw it 42 times at a 5.5 YPA clip while facing plenty of pressure.  Mixon did score a late touchdown from four yards out to save his fantasy day.  Mixon and the Bengals will be involved in a potential Week 7 shootout at Kansas City.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 11 times for 64 yards and one touchdown in the Bengals' Week 6 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Mixon continued to rarely leave the field with Giovanni Bernard sidelined. He fell victim to gameflow with the Bengals playing from behind but still managed a solid per-carry average. Mixon had some of his better runs called back on penalties. With Bernard likely at least another week away, Mixon is locked into another heavy workload in Week 8 against the Bucs.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 13 times for 50 yards in Week 7 against the Chiefs.

impact: Mixon continued to rarely leave the field with Giovanni Bernard sidelined. He fell victim to gameflow with the Bengals playing from behind but still managed a solid per-carry average. Mixon had some of his better runs called back on penalties. With Bernard likely at least another week away, Mixon is locked into another heavy workload in Week 8 against the Bucs.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 13 times for 50 yards in Week 7 against the Chiefs.

impact: Mixon's highlight play was a 43-yard run where he basically made every single Bucs defender miss.  Being utilized as a true workhorse under OC Bill Lazor, Mixon has earned every-week RB1 treatment.  He shouldn't lose many touches even with Giovani Bernard (knee) probable to return after the Bengals' Week 9 bye.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 21 times for 123 yards and two touchdowns and caught 3-of-4 targets for 15 yards in the Bengals' Week 8 win over the Bucs.

impact: Mixon started the day hot, touching the ball five times on the opening drive of the game for 42 total yards, then was hardly heard from again. The 13 touches for Mixon were his fewest in a game on the season as the Bengals worked Giovani Bernard back into the lineup and then let the game get completely away from them. Mixon will look for a better day in Week 11, but will run into a tough task on the road in Baltimore.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 11 times for 61 yards while catching two passes for 24 yards in Sunday's Week 10 loss to the Saints.

impact: Fantasy owners were lucky to come away with Mixon's goal-line score, set up by his own 28-yard reception on a screen pass.  Because the Bengals' running game was completely bottled up by the Ravens, and Cincinnati unsuccessfully leaned toward the pass with a 37-to-16 pass-to-run ratio.  Mixon will have a stronger outlook as a fringe RB1/2 at home versus the Browns next week.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 12 times for 14 yards and a touchdown and caught 3-of-3 targets for 38 yards in the Bengals' Week 11 loss to the Ravens.

impact: Making his first appearance since Week 1, Olsen appeared to be an every-snap player. He looked no worse for the wear, finding plenty of cushion in the Redskins' defense. Olsen will be at risk of re-injury going forward but acing today's test was a huge step in the right direction toward earning every-week fantasy trust. He does have a tough matchup for Week 7. The Eagles have been vulnerable to the pass but stout up the seam.
report: Greg Olsen caught 4-of-7 targets for 48 yards in the Panthers' Week 6 loss to the Redskins.

impact: Olsen got lost in a brutal first half by Cam Newton, who went 4-of-9 passing for 24 yards in the first two quarters. Devin Funchess and Torrey Smith did the second-half heavy lifting until Olsen’s goal-line score that proved the game winner. Week 8 opponent Baltimore has shown vulnerability in the middle of the field, so Olsen will have a better matchup next week than Carolina’s wideouts.
report: Greg Olsen caught 2-of-5 targets for five yards and a touchdown in the Panthers’ Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: Olsen got lost in a brutal first half by Cam Newton, who went 4-of-9 passing for 24 yards in the first two quarters. Devin Funchess and Torrey Smith did the second-half heavy lifting until Olsen’s goal-line score that proved the game winner. Week 8 opponent Baltimore has shown vulnerability in the middle of the field, so Olsen will have a better matchup next week than Carolina’s wideouts.
report: Greg Olsen caught 2-of-5 targets for five yards and a touchdown in the Panthers’ Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: His touchdown was from 11 yards out and has scored in 2-of-3 games since coming back from his broken foot.  This was his best game of the season.  Playing every down, Olsen will be a locked-in TE1 next week against Tampa.
report: Greg Olsen caught all four of his targets for 56 yards and one touchdown in the Panthers' Week 8 win over the Ravens.

impact: The catches and yards were both new season highs in what was easily Olsen's best game of 2018. Olsen continues to look 100 percent healthy even as he plays on a foot that is expected to require offseason surgery. Still a critical part of the Panthers' offense, Olsen will be locked and loaded as a TE1 for Thursday's short-week matchup with the Steelers.
report: Greg Olsen caught 6-of-6 targets for 76 yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 9 win over the Bucs.

impact: Olsen had a quiet night as the Panthers got boat raced. He came into the evening with a score in three-straight games and having cleared 56 yards in back-to-back contests. Olsen continued to look spry in the open field, belying his tenuous foot health. He will be a mid-range TE1 for Week 11 against the Lions.
report: Greg Olsen caught 4-of-6 targets for 40 yards in the Panthers' Week 10 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Olsen’s touchdown streak was broken last week against the Steelers, but he quickly started a new one in this game. Olsen was left wide open on play action at the goal line to cap an easy opening drive for the Panthers. That touchdown proved important for his fantasy day. Olsen did not catch any other passes in the first half, and he was limited to just one eight-yard catch after the break. He should find more success next week against the Seahawks.
report: Greg Olsen hauled in 2-of-3 targets for nine yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 11 loss to the Lions.

impact: Osweiler was not sacked. Making his first start for the Dolphins in place of an injured Ryan Tannehill, Osweiler was his usual head-scratching self in the first half but woke up by contributing 266 yards on 16-of-25 passing after the break. Brock had his most success throwing to Albert Wilson, who erupted for a pair of second-half touchdowns including a 75-yarder to tie the game with time winding down in the fourth quarter. Osweiler is now 3-0 against the Bears for his career. He's the first Dolphins signal-caller to reach the 300-yard mark in passing yards since Jay Cutler reached that threshold in Week 9 last season. If Tannehill's shoulder is still an issue, Osweiler could see the field again next week against the Lions.
report: Brock Osweiler completed 28-of-44 passes for a career-high 380 yards with three touchdowns and two interceptions while adding eight yards on two carries Sunday in the Dolphins’ Week 6 win over the Bears.

impact: The two-score day was Osweiler's second straight in place of Ryan Tannehill. Frankly, Osweiler has looked better than Tannehill. Both his scores were dimes delivered into the end zone. With the Dolphins playing on Thursday Night Football in Week 8, Tannehill seems unlikely to get cleared. Despite his good play — relatively speaking — Osweiler will remain a last-gasp QB2, especially since the Dolphins will likely be without Albert Wilson (hip). Wilson went down in the first half Sunday.
report: Brock Osweiler completed 22-of-31 passes for 239 yards and two touchdowns in the Dolphins' 32-21, Week 7 loss to the Lions.

impact: Osweiler was not sharp in this game. He did start off with a 26-yard gain to Danny Amendola, but he missed Amendola for what would have been a long gain later in the first quarter and threw behind DeVante Parker on what would have been another long play in the second. Miami finished the first half with just six points. Osweiler did even less after the break, but the defense bailed him out with a pick-six to essentially ice the game. With a trip to Green Bay up next, Osweiler will have to do more next week if the Dolphins hope to walk away with a win.
report: Brock Osweiler completed 15-of-24 passes for 139 yards in the Dolphins' Week 9 win over the Jets.

impact: In his defense, Miami was without starting tackles Laremy Tunsil and Ja'Wuan James, as well as starting LG Ted Larsen. Even so, Osweiler looked miserable under center and inevitably failed to throw a touchdown for the third consecutive game. Perhaps the Dolphins gets healthy and opt to open up the playbook over their upcoming bye, but the most likely scenario is David Fales taking reps if Ryan Tannehill is unable to return. Miami will again face an uphill battle in Week 12 against the Colts' unwavering pass attack.
report: Brock Osweiler completed 23-of-37 passes for 213 yards and one pick in Miami's dreadful Week 10 loss to the Packers.

impact: Suddenly a Dolphin a few weeks ago, O'Leary now has five catches over his past two games. He should stay involved for the Dolphins' Week 8 Thursday night game, as both Albert Wilson (hip) and Kenny Stills (leg) are banged up.
report: Nick O'Leary caught 2-of-3 targets for 23 yards in the Dolphins' Week 7 loss to the Lions.

impact: Suddenly a Dolphin a few weeks ago, O'Leary now has five catches over his past two games. He should stay involved for the Dolphins' Week 8 Thursday night game, as both Albert Wilson (hip) and Kenny Stills (leg) are banged up.
report: Nick O'Leary caught 2-of-3 targets for 23 yards in the Dolphins' Week 7 loss to the Lions.

impact: Michel looked fully healthy despite being a game-time decision. The Patriots continued to feature him in an early-down role, giving him his largest workload of the year. Both of Michel’s touchdowns came on goal-line conversions, and he’s now scored in three straight games. Michel will remain a locked-in RB2 for Week 7.
report: Sony Michel rushed 24 times for 106 yards and two touchdowns in Week 6 against the Chiefs.

impact: The Patriots got nothing going on the ground early, then fell behind by multiple scores.  That's a perfect recipe for Michel to be a fantasy bust.  Michel will have New England's Week 11 bye to work through any lingering effects of his recurring knee woes.  He still offers RB2 upside for the stretch run.
report: Sony Michel managed 31 yards on 11 carries in New England's Week 10 loss to the Titans.

impact: Miller wasn't targeted in the pass game against a Colts defense that has shown an inability to cover running backs.  Instead, the Texans opted to feature rookie WR Keke Coutee in the short passing game, targeting him a team-high 15 times.  Miller remains without a rushing touchdown through four games and ceded 12 carries to Alfred Blue, who mustered just 31 yards.  Miller has been a steady RB2 to this point, but has provided no ceiling.  He gets the Cowboys in Week 5.
report: Lamar Miller rushed 15 times for 49 yards in the Texans' Week 4 win over the Colts.

impact: Alfred Blue got his share of carries in this game, but Miller still operated as the clear lead back. That usage did not lead to a big fantasy day, but Miller played better than his numbers suggest. He also could have had a touchdown on a trick play, but DeAndre Hopkins just missed him. All of that said, a possible D'Onta Foreman return and a tough matchup with Jacksonville will make Miller more of a low-end FLEX option next week.
report: Lamar Miller rushed 15 times for 46 yards and caught 2-of-3 targets for 25 yards in the Texans' Week 6 win over the Bills.

impact: The Texans stayed committed to their rushing attack as underdogs on the road, and Miller rewarded them with his best game of the season.  He out-touched Alfred Blue 23 to 8 as Houston reeled off its fourth straight victory following an 0-3 start.  Suddenly favorites to win the AFC South, the Texans go back home for Week 8 Thursday Night Football against the Dolphins.  Back in Houston's featured-back role, Miller will be a quality RB2 play in that game.
report: Lamar Miller rushed 22 times for 100 yards and a touchdown and caught 1-of-3 targets for -1 yard in the Texans' Week 7 win over the Jaguars.

impact: His 27 receiving yards (on just two catches) through the air were more than he could muster on 12 carries on the ground, hence why Alfred Blue came in and out-carried Miller 15-12 on the day. The broadcast noted that coach Bill O'Brien discussed scaling Miller's workload back to "keep him healthy" during their production meeting, so that's another explanation. Miller was completely ineffective, though, averaging 1.8 YPC. Alfred Blue didn't perform much better (2.6 YPC), but it's still concerning the two essentially split work. Miller was coming off of consecutive standout 100-yard outings and he'll look to replicate that (as long as the volume is there) when Houston returns from their bye against the Redskins.
report: Lamar Miller basically fell down on all 12 of his carries, rushing for 21 yards in the Texans' Week 9 win over the Broncos.

impact: He out-touched Alfred Blue 23 to 8 after Blue and Miller shared carries in Week 9, prior to Houston's Week 10 bye.
