When healthy, it's clear Miller is coach Bill O'Brien's preferred backfield option.  Ahead of a difficult Week 12 matchup versus Tennessee's stout run defense, Miller will remain a volume-based RB2.
report: Lamar Miller rushed 20 times for 86 yards and caught 3-of-5 targets for 22 yards in the Texans' Week 11 win over Washington.

impact: Active for the first time this season, Meredith made the most of his lone target. Meredith’s 11-yarder staked New Orleans to a 23-21 lead with just over six minutes remaining in the third quarter. The 26-year-old cleared one hurdle by recording his first catch in over 20 months, but he’s still not worthy of fantasy consideration. Meredith will try to take another step forward against the Giants in Week 4.
report: Cameron Meredith registered an 11-yard touchdown on his lone target Sunday in the Saints’ Week 3 win over the Falcons.

impact: Meredith caught his lone target for an 11-yard score in his 2018 debut last week and was more involved this Sunday.  The stat line isn't sexy, but Meredith should continue to push for heavy snaps behind Michael Thomas.  He'll again be on the WR4/5 map next week at home against the Redskins.
report: Cameron Meredith caught 3-of-4 targets for 32 yards in the Saints' Week 4 win over the Giants.

impact: Miller appeared to suffer a hand or arm injury late in the game and didn't return, but the Bears were quiet on in-game news. Through three weeks, Miller has caught 8-of-11 targets for 60 yards and a touchdown.
report: Anthony Miller caught 4-of-5 targets for 35 yards in Sunday's Week 3 win over the Cardinals.

impact: This was the rookie's first game back from a dislocated shoulder. Miller's day, at least for fantasy purposes, would have been a lot different had he pulled in a Mitchell Trubisky deep bomb in the first quarter. He was wide open but Trubisky badly overthrew him. Miller did visit the end zone later on, snagging a 29-yard touchdown grab to put Chicago back ahead (at least briefly) in the fourth quarter. The second-round pick has scored in two of his past three outings, though he's averaged just 25 receiving yards per game during that span. Miller will remain off the fantasy radar next week against New England.
report: Anthony Miller secured one-of-four targets for 29 yards and a touchdown Sunday in the Bears’ Week 6 loss to Miami.

impact: Miller earned an end-zone target in the first half, but he failed to haul it in. He came back with an important third-down conversion late in the third quarter and added a catch on the final drive, but that was it despite seven targets, although Mitchell Trubisky's play certainly did not help. Miller is just a bench stash at this point.
report: Anthony Miller hauled in 2-of-7 targets for 35 yards in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Miller earned an end-zone target in the first half, but he failed to haul it in. He came back with an important third-down conversion late in the third quarter and added a catch on the final drive, but that was it despite seven targets, although Mitchell Trubisky's play certainly did not help. Miller is just a bench stash at this point.
report: Anthony Miller hauled in 2-of-7 targets for 35 yards in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Miller led the team in targets with Allen Robinson out. He got open on a back shoulder corner route for his TD, but didn't do much with his expanded role. Miller would be the preferred play over Taylor Gabriel if Robinson misses another week.
report: Anthony Miller caught 3-of-7 passes for 37 yards and a touchdown in Week 8 against the Jets.

impact: He led the team in catches, receiving yards, and targets in a game where Mitchell Trubisky needed only complete 12 passes in a smooth-sailing win.  Bears Week 10 opponent Detroit has been getting lit up by slot receivers, so Miller will stay in the WR4/flex discussion in Chicago's next game.
report: Anthony Miller caught 5-of-6 targets for 49 yards in the Bears' Week 9 win over the Bills.

impact: The 122 yards were more than Miller had in his previous three games combined. The rookie out of Memphis made his living off long plays. He was the recipient of a 45-yard touchdown strike—his fourth of the season—from Mitchell Trubisky early in the second quarter and later broke free for a 55-yard catch-and-run on Chicago's opening drive of the second half. Detroit's secondary showed little resistance without Darius Slay (knee), leading to the biggest game of Miller's young career. The 24-year-old will try to build off Sunday's breakout next week when the Bears host division-rival Minnesota on Sunday Night Football.
report: Anthony Miller cruised to five catches for 122 yards and a touchdown on six targets Sunday in the Bears’ Week 10 victory over the Lions.

impact: As expected, McGuire immediately took over as the No. 2 running back behind Isaiah Crowell. He only had two carries heading into the two-minute drive in the second quarter, but he jump-started that series with a 20-yard catch on the first play. With the offense chasing the game in the fourth, McGuire added a few touches and yards, but he was never going to have a big game with the offense struggling. That could be a concern moving forward, but he looks like at worst a bench stash worth picking up even in shallow leagues.
report: Elijah McGuire carried the ball seven times for 30 yards and hauled in 3-of-5 targets for 37 yards in the Jets' Week 9 loss to the Dolphins

impact: He outgained Isaiah Crowell 57 to 37, although Crowell put up more fantasy points due to his five-yard rushing TD in what amounted to garbage time.  McGuire has looked like Gang Green's best back since coming off IR/return two games ago.  The Jets should consider increasing McGuire's stretch-run workload after their Week 11 bye.  McGuire is a hold in 12- and 14-team PPR leagues.
report: Elijah McGuire rushed six times for 30 yards and caught 3-of-6 targets for 27 yards in the Jets' Week 10 loss to Buffalo.

impact: McDonald's biggest impact came when he was called for an illegal block in the back penalty. He got soundly out-produced by Jesse James, though both players drew five targets. Per Pro Football Focus, James out-snapped McDonald just 45-37. For now, James and McDonald are going to cancel each other out as TE2s in fantasy.
report: Vance McDonald caught 3-of-5 targets for 26 yards in the Steelers' Week 2 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: McDonald got out-produced by Jesse James as Ben Roethlisberger focused on getting Antonio Brown going. McDonald has had some monster games but has also yet to draw more than five targets in a contest. He will be a volatile TE1 in a down year for the position.
report: Vance McDonald caught 1-of-2 targets for six yards in the Steelers' Week 5 win over the Falcons.

impact: McDonald did almost all of his damage in the first half, catching five balls for 67 yards.  Jesse James then got most of the looks in the second half, catching five balls for 26 yards.  McDonald has big games here and there and is long on talent.  He'll be a TE1 Week 8 against the Browns after the bye.
report: Vance McDonald caught 7-of-8 targets for 68 yards in the Steelers' Week 6 win over the Bengals.

impact: McDonald did almost all of his damage in the first half, catching five balls for 67 yards.  Jesse James then got most of the looks in the second half, catching five balls for 26 yards.  McDonald has big games here and there and is long on talent.  He'll be a TE1 Week 8 against the Browns after the bye.
report: Vance McDonald caught 7-of-8 targets for 68 yards in the Steelers' Week 6 win over the Bengals.

impact: McDonald's highlight of the day came on a 22-yard reception in the third quarter in which he ran over Derrick Kindred. McDonald was victim of the Steelers not being forced to pass in the second half of the game. McDonald will be fringe-TE1 option in Week 9 against a Ravens defense that has allowed an opposing tight end to score in back-to-back games.
report: Vance McDonald caught all three of his targets for 47 yards in Sunday's Week 8 win over the Browns.

impact: It was an innocuous day for the tight end, though McDonald was involved in one bizarre play. Tavon Young recovered a fumble after stripping McDonald late in the second quarter and took it all the way for a touchdown, though replay showed that McDonald was down by contact. The 28-year-old hasn't found the end zone since Week 3, but remains a streaming consideration at a weak fantasy position. He'll look to bounce back Thursday when the Steelers host Carolina.
report: Vance McDonald contributed three catches for 25 yards on six targets Sunday in Pittsburgh’s Week 9 win over the Ravens.

impact: McDonald cashed in a plus matchup for his second score of the year. He made a lovely, diving catch in the back of the end zone, though it seemed unclear if he actually possessed the ball. The replay booth did not see enough to overturn the call. McDonald will be a boom-or-bust TE2 for Week 11 against the Jaguars.
report: Vance McDonald caught 4-of-4 targets for 44 yards and a touchdown in the Steelers' Week 10 win over the Panthers.

impact: The highlight of the day for McDonald was skying over Jaguars defenders in the end zone for an 11-yard touchdown to pull the Steelers within a field goal late in the fourth quarter. McDonald hasn't reached 50 yards in a game since Week 6, but will still find himself a passable tight end option Week 12 when the Steelers head to Denver.
report: Vance McDonald caught 3-of-6 targets for 27 yards in Sunday's Week 11 win over the Jaguars.

impact: He averaged a pathetic 4.0 yards per attempt, and not a single Jets pass catcher reached 35 yards.  McCown was not the savior for Gang Green's broken offense, which has been decimated by injuries and poor line play.  Sam Darnold (foot) figures to resume starting when the Jets come out of their Week 11 bye.
report: Josh McCown completed just 17-of-34 passes for 135 yards and two interceptions in the Jets' Week 10 blowout loss to the Bills.

impact: McCoy has now been held below 10 touches in 2-of-3 games and has handled the ball only 29 times all season. Speaking afterward, McCoy said "the plan was to get me the ball," and that he had no explanation for his light usage. The scoreboard was a major problem — the Bills were trailing all afternoon — but McCoy is more than capable of catching the ball, and change-of-pace Marcus Murphy was inactive. The Bills' Josh Allen-led offense is proving catastrophic for McCoy's fantasy value. He will be a high-risk FLEX option in Week 5 against the Titans' upstart defense.
report: LeSean McCoy rushed five times for 24 yards in the Bills' Week 4 loss to the Packers, adding three receptions for 13 additional yards.

impact: And it felt like a career game for McCoy after how poorly he started the season.  McCoy's 26 touches and 108 total yards were both easily year highs on a Bills offense that has struggled to function week to week.  Nevertheless, McCoy showed juice on several chunk-yardage gains and clearly has plenty left in his tank.  He will remain a risky RB2/flex option in Week 6 at Houston.
report: LeSean McCoy rushed 24 times for 85 yards and caught 2-of-3 targets for 23 yards in the Bills' Week 5 win over the Titans.

impact: Aside from Josh Allen scrambles and a random Nathan Peterman touchdown, McCoy was the Bills' offense in this one. He started his day with a 22-yard catch on an ill-advised throw from Allen, and he consistently made things happen in the running game. Unfortunately, it was not enough for the Bills to score more than 13 points. Volume will hopefully keep McCoy in the FLEX range all season, but touchdowns will be difficult to find, assuming he is not traded.
report: LeSean McCoy rushed 16 times for 73 yards and hauled in 3-of-5 targets for 21 yards in the Bills' Week 6 loss to the Texans.

impact: McCoy injured his head early in the first quarter after taking a hit from Colts CB Kenny Moore. It looked like he may have also injured his right leg/ankle on the play. He'll finish his day with just one yard on two carries. With Shady ruled out, ball-carrier responsibilities will now fall with Chris Ivory.
report: LeSean McCoy (head) will not return to Sunday's Week 7 game against the Colts.

impact: McCoy has 23 yards on 22 carries over the past two weeks, and it's through no fault of his own.  The Bills' offense can't move the ball, and the offensive line isn't opening any holes.  Chris Ivory did exit Sunday's loss with a shoulder injury, potentially raising McCoy's workload projection ahead of a Week 10 date with the Jets.  McCoy will remain a low-floor RB2/flex in that game.
report: LeSean McCoy rushed ten times for ten yards and caught 4-of-4 targets for 19 yards in the Bills' Week 9 loss to Chicago.

impact: The Bills embarrassed the Jets 41-10 in a game that will likely seal Todd Bowles' fate in New York.  A colossal Weeks 1-9 fantasy bust, McCoy roared on Sunday against a Jets run defense that has fallen apart since a strong start.  Matt Barkley gave Buffalo its most competent quarterback play all season, although the Bills will likely turn back to top-ten pick Josh Allen after their Week 11 bye.  McCoy will remain a volatile RB2 option down the stretch.
report: LeSean McCoy rushed 26 times for 113 yards and two touchdowns and caught his lone target for five yards in the Bills' Week 10 win over the Jets.

impact: Greg Olsen exited early with a foot injury, which allowed McCaffrey to flourish even more in Carolina's passing game. His nine targets and 45 receiving yards were both team-highs. It's still concerning that Cam Newton used his towering 6'5" 245-pound frame to bowl over defenders inside the five-yard line, essentially robbing CMC of a goal line score. It's also an issue for McCaffrey's future outlook that he handled only three more carries (10) than C.J. Anderson (7). His floor is safe due to his involvement as a receiver, but at least through Week 1, McCaffrey isn't being used like the bell-cow coach Ron Rivera promised he'd be.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed 10 times for 50 yards and caught 6-of-9 targets for 45 yards in the Panthers' Week 1 victory over the Cowboys.

impact: McCaffrey clearly did very little as a rusher and was unable to convert his one inside-the-10-yard-line carry, picking up one yard from the six before Jarius Wright then caught a five-yard score.  However, McCaffrey was easily Cam Newton's lone reliable target, setting a new career-high with his 14 grabs.  He was targeted on 33% of Newton's passes.  Still, a touchdown would have been nice, but McCaffrey did well for his PPR owners in a predictable spot against the Deion Jones-less Falcons.  McCaffrey will be an RB1 next week in Cincinnati.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed eight times for 37 yards and caught 14-of-15 targets for 102 yards in the Panthers' 31-24, Week 2 loss to the Falcons.

impact: The Panthers' coaching staff must have spotted something it liked about attacking Cincinnati's interior defense on tape, because they did it over and over and over again with such dominance McCaffrey more than doubled his previous single-game high for rushing yards.  As Carolina needed only 15 pass completions to win, McCaffrey's receiving usage took a corresponding hit.  He'll rest his legs during the Panthers' Week 4 bye.  McCaffrey's weekly touch counts three games in are 16 > 22 > 30.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed 28 times for 184 yards and caught 2-of-2 targets for ten yards in the Panthers' Week 3 win over the Bengals.

impact: McCaffrey's usage in the passing game, or lack thereof, was somewhat of a disappointment, though he salvaged the afternoon for fantasy owners by scoring a late touchdown on a screen from Cam Newton. The 18-yard score from Newton marked C-Mac's first end-zone since Week 15 of last season. McCaffrey dominated the backfield work as usual, out-touching veteran bruiser C.J. Anderson by an enormous 22-4 margin. The talented 22-year-old will remain an upper-echelon fantasy option when he takes the field next week at Washington.
report: Christian McCaffrey earned 58 yards on 17 carries while also securing five targets for 35 yards and a touchdown on six targets Sunday in Carolina’s Week 5 win over the Giants.

impact: McCaffrey was finding nice holes on the ground in the early going, but the Panthers quickly abandoned the run after a pair of D.J. Moore turnovers had them playing from behind. McCaffrey probably should have had a few more catches, but Cam Newton didn't see him on a few wide-open looks. McCaffrey will enter next week's game with the Eagles averaging 117 yards from scrimmage.
report: Christian McCaffrey caught 7-of-8 targets for 46 yards in the Panthers' Week 6 loss to the Redskins, adding eight carries for 20 additional yards.

impact: McCaffrey’s touches were a season low because the Panthers fell behind 17-0 at the half. CMC did play a big role in the comeback victory on a 22-yard reception down the left sideline, but he was tackled inside the five-yard line before Greg Olsen’s game winner. McCaffrey was essentially vultured by Curtis Samuel from 14 yards out on an end-around earlier in the game where McCaffrey operated as a decoy. Even against a tough Ravens defense in Week 8, McCaffrey’s passing-game involvement will keep him in the low-end RB1 hunt.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed seven times for 29 yards and caught 6-of-6 targets for 51 yards in the Panthers' Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: McCaffrey’s touches were a season low because the Panthers fell behind 17-0 at the half. CMC did play a big role in the comeback victory on a 22-yard reception down the left sideline, but he was tackled inside the five-yard line before Greg Olsen’s game winner. McCaffrey was essentially vultured by Curtis Samuel from 14 yards out on an end-around earlier in the game where McCaffrey operated as a decoy. Even against a tough Ravens defense in Week 8, McCaffrey’s passing-game involvement will keep him in the low-end RB1 hunt.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed seven times for 29 yards and caught 6-of-6 targets for 51 yards in the Panthers' Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: The yards are nothing to write home about, but McCaffrey scored for the first time since Week 5, with both coming in the red zone.  His first was an 11-yard run where McCaffrey was nearly bottled up in the backfield for a loss.  His second touchdown was a fluke pass intended for Devin Funchess at the goal line that Eric Weddle batted into the air before McCaffrey skied in to catch it in the end zone.  McCaffrey will be an RB1 next week at home against the Bucs.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed 14 times for 45 yards and one touchdown and caught 4-of-6 targets for 11 yards in the Panthers' Week 8 win over the Ravens.

impact: McCaffrey's 157 yards from scrimmage were his second most of the season. The second-year pro had little trouble finding huge cushions against the Bucs' pathetic defense, notching gains of 32, 35, 14 and 20 yards. He also notched three carries inside the Bucs' five-yard line, converting two of them for scores. It was what McCaffrey should have done against the Bucs' embarrassingly-bad defense. The sledding will be tougher against the Steelers on Thursday Night Football in Week 10.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed 17 times for 79 yards and two touchdowns in the Panthers' Week 9 win over the Bucs, adding five receptions for 78 additional yards.

impact: McCaffrey rolled up 60 yards on the Panthers' opening drive, capping it off with a silky smooth 20-yard touchdown reception. His 25-yarder from Cam Newton one quarter later was almost as pretty. McCaffrey's third score was a fantasy gift, as he punched in a goal line carry with the Panthers losing 52-14 late in the fourth quarter. The No. 8 overall pick of last year's draft now has seven touchdowns over his past three games. That's Todd Gurley/Kareem Hunt-level production. For Week 11, CMC gets a Lions run defense that's been soft.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed 14 times for 77 yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 10 loss to the Steelers, adding five receptions for 61 yards and two additional scores.

impact: McCaffrey finished the game with 110 total yards, but it was a bit of a quiet day for the star back. He did not make many impact plays outside of a 34-yard catch in the fourth quarter, and he was shockingly easy to tackle on several of his opportunities in the open field. His fantasy day could have been much better, but he was tackled inside the five on two different drives. McCaffrey will remain a solid RB1 next week against the Seahawks.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed 13 times for 53 yards and hauled in 6-of-8 targets for 57 yards in the Panthers' Week 11 loss to the Lions.

impact: It was the Browns' first victory in 635 days. Unfathomable. With all due respect to Taylor, Mayfield looked like he was playing a different sport. Quick and decisive where Taylor was methodical and inaccurate, Mayfield was firing lasers. His numbers would have been even better if not for a few drops, though he was also lucky to escape without an interception. There will be some rookie growing pains, but Mayfield is going to transform an offense that was close to unwatchable throughout its first 2.5 games. His insertion under center will vault David Njoku back into TE1 consideration while putting Antonio Callaway on the WR3 map.
report: On in relief of an injured Tyrod Taylor (concussion), Baker Mayfield completed 17-of-23 passes for 201 yards, zero touchdowns and zero interceptions in the Browns' 21-17, Week 3 win over the Jets.

impact: He added four rushes for ten yards.  One of Mayfield's picks was innocous, getting inercepted by Raiders S Reggie Nelson at the end of regulation.  Otherwise, Mayfield consistently kept Cleveland's offense on the move despite getting very little help from his pass catchers.  Antonio Callaway committed multiple drops, and Jarvis Landry, David Njoku, and Duke Johnson all dropped passes as well.  Mayfield will be a two-QB-league starter in Week 5 against the Ravens.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 21-of-41 passes for 295 yards, two touchdowns, and two interceptions in the Browns' Week 4 loss to Oakland.

impact: Mayfield added 23 yards rushing on two attempts. He connected with Rashard Higgins for a 19-yard touchdown with 40 seconds left in the first half for the only touchdown of the game. Mayfield was at his best in overtime, connecting on 4-of-7 passes for 80 yards, including a 39-yard catch and run by Derrick Willies to set up the game-winning field goal. Mayfield has brought excitement to the Browns organization, leading the team two wins over the past the three weeks, but those real-life results have not translated to major fantasy success. Mayfield will enter Week 6 as a lower-end QB2 when the Browns host the Chargers.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 25-of-43 passes for 342 yards with one touchdown and one interception in Sunday's Week 5 win over the Ravens.

impact: Mayfield added eight yards rushing on two carries. Sunday was the first game in which Mayfield looked like a rookie as he threw two interceptions on late throws. He was under constant pressure, taking five sacks in the game and was constantly moved off his spot by the Charger pass rush. Mayfield's lone touchdown came on a 1-yard cosmetic score to David Njoku in garbage time. Despite his struggles today, Mayfield will be a popular streaming option Week 7 on the road versus the Buccaneers.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 22-of-46 passes for 238 yards with one touchdown and two interceptions in Sunday's Week 6 loss to the Chargers.

impact: Mayfield added a season-high 43 rushing yards on four carries on the ground. The day overall was a disappointment for fantasy owners as the Bucs had allowed a 300-yard passer in every game to date prior to Sunday. Mayfield and the Browns were invisible in the first half as he threw for just 62 yards through the opening two quarters. In the second half, Mayfield found David Njoku for a 15-yard score to open the half and then connected with Jarvis Landry for a 16-yard score to tie the game with 2:28 left in regulation. Mayfield was under constant duress once again, taking five sacks, the third straight game in which he was sacked at least five times. His one blemish on the day was when he rushed for a clear first down deep in Tampa Bay territory on fourth down, but then fumbled the ball backwards out of bounds behind the sticks, costing the Browns at least a field goal attempt. Mayfield will only be a QB2 option Week 8 when the Browns head to Pittsburgh.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 23-of-34 passes for 215 yards and two touchdowns in Sunday's Week 7 loss to the Buccaneers.

impact: Mayfield added a season-high 43 rushing yards on four carries on the ground. The day overall was a disappointment for fantasy owners as the Bucs had allowed a 300-yard passer in every game to date prior to Sunday. Mayfield and the Browns were invisible in the first half as he threw for just 62 yards through the opening two quarters. In the second half, Mayfield found David Njoku for a 15-yard score to open the half and then connected with Jarvis Landry for a 16-yard score to tie the game with 2:28 left in regulation. Mayfield was under constant duress once again, taking five sacks, the third straight game in which he was sacked at least five times. His one blemish on the day was when he rushed for a clear first down deep in Tampa Bay territory on fourth down, but then fumbled the ball backwards out of bounds behind the sticks, costing the Browns at least a field goal attempt. Mayfield will only be a QB2 option Week 8 when the Browns head to Pittsburgh.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 23-of-34 passes for 215 yards and two touchdowns in Sunday's Week 7 loss to the Buccaneers.

impact: Mayfield added nine yards rushing on his lone carry. He struggled on the road in this one as his 5.0 yards per pass attempt were his lowest in a start this season. He threw both of his touchdowns in the second half, a 1-yard score to Antonio Callaway in the third quarter and then a 24-yard cosmetic score to Seth DeValve with six seconds left in regulation. Mayfield will enter Week 9 as a QB2 at home when the Browns host the high-powered Chiefs.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 22-of-36 passes for 180 yards and two touchdowns with an interception in Sunday's Week 8 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Despite the loss, there were positives to draw from Mayfield's sixth start. His 7.1 yards per pass attempt were his most since Week 5 while his 69 percent completion rate was the highest rate he's completed in any start this season. Mayfield threw multiple touchdowns for the third straight game, with both going to Duke Johnson on Sunday. Mayfield will once again find a favorable matchup in Week 10 at home against the Falcons.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 29-of-42 passes for 297 yards with two touchdowns and one interception in Sunday's Week 9 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: After a promising outing in new OC Freddie Kitchens' Week 9 debut, Mayfield had his best game of the season against the Falcons. The No. 1 overall pick completed his first 13 passes as the Browns got out to a 21-10 third quarter lead. The Browns were using some exotic formations, including three-back, full-house backfields. Mayfield really spread the ball around, with nine different players catching passes. He was accurate and decisive. The Browns go on bye for Week 11 before returning against the Bengals' sieve-like defense in Week 12.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 17-of-20 passes for 216 yards and three touchdowns in the Browns' 28-16, Week 10 win over the Falcons.

impact: Matthews apparently played over 30 snaps, but he wasn't seen.  Learning a new offense after missing basically everything to this point, it may take a few weeks until we see Matthews on the same page with his quarterbacks.
report: Rishard Matthews was not targeted in the Titans' Week 1 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: It's the second week in a row that Matthews has basically been invisible. The Titans were admittedly down to their backup quarterback and third-string left tackle, but Matthews still finished sixth on the team in receiving yards. His 2018 campaign is off to a horrendous start after spending most of camp on PUP with a torn meniscus.
report: Rishard Matthews caught 2-of-4 targets for eight yards in the Titans' Week 2 win over the Texans.

impact: He can be dropped with yardage totals of 0, 8, and 3 through three games.
report: Rishard Matthews caught 1-of-2 targets for three yards in Week 3.

impact: Coming off the bench to replace concussed Blaine Gabbert from the first quarter on, Mariota's passes consisted of wobbly, egg-beater floaters that were difficult for his receivers to catch.  Mariota is playing with a nerve problem in his throwing elbow.  But he showed impressive toughness, racking up yards on the ground and doing just enough to eke out the three-point win.  Mariota isn't roster worthy in 12-team leagues, but we would guess he'll start in Week 4 against Philadelphia.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 12-of-18 passes for 100 yards and rushed seven times for 51 yards in the Titans' Week 3 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Dealing with an elbow injury, Mariota had failed to top 103 yards in any game this season, but he looked quite a bit better in this one. Coming out firing, Mariota had 115 yards in the first quarter despite missing Corey Davis on what should have been a long gain, and he kept pushing the ball downfield all game. His newfound health did not stifle his rushing numbers, either, as he consistently made big plays on the ground. His magnum opus was a 16-play, 75-yard drive in overtime to win the game. He converted one fourth down with a great throw to Taywan Taylor, another with a dump off to Dion Lewis, and found Davis in the end zone for the game-winner. Now healthy, Mariota will be in the QB1 conversation next week in Buffalo.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 30-of-43 passes for 344 yards, two touchdowns, and an interception in the Titans' Week 4, overtime win over the Eagles, adding 46 yards and a touchdown on the ground.

impact: He only rushed twice for ten yards, although one was a hurdling doozy for a key first down.  Mariota was not helped by a back-breaking third-down drop by Nick Williams in the fourth quarter that would have gone for an easy touchdown, but Mariota also got away with numerous head-scratching throws when under duress.  Mariota heads back to Nashville in Week 6 for a brutal matchup versus Baltimore.  He has settled in as a dicey two-quarterback-league play.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 14-of-26 passes for 129 yards and an interception in the Titans' Week 5 loss at Buffalo.

impact: Mariota didn't stand a chance behind the Titans' O-line Sunday afternoon, losing 66 yards on a whopping 11 sacks taken. It was the second time in as many games that Tennessee's offense failed to score a touchdown, and the third time in the last four weeks that Mariota's failed to eclipse the daunting 130-yard mark. Even Corey Davis was dragged down in the Titans' woeful performance, hauling in just one catch for 24 yards. It's possible Mariota's playing through an ailing elbow injury suffered earlier in the year, but Coach Mike Vrabel's offense has still undoubtedly been one of the most disappointing units of 2018. The Titans will attempt to bounce back in Wembley against the Chargers next week.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 10-of-15 passes for 117 yards in the Titans' dreadful Week 6 loss to the Ravens.

impact: He added 38 yards on seven rushes. Mariota led the Titans to a game-tying fourth-quarter drive but failed to hit the two-point conversion. It was an improvement from last week, but Mariota continues to be a huge disappointment under a new coaching staff. The Titans had just three touchdowns in their last 45 drives going into Sunday. Mariota will be a QB2 coming out of the bye in Week 9 against the Cowboys.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 24-of-32 passes for 237 yards with a touchdown and an interception in Week 7 against the Chargers.

impact: He added 38 yards on seven rushes. Mariota led the Titans to a game-tying fourth-quarter drive but failed to hit the two-point conversion. It was an improvement from last week, but Mariota continues to be a huge disappointment under a new coaching staff. The Titans had just three touchdowns in their last 45 drives going into Sunday. Mariota will be a QB2 coming out of the bye in Week 9 against the Cowboys.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 24-of-32 passes for 237 yards with a touchdown and an interception in Week 7 against the Chargers.

impact: He added 32 yards and a third touchdown on 10 attempts as a runner, including a couple late kneel-downs.  Things couldn't have started any worse for the Titans' offense, as Mariota was sack-fumbled on the opening series and then lost a second fumble on the very next possession on a botched handoff with Dion Lewis.  Things quickly turned around in the second quarter and the rest of the way, with Mariota hooking up with Lewis for an 18-yard score on a screen pass.  He also had a perfectly-paced 36-yard deep shot down the middle to Darius Jennings on a bit of a wobbler into triple-coverage.  Mariota's second passing score was a beautifully-read RPO shovel pass to Jonnu Smith from seven yards away.  Mariota has had his two best games of the season against NFC East teams.  The Titans host the Patriots in Week 10.  Mariota will be a QB2.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 21-of-29 passes for 240 yards and two touchdowns in the Titans' 28-14, Week 9 win over the Cowboys on Monday night.

impact: He added a 21-yard reception and two carries for 21 yards on the ground.  Mariota has now been highly efficient in three straight games, the first a one-point loss to the Chargers in a game the Titans very nearly won, and the last two upset victories over Dallas and New England.  Mariota is squarely in the QB1 crosshairs ahead of a potential Week 11 shootout at Indy's Lucas Oil Stadium.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 16-of-24 passes for 228 yards and two touchdowns in the Titans' Week 10 win over the Patriots.

impact: Sharing time with Jalen Richard as the Raiders' backups to Marshawn Lynch, Martin is worth rostering in fantasy leagues only as a deep-league handcuff/stash.
report: Doug Martin managed 11 yards on five carries in the Raiders' Week 4 win.

impact: Martin has been one of the league's least effective ball-carriers in recent years, but he actually looked decent in his first start of 2018, particularly in the second half when he contributed 55 yards on nine carries. Unfortunately the ex-Buc lost a fumble at the worst possible time with Oakland trying to mount a fourth-quarter comeback. He was also stonewalled on each of his two goal-line carries during the third quarter. Martin lost passing-down reps to Jalen Richard but still out-touched him 15-10 on the afternoon. The Muscle Hamster should continue to lead the backfield in Marshawn Lynch's absence. With six teams on bye, he'll be an acceptable RB2/3 next week at San Francisco.
report: Doug Martin collected 72 yards on 13 carries while also snagging two catches for 17 yards on two targets Sunday in Oakland’s Week 8 loss to the Colts.

impact: Martin was a bright spot for the Raiders in this one. He kept the offense moving for 50 yards on the ground in the first half, and he came up with a 23-yard catch-and-run after the break. Unfortunately, he took a back seat with the Raiders chasing the game late, something which will be a problem for the rest of the season. Martin has quietly looked pretty good the last several weeks, but the offense makes him just a FLEX play even in a good matchup against the Cardinals.
report: Doug Martin rushed 15 times for 61 yards and hauled in all three of his targets for 31 yards in the Raiders' Week 10 loss to the Chargers.

impact: Martin also caught a six-yard pass. All 11 of Martin's touches came before the break. The veteran was not injured. Coach Jon Gruden told the CBS booth he simply wanted to see what Jalen Richard and DeAndre Washington could do in the second half. Martin took the benching in stride, enthusiastically chest bumping Gruden after the Raiders' last-second victory. Richard was effective in Martin's absence, but the Cardinals are a soft run matchup. Only Richard will have any FLEX appeal for Week 12 against the Ravens' elite defense. Martin's 2018 fantasy future is uncertain.
report: Doug Martin rushed 10 times for 52 yards in the Raiders' Week 11 win over the Cardinals but was benched at halftime.

impact: Marshall served as the No. 1 target after Doug Baldwin left with a knee injury, pacing the team in targets and getting several chances in the end zone. He was flagged for offensive pass interference on one of those targets, but he was able to come down with a beautiful throw from Russell Wilson for a 20-yard touchdown. With Baldwin looking at best questionable for Week 2, Marshall needs to be added in most leagues.
report: Brandon Marshall hauled in 3-of-6 targets for 46 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 1 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Marshall tied for the team lead with six targets but obviously he didn’t make the most of it. He beat Chidobe Awuzie for a 27-yard grab in the third quarter, then celebrated by doing pushups. Even with Doug Baldwin sidelined the past two games, Marshall has yet to establish himself as anything more than a deep bench stash in fantasy.
report: Brandon Marshall snagged two-of-six targets for 30 yards Sunday in Seattle’s Week 3 win over the Cowboys.

impact: Marshall tied for the team lead with six targets but obviously he didn’t make the most of it. He beat Chidobe Awuzie for a 27-yard grab in the third quarter, then celebrated by doing pushups. Even with Doug Baldwin sidelined the past two games, Marshall has yet to establish himself as anything more than a deep bench stash in fantasy.
report: Brandon Marshall snagged two-of-six targets for 30 yards Sunday in Seattle’s Week 3 win over the Cowboys.

impact: With Doug Baldwin returning to action, Marshall was relegated to an ancillary option in the offense. He now has 10 catches for 125 yards on the season. He is not worth rostering in fantasy leagues moving forward. Seattle hosts the Rams in Week 5.
report: Brandon Marshall caught 1-of-3 targets for 5 yards in Sunday's Week 4 win over the Cardinals.

impact: With Doug Baldwin returning to action, Marshall was relegated to an ancillary option in the offense. He now has 10 catches for 125 yards on the season. He is not worth rostering in fantasy leagues moving forward. Seattle hosts the Rams in Week 5.
report: Brandon Marshall caught 1-of-3 targets for 5 yards in Sunday's Week 4 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Marshall's lone target came on a deep shot down the sideline in the second quarter. Quickly falling behind David Moore on the depth chart, Marshall can be dropped.
report: Brandon Marshall failed to catch his only target in the Seahawks' Week 5 loss to the Rams.

impact: Marshall's lone target came on a deep shot down the sideline in the second quarter. Quickly falling behind David Moore on the depth chart, Marshall can be dropped.
report: Brandon Marshall failed to catch his only target in the Seahawks' Week 5 loss to the Rams.

impact: The stat line is not bad, but Manning sailed a few key throws including missing Odell Beckham on what should have been two touchdowns and too often checked down underneath the coverage. To be fair, the pass rush had something to do with that – Ereck Flowers was basically a turnstile on his interception. He did get things going on a potential game-winning drive in the fourth quarter, but that series ended on fourth down. Even with an easier matchup against the Cowboys next week, Manning will only be an option in two-quarterback formats.
report: Eli Manning completed 22-of-37 passes for 224 yards and an interception in the Giants' Week 1 loss to the Jaguars.

impact: Manning was under countless pressures, getting sacked six times. He was a statue in the pocket, holding on to the ball too long and failing to extend plays. Manning's touchdown came to a wide-open Evan Engram in garbage time. It's another concerning game coming off last week's zero touchdown effort. Manning won't be a streaming option for Week 3's matchup with Houston.
report: Eli Manning completed 33-of-44 passes for 279 yards and a touchdown in the Giants' Week 2 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: It's a needed rebound after a rough two-week stretch for Manning. The Giants' offensive line stepped up with  RT Ereck Flowers benched, allowing Manning to completed 86 percent of his passes. Manning's touchdowns went to Sterling Shepard and Rhett Ellison in the red-zone. It's a small step for Manning, but he remains one of the shakiest quarterbacks in the league. Even with a plus Saints matchup, Manning will be hard to trust as a Week 4 streamer.
report: Eli Manning completed 25-of-29 passes for 297 yards and two touchdowns in the Giants' Week 3 win over the Texans.

impact: Manning played it safe all day, as evidenced by his horrid yards per attempt.  The Saints have been getting torched over the top of their defense all year, but Manning opted not to challenge them deep, instead opting for short, chain-moving passes that never threatened this defense.  His longest pass of the first half went for 11 yards.  Manning is barely even a two-quarterback league fantasy option heading into a road date with the Panthers in Week 5.
report: Eli Manning completed 31-of-41 passes for 255 yards and one touchdown in the Giants' Week 4 loss to the Saints.

impact: Manning lost a yard on his lone sack. Eli got off to a painfully slow start, completing just 12-of-20 passes for 119 scoreless yards in the first half. He didn't fare much better after the break, at least initially. Manning threw a costly interception in the third quarter on a pass intended for Odell Beckham, then committed another pick on his very next pass (Mike Adams got him both times). The 37-year-old rebounded nicely after that, however, leading a pair of late touchdown drives to give the Giants a one-point lead with 1:08 remaining. His best throw of the day came on a 33-yard deep strike to Odell Beckham, which was caught for a touchdown. Despite their efforts, the Giants eventually lost on a 63-yard, walk-off field goal by Graham Gano. New York will look to improve on its 1-4 record Thursday night against the Eagles.
report: Eli Manning completed 22-of-36 passes for 326 yards with two touchdowns and two interceptions while adding one yard on his only carry Sunday in the Giants’ Week 5 loss to Carolina.

impact: Manning stunk the joint up, with the vast majority of his yardage either being tacked on after the catch by Saquon Barkley or coming in garbage time. His pick was an inexcusable force to a blanketed "Scott Simonson." Manning, of course, was under siege behind the Giants' putrid offensive line, though the zero-mobility 37-year-old line probably makes his line look even worse than it actually is. Manning's play has become a dispiriting series of quick outs and check downs. Amazingly/hilariously, coach Pat Shurmur called a screen on what should have been a first half Hail Mary. For all his struggles, Manning will have an attackable Week 7 matchup in the Falcons' hollowed-out defense.
report: Eli Manning completed 24-of-43 passes for 281 yards, zero touchdowns and an interception in the Giants' 31-13, Week 6 loss to the Eagles.

impact: Manning had a huge second half, but the offense really struggled in the red zone.  Manning didn't throw his touchdown until he heaved a prayer for a one-yard score to Odell Beckham with five seconds left on the clock after Manning failed to score on consecutive QB sneaks from the one-yard line.  Earlier in the game, he missed OBJ on an open nine-yard touchdown before the Giants had to settle for a field goal.  Manning's 399 yards mark a season-best, but this offense is still broken.  Manning won't be a recommended play next week against the Redskins.
report: Eli Manning completed 27-of-38 passes for 399 yards and one touchdown in the Giants' Week 7 loss to the Falcons.

impact: He took seven sacks.  Manning is completely devoid of athleticism at this stage of his career, and his slow-twitch pocket movement is a terrible combination with New York's swinging-gate offensive line.  Manning's touchdown was a two-yarder to Evan Engram in what amounted to garbage time of Sunday's 20-13 loss.  The Giants will have to consider turning to rookie Kyle Lauletta during their Week 9 bye.  They began the tank last week by trading two starters.
report: Eli Manning completed 30-of-47 passes for 316 yards, one touchdown, and two interceptions in the Giants' Week 8 loss to Washington.

impact: The yards-per-attempt (6.1) is pretty hideous, but Manning got the job done with a big second half.  He had 63 yards on 15 attempts before the break, but found Odell Beckham and Sterling Shepard for touchdowns in the third and fourth quarters after the Giants fell behind 20-10.  Beckham caught two of Manning's three scores, totaling 4-73-2 on 11 targets.  Shepard's three-yarder came with 53 second left to give the G-Men a 27-23 lead.  The Giants will head back home to face the Bucs in Week 11.  It's a prime matchup for Eli, but he's still nothing more than a mid-range QB2.
report: Eli Manning completed 19-of-31 passes for 188 yards and three touchdowns in the Giants' 27-23, Week 10 win over the 49ers on Monday night.

impact: Eli Manning and the passing game as a whole grabbed some popcorn and watched as Saquon Barkley led the way with season-highs in carries (27), rushing yards (142), and total touchdowns (3). Even so, it was a tremendously efficient performance for Manning, who primarily relied on YAC to build up his total yardage. He'll be asked to do more in what is actually a plus matchup on paper against the Eagles' ailing secondary in Week 12.
report: Eli Manning efficiently completed 17-of-18 passes for 231 yards and two touchdowns in the Giants' Week 11 victory over the Bucs.

impact: Relentlessly hyped all offseason, Mahomes came out and made a statement against the Chargers' Joey Bosa-less defense. His third pass was a 58-yard touchdown strike to Tyreek Hill. Mahomes found Hill a silly seven times for 169 yards and a pair of TDs. Two of Mahomes' four scores were goal line shovel passes. In addition to the passing, Mahomes was used frequently as a runner, both on traditional and read options. Mahomes looked like a born playmaker in just his second NFL start. There are going to be growing pains with any young player, but Mahomes could rapidly become an every-week QB1. He gets the Steelers in Pittsburgh for Week 2.
report: Patrick Mahomes competed 15-of-27 passes for 256 yards and four touchdowns in the Chiefs' 38-28, Week 1 win over the Chargers, adding five rushes for 21 additional yards.

impact: With 10 touchdowns, Mahomes now owns the record for the most scores through the first two weeks of the season. Mahomes was just reaving souls, ripping chunk plays whenever and wherever he wanted. Unlike last week's Tyreek Hill-dominated affair, Mahomes got everyone involved, finding each of Hill, Travis Kelce and Sammy Watkins for at least 90 yards. Mahomes was throwing lasers into tight coverage in the red zone, finding Kelce and Chris Conley for impressive scores. Mahomes is the real deal and could not have a better setup on a videogame. He will look to stay scorching as an elite QB1 in Week 3 against the 49ers.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 23-of-28 passes for 326 yards and six touchdowns in the Chiefs' 42-37, Week 2 win over the Steelers.

impact: The three scores give Mahomes the record for most touchdown passes (13) in the first three games of a season, and he could have had more. He missed a couple throws in the first half including what should have been a touchdown to Tyreek Hill, and the Chiefs attempted just 13 passes in the second half of the easy win. Leading what looks like an unstoppable offense, blowouts might be the only thing which can stop Mahomes from putting up massive fantasy days. A trip to Denver next Monday night might look daunting, but the Broncos' defense has struggled a bit early in the season. Mahomes will be the top overall quarterback next week.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 24-of-38 passes for 314 yards and three touchdowns in the Chiefs' Week 3 win over the 49ers.

impact: He also rushed for an eight-yard touchdown, his first score on the ground this season.  Mahomes got off to a real rough start, heading into halftime with just 65 yards passing.  The Broncos were coming at him from all angles, and Mahomes was running for his life most of the night.  His 192 yards passing outside the pocket, according to ESPN, are the most in the last decade.  The Chiefs were down by 10 with just over 12 minutes left, and Mahomes ended up engineering an incredible comeback, creating plays with his legs, throwing darts on the run, and even completing a pass left-handed to Tyreek Hill while running for his life on third down.  He also overcame a 2nd-and-30 situation in the fourth quarter with pass plays of 23 and 35 yards.  The box-score numbers don't tell the whole story.  Mahomes is a star and gets a tough Jaguars defense in K.C. for Week 5.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 28-of-45 passes for 304 yards and one touchdown in the Chiefs' 27-23, Week 4 win over the Broncos on Monday night.

impact: This was the toughest test of Mahomes' young career, and he passed with flying colors. He was extremely sharp early, spreading the ball around in his trademark fashion, and capped the opening drive with a four-yard rushing score off a bootleg. He did throw his first interception on the season in the second quarter on a high pass across the middle, but that was the only time Kansas City's offense was stopped in the first half. He did not have much to do in the second half, but Mahomes answered a Jacksonville touchdown drive with one of his own in which he hit Tyreek Hill with a great pass for 36 yards up the sideline. He threw another careless interception in the fourth, but it did not ultimately matter. The fantasy stats were not spectacular, but Mahomes has proven he is matchup-proof. He will be a high-end play next week in New England.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 22-of-38 passes for 313 yards and two interceptions and rushed four times for 13 yards and a touchdown in the Chiefs' Week 5 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Mahomes struggled in the first half before exploding over the final two quarters.  He hit Kareem Hunt for a 67-yard touchdown on the opening drive of second half, with all three of his other TDs going to Tyreek Hill. Mahomes got some help from a Patriots secondary that let Hill get past them for huge gains with broken coverages. The Chiefs lost on a last second field goal, but this was another strong showing from Mahomes after leading the Chiefs to a win over Jacksonville last week. Mahomes will be a top-three quarterback play against the Bengals in Week 7.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 23-of-36 passes for 352 yards with four touchdowns and two interceptions in Kansas City's Week 6 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Mahomes’ first two touchdowns were dumpoffs to Kareem Hunt. He hit a wide open Demetrius Harris and Tyreek Hill in the red-zone for his other scores. Mahomes underthrew Hill on a deep shot for his interception but was otherwise flawless in the blowout win. Mahomes is playing at an MVP level with a 22:5 TD/INT ratio through seven games. Even in a tough matchup with Denver, he's a top-five quarterback play for Week 8.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 28-of-39 passes for 358 yards with four touchdowns and an interception in the Chiefs' Week 7 win over the Bengals, adding four rushes for 45 yards.

impact: Mahomes’ first two touchdowns were dumpoffs to Kareem Hunt. He hit a wide open Demetrius Harris and Tyreek Hill in the red-zone for his other scores. Mahomes underthrew Hill on a deep shot for his interception but was otherwise flawless in the blowout win. Mahomes is playing at an MVP level with a 22:5 TD/INT ratio through seven games. Even in a tough matchup with Denver, he's a top-five quarterback play for Week 8.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 28-of-39 passes for 358 yards with four touchdowns and an interception in the Chiefs' Week 7 win over the Bengals, adding four rushes for 45 yards.

impact: He was sacked twice for a loss of 12 yards. After Sunday's win, Mahomes is now 3-0 in his career against Denver. Sunday also extended the 23-year-old's streak of 300-yard games to seven. Mahomes had his most success throwing to Sammy Watkins, who exploded for 107 yards and two touchdowns on a season-high eight catches. The second-year stud threw an ugly interception in the second half on a pass he forced to Travis Kelce, but that was his lone blemish in an otherwise stellar outing. The current MVP front-runner will look to stay hot next week when the 7-1 Chiefs travel to Cleveland.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 24-of-34 passes for 303 yards with four touchdowns and one interception while losing one yard on two carries Sunday in the Chiefs’ Week 8 win over the Broncos.

impact: Mahomes also added 18 yards rushing on two carries. The 375 passing yards were a new career-high and were the eighth straight game in which Mahomes surpassed 300-yards passing, just the fourth player to have such a streak in NFL history. He'll gun to tie the all-time record of nine straight games done by Drew Brees twice. Mahomes threw a 50-yard touchdown on a screen pass to Kareem Hunt on the opening drive and then 11 and 13-yard strikes to Travis Kelce for scores. The Chiefs host the Cardinals in Week 10.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 23-of-32 passes for 375 yards with three touchdowns and one interception in Sunday's Week 9 win over the Browns.

impact: It's the first time in the last four weeks Mahomes has been held under 300-plus yards and three touchdowns. Mahomes threw both of his TDs to Tyreek Hill, who accounted for half of his yards. He faced a stronger than expected Cardinals pass rush, taking five sacks. Mahomes made some plays outside of the pocket with 21 yards on four carries. Mahomes is now up to a league best 31 touchdowns through 10 games. The Chiefs get the Rams for a likely Monday night shootout in Week 11.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 21-of-28 passes for 249 yards and two touchdowns in Week 10 against the Cardinals.

impact: He now has 11 and 13 touches through two 2018 appearances.  Mack shook off a first-drive dropped pass that was pick-sixed by Mo Claiborne to give the Colts' running game a jolt after it struggled mightily in the first five weeks.  The backfield remains a timeshare situation, however, and Mack has passing-game limitations.  He will be a boom-bust flex option in Week 7 versus Buffalo.
report: Marlon Mack rushed 12 times for 89 yards and caught 1-of-2 targets for four yards in the Colts' Week 6 loss to the Jets.

impact: Mack supplied his first touchdowns since Week 17 of last season while setting career-highs in rushing yards, yards from scrimmage and touches. The second-year USF alum burned the Bills for a number of big plays including a 29-yard touchdown off a screen pass from Andrew Luck during the second quarter. He added another score in the fourth, breaking loose for a 20-yard rushing touchdown. Mack was slowed by a hamstring injury early in the year but he hasn't shown any ill effects the last two weeks, exploding for 252 yards (215 rushing, 37 receiving) on 34 touches during that span. Now firmly entrenched as Indy's lead back, Mack will be in the RB2 discussion when the Colts travel to Oakland for Week 8.
report: Marlon Mack broke out for 126 yards and a touchdown on 19 carries while also chipping in with two catches for 33 yards and another touchdown on three targets Sunday in the Colts’ Week 7 win over the Bills.

impact: Mack missed two practices with an ankle injury this week but he didn't look hurt Sunday as the Colts rolled to their second straight win. He ripped the Raiders for 132 rushing yards, bettering the career mark he set against Buffalo in Week 7. In doing so, he became the first Colt to rush for 100 yards in back-to-back weeks since Joseph Addai in 2007. Both of Mack's touchdowns came in the fourth quarter as Indy out-scored Oakland 21-0 in the final frame. He's been an absolute boss, contributing 401 yards from scrimmage with four touchdowns in three games since coming back from a hamstring injury. Mack has benefited from workhorse usage, averaging 20.3 touches during that span. At worst, the second-year USF alum will be a high-end RB2 when the Colts return from their upcoming bye week.
report: Marlon Mack blew up for 132 yards and two touchdowns on 25 carries while also grabbing two catches for 17 yards on four targets Sunday in the Colts’ Week 8 win over Oakland.

impact: The Colts' passing game shredded the Jaguars early in this contest, but the rushing attack struggled to get anything going. That was especially true in the second half, where Mack went for just two yards on three carries. This was easily Mack's worst game since returning from injury. He will look to get back on the right track next week against the Titans.
report: Marlon Mack rushed 12 times for 29 yards and caught both of his targets for nine yards in the Colts' Week 10 win over the Jaguars.

impact: With the game a laugher from the early going, Mack ceded 10 touches to Nyheim Hines and Jordan Wilkins. Mack has now turned in back-to-back pedestrian performances after the schedule tightened up with the Jaguars and Titans, but the Dolphins will provide a Week 12 breather. Matt Burke's defense has been straight up dismantled by the run of late. Mack will be a high-end RB2.
report: Marlon Mack rushed 16 times for 61 yards and a touchdown in the Colts' Week 11 win over the Titans, adding an eight-yard reception.

impact: It looked like Kupp's season might be over in the first half after he was carted to the locker room following a horse-collar tackle. He was reportedly extremely stiff upon arriving to the locker room. Evidently it was all downhill from there. Perhaps Kupp will mostly be a second half decoy, but his return is the best possible news for the Rams.
report: Cooper Kupp (knee) returned for the second half of Sunday's game against the Broncos.

impact: Kupp appeared to wreck his knee in the first half before stunningly returning after the break. It ended up a technicality, however, as Kupp was barely out there as the Rams gutted out an ugly road victory. Kupp's initial tests brought back good news, but we would not take his Week 7 status for granted. Further testing might be required on Monday, while the Rams could take a conservative approach with the 49ers on deck for Week 7.
report: Cooper Kupp was held without a catch on one target in the Rams' Week 6 win over the Broncos.

impact: Kupp was quiet early in his first game back, but he got on the board with a 26-yard catch on a great throw from Jared Goff in the second quarter. That was his only action of the first half. He had a mostly quiet start to the second half, as well, but he caught fire in the fourth quarter, catching three passes including a 41-yard touchdown on a game-tying touchdown drive. The Rams ended up losing, but this was a solid first game back from Kupp. He will be a great option next week against the Seahawks.
report: Cooper Kupp hauled in 5-of-6 targets for 89 yards and a touchdown in the Rams' Week 9 loss to the Saints.

impact: He added a two-point conversion, but it was another disappointing fantasy day for Kittle. He made a couple big plays including one in which he ran over a defensive back in the third quarter, but he dropped what would have been a big gain in the first quarter and had a touchdown called back on a questionable offensive pass interference call. Even worse, it looks like Jimmy Garoppolo is dealing with a season-ending knee injury. If that turns out to be the case, Kittle will be downgraded to a low-end TE1 option moving forward.
report: George Kittle hauled in 5-of-7 targets for 79 yards in the 49ers' Week 3 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: C.J. Beathard showered Kittle with a team-high eight targets in the first 49ers game post-Garoppolo. Kittle was being held in check until he escaped over the middle for an 82-yard touchdown late in the third quarter. The 49ers were without receivers Marquise Goodwin and Dante Pettis for much of the game after they suffered leg injuries, and Kittle would get a bump if they miss next week's game against the Cardinals. Kittle is still in the TE1 mix even with Garoppolo out for the season.
report: George Kittle caught six passes for 125 yards and one touchdown in the 49ers' Week 4 loss to the Chargers.

impact: Kittle was responsible for San Francisco's longest play of the afternoon, breaking off a 45-yard catch-and-run down the right sideline with a little under 10 minutes to go in the fourth quarter. Garbage time was Kittle's ally on Sunday as the tight end went for 62 yards on three catches with the Niners playing from behind in the second half. Kittle has shown a strong rapport with quarterback C.J. Beathard, which is nothing new since the two were college teammates together at Iowa. The 24-year-old has given fantasy owners a surprisingly consistent floor this year, eclipsing 75 yards in four of five games. He'll look to make it five out of six next week at Green Bay.
report: George Kittle earned five catches for 83 yards on seven targets Sunday in the 49ers’ Week 5 loss to Arizona.

impact: Kittle was the offense for most of this game. He sparked the only scoring drive of the first half with a 23-yard gain in the second quarter and finished the drive with a 10-yard touchdown catch. He had 77 of C.J. Beathard’s 106 yards at the break. The offense's futility limited him in the second half, but he still got loose for a 21-yard gain in the third quarter. Kittle has now topped 75 yards in five of seven games and has two touchdowns in his last four. He will be a high-end TE1 next week in Arizona.
report: George Kittle hauled in 5-of-8 targets for 98 yards and a touchdown in the 49ers' Week 7 loss to the Rams.

impact: Kittle was the offense for most of this game. He sparked the only scoring drive of the first half with a 23-yard gain in the second quarter and finished the drive with a 10-yard touchdown catch. He had 77 of C.J. Beathard’s 106 yards at the break. The offense's futility limited him in the second half, but he still got loose for a 21-yard gain in the third quarter. Kittle has now topped 75 yards in five of seven games and has two touchdowns in his last four. He will be a high-end TE1 next week in Arizona.
report: George Kittle hauled in 5-of-8 targets for 98 yards and a touchdown in the 49ers' Week 7 loss to the Rams.

impact: Kittle's targets, catches, and yards all played second-fiddle to Kendrick Bourne's surprising 7/71 performance. Kittle's day may have been even better had he not been forced to exit early to check for a potential concussion. Kittle's now seen at least seven targets in five of his last six games and at least six targets in every outing since Week 3. He remains an every-week TE1, and top-four option at his position for the rest of the season.
report: George Kittle secured 5-of-8 targets for 57 yards in the Niners' Week 8 loss to the Cardinals.

impact: There were questions surrounding the 49ers offense with undrafted QB Nick Mullens starting in his first NFL game, but Mullens played like a polished vet. After an injury scare that momentarily sent him to the locker room, Kittle made a sick one-handed catch over the middle that he ended up taking for 71 yards before he finished the drive with a five-yard touchdown. Kittle now has a seven straight games with at least four receptions, and he's always a threat for a long catch-and-run, which makes him a top-five fantasy TE from here on out.
report: George Kittle caught all four of his targets for 108 yards with one touchdown in the 49ers Week 9 win over the Raiders.

impact: Kittle has emerged as a top 3-4 tight end in the league as a sophomore and has really steadied himself as a weekly difference maker.  He's the main vein of the passing offense, and the nine grabs and 10 targets set new season bests.  Kittle was cooking in the first half with 5-66 on five targets.  He later had a catch called back on a penalty.  Kittle will get the Bucs in Week 12 after the bye.
report: George Kittle caught 9-of-10 targets for 83 yards in the 49ers' Week 10 loss to the Giants.

impact: As promised, Kirk was more involved this week, but it did not matter much in a game Sam Bradford failed to top 100 yards. Kirk did have some good plays including a run after catch which almost netted him a first down on third-and-long, but he will not be a fantasy factor as long as Bradford is under center.
report: Christian Kirk hauled in 4-of-5 targets for 27 yards in the Cardinals' Week 2 loss to the Rams.

impact: After catching 5-of-7 targets for 31 yards over the first two games of the season, Kirk lead the Cardinals across the board in targets, catches and yards on Sunday. His highlight on the day was a 32-yard catch in the 4th quarter from Sam Bradford. Kirk was then Josh Rosen's favorite target, seeing three targets on the two possessions that Rosen helmed. For now, Kirk is still only a speculation add at best as the Arizona offense is not one to expect a lot of consistent production from for their best players, let alone an ancillary option.
report: Christian Kirk caught 7-of-8 targets for 90 yards in Sunday's Week 3 loss to the Bears.

impact: Kirk trailed on Larry Fitzgerald in targets, but failed to produce much in Josh Rosen's first career start. Kirk was wide open for a potential touchdown in the 1st quarter, but Rosen went elsewhere with the football. Kirk is only worth a stash in deep leagues with Arizona's offense struggling to prop up any fantasy options at all at the moment.
report: Christian Kirk caught 4-of-5 passes for 28 yards in Sunday's Week 4 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: Kirk broke loose for a 75-yard touchdown on the Cardinals' first play from scrimmage. That was Arizona's longest play from scrimmage this year. It also marked his first career touchdown. The rookie's involvement dwindled after that as the Cardinals got ahead and rode David Johnson to the finish line. The 21-year-old has easily been the Cardinals' most productive receiver this year, leading the team in yards two of the past three weeks. He's not a must-own by any means but Kirk has certainly showed promise in the early going. We'll see if he can keep it up next week when the Cardinals head to Minnesota.
report: Christian Kirk corralled three-of-four targets for 85 yards and a touchdown Sunday in the Cardinals’ Week 5 win over the Niners.

impact: It's the second straight week Kirk's led the Cardinals in receiving. Kirk has been Josh Rosen's go-to target, with his seven targets finishing behind only Larry Fitzgerald (8). Kirk had 44 yards on the first two series before the Cardinals offense stalled out. His ROS outlook is on the rise with Rosen. Kirk is a WR3/FLEX for Week 7 against the Broncos.
report: Christian Kirk caught 6-of-7 passes for 77 yards in Week 6 against the Vikings.

impact: It was the third consecutive game the rookie's seen at least seven targets, scoring in two of said three performances. Kirk took a backseat to Fitzgerald (for at least one game) in OC Byron Leftwich's play-calling debut, watching the old timer erupt for 8/102/1. It was still a massively successful outing for Kirk, whose touchdown turned out to be the game-winner with just 0:34 left to play. With no realistic options to take serious in the team's passing game outside of Fitzgerald and, to a lesser extent, David Johnson, Kirk is locked-in as Arizona's No. 2 wideout (and an ensuing FLEX option) when the Cards return and play the Chiefs post-bye.
report: Christian Kirk caught 3-of-7 targets for 42 yards and one touchdown in the Cardinals' Week 8 victory over the Niners.

impact: It's a quiet game for Kirk coming off his Week 8 heroics. Kirk's longest catch was called back on a holding penalty. His snaps were up with Chad Williams out, but the Cardinals went run heavy in a game they kept closer than expected. Kirk has rebound matchup against Oakland in Week 11.
report: Christian Kirk caught 2-of-6 targets for eight yards in Week 10 against Kansas City.

impact: Kirk made the play of the day for the Cardinals in the first quarter, catching a screen in heavy traffic before shaking the entire defense to house a 59-yard score. He later made a critical red zone grab on a Josh Rosen pass that was delivered late. Kirk has routinely looked explosive but is having trouble in the box score department because of Rosen's shaky play. He will be an upside WR4 for Week 12 against the Chargers.
report: Christian Kirk caught 3-of-4 targets for 77 yards and a touchdown in the Cardinals' Week 11 loss to the Raiders.

impact: Kessler replaced Blake Bortles a little after halftime following Bortles’ second lost fumble. A weak-armed game manager, Kessler engineered just one touchdown drive. Kessler’s pick came on a dropped pass, which deflected to Texans S Tyrann Mathieu. Kessler will presumably get the Week 8 start against Philadelphia in London, although he won’t be more than a low-end two-quarterback-league play.
report: Cody Kessler completed 21-of-30 passes for 156 yards, one touchdown, and one interception in the Jaguars' Week 7 loss to the Texans.

impact: After throwing just seven interceptions last season, Keenum did not start off on the right foot with his new team. He made up for it with a 75-yard drive he capped with a four-yard touchdown, his third of the game, to Demaryius Thomas to put Denver ahead for good. With Thomas and Emmanuel Sanders, who had a 10/135/1 line on Sunday, to target, Keenum will be worth streaming consideration in good matchups all season. He gets one of those next week against the Raiders.
report: Case Keenum completed 25-of-39 passes for 329 yards, three touchdowns, and three interceptions in the Broncos' Week 1 win over the Seahawks.

impact: Keenum added 16 yards rushing and a touchdown on the ground. After a quiet first half in which he completed just 5-of-11 passes for 38 yards, Keenum bounced back in the second half to complete 14-of-24 passes for 184 yards and lead the Broncos on four scoring drives. Keenum will be a lower-end QB2 for fantasy in Week 3 on the road versus the Ravens.
report: Case Keenum completed 19-of-35 passes for 222 yards with an interception in Sunday's Week 2 win over the Raiders.

impact: Keenum was not good in this one. Consistently settling for the short pass amid pressure, Keenum had just 104 yards heading into the fourth quarter. After two touchdowns to open the game -- one set up by a blocked punt -- the Broncos punted seven straight times. The next play ended when Keenum was picked off on second-and-goal from the 15, and the final drive ended on fourth down deep in Baltimore territory. The good news is Keenum will get to face the Chiefs' defense at home next Monday night.
report: Case Keenum completed 22-of-34 passes for 192 yards, zero touchdowns, and an interception in the Broncos' Week 3 loss to the Ravens.

impact: The Broncos held what looked like a pretty commanding 23-13 lead with just over 12 minutes left, but then Patrick Mahomes happened and led an incredible comeback as Keenum simultaneously collapsed.  This was as good of an on-paper matchup as Keenum is going to see this season.  The Chiefs were playing the worst pass defense in the league entering Week 4, and Keenum was unable to attack it.  He had one big shot to Courtland Sutton early for 42 yards, but that was about it.  Keenum then missed a wide-open Demaryius Thomas with less than a minute to play on what should have been a walk-in 28-yard touchdown.  Keenum has been dreadful four weeks into his Broncos career, tossing six picks to three touchdowns.  He hasn't thrown for a score since Week 1 and won't be a fantasy option next week at the Jets.
report: Case Keenum completed 21-of-33 passes for 245 yards, no touchdowns, and one interception in the Broncos' 27-23, Week 4 loss to the Chiefs on Monday night.

impact: There is a major gap between reality and Keenum's stat line; he was dreadfully inaccurate when this game was in doubt, took four sacks, fumbled twice, and was a major part of the problem in the Broncos' 34-16 loss.  Keenum padded his stats with a garbage-time 42-yard touchdown to Demaryius Thomas.  Still not yet the subject of benching rumors, Keenum will be a two-quarterback-league play in next week's potential shootout against the Rams.
report: Case Keenum completed 35-of-51 passes for 377 yards, two touchdowns, and an interception in the Broncos' Week 5 loss to the Jets.

impact: It was Keenum's second-straight 300-yard game, though he hardly looked good doing it. A huge chunk of Keenum's yards came on a pair of underthrown deep balls to Demaryius Thomas and Courtland Sutton. Keenum's arm appeared limited all afternoon. Keenum briefly checked out at the end of the first half as he was evaluated for a concussion, but he thankfully cleared. With just eight total touchdowns through six games, Keenum is barely staying on the QB2 radar. He gets the Cardinals on Thursday Night Football for Week 7.
report: Case Keenum completed 25-of-41 passes for 322 yards, two touchdowns and an interception in the Broncos' 23-20, Week 6 loss to the Rams.

impact: "Case is our quarterback," Joseph said after yet another Broncos loss on Sunday.  Keenum was checked for a concussion at the end of the first half, and sophomore Chad Kelly came into a standing ovation from Broncos fans to kneel it out on the final play of the second quarter.  Kelly was also tremendous in the preseason.  Keenum hasn't been the worst of the Broncos' problems, but his play also leaves the rest of the team zero margin for error since he's simply unable to deliver anything more than mediocre quarterbacking.  There haven't been more than a couple worse starting quarterbacks in the league through six weeks.  Keenum is tied for the league lead with eight interceptions, and only Josh Allen and Marcus Mariota have worse passer ratings.  Joseph and Keenum will go down with arms linked.
report: Coach Vance Joseph remains committed to Case Keenum as the Broncos' starting quarterback.

impact: Keenum added four carries for four yards. They're disappointing numbers considering the lopsided nature of the score, though five Cardinals turnovers kept setting the Broncos up with gorgeous field position, limiting Keenum's yardage opportunities. The Broncos' defense also housed a pair of pick sixes. Lastly, Emmanuel Sanders threw a 28-yard touchdown on a trick play. Keenum has been barely playable in two-quarterback leagues this season, but he will be a top-18 option against the Chiefs' barely-there defense in Week 8.
report: Case Keenum completed 14-of-21 passes for 161 yards, one touchdown and an interception in the Broncos' 45-10, Week 7 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Keenum added four carries for four yards. They're disappointing numbers considering the lopsided nature of the score, though five Cardinals turnovers kept setting the Broncos up with gorgeous field position, limiting Keenum's yardage opportunities. The Broncos' defense also housed a pair of pick sixes. Lastly, Emmanuel Sanders threw a 28-yard touchdown on a trick play. Keenum has been barely playable in two-quarterback leagues this season, but he will be a top-18 option against the Chiefs' barely-there defense in Week 8.
report: Case Keenum completed 14-of-21 passes for 161 yards, one touchdown and an interception in the Broncos' 45-10, Week 7 win over the Cardinals.

impact: He lost 40 yards on five sacks. Keenum had his deep ball working, especially when he uncorked a 49-yard bomb to Emmanuel Sanders on the opening drive. He also connected on a 42-yard heave to Courtland Sutton later in the afternoon. The 30-year-old slung a couple of touchdowns as well—one to Jeff Heuerman and another to undrafted receiver Tim Patrick—but fantasy owners likely could have done without his two turnovers. Both miscues—a fumble on a Dee Ford strip-sack and an interception off a flea-flicker to Demaryius Thomas—came with Denver trailing in the fourth quarter. Keenum has now thrown 10 touchdowns against 11 picks this season. The 3-5 Broncos will look to bounce back when they return home to face Houston in Week 9.
report: Case Keenum completed 22-of-32 passes for 262 yards with two touchdowns and one interception while adding a nine-yard carry Sunday in the Broncos’ Week 8 loss to Kansas City.

impact: It was a shrug-inducing day for Keenum, who at least notched the one score to make his outing semi-respectable. He ultimately missed a few downfield throws (as he's one to do) and wasn't helped any on a deep touchdown-drop by rookie Courtland Sutton. Demaryius Thomas' absence didn't seem to faze him any, though, as he instead locked in on TE Jeff Heuerman (10/83/1) for a team-high 11 targets. Keenum's now thrown an even number of touchdowns and picks (11) this season. He'll again be a viable streamer when the Broncos return from their bye and face the Chargers in Week 11.
report: Case Keenum completed 26-of-42 passes for 290 yards and one touchdown in the Broncos' Week 9 loss to the Texans.

impact: Keenum faced pressure from Joey Bosa all day, but was never sacked. The 30-year-old got off to a sluggish start, completing just nine of 17 throws for 56 scoreless yards in the first half. Keenum found a little more daylight after halftime, however, reviving Emmanuel Sanders after he was invisible for much of the first three quarters. The first-year Bronco was money on the final drive, converting five of six passes (the lone incompletion came when he spiked it to stop the clock with three seconds remaining) for 86 yards as the Broncos walked it off on a game-winning field goal by Brandon McManus. Keenum and the 4-6 Broncos host Pittsburgh in Week 12.
report: Case Keenum completed 19-of-32 passes for 205 yards Sunday in the Broncos’ Week 11 victory over the Chargers.

impact: He also converted a pair of two-point conversions. Kamara erupted in the first half, dominating the Bucs for 114 yards (29 rushing, 85 receiving) on 10 touches. The highlights included a mesmerizing 35-yard catch off a screen pass and a five-yard touchdown scamper to cap the Saints’ opening drive. Kamara was mostly stymied in the second half—he managed just 27 yards on seven touches—though he did vulture a pair of touchdowns including a seven-yard receiving score that closed the gap to eight with 3:31 remaining in the fourth quarter. The reigning Rookie of the Year received workhorse usage, out-touching backup Mike Gillislee 17-3 while outgaining him by over 100 yards. Kamara remains one of the most unique weapons in football and should be in for another obscene stat line next time out against Cleveland.
report: Alvin Kamara rushed eight times for 29 yards and two touchdowns while also nabbing nine catches for 112 yards and another touchdown on 12 targets Sunday in the Saints’ Week 1 loss to the Buccaneers.

impact: Kamara also added a 2-point conversion in the 4th quarter. Out of the gates, Kamara has struggled to gain yardage on the ground, rushing 21 times for just 75 yards (3.6 YPC) but has been electric in the receiving game, catching 15-of-18 targets for 165 yards.
