impact: Battling quad and hamstring issues much of the first five weeks, Goodwin entered Monday with a combined five catches for 54 yards and one score in three games played.  This game came out of nowhere, but Goodwin can do this anytime he steps on the field when healthy.  He ran right by CB Kentrell Brice for a 67-yard touchdown in the first quarter before then beating veteran Tramon Williams for a 30-yard score nine minutes later.  Where Goodwin was dropped in fantasy, he needs to be picked up immediately.  He'll be a WR3/4 next week against the Rams.
report: Marquise Goodwin caught 4-of-5 targets for 126 yards and two touchdowns in the 49ers' 33-30, Week 6 loss to the Packers on Monday night.

impact: Goodwin left the game briefly with a lower-leg injury, but he was able to return and catch two passes deep into garbage time. It was a disappointing follow up to his 126-yard, two-touchdown explosion on Monday night, but it is promising he easily led the receivers with five targets. The matchup next week in Arizona is not great, but Goodwin will be worth a look as a WR3.
report: Marquise Goodwin hauled in 2-of-5 targets for 24 yards in the 49ers' Week 7 loss to the Rams.

impact: Goodwin left the game briefly with a lower-leg injury, but he was able to return and catch two passes deep into garbage time. It was a disappointing follow up to his 126-yard, two-touchdown explosion on Monday night, but it is promising he easily led the receivers with five targets. The matchup next week in Arizona is not great, but Goodwin will be worth a look as a WR3.
report: Marquise Goodwin hauled in 2-of-5 targets for 24 yards in the 49ers' Week 7 loss to the Rams.

impact: Goodwin salvaged his one-catch day by showing off his olympic speed and taking his only reception to the house on a 55-yard touchdown sprint through the middle of Arizona's secondary. The results have been boom-bust, but Goodwin's at least showed consistency in seeing four targets in every outing since Week 3. He has a chance to boom against the Raiders' shaky secondary in San Francisco's quick turnaround on Thursday.
report: Marquise Goodwin hauled in just 1-of-4 targets for a 55-yard touchdown scamper in the Niners' Week 8 loss to the Cardinals.

impact: Goodwin's longest catch went for 26 yards on a deep crosser on the third-to-last play of the game with the 49ers down 27-23.  The Niners clocked the ball with one second left at the 21-yard line before then having an incomplete pass in the end zone.  Goodwin's bigger concern was a pair of helmet shots in the third quarter that had him off the field in the medical tent.  He has a lengthy concussion history.  The Niners are now on bye before Week 12 against the Bucs.
report: Marquise Goodwin caught 4-of-5 targets for 69 yards in the 49ers' Week 10 loss to the Giants.

impact: Golladay did most of his work well before this one got out of hand in the third quarter.  At one point, he was leading the Lions with eight targets before Golden Tate ended the night with 15 and a touchdown.  Golladay also made one of the best plays of the night for the Lions, decking CB Trumaine Johnson after an interception, forcing a fumble and recovering it on his own in Jets territory.  Unfortunately, the Lions did nothing with it.  Golladay played a career-high 65 snaps (hat tip to PFF's Nathan Jahnke) and needs to be added where he's available.  Golladay will head into Week 2 at San Francisco as a big-play threat WR3/4.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 7-of-12 targets for 114 yards in the Lions' 48-17, Week 1 loss to the Jets on Monday night.

impact: He caught Ahkello Witherspoon napping on his 30-yard touchdown in the first quarter, which accounted for the Lions’ first points of the afternoon. Golladay didn’t score again but he was a consistent presence in the Lions’ passing game, just as he was a week ago when he registered a career-high 114 yards in a loss to the Jets. The 24-year-old showed flashes as a rookie but struggled to stay healthy. Now he’s in the midst of a sophomore breakout and has risen to must-start status in all formats. Look for Golladay to keep the train rolling next week against New England.
report: Kenny Golladay finished with six catches for 89 yards and a touchdown on nine targets Sunday in the Lions’ Week 2 loss to San Francisco.

impact: Golladay continued to start over Golden Tate in two-wide sets. He scored the Lions' first touchdown of the game, extending the ball across the goal-line on a play where he was tackled at the one-yard line. Golladay has at least 100 yards or a touchdown in every game this season. He's a WR2 for Week 4's matchup with the Cowboys.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 6-of-7 passes for 53 yards and a touchdown in the Lions' Week 3 win over the Patriots.

impact: Even with Golladay seeing his lowest target total of the season, the second-year wideout was still reasonably productive in the loss to Dallas. While Golladay’s shrinking volume is somewhat concerning, the 24-year-old has established a nice floor for himself, topping 50 yards in all four games this year after reaching that mark just five times all of last season. He’ll be safe to employ as a WR3/flex against the Packers in Week 5.
report: Kenny Golladay came down with four catches for 74 yards on four targets Sunday in Detroit’s Week 4 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: Golladay caught a 47-yard touchdown in the first quarter, but it was called back on an illegal hands to the face penalty.  He then went 60 yards down the sideline on his first official catch, stiff-arming a defender to the ground before being tackled inside the 10-yard line only to see LeGarrette Blount score a couple plays later.  Golladay eventually found the end zone from five yards away in the second half, and his nine targets led the team on a day Matthew Stafford attempted just 26 passes with the Lions holding a commanding lead much of the afternoon.  Golladay has seen at least nine targets in 3-of-5 games and is a locked-in WR2 heading into the bye.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 4-of-9 targets for 98 yards and one touchdown in the Lions' 31-23, Week 5 win over the Packers.

impact: Golladay also drew a 15-yard DPI. Golladay drew zero first half targets in what ended up a nightmare fantasy day. Golladay nearly saved it with a 13-yard score in the second half, but it was called back by a Lions penalty. The Dolphins' secondary did an excellent job on each of the Lions' "big three." Golladay now has just 10 catches over his past three games. He will look to heat back up in Week 8 against the Seahawks.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 2-of-2 targets for 37 yards in the Lions' Week 7 win over the Dolphins.

impact: Golladay also drew a 15-yard DPI. Golladay drew zero first half targets in what ended up a nightmare fantasy day. Golladay nearly saved it with a 13-yard score in the second half, but it was called back by a Lions penalty. The Dolphins' secondary did an excellent job on each of the Lions' "big three." Golladay now has just 10 catches over his past three games. He will look to heat back up in Week 8 against the Seahawks.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 2-of-2 targets for 37 yards in the Lions' Week 7 win over the Dolphins.

impact: Golladay now has just three catches for 49 yards over his past two games. Lack of volume was to blame in Week 7, but Matthew Stafford uncorked 40 throws against the Seahawks this afternoon. 10 of them were directed Marvin Jones' way. With only 11 catches in the past month, Golladay is trending toward WR3 territory. His upside makes him difficult to bench, however. A Minnesota road trip is in the offing for Week 9.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 1-of-1 targets for 12 yards in the Lions' Week 8 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: Golladay was stuck on one catch for 15 yards on two targets before picking up a couple grabs on the final meaningless offensive possession.  It was a really discouraging day in the first game without Golden Tate following the trade.  Matthew Stafford was sacked 10 times, and the offense was terrible much of the afternoon.  Golladay's four targets were tied with Michael Roberts for fourth on the team behind Marvin Jones and Theo Riddick, who each had eight, and Kerryon Johnson with five.  The Lions go to Chicago in Week 10.  Golladay will be a WR3.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 3-of-4 targets for 46 yards in the Lions' Week 9 loss to the Vikings.

impact: Golladay came alive late, drawing 10 second-half targets from Matthew Stafford. He benefited from game-script—most of his receiving output came with Detroit in catch-up mode—as well as an injury to lead receiver Marvin Jones (knee), who bowed out late in the third quarter. Golladay dusted Kyle Fuller for his lone touchdown, scoring from five yards out with 8:30 to go in the fourth quarter. He was targeted on a two-point conversion attempt later in the quarter but was ruled down just shy of the goal line. The 13 targets were a career-high for the 25-year-old. With Jones hurt, Golladay could be in for another huge workload next week when the Lions host Carolina in the Motor City.
report: Kenny Golladay corralled six catches for 78 yards and a touchdown on 13 targets Sunday in the Lions’ Week 10 loss to the Bears.

impact: Golladay was expected to be a target hog with Marvin Jones out, and that is exactly what happened. He recorded two catches on the opening drive including one which he took out of the hands of Panthers CB James Bradberry. He finished the second quarter with a slightly disappointing 34 yards on four catches, but he was targeted seven times before halftime. He did more with the work in the second half. He made a nice play to break a tackle and get a first down in the third quarter, and then he converted a third-and-long with a 36-yard catch in the fourth. He topped himself a couple plays later, laying out for a 19-yard touchdown which amounted to the game-winning score. Golladay now has 27 targets in the last two games. He will be a high-end WR2 even in a tough matchup against the Bears on Thanksgiving if Jones is forced to sit again.
report: Kenny Golladay hauled in 8-of-14 targets for 113 yards and a touchdown in the Lions' Week 11 win over the Panthers.

impact: The only thing not to like about Goff’s performance was he only threw one touchdown. He probably should have had two more, but he underthrew Brandin Cooks, who had to come back to the ball and the defender, and missed a wide-open Robert Woods in the end zone. Neither play ultimately mattered in a game the Rams won going away. Goff might need to be sharper next week against the Chargers, though.
report: Jared Goff completed 24-of-32 passes for 354 yards, a touchdown, and an interception in the Rams' Week 2 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Goff has back-to-back games with 354 passing yards, but his three touchdowns are the most since Week 15 of 2017. Robert Woods was Goff's primary target today as the two connected for two touchdowns, but Brandin Cooks came just one foot short of his first touchdown too. Sean McVay has this offense cooking right now -- they have scored at least 33 points in all three games -- but they have a test with the Vikings coming up on Thursday Night Football.
report: Jared Goff completed 29-of-36 passes for 354 yards, three touchdowns, and an interception in the Rams' Week 3 win over the Chargers.

impact: It was not pretty, but Goff helped lead the Rams to a 5-0 start with three scoring drives in the second half and some timely plays, most notably a fourth-down conversion on a sneak to ice the game late in the fourth quarter. Goff's first interception was a forced throw which was tipped into the air at the goal line, but the second came on a Hail Mary at the end of the first half. That said, he probably deserved at least two interceptions and got lucky on several throws. Goff could have had another score, but Todd Gurley was ruled down at the one on a jet shovel pass in the second quarter. Goff has now thrown for at least 320 yards in four straight games. He will be a back-end QB1 next week in Denver.
report: Jared Goff completed 23-of-32 passes for 321 yards, a touchdown, and two interceptions in the Rams' Week 5 win over the Seahawks.

impact: Goff had his first scoreless start of the season as the Rams gutted the Broncos on the ground. He now has just one touchdown and three picks over his past two starts, both Rams victories. Today's giveaway came on a twice-tipped pass. There has been little overt reason for alarm. It just seems to be the normal ebbs and flows of a fantasy campaign. Goff nearly received some awful news this afternoon when Cooper Kupp appeared to shred his knee, but he miraculously returned after the break. Goff will remain a locked-in QB1 for Week 7 against the 49ers.
report: Jared Goff completed 14-of-28 passes for 201 yards, zero touchdowns and an interception in the Rams' 23-20, Week 6 win over the Broncos.

impact: With the 49ers turning it over for fun, Goff did not have to do much in this one. He still managed a respectable fantasy outing with two touchdowns. The first came on a great route by Brandin Cooks in the second quarter, and the second was on a screen pass to Todd Gurley in the fourth. After a hot run, Goff has now thrown for just 403 yards and two scores total in his last two games. He should fare better next week against the Packers.
report: Jared Goff completed 18-of-24 passes for 202 yards and two touchdowns in the Rams' Week 7 win over the 49ers.

impact: With the 49ers turning it over for fun, Goff did not have to do much in this one. He still managed a respectable fantasy outing with two touchdowns. The first came on a great route by Brandin Cooks in the second quarter, and the second was on a screen pass to Todd Gurley in the fourth. After a hot run, Goff has now thrown for just 403 yards and two scores total in his last two games. He should fare better next week against the Packers.
report: Jared Goff completed 18-of-24 passes for 202 yards and two touchdowns in the Rams' Week 7 win over the 49ers.

impact: Goff had a shaky first half in a hostile Coliseum — the Rams' stadium was taken over by Packers fans — but he survived to get cooking after the break. The three scores were as many as Goff totaled in Weeks 5-7. With his receivers dealing with sticky coverage, Goff relentlessly found Todd Gurley on S Jermaine Whitehead. The Rams are headed for what should be another shootout with the Saints in Week 9.
report: Jared Goff completed 19-of-35 passes for 295 yards and three touchdowns in the Rams' 29-27, Week 8 win over the Packers.

impact: Not to be outdone by Drew Brees on the other side, Goff had an outstanding start to this game. Following an opening touchdown drive, Goff hit Brandin Cooks in stride for a 48-yard catch before finding the receiver again in the back of the end zone. He made an even better throw to Cooper Kupp on the next series, letting the ball go well before the receiver made his break. Things went a bit downhill from there as Goff did not see Alex Anzalone, who came up with a great interception, but he recovered to lead a field goal drive just before the half. He came out firing after the break, completing 7-of-9 passes including an 18-yard score to get the Rams back in the game and then finding Kupp for a 41-yard touchdown to tie it up. That was the end of the magic, however, and the Rams failed to score on their final two possessions of the loss. Even so, Goff played well and now has multiple scores in three straight. He will be on the QB1 map next week against the Seahawks.
report: Jared Goff completed 28-of-40 passes for 391 yards, three scores, and an interception in the Rams' Week 9 loss to the Saints.

impact: Goff missed a few easy throws but otherwise guided the Rams to a huge home victory. The Rams can now clinch the NFC West as early as next week. The big news, however, is Cooper Kupp's knee injury. Were Kupp to be lost for the season, it would be the biggest test the Rams have faced during the Sean McVay era. Josh Reynolds is the next man up in three-receiver sets. Even if Kupp is absent, Goff will be locked and loaded as a top-five QB1 for next Monday's guaranteed shootout with the Rams. It has game of the year potential.
report: Jared Goff completed 28-of-39 passes for 318 yards and two touchdowns in the Rams' 36-31, Week 10 win over the Seahawks.

impact: After getting benched a week ago, Goedert was a huge part of the offensive game plan in Week 3. He started the game off with his first career touchdown, a 13-yard score in which he was uncovered. Despite the promising game, Goedert will not be a fantasy option heading into Week 4 against the Titans.
report: Dallas Goedert caught 7-of-7 targets for 73 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 3 win over the Colts.

impact: There was always a chance Goedert's break out performance in Week 3 was something of a fluke, and those chances grew once Alshon Jeffery was cleared to return. Goedert was not targeted in the first half of this game, and he only played around half the snaps. Goedert should have some a couple more big games this season, but predicting them will be difficult while Zach Ertz is healthy.
report: Dallas Goedert hauled in both his targets for 13 yards in the Eagles' Week 4 loss to the Titans.

impact: Goedert now has four catches for 29 yards since Alshon Jeffery's healthy return. He is off the TE2 radar until further notice.
report: Dallas Goedert caught 2-of-2 targets for 16 yards in the Eagles' Week 5 loss to the Vikings.

impact: Goedert’s involvement in Philly’s weekly game plans has been inconsistent, but he was a big part of this week’s. The Eagles got him rolling on an early 21-yard screen pass Goedert nearly took to the house, and the second-round rookie did find pay dirt later in the second quarter from one yard out. Goedert is merely a volatile TE2, but he would be a locked-in TE1 if Zach Ertz were ever to miss time.
report: Dallas Goedert caught 4-of-5 targets for 43 yards and a touchdown in the Eagles’ Week 7 loss to Carolina.

impact: Goedert’s involvement in Philly’s weekly game plans has been inconsistent, but he was a big part of this week’s. The Eagles got him rolling on an early 21-yard screen pass Goedert nearly took to the house, and the second-round rookie did find pay dirt later in the second quarter from one yard out. Goedert is merely a volatile TE2, but he would be a locked-in TE1 if Zach Ertz were ever to miss time.
report: Dallas Goedert caught 4-of-5 targets for 43 yards and a touchdown in the Eagles’ Week 7 loss to Carolina.

impact: Goedert was not a focal point of the offense by any stretch, but he made the most of his opportunity. With the Eagles hunting for a touchdown just before halftime, Goedert came open across the middle of the field, and a bootlegging Carson Wentz found him with a laser. The rookie did the rest, avoiding a tackler and scampering into the end zone. Goedert now has a touchdown in back-to-back games, but he will not be a trustworthy fantasy option while Zach Ertz is healthy.
report: Dallas Goedert caught his only target for a 32-yard touchdown in the Eagles' Week 8 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Godwin came out hot with three first-half catches including a nine-yard touchdown strike from Ryan Fitzpatrick with a little under five minutes remaining in the second quarter. He also made a phenomenal diving catch for a 16-yard pick-up in the first quarter. Godwin did cough up the football once, but was able to recover it. Despite his strong start, the second-year wideout was only targeted once after halftime as the Bucs milked the clock by leaning on their ground game. With DeSean Jackson in the concussion protocol, Godwin could be a near every-down player against the Eagles in Week 2.
report: Chris Godwin collected three catches for 41 yards and a touchdown on four targets Sunday in the Buccaneers’ Week 1 win over New Orleans.

impact: Godwin has now scored in each of the Bucs' first two games, although he continues to play in a rotation on Tampa Bay's deep pass-catcher corps.  DeSean Jackson has been white hot, and Mike Evans is playing at one of the highest levels of his career.  Godwin will be a WR3/flex option in Week 3 versus Pittsburgh.
report: Chris Godwin caught 5-of-6 targets for 56 yards and a touchdown in the Bucs' Week 2 win over Philadelphia.

impact: It's the first time all year that Godwin failed to score. With the Bucs trailing big at the half for the second time in as many weeks, it was DeSean Jackson (5-112) and Mike Evans (6-59) who unsurprisingly flourished ahead of Godwin. Adam Humphries continues to stick in a WR3 machination with the second-year pro, finishing with 6-36 on the afternoon. Consider it one bad day for Godwin. He's still a WR4/FLEX with Jameis Winston under center after Tampa Bay's Week 5 bye.
report: Chris Godwin caught his only two targets for 22 yards in Sunday's Week 4 trouncing to the Bears.

impact: Godwin was shockingly uninvolved in the blowout loss before the bye, but he bounced back in this one. He had two catches on Tampa's opening touchdown drive, and he finished tied for the team lead with nine targets. His touchdown came from nine yards out on a play he was left open just short of the goal line. With four touchdowns in five games this season, Godwin will be a FLEX option next week against the Browns.
report: Chris Godwin caught 6-of-9 targets for 56 yards and a touchdown in the Bucs' Week 6 loss to the Falcons.

impact: Godwin did most of his damage in the first half, catching four passes for 36 yards before the break. Afterwards, he received just two targets as he's still running behind all of Mike Evans, Adam Humphries and DeSean Jackson. Godwin remains a touchdown-or-bust fantasy option Week 8 against the Bengals.
report: Chris Godwin caught 5-of-6 passes for 59 yards in Sunday's Week 7 win over the Browns.

impact: Godwin is one of the most touchdown-dependent receivers in the league as a rotational player averaging fewer than 50 yards per game.  He needs the Bucs to make good on DeSean Jackson's trade wish in order to become a reliable WR3.  Mike Evans' late-game leg injury is also worth monitoring for Godwin's outlook.
report: Chris Godwin caught 2-of-7 targets for 32 yards in the Bucs' Week 8 loss to the Bengals, adding a two-point conversion.

impact: Godwin was not really heard from as Adam Humphries gobbled up eight targets behind Mike Evans and DeSean Jackson. Averaging just 48 yards per game, Godwin has settled in as a low-end WR4.
report: Chris Godwin caught 2-of-3 targets for 40 yards in the Bucs' Week 9 loss to the Panthers.

impact: Godwin was the intended receiver on Ryan Fitzpatrick's first interception, but it didn't register as an official target as it sailed well over his head at the goal line and into Josh Norman's hands.  Godwin has been super touchdown-dependent much of the year and will be a WR4 next week against the Giants.
report: Chris Godwin caught all seven of his targets for 103 yards in the Bucs' Week 10 loss to the Redskins.

impact: Gesicki played a ton, but he's not yet on the same page as Ryan Tannehill.  As Miami heads to face the Jets, look elsewhere for Week 2 tight end streamers.
report: Mike Gesicki caught 1-of-2 targets for 11 yards in the Dolphins' Week 1 win over the Titans.

impact: Even with starter AJ Derby sitting, Gesicki was invisible. The No. 42 overall pick has five grabs through four games. He's on pace for 204 yards.
report: Mike Gesicki caught 1-of-2 targets for nine yards in the Dolphins' Week 4 loss to the Patriots.

impact: It's one of his better games of the season. With AJ Derby out, Gesicki's role has been trending up, but the Dolphins need to get him more involved in an offense that lacks playmakers. Gesicki has a matchup with Chicago in Week 6.
report: Mike Gesicki caught 3-of-5 passes for 23 yards in Week 5 against the Bengals.

impact: The rookie took a backseat to Nick O’Leary, who outgained him by nearly 40 yards. Despite his immense athleticism, the Penn State alum has yet to become a factor in the fantasy realm. He’ll be off the streaming radar against Detroit in Week 7.
report: Mike Gesicki corralled one-of-two targets for 11 yards Sunday in the Dolphins’ Week 6 win over Chicago.

impact: Gesicki was also evaluated for a concussion but thankfully cleared. The 44 yards were a new career high. He could break that number again in Week 8 if neither Albert Wilson (hip) nor Kenny Stills (leg) can get cleared for Thursday Night Football against the Texans. That being said, Gesicki will remain a last-gasp TE2.
report: Mike Gesicki caught 3-of-3 targets for 44 yards in the Dolphins' Week 7 loss to the Lions.

impact: Gesicki saw five targets last week against the Texans, but he slipped back into a low-usage role in this one. His only target came well into the second half. He is only rosterable in Dynasty formats.
report: Mike Gesicki failed to corral his only target Week 9 against the Jets.

impact: This marks Garoppolo's first career loss after opening 7-0 as a starter.  Garoppolo tried to lead a comeback with the Vikings up by 18 deep into the third quarter, but the red-zone offense left a lot to be desired Sunday.  Garoppolo missed a wide-open George Kittle on a would-be four-yard touchdown and earlier overshot Kittle on a deep ball after he beat Harrison Smith.  Garoppolo also had a possible 80-yard TD dropped by Kittle.  His touchdown was a beautiful 22-yard hookup with rookie Dante Pettis after Garoppolo spun out of a sack.  He missed too many throws in this one, however, though it was a very tough road date with one of the league's best defenses.  The Niners will host the Lions in their home opener next Sunday.  Garoppolo will be a back-end QB1.
report: Jimmy Garoppolo completed just 15-of-33 passes for 261 yards, one touchdown, and three interceptions in the 49ers' 24-16, Week 1 loss to the Vikings.

impact: Jimmy G also took six sacks for a loss of 50 yards. Garoppolo dialed up a sideline pass to a wide-open Kendrick Bourne for his first touchdown of the day early in the second quarter. He added to his touchdown tally with another score in the third quarter, this time connecting with tight end Garrett Celek for 11 yards. Garoppolo narrowly avoided disaster in the fourth as a Tracy Walker interception was negated by a holding call on Quandre Diggs. That interception would have set the Lions up with first-and-goal and a chance to take the lead with just over two minutes remaining. As his six sacks would attest to, Garoppolo often held on to the ball too long, though all in all, Sunday was a much better performance than his last one against the Vikings in Week 1. Now 8-1 as an NFL starting quarterback, Handsome Jimmy will head to KC next week for a shootout with Patrick Mahomes and the 2-0 Chiefs.
report: Jimmy Garoppolo completed 18-of-26 passes for 206 yards and two touchdowns while contributing four yards on three carries Sunday in the 49ers’ Week 2 win over the Lions.

impact: Pro Football Focus charted Gates as playing 33-of-82 snaps. His production was identical to Virgil Green's. Gates will be on the TE2 radar for Week 2 against a Bills defense that struggled to defend the middle of the field last season.
report: Antonio Gates caught 2-of-3 passes for 16 yards in the Chargers' Week 1 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: He had just one target. Gates has been an afterthought in the Chargers' offense after two catches in the season opener. He's droppable in fantasy leagues.
report: Antonio Gates was held without a catch in Week 2 against Buffalo.

impact: The five targets are a season-high for the veteran tight end. Gates' red zone ability could lead him to a few touchdowns this year, but the 38-year-old is off the fantasy radar with how little volume he has seen.
report: Antonio Gates caught 3-of-5 targets for 45 yards in the Chargers' Week 3 loss to the Rams.

impact: That's back-to-back games with five targets, but he was able to score a touchdown this time around when he escaped to the corner of the end zone without a defender in sight. Gates is a touchdown-dependent TE2, but there should be a couple touchdown opportunities next week against the Raiders.
report: Antonio Gates caught 2-of-5 targets for 26 yards and a touchdown in the Chargers' Week 4 win over the 49ers.

impact: Gates remains a touchdown-dependent streamer as he's posted just 7-90-1 in the Chargers' last three games. With his weekly snaps continuously getting eaten into by fellow tight end Virgil Green (1-13-1), Gates can stay on the wire until the utmost perfect matchup presents itself.
report: Antonio Gates caught both of his targets for 19 yards in the Chargers' Week 5 win over the Raiders.

impact: Gates remains a touchdown-dependent streamer as he's posted just 7-90-1 in the Chargers' last three games. With his weekly snaps continuously getting eaten into by fellow tight end Virgil Green (1-13-1), Gates can stay on the wire until the utmost perfect matchup presents itself.
report: Antonio Gates caught both of his targets for 19 yards in the Chargers' Week 5 win over the Raiders.

impact: The 80 yards were as many as Gates had in his previous six games COMBINED. Gates has spent much of the year fighting a losing battle with Father Time, but on Sunday, the aging tight end turned the tables with a throwback performance. The 38-year-old was on the receiving end of a six-yard touchdown dart from Philip Rivers early in the third quarter. That was his first end-zone visit since Week 4 and marked his 12th career touchdown against Denver. Gates nearly sat out this week due to a knee injury, but obviously he didn't show any ill effects on Sunday. It was nice to see a living legend strut his stuff, though we wouldn't expect a repeat performance from Gates when the Chargers host Arizona on Thanksgiving weekend.
report: Antonio Gates contributed five grabs for 80 yards and a touchdown on seven targets Sunday in the Chargers’ Week 11 loss to the Broncos.

impact: The 49ers were stuck with just three active receivers for much of the game with Marquise Goodwin and Dante Pettis both leaving the game early with knee injuries. Garcon was still unable to do much with the extra looks, as has been the case all year. Through four weeks, Garcon has 14 receptions for 156 scoreless yards, and he's has failed to score 10 PPR points in a game despite Goodwin being in-and-out of the lineup.
report: Pierre Garcon caught 4-of-7 targets for 52 scoreless yards in the 49ers' Week 4 loss to the Chargers.

impact: He dropped at least two of those targets. This was easily Garcon's biggest workload of 2018, though obviously he wasn't able to take advantage. Even with Marquise Goodwin injured, Garcon has done next to nothing, reeling in just 16-of-33 targets (48.5 percent) for 188 scoreless yards this season. The 32-year-old will take a 16-game touchdown drought into next week's matchup at Green Bay.
report: Pierre Garcon managed five catches for 47 yards on 12 targets Sunday in the Niners’ Week 5 loss to the Cardinals.

impact: With C.J. Beathard struggling, Garcon never had a chance. He has still failed to top 60 yards in any game this season, and he has scored a touchdown since Week 14 of the 2016 season. He can be left on the wire.
report: Pierre Garcon took his only target five yards in the 49ers' Week 7 loss to the Rams.

impact: Hyde added three yards on one catch. He ran just nine times for 26 yards in the first half before having a positive drive in the 3rd quarter where he carried four times for 30 yards a touchdown. The Browns offensive line appears to be a real problem for generating consistent yardage, but Hyde handled 22-of-30 Cleveland rushing attempts to open the season. Hyde will be an RB2 option next week on the road versus the Saints.
report: Browns RB Carlos Hyde rushed 22 times for 62 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 1 game versus the Steelers.

impact: Hyde added one catch for seven yards in the passing game. It was the second-consecutive game where Hyde struggled on the ground, but was bailed out by a 1-yard rushing score, this time following a pass interference in the end zone. Hyde has now rushed 38 times for 108 yards through two games. He will remain a fringe RB2 in Week 3 versus the Jets.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed 16 times for 43 yards and touchdown in Sunday's Week 2 loss to the Saints.

impact: He added two receptions for five yards. No joke: Hyde then had to rush to the hospital for the birth of his child. Best wishes to the Hyde family. As for the game, nearly all of Hyde's damage, including both his scores, came after Baker Mayfield checked in for Tyrod Taylor (concussion). The Browns' offense looked reborn with Mayfield under center, complicating the defense's thinking and freeing up running lanes. Hyde took advantage with his trademark power running. Hyde will be an upside RB2 for a tasty Week 4 matchup with the Raiders.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed 23 times for 98 yards and two touchdowns in the Browns' Week 3 win over the Jets.

impact: He has at least 17 touches in all four games and 22 or more in three of them.  Hyde's touchdown came from a yard out following Antonio Callaway's 51-yard catch.  Hyde drew just one target, however, and Nick Chubb broke off 63- and 41-yard touchdown sprints, potentially earning the explosive rookie more work.  Until the Browns make a tangible playing-time adjustment in the backfield, however, Hyde will remain a high-volume RB2 play.  Cleveland hosts Baltimore next.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed 22 times for 82 yards and a touchdown in the Browns' Week 4 loss to the Raiders.

impact: Hyde found little to no room against a strong Baltimore defense. He had a 17-yard run early in the game but was still held to 3.7 yards per rush on the day. Hyde has been living off of touchdown production early in the season, but still has amassed 17 or more touches in every game this season. That kind of usage is nothing to scoff at, making Hyde a volume-based RB2 in a better matchup Week 6 at home against the Chargers.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed 17 times for 63 yards while catching 2-of-3 targets for 14 yards in Sunday's Week 5 win over the Ravens.

impact: Hyde has now failed to score in back-to-back games and it has exposed the low floor he carries weekly. Hyde has rushed for 4.0 yards per carry in just once game this season and has rushed 31 times for 97 yards over the past two weeks. His biggest obstacle for maintaining a fantasy floor is he has just six catches on the season and was not even targeted in the passing game on Sunday. Hyde will enter Week 7 as a touchdown-dependent RB2 option in Week 7 on the road in Tampa Bay.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed 14 times for 34 yards in Sunday's Week 6 loss to the Chargers.

impact: He did not catch either of his targets. Hyde operated as the lead back early in the game, but he could not get anything going. He gained just eight yards of five carries in the first half, and things did not get any better after the break. With Leonard Fournette expected back after the bye, it is fair to wonder how much work Hyde will see the rest of the season. That said, Fournette has already suffered a setback once when trying to return from his hamstring injury, so his status cannot be taken for granted. That makes Hyde a hold through the bye week despite this poor showing.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed six times for 11 yards in the Jaguars' Week 8 loss to the Eagles.

impact: Hyde got his first carry of the game near the end of the third quarter, and he finished the game with just three touches. He is just a handcuff with Leonard Fournette back healthy.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed three times for five yards in the Jaguars' Week 10 loss to the Colts.

impact: Hyde was part of the Jaguars rushing attack in the first half, carrying six times for 37 yards before the half, but then was not heard from in the second half. Hyde is only a handcuff to Leonard Fournette at this point of the season.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed eight times for 44 yards in Sunday's Week 11 loss to the Steelers.

impact: It's another disappointing target share for Gallup after one catch in the season opener. The Cowboys have played Gallup behind journeyman Deonte Thompson despite his strong preseason, and re-signed Brice Butler this week, further muddling their receivers. Gallup remains a strong hold in dynasty, but it may take an injury for Dallas to realize his potential.
report: Michael Gallup caught 1-of-2 targets for five yards in Week 2 against the Giants.

impact: The rookie bobbled a ball that eventually found its way into the hands of Earl Thomas. That was one of two interceptions for Thomas, who may have been auditioning to be Gallup’s teammate in Dallas. Even in a wide-open pass-catching corps, the third-rounder has failed to make a difference. He’s managed just three catches over his first three NFL appearances.
report: Michael Gallup pulled in one-of-four targets for 17 yards Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 3 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: Gallup skied over Nevin Lawson for an impressive 37-yard catch in the first quarter. That’s more yards than he had in his previous three games combined. The rookie drew an end-zone target from Dak Prescott later on that same drive but the two couldn’t connect. For all his talent, Gallup has managed to haul in just five-of-12 targets this year. Maybe his day will come but right now, the Colorado State alum is miles off the fantasy radar.
report: Michael Gallup pulled in two catches for 45 yards on five targets Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 4 win over the Lions.

impact: Gallup nearly made a brilliant touchdown catch in double coverage during the first half but he didn't get both of his feet in bounds. The rookie has shown flashes here and there but not enough for him to warrant redraft consideration.
report: Michael Gallup chipped in with one catch for 27 yards on two targets Sunday in Dallas’ Week 6 win over the Jaguars.

impact: With Tavon Austin inactive, Gallup was afforded additional opportunity and delivered with a team- and career-high 81 receiving yards. 49 yards came on a deep-ball over the top in which Gallup simply beat the defense and found himself wide open near the sideline. Dallas' leading receiver seems to rotate weekly, but this is a great development for the rookie in the event Austin misses any further time. The Cowboys are on bye next week.
report: Michael Gallup hauled in 3-of-5 targets for a team-high 81 yards and one score in Dallas' Week 7 loss to the Redskins.

impact: Gallup ran as the clear No. 2 wideout alongside new No. 1 Amari Cooper, and the rookie's six targets were second on the team to Cooper's eight.  Gallup is playing a solid snap share, but this pass offense is one of the worst in the league.  With byes coming to an end, Gallup is WR5 material.
report: Michael Gallup caught 3-of-6 targets for 51 yards in the Cowboys' Week 9 loss to the Titans.

impact: In three games since the Amari Cooper trade, Gallup has receiving lines of 3-51, 2-34, and 1-10 with no touchdowns.  He's not a redraft fantasy asset.
report: Michael Gallup caught 1-of-5 targets for 10 yards in the Cowboys' Week 11 win over the Falcons.

impact: Gabbert was predictably bad, but the bigger story is the Titans may have to start him in Week 2 with Marcus Mariota (elbow) ailing.  The Titans host the Texans next.  We'll have a better idea of Mariota's injury on Monday.
report: Blaine Gabbert completed 11-of-22 passes for 117 yards and an interception in the Titans' Week 1 loss to Miami.

impact: Both Gabbert and Marcus Mariota (elbow) warmed up for the Titans' Week 2 division bout against the Texans, but it was the former who took all reps with the first-string offense. The Titans only have two available quarterbacks, so Mariota could still stay glued to the sidelines despite being active. There has been no official announcement on Tennessee's starter.
report: Blaine Gabbert is warming up with the Titans' first string offense.

impact: Gabbert barely cracked the century mark in his spot-start for Marcus Mariota (elbow), tossing for 117 yards and an abysmal 5.8 YPA. Gabbert's fantasy production typically derives (and hinges on) his legs, but he mustered only two scrambles for two yards in Tennessee's Week 2 win. Corey Davis (5-55) still managed to lead all Titans skill players with a team-high seven targets, so consider him the focal point of Tennessee's passing game no matter who is under center moving forward.
report: Blaine Gabbert completed 13-of-20 passes for 117 yards and one touchdown in the Titans' Week 2 win over the Texans.

impact: Gabbert took a first-quarter hit so massive that he was noticeably woozy and eventually left the field with trainers.  Marcus Mariota, dealing with a nerve problem in his throwing-arm elbow, has taken over at quarterback against Jacksonville.
report: Blaine Gabbert left Sunday's Week 3 game with a concussion.

impact: Gabbert was forced into the game in the dying moments of the first half after Marcus Mariota re-injured his throwing elbow. The Titans were already losing 24-0. Gifted an entire half of garbage time, Gabbert did nothing until the final two minutes, when he found Tajae Sharpe in the end zone. Hilariously, his interception was thrown literally right to LB Darius Leonard. The Titans won't have a prayer if Gabbert is forced to start next Monday night's game against the Texans.
report: Blaine Gabbert completed 11-of-16 passes for 118 yards, one touchdown and an interception in the Titans' 38-10, Week 11 loss to the Colts.

impact: It's the third consecutive game that Gabriel's seen at least seven targets. He even out-shined perennial No. 1 Allen Robinson (2-23-1) on Mitchell Trubisky's career six-score day. The Bears' offense has quietly developed and thus progressively improved in every outing so far this season, slowly raising Gabriel's stock with every passing game. He'll come out of Chicago's Week 5 bye as a strong FLEX option against the Dolphins.
report: Taylor Gabriel brought in all seven of his targets for a career-high 104 yards and two touchdowns in the Bears' Week 4 win over the Bucs.

impact: Make that two 100-yard receiving games in a row for Gabriel, who went off for 104 yards against Tampa Bay prior to the Bears' bye week. Gabriel didn't find the end zone in this one but he still made his presence felt with a number of big plays, the first of those coming on a 47-yard deep bomb from Mitchell Trubisky during the second quarter. He bettered that with a 54-yarder in the third quarter, again dusting overmatched corner Torry McTyer for a huge gain. The speedy 27-year-old has quickly emerged as Trubisky's preferred deep threat. He'll look to keep it going against New England in Week 7.
report: Taylor Gabriel snagged all five of his targets for 110 yards while adding a nine-yard rush Sunday in the Bears’ Week 6 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: With Mitchell Trubisky struggling early, Gabriel caught just one pass in the first half for seven yards. He did get a carry inside the 10-yard line in the third quarter and drew a long defensive pass interference on the next series, but this was a big letdown after back-to-back 100-yard games. He will look to get back on track next week against the Jets.
report: Taylor Gabriel hauled in 3-of-4 targets for 26 yards in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: With Mitchell Trubisky struggling early, Gabriel caught just one pass in the first half for seven yards. He did get a carry inside the 10-yard line in the third quarter and drew a long defensive pass interference on the next series, but this was a big letdown after back-to-back 100-yard games. He will look to get back on track next week against the Jets.
report: Taylor Gabriel hauled in 3-of-4 targets for 26 yards in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: It's a disappointing game for Gabriel with Allen Robinson sidelined. He was out-targeted by Anthony Miller, and couldn't get anything going downfield with Mitchell Trubisky. Gabriel has been trending down the last two since posting consecutive 100-yard games. Even if Robinson doesn't return next week, he's just a WR4 option.
report: Taylor Gabriel caught 4-of-6 passes for 52 yards in Week 8 against the Jets.

impact: Gabriel got on the board for 30 yards and two catches early, but the Bears wound up not even needing their passing game with two defensive touchdowns and two Jordan Howard scores against a Bills team that scored nine points.  Gabriel will continue to be a high-variance fringe WR3 in Week 10 against the Lions.
report: Taylor Gabriel caught 3-of-5 targets for 45 yards in the Bears' Week 9 win over the Bills.

impact: He was a non-factor in Allen Robinson's return from injury. Gabriel had a productive stretch earlier this year but that seems to have come and gone. The 27-year-old deep threat won't be of much fantasy interest next week against the Vikings.
report: Taylor Gabriel came up empty on his three targets Sunday in the Bears’ Week 10 victory over Detroit.

impact: Hurst got in the action early, catching a seven-yard pass on the second drive of the game, but failed to reel in another pass on the day. Tight ends Mark Andrews (three targets) and Nick Boyle (two) each were involved as much as Hurst. This is likely going to be a frustrating split for the short term until Hurst claims a grasp on the job, leaving him as a TE2 Week 6 against the Titans.
report: Hayden Hurst caught 1-of-2 targets for seven yards in Sunday's Week 5 loss to the Browns.

impact: This could maybe be construed as a revenge game for Hurst, who spent two years in the Pittsburgh Pirates organization before reigniting his football career at South Carolina. Obviously that narrative, though fascinating, had no bearing on Sunday's outcome. With Baltimore's offense falling apart at the seams, the first-round rookie can't be counted on for fantasy purposes.
report: Hayden Hurst finished with one catch for 21 yards on two targets Sunday in the Ravens’ Week 9 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Hurns played a season-high 66.1 percent of the Cowboys’ offensive snaps, but didn’t do much with the opportunity. The Cowboys’ passing game continues to be stuck in neutral, though it’s unlikely Hurns will be the one to fix things.
report: Allen Hurns corralled two-of-four targets for 22 yards Sunday in Dallas’ Week 3 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: This would technically qualify as a step forward for Hurns, who had been limited to a mere 41 yards on four catches over his previous three outings. The ex-Jaguar actually made a few nice grabs on Sunday including a nice sideline catch against All-Pro corner Darius Slay, but it’s clear the Cowboys’ offense will continue to live and die by Zeke Elliott. Fantasy owners who thought they could catch lightning in a bottle by taking a late-round flyer on Hurns this summer have not been rewarded for their efforts. He can be ignored against the Texans in Week 5.
report: Allen Hurns grabbed three-of-five targets for 30 yards Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 4 win over the Lions.

impact: Hurns may have had some butterflies going against his former team for the first time Sunday. Whatever the reason, Hurns couldn't get on the same page with Dak Prescott. Perhaps he'll fare better next week when the Cowboys travel to D.C. for a divisional showdown against the Redskins.
report: Allen Hurns was targeted five times but didn’t record a catch Sunday in the Cowboys’ Week 6 win over the Jaguars.

impact: It was the first time Hurns eclipsed the 30-yard mark all year. His only touchdown on the season remains his Week 5 score against the Texans in which he was left wide open in the back of the end zone. The Cowboys can barely support one receiver, let alone two. Hurns shouldn't be owned.
report: Allen Hurns caught 5-of-6 targets for a season-high 74 yards in the Cowboys' Week 7 loss to the Redskins.

impact: It was the first time Hurns eclipsed the 30-yard mark all year. His only touchdown on the season remains his Week 5 score against the Texans in which he was left wide open in the back of the end zone. The Cowboys can barely support one receiver, let alone two. Hurns shouldn't be owned.
report: Allen Hurns caught 5-of-6 targets for a season-high 74 yards in the Cowboys' Week 7 loss to the Redskins.

impact: For the first time in a full game, Hunt was held without a reception. The Chiefs were playing from ahead but got dominated in time of possession and kept making big plays through the air. Hunt simply was not needed on the ground. Spencer Ware was involved behind him but only to the tune of four touches. Hunt should have a bounce-back effort in Week 2 against a Steelers run defense that has not been the same since Ryan Shazier went down.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 16 times for 49 yards in the Chiefs' Week 1 win over the Chargers.

impact: Hunt was running with power, but he simply wasn't needed for a monster workload with Patrick Mahomes getting whatever he wanted through the air. The aggressive Mahomes has now found Hunt for just one catch through two games after Hunt averaged 3.5 receptions (throwing out a Week 17 cameo) last season. Hunt's ceiling remains sky-high in the Chiefs' high-voltage offense, but his weekly floor is going to be a little lower than it was as a rookie.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 18 times for 75 yards in the Chiefs' Week 2 win over the Steelers, adding a five-yard touchdown reception.

impact: Hunt eased the minds of worried fantasy players with two one-yard touchdown runs in the first quarter, and he buoyed his fantasy game with 22 yards on a close-out drive in the fourth. There are still reasons for concern, however. He saw just one target, did not catch that pass, and sat out the two-minute drill at the end of the first half. He now has one catch through three games. Being attached to the best offense in the league should offer plenty of scoring chances, but the lack of receiving usage gives Hunt a concerning floor moving forward.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 18 times for 44 yards and two touchdowns in the Chiefs' Week 3 win over the 49ers.

impact: Hunt added three catches for 54 yards on four targets.  In the first half, he was the focal point of the offense, as the Broncos' pass-rush and backend coverage made things difficult on Patrick Mahomes.  It's Hunt's first 100-yard rushing game of the season after six as a rookie.  Hunt was stuffed a couple times inside the five-yard line early before later cashing one in from four yards out late in the fourth quarter to cap the comeback and give the Chiefs a 26-23 lead.  Hunt will be a borderline RB1 next week at home against the stout Jaguars.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 19 times for 121 yards and one touchdown in the Chiefs' 27-23, Week 4 win over the Broncos on Monday night.

impact: He added seven yards on one catch. Hunt understandably struggled to gain consistent yardage against a tough front, but he got loose for a 24-yard gain in the third quarter -- he cost the offense 15 yards with an unsportsmanlike penalty at the end of that carry -- and sealed the game with a four-yard touchdown run on the first play of the fourth. He padded his stats with 31 yards including a 15-yard gain on a drive deep into garbage time. Hunt now has five touchdowns in his last four games. He will be a solid RB1 next week in New England.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 22 times for 87 yards and a touchdown in the Chiefs' Week 5 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Hunt lost some snaps to Spencer Ware with the Chiefs playing from behind early, but the Chiefs went back to him in the second half. He was left wide open on a third-and-short for a 67-yard TD to start the third quarter. Hunt should’ve had another touchdown but was stopped at the goal-line. After a slow start, Hunt’s been on fire over the last month, with at least 100 total yards or a touchdown in three straight games. He'll be an RB1 in Week 7 against the Bengals.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 10 times for 80 yards and caught 5-of-6 passes for 105 yards and a touchdown in Week 6 against the Patriots.

impact: Hunt had one of the highlights of the year in this one, breaking multiple tackles and hurdling over a defender on a play that set up his first receiving touchdown. On his second, he took a red-zone dumpoff down the right sideline and extended over the pylon before going out of bounds. Hunt converted a goal-line carry for his rushing score on the Chiefs first drive of the second half. It's the second straight week Hunt's had an expanded pass game role after going over 100 yards receiving against the Patriots. Hunt has been on fire with a touchdown in five straight weeks. He'll remain a locked-in RB1 for Week 8 against Denver.
report: Kareem Hunt had 15 carries for 86 yards and a touchdown and caught 5-of-6 passes for 55 yards and two touchdowns in Week 7 against the Bengals.

impact: Hunt had one of the highlights of the year in this one, breaking multiple tackles and hurdling over a defender on a play that set up his first receiving touchdown. On his second, he took a red-zone dumpoff down the right sideline and extended over the pylon before going out of bounds. Hunt converted a goal-line carry for his rushing score on the Chiefs first drive of the second half. It's the second straight week Hunt's had an expanded pass game role after going over 100 yards receiving against the Patriots. Hunt has been on fire with a touchdown in five straight weeks. He'll remain a locked-in RB1 for Week 8 against Denver.
report: Kareem Hunt had 15 carries for 86 yards and a touchdown and caught 5-of-6 passes for 55 yards and two touchdowns in Week 7 against the Bengals.

impact: The 50 rushing yards were his fewest since Week 3. Hunt scored in thrilling fashion, nabbing a fourth-down shovel pass from Patrick Mahomes and hurdling a defender on his way to the end zone for a 23-yard touchdown. That extended Hunt's touchdown streak to seven games. The 23-year-old was scarcely used in the passing game early on, but he's quickly become one of Mahomes' favorite targets, delivering four touchdown receptions over his last three games. Last year's NFL rushing leader should be in for another big fantasy performance when the Chiefs travel to Cleveland in Week 9.
report: Kareem Hunt went for 50 yards on 16 carries while also contributing five catches for 36 yards and a touchdown on six targets Sunday in Kansas City’s Week 8 win over the Broncos.

impact: Hunt got the day started with a 50-yard screen pass for a touchdown on the opening drive of the game and then added rushing scores of one and 10 yards. That was Hunt's second three-touchdown game over his past three weeks and he has now has scored a touchdown in eight straight games. Hunt gets a juicy matchup against the soft Arizona run defense at home in Week 10.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 17 times for 91 yards and two touchdowns with one catch for 50 yards and a touchdown in Sundays Week 9 win over the Browns.

impact: Hunt finished just under 100 total yards. It's also the first time since Week 1 he was held out of the end-zone. Spencer Ware vultured Hunt's best chance to score at the three-yard line. There just wasn't much room for Hunt to do anything against a Cardinals defense that did a good job of limiting Kansas City's run game. Hunt should rebound in a Week 11 matchup against the Rams.
report: Kareem Hunt rushed 16 times for 71 yards and caught two passes for 25 yards in Week 10 against the Cardinals.

impact: He was shut out in the first half, but was more effective after halftime, chipping in with three catches on four second-half targets. Humphries took a screen pass from Ryan Fitzpatrick 65 yards to the house late in the second quarter, but the play was called back for an illegal block by left tackle Donovan Smith. In a busy Bucs’ receiving corps, Humphries is unlikely to be a major fantasy factor next week against the Eagles.
report: Adam Humphries supplied three catches for 27 yards on five targets Sunday in the Buccaneers’ Week 1 win over the Saints.

impact: Humphries only ended up with four targets, but he made the most of them. His biggest play came on a 51-yard catch-and-run early in the third quarter. Despite that big play, Humphries is not a viable fantasy option outside of deep leagues.
report: Adam Humphries hauled in 3-of-4 targets for 82 yards in the Bucs' Week 6 loss to the Falcons.

impact: Humphries continues to work as the Bucs true WR2 in terms of snaps and routes and Sunday he was only out-targeted by Mike Evans (10) and O.J. Howard (nine). Humphries is the worst kind of player because he is not valuable for fantasy purposes on his own merit while remaining a thorn in the side of the fantasy ceilings for the members of the Tampa Bay passing game. He is not a viable fantasy option Week 8 against the Bengals.
report: Adam Humphries caught 4-of-8 targets for 37 yards in Sunday's Week 7 win over the Browns.

impact: Humphries continues to work as the Bucs true WR2 in terms of snaps and routes and Sunday he was only out-targeted by Mike Evans (10) and O.J. Howard (nine). Humphries is the worst kind of player because he is not valuable for fantasy purposes on his own merit while remaining a thorn in the side of the fantasy ceilings for the members of the Tampa Bay passing game. He is not a viable fantasy option Week 8 against the Bengals.
report: Adam Humphries caught 4-of-8 targets for 37 yards in Sunday's Week 7 win over the Browns.

impact: The Bucs' slot receiver entered this game with just one TD over his last 25 appearances, and Humphries remained scoreless after replay review showed he was down at the one-yard line following a 17-yard reception.  Humphries is a useful real-life player who lacks fantasy football value.
report: Adam Humphries caught 7-of-10 targets for 76 yards in the Bucs' Week 8 loss to the Bengals.

impact: Open at will as the Panthers focused on shutting down Mike Evans, DeSean Jackson and Chris Godwin, Humphries tied for the fourth-most yardage of his career. The touchdowns were his first since last Week 15. Humphries has been more involved in recent weeks, clearing 40 yards in three-straight games. He will be a desperation WR5 for Week 10 against the Redskins.
report: Adam Humphries caught 8-of-8 targets for 82 yards and two touchdowns in the Bucs' Week 9 loss to the Panthers.

impact: After seeing at least eight targets in three straight games, Humphries took a back seat to Chris Godwin (7-100) in this one as the No. 3 receiver.  Humphries will be a WR4 next week against the Giants in Newark.
report: Adam Humphries caught 2-of-3 targets for 53 yards in the Bucs' Week 10 loss to the Redskins.

impact: Humphries was on his way to another pedestrian outing before phoning a friend and hauling in another touchdown from Jameis Winston. The two had shown rapport in Winston's last stint as starter, and it showed again in the (slightly less than) two quarters he was in for Ryan Fitzpatrick (benched). It's hard not to consider Humphries a low-end WR3/FLEX against the Niners next week if Winston is again declared starter.
report: Adam Humphries caught 3-of-5 targets for 60 yards and one touchdown in the Bucs' Week 11 loss to the Giants.

impact: Howard took advantage of his limited workload, pulling in a 35-yard grab in tight coverage before nabbing a 19-yarder on a well-placed back-shoulder throw from Ryan Fitzpatrick. He out-snapped teammate Cameron Brate by a significant 43-24 margin. Howard will be in the TE2 mix next time out against Philadelphia.
report: O.J. Howard absorbed both of his targets for 54 yards Sunday in Tampa Bay’s Week 1 win over the Saints.

impact: Howard caught a 35-yard pass in tight coverage for his big Week 1 play, then delivered a 75-yard catch-and-run touchdown to pad Ryan Fitzpatrick's stats on Sunday versus Philly.  Howard only has target totals of 2 and 4 through two weeks.  He will remain a volatile TE1 option in Week 3 against the Steelers, who served up a pair of Travis Kelce touchdowns in Week 2.
report: O.J. Howard caught 3-of-4 targets for 96 yards and a touchdown in the Bucs' Week 2 win over the Eagles.

impact: Howard suffered a knee injury in the second quarter of Sunday's loss to Chicago and wasn't able to return. The Bucs don't believe the injury is serious, but they still want him to get checked out. Luckily for fantasy owners, Howard will have the bye week to heal up. Cameron Brate would fill in at tight end if Howard can't go against the Falcons in Week 6.
report: O.J. Howard (knee) will undergo an MRI on Monday.

impact: Howard was not limited at all despite coming back quickly from his sprained MCL. HIs first catch of the game was a 10-yard touchdown in which he out-muscled a linebacker, and but he really took over in the second half, catching three passes for 52 yards. Apparently fully healthy, Howard will be a TE1 next week against the Browns.
report: O.J. Howard hauled in all four of his targets for 62 yards and a touchdown in the Bucs' Week 6 loss to the Falcons.

impact: Howard's nine targets were the most he's had in a game this season. His best play of the day came on a 24-yard catch over a defender in which he was down at the 2-yard line. Howard now has 20 catches for 351 yards and two scores through six games and will be a lower-TE1 option in Week 8 against a Bengals team that has struggled to defend the tight end position all season.
report: O.J. Howard caught 5-of-9 passes for 67 yards in Sunday's Week 7 win over the Browns.

impact: Howard's nine targets were the most he's had in a game this season. His best play of the day came on a 24-yard catch over a defender in which he was down at the 2-yard line. Howard now has 20 catches for 351 yards and two scores through six games and will be a lower-TE1 option in Week 8 against a Bengals team that has struggled to defend the tight end position all season.
report: O.J. Howard caught 5-of-9 passes for 67 yards in Sunday's Week 7 win over the Browns.

impact: Hyper efficient as usual, Howard's 18-yard score narrowed the deficit to two points late in the fourth quarter, and Chris Godwin tied the game with a two-point conversion one play later.  The Bucs went on to lose in overtime.  Even though Howard is not heavily targeted, he is catching everything in sight and making big plays.  He will be an upside TE1 play in Week 9 at Carolina.
report: O.J. Howard caught 4-of-4 targets for 68 yards and a touchdown in the Bucs' Week 8 loss to the Bengals.

impact: Howard's scores, his fourth and fifth of the season, went for three and four yards. The first came on a "counter boot." The second, Howard was sent in motion and created a sufficient amount of space. Today was actually Howard's first healthy game since Week 1 where he failed to clear 60 yards. He will be a top-five tight end for Week 10 against the Redskins.
report: O.J. Howard caught 4-of-6 targets for 53 yards and a pair of touchdowns in the Bucs' Week 9 loss to the Panthers.

impact: Cameron Brate had one catch for 14 yards on three targets as the Redskins blanketed the Bucs' tight end duo.  Howard will get back on track next week as a lock-and-load TE1 on the road against the lowly Giants.
report: O.J. Howard caught his lone target for 15 yards in the Bucs' Week 10 loss to the Redskins.

impact: The Giants have struggled against tight end of the year, so it wasn't shocking to see Howard get back on track. He was being checked on the sideline by trainers for a brief period during the team's final drive, so there was actually room for an even bigger day had he stayed on the field. He'll be a TE1 again next week against the Niners.
report: O.J. Howard caught 5-of-6 targets for 78 yards in the Bucs' Week 11 loss to the Giants.

impact: The only difference from Hooper's normal day is he caught a touchdown.  Otherwise, the yards and five targets are par for the course for him.  Hooper's score came from eight yards out.  When he scores, he's an obvious fantasy difference-maker, but those touchdowns are hard to predict.  For now, Hooper will remain a TE2 most weeks but has streamer appeal Week 3 against the Saints.
report: Austin Hooper caught all five of his targets for 59 yards and one touchdown in the Falcons' Week 2 win over the Panthers.

impact: It was a quiet afternoon for the Falcons tight end, though he did chip in with a two-point conversion following Tevin Coleman’s touchdown early in the fourth quarter. Hooper has only topped 30 yards once this season and won’t be an appealing streamer against the Bengals in Week 4.
report: Austin Hooper turned in three catches for 23 yards on four targets Sunday in Atlanta’s Week 3 loss to the Saints.

impact: Hooper went for 59 yards and a touchdown in Week 2, but he has predictably scuffled since, catching just four passes for 42 yards in two games. He did have an end-zone target in this game, and that usage makes him a touchdown-or-bust fantasy option.
report: Austin Hooper hauled in 1-of-2 targets for 19 yards in the Falcons' Week 4 loss to the Bengals.

impact: Under constant pressure, Matt Ryan was constantly checking down. That includes a first half "Hail Mary." The receptions were a new personal best while the yards were the third most of Hooper's career. Hooper might actually stay hot for Week 6, where the Falcons host the Bucs. No team has allowed more fantasy points to opposing tight ends.
report: Austin Hooper caught 9-of-12 targets for 77 yards in the Falcons' Week 5 loss to the Steelers.

impact: It is Hooper's second game in a row with nine catches after failing to top seven in any of his first 34 games. His touchdown came on a delay route where he was left wide open in the flat and stiffed armed a corner to the ground on his way into the end zone. He also came up with a big third-down conversion on the Falcons' final drive to help set up a field goal. With Calvin Ridley (ankle) and Mohamed Sanu (hip) questionable, Hooper will be a back-end TE1 next week.
report: Austin Hooper hauled in 9-of-10 targets for 71 yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 6 win over the Bucs.

impact: Hooper has two games of double-digit targets and five or fewer in the other six.  In a crowded Falcons pass-catcher corps, Hooper will remain a high-variance, low-end TE1 open when Atlanta visits Cleveland in Week 10.
report: Austin Hooper caught 3-of-3 targets for 41 yards in Atlanta's Week 9 win at Washington.

impact: After two games where he combined for just seven targets, Hooper drew more than 10 looks for the third five in five contests. Hooper is heavily involved any time Matt Ryan is compelled to check down. Hooper's touchdown came on a broken play fourth down late in the fourth quarter. He will be on the TE1 borderline for Week 11 against the Cowboys.
report: Austin Hooper caught 10-of-11 targets for 56 yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 10 loss to the Browns.

impact: He was getting peppered with targets early, seeing seven of his looks in the first half.  Hooper will be a TE1 on Thursday night against the Saints.  Hooper had three grabs for 23 scoreless yards against the Saints in Week 3.
report: Austin Hooper caught 4-of-8 targets for 27 yards in the Falcons' Week 11 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: Howard was the focal point on offense, out touching Tarik Cohen (five carries, three catches) by a wide margin. He put Chicago in position to win late, but their defense couldn't hold on. Howard had a larger third-down role than last year, but still ceded pass game snaps to Cohen. He'll remain a high-floor RB2 for Week 2 against Seattle.
report: Jordan Howard had 15 carries for 82 yards and caught five passes for 25 yards in Week 1 against the Packers.

impact: Howard is averaging 19 touches per game through two weeks but has yet to find the end zone and had a long run of just seven yards Monday night.  He continues to be the clear backfield focal point over Tarik Cohen, who touched the ball just five times in this one after eight times in Week 1.  Howard will look to find pay dirt next week in a soft road date against the Cardinals.
report: Jordan Howard rushed 14 times for 35 yards and caught 3-of-4 targets for 33 yards in the Bears' Week 2 win over the Seahawks.

impact: Howard found little room to operate on the ground for the second straight week, but was able to get into the end zone on a 1-yard plunge for the Bears' lone touchdown of the game. After a strong 15-82 rushing line to start the season in Week 1, Howard has now carried 38 times for 96 yards the past two weeks. Howard will remain a strong volume-based fantasy Week 4 at home against the Buccaneers coming off a short week.
report: Jordan Howard rushed 24 times for 61 yards and a touchdown while catching 2-of-2 targets for 20 yards in Sunday's Week 3 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Chicago led 38-3 at the half, which would usually make for terrific game script for Howard to go out and ice the rest of the game. But it was Tarik Cohen who stayed involved from kick-off to the final whistle, leading the Bears in both targets and carries. Howard failed to haul in his only target Sunday, too. The argument to start Howard has been strictly usage-based to this point as he has yet to eclipse the 100-yard mark despite averaging 16 carries per game. If Cohen continues cutting into his playing time, it will be time for owners to rethink their position on him. This timeshare will be worth monitoring when the Bears return from their bye in Week 6.
report: Jordan Howard rushed 11 times for 25 yards in the Bears' Week 4 victory over the Bucs.

impact: Howard contributed a handful of big runs but was again out-shined by backfield-mate Tarik Cohen, who impressed with 121 yards from scrimmage. Despite assurances from coach Matt Nagy that Howard would play a bigger role in the passing game this year, he's mostly been a non-factor in that area, just as he's been throughout his career. Howard had a chance for a touchdown in the first half but coughed it up on the goal line, resulting in a turnover. With Cohen's workload on the rise, Howard is looking like a fringe RB2, which isn't what fantasy owners thought they were getting when they drafted him in August. We'll see how Chicago's backfield distribution shakes out next week against New England.
report: Jordan Howard logged 69 yards on 14 carries while failing to reel in his lone target Sunday in Chicago’s Week 6 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: He added nine yards on one catch. Howard continued to split carries with Tarik Cohen even when the game was close and struggled to find consistent success on the ground, but he helped out his fantasy backers with a two-yard touchdown in the second quarter. He appeared to have another score on the first drive of the second half, but the play was negated by an illegal formation penalty. He did surprise with a twisting catch on his only target, but Howard mostly took a backseat from that point on with the Bears trailing. He now has 14 or fewer touches in each of his last three games. Howard will be an RB3/FLEX option next week against the Jets.
report: Jordan Howard rushed 12 times for 39 yards and a touchdown in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: He added nine yards on one catch. Howard continued to split carries with Tarik Cohen even when the game was close and struggled to find consistent success on the ground, but he helped out his fantasy backers with a two-yard touchdown in the second quarter. He appeared to have another score on the first drive of the second half, but the play was negated by an illegal formation penalty. He did surprise with a twisting catch on his only target, but Howard mostly took a backseat from that point on with the Bears trailing. He now has 14 or fewer touches in each of his last three games. Howard will be an RB3/FLEX option next week against the Jets.
report: Jordan Howard rushed 12 times for 39 yards and a touchdown in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Tarik Cohen stole the show early, but Howard sealed the win for Chicago with a late fourth-quarter TD. Howard didn't have any highlights outside of his touchdown and wasn't involved in the pass game. He's been more touchdown dependent than usual this year, but Howard has double-digit carries in every game this season. Howard will be an RB2 for a Week 9 matchup against Buffalo.
report: Jordan Howard had 22 carries for 81 yards and a touchdown in Chicago's Week 8 win over the Jets.

impact: Fantasy owners were fortunate to come away with the scores -- one at the goal line and the other from 18 yards out -- because Howard would have been a major dud without them.  He didn't see a single target in the passing game in a matchup where the Bears barely even had the ball because their defense scored twice.  Howard did out-touch Tarik Cohen 14 to 7.  Nevertheless, Howard will remain a touchdown-dependent RB2 option when the Bears host the Lions next.
report: Jordan Howard rushed 14 times for 47 yards and two touchdowns in the Bears' Week 9 romp over Buffalo.

impact: Sunday spelled an end to Howard's three-game touchdown streak. Tarik Cohen out-touched Howard by a commanding 11-2 margin in the first half and was even featured on the goal line. Howard took on more work with Chicago looking to kill clock in the second half, but obviously he wasn't able to take advantage. The third-year back has been lousy as a ball-carrier recently, averaging an underwhelming 3.13 yards per carry over his last four games. He'll be a touchdown-or-bust RB2 when the Vikings come to town in Week 11.
report: Jordan Howard scrounged up 21 yards on 11 carries while securing his lone target for an 11-yard gain Sunday in Chicago’s Week 10 win over the Lions.

impact: It's a solid game against a tough Vikings run defense. Howard had more touches than Tarik Cohen (10), but they played close to the same amount of snaps. Howard's 18 carries were the most since Week 8. There haven't been many big games from Howard this year, with fewer than 50 rushing yards in four of the last seven weeks. He'll be an RB2 for Week 12 against Detroit.
report: Jordan Howard had 18 carries for 63 yards in Chicago's Week 11 win over the Vikings.

impact: Hopkins came into the week questionable due to various nicks and bruises, but he looked like his normal self in this one, working over an undermanned Colts secondary that didn't have any answers for the WR1.  Hopkins' score was of the five-yard variety on a perfect fade from Deshaun Watson.  Especially after Will Fuller left early in the second half with a hamstring injury, Hopkins and Keke Coutee were the targets on virtually every Watson pass.  The Cowboys are up next.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 10-of-12 targets for 169 yards and one touchdown in the Texans' 37-34, Week 4 win over the Colts.

impact: Hopkins was the only reliable part of the Texans' attack on Sunday. Even with Deshaun Watson struggling behind an overmatched offensive line, he comfortably won his battle with Tre'Davious White. He drew two holding penalties on the young corner in the first half, and he out-muscled him for his touchdown in the first quarter. He slowed down with the rest of the offense in the second half, but he did chip in a 24-yard catch after the break. Hopkins faces a tough matchup with the Jaguars next week, but he is a must-start option no matter the matchup.
report: DeAndre Hopkins hauled in 5-of-6 targets for 63 yards and a touchdown in the Texans' Week 6 win over the Bills.

impact: Hopkins scored an early touchdown, and that was about all the Texans needed to take down the Jags in a smooth-sailing 20-7 victory. Hopkins has eight or more targets in 7-of-7 games. A matchup-agnostic WR1, Hopkins can expect to tangle with Xavien Howard’s shadow coverage on Thursday Night Football next.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 3-of-8 targets for 50 yards and a touchdown in the Texans’ Week 7 win over the Jaguars.

impact: It was an easy night at the office for Hopkins and company. The superstar wideout was left completely uncovered on his 49-yard touchdown to begin the fourth quarter. He literally had time to stop and wait for the ball before taking it untouched to the end zone. Score No. 2 came later in the period against Xavien Howard. Hopkins got free and corralled a perfectly thrown two-yarder near the back line. Hopkins and Howard exchanged words during the week. Hopkins got the final word, though is worth noting that he lost a long reception to OPI. The dubious call negated a bonkers one-handed catch. Look up the replay. The Broncos are on deck for Week 9. If Will Fuller (knee) is sidelined, 10 targets will be Hopkins' bare minimum in Denver.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 6-of-7 targets for 82 yards and two touchdowns in the Texans' Week 8 win over the Dolphins.

impact: It was an easy night at the office for Hopkins and company. The superstar wideout was left completely uncovered on his 49-yard touchdown to begin the fourth quarter. He literally had time to stop and wait for the ball before taking it untouched to the end zone. Score No. 2 came later in the period against Xavien Howard. Hopkins got free and corralled a perfectly thrown two-yarder near the back line. Hopkins and Howard exchanged words during the week. Hopkins got the final word, though is worth noting that he lost a long reception to OPI. The dubious call negated a bonkers one-handed catch. Look up the replay. The Broncos are on deck for Week 9. If Will Fuller (knee) is sidelined, 10 targets will be Hopkins' bare minimum in Denver.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 6-of-7 targets for 82 yards and two touchdowns in the Texans' Week 8 win over the Dolphins.

impact: A 50% target share is unfathomable, but with Will Fuller (torn ACL) and Keke Coutee (hamstring) unavailable, Deshaun Watson foreseeably honed-in on Hopkins on half of his passing attempts. It's the third time this season Hopkins has seen at least 12 targets, and the sixth time he's recorded double-digit looks. No other receiver, including newcomer Demaryius Thomas, saw more than three targets on the day. Coutee will likely be healthy after the team's Week 10 bye, but if he misses further action, Hopkins' usage and apparently untapped ceiling are something to keep in mind. He's an elite matchup-proof WR1 regardless.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 10-of-12 targets for 105 yards and one touchdown in the Texans' Week 9 victory over the Broncos.

impact: The Texans completed only 16 passes as a team and Deshaun Watson threw for just 208 yards, so Hopkins' fantasy owners were lucky to come away with this productive a stat line.  Hopkins was shadowed by Josh Norman for most of the game.  He will get a softer Week 12 matchup on Monday Night Football against Titans perimeter CBs Adoree Jackson and Malcolm Butler.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 5-of-6 targets for 56 yards and a touchdown in the Texans' Week 11 win over the Redskins.

impact: There's no way to spin what was an extremely disappointing performance. Hogan's five targets were fourth on the team behind Rob Gronkowski, Phillip Dorsett and James White. Fantasy owners need to shake it off — Hogan is still the team's No. 1 receiver while Julian Edelman is sidelined — but a Week 2 bounce-back will be difficult against the Jaguars' elite secondary.
report: Chris Hogan caught 1-of-5 targets for 11 yards in the Patriots' Week 1 win over the Texans.

impact: Hogan's first score came on Jalen Ramsey in man-to-man coverage in the end zone. He got free as a diving Ramsey couldn't find him. TD2 came as Tom Brady got the Jags to bite on a short fake and hit Hogan over the middle of the field. Hogan did the rest of the work on the 29-yard grab. Hogan has just four catches through two games, but that's a number he should at least double in Week 3 against the Lions, especially if CB Darius Slay (concussion) is sidelined.
