report: James Conner rushed 19 times for 111 yards and two touchdowns in the Steelers' 28-21, Week 6 win over the Bengals.

impact: Conner started off slowly, notching just 33 yards on the ground with 12 yards on one catch in the first half. He then wore the Browns out in the second half, rushing for 14 times for 113 yards and both scores after the break with four catches for 54 yards after the break. He broke long runs of 30 and 22 yards, the latter a game-ending dagger for a touchdown that put the Steelers ahead 33-12. Conner now has four games with over 100-yards rushing and two touchdowns on the season. It remains to be seen when Le'Veon Bell actually returns to the team, but Conner is a set-and-forget RB1 option until that happens, even against a stout Ravens defense on the road in Week 9.
report: James Conner rushed 24 times for 146 yards and two touchdowns while catching 5-of-6 targets for 66 yards in Sunday's Week 8 win over the Browns.

impact: Conner, who spent the bulk of last season filling up Gatorade cups for workhorse Le'Veon Bell, has now gone over 100 yards rushing in four straight games. The knock on Conner has been that most of his damage this year has come against subpar defenses, but obviously that wasn't the case on Sunday. The former Pitt Panther had more yards from scrimmage on the Steelers' first two drives (57) than he did the entire game when he faced the Ravens at home in Week 4 (44 yards on 12 touches). His lone touchdown came on a seven-yard screen from Ben Roethlisberger with time winding down in the first quarter. That marked the first receiving score of his two-year career. With Bell nowhere to be found, Conner will maintain his upper-echelon RB1 status next week when the Steelers host Carolina on Thursday Night Football.
report: James Conner delivered 107 yards on 24 carries while adding seven catches for 56 yards and a touchdown on nine targets Sunday in Pittsburgh’s Week 9 win over the Ravens.

impact: Conner was announced as "questionable" early in the fourth quarter but was never going to return with the Steelers winning 52-14. His status is unclear. Conner was in and out of the medical tent all evening. The abbreviated night helped snap a string of four-straight 129-plus yard performances. In addition to his head injury, the big question for Conner's Week 11 will be the potential return of Le'Veon Bell. Even if Bell is back, we expect Conner to start against the Jaguars.
report: James Conner rushed 13 times for 65 yards and a touchdown in the Steelers' Week 10 win over the Panthers, adding an eight-yard reception before departing with a possible concussion.

impact: Conner was stifled by a stiff Jacksonville run defense, having just a long gain of nine yards on the ground. The Steelers were then scripted out of the run game chasing points in the second half. Conner added six catches, but they were all dump offs. He had a great opportunity to save his lackluster day on the final drive, but took his eyes of the ball and dropped a gift-wrapped 28-yard touchdown. Conner will look to get back on track in Week 12 at Denver.
report: James Conner rushed nine times for 25 yards while catching 6-of-9 targets for 24 yards in Sunday's Week 11 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Collins was breaking tackles — especially on his 24-yard catch-and-rumble in the third quarter — but coach John Harbaugh was addicted to giving Buck Allen touches. At one point in the broadcast, color commentator Troy Aikman matter of factly referred to Allen as the Ravens' goal-line back. Allen indeed converted from the one-yard line for a second quarter score. Collins failed on a one-yard attempt of his own just before the break. On a 3rd-and-1 in the fourth, Harbaugh dialed up a
report: Alex Collins rushed nine times for 35 yards in the Ravens' Week 2 loss to the Bengals, adding three catches for 55 additional yards.

impact: He added another six yards on three catches. Collins did lose some goal-line work to Javorius Allen, who scored two touchdowns including a short rushing score, but Collins saw his fair share of work near the goal line including a six-yard touchdown run in the first quarter. More importantly, he continues to look like a much better player than his backfield partner. Allen's role is a concern, but Collins will remain an RB2 next week against the Steelers.
report: Alex Collins rushed 18 times for 68 yards and a touchdown in the Ravens' Week 3 win over the Broncos.

impact: Collins was left uncovered in the flats for a three-yard touchdown after an early Steelers turnover.  He later fumbled at the goal-line and was benched for the rest of the first half. Ball security has been a concern for Collins going back to last year, and he's lost two fumbles through four weeks. Collins was already losing red-zone work to Javorius Allen and may continue to see his role decline there moving forward.
report: Alex Collins rushed 11 times for 42 yards and caught a three-yard touchdown in Baltimore's Week 4 win over the Steelers.

impact: Collins' first touch of the game was a 19-yard run, but he found little room or opportunity to do much else afterwards. Collins was out-touched by Javorius Allen 14-to-13 despite out-rushing Allen 12-to-8 and was lifted for Allen at the goal line once again. Collins has been shaky to start out the season, receiving 14 or fewer touches in four of the first five games of the season. He will be a lower-end RB2 option at best Week 6 when the Ravens head to Tennessee.
report: Alex Collins rushed 12 times for 59 yards while catching 1-of-4 targets for seven yards in Sunday's Week 5 loss to the Browns.

impact: Finally handed the utmost perfect game script on a silver platter, Collins notably out-carried teammate Javorius Allen 19-1 on the day. It only amounted to a measly 2.8 YPC, but Collins benefited by punching in one of his two carries inside the five-yard line for a score. His other touchdown came on a scamper from 13-yards out. His volume was still tremendously encouraging given that he played just 27-of-87 snaps last week, his lowest mark of the season. He'll again be a touchdown-dependent RB2 in what should be a faster paced game in Week 7 against the Saints.
report: Alex Collins rushed 19 times for 54 yards and two scores in the Ravens' Week 6 trouncing of the Titans.

impact: Collins out-touched Buck Allen 14-6, though he's now been held below 60 yards rushing in four-straight games. Collins has yet to have a 70-yard game on the ground. The Ravens' offensive line has been banged up of late. Collins will be an uninspiring RB2 for Week 8 against the Panthers.
report: Alex Collins rushed 11 times for 38 yards in the Ravens' Week 7 loss to the Saints, adding three receptions for 10 additional yards.

impact: Collins lucked into a goal-line touchdown after teammate Mark Andrews drew a pass interference flag at the one-yard line. Aside from the touchdown—his fourth in four games—Collins was mostly held in check, though obviously his chances were limited with Baltimore playing from behind in the second half. The 10 touches were Collins' fewest since Week 1 and his workload could be even more diluted once the Ravens finally incorporate trade acquisition Ty Montgomery into their offense. Collins and the struggling Ravens will take a three-game losing skid into next week's bye.
report: Alex Collins turned nine carries into 35 yards and a touchdown while adding a four-yard catch on his lone target Sunday in the Ravens’ Week 9 loss to Pittsburgh.

impact: Collins was completely ineffective outside of his seven-yard scoring run, and the Ravens determined UDFA Gus "The Bus" Edwards showed a hotter early-game hand.  Collins touched the ball just once after halftime.  Even ahead of a mouth-watering Week 12 date with Oakland, Collins will be very difficult to trust as a flex option.  Edwards appears to be the Ravens' new lead back.
report: Alex Collins rushed seven times for 18 yards and a touchdown in the Ravens' Week 11 win over the Bengals.

impact: After a massive opening week to the season, Cook fell back in line with his career output, but was still tied for second on the team in targets. Catching 13-of-16 targets to open the season, Cook will remain a fringe TE1 entering Week 3 versus the Dolphins.
report: Jared Cook caught 4-of-4 targets for 49 yards in Sunday's Week 2 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Cook appeared to find the end zone for his first touchdown of the season in the third quarter, but replay review revealed he was down at the one. Cook has been the Raiders' only consistent pass catcher, notching at least four receptions every week out. He is proving to be a legitimate TE1 in his age-31 season.
report: Jared Cook caught 5-of-6 targets for 31 yards in the Raiders' Week 3 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: Cook dropped at least two targets, but he atoned with twin seven-yard scores and several chunk gains between the twenties.  Through four games, Cook leads the Raiders in every meaningful receiving category and has easily been the team's most-consistent pass catcher.  Cook has solidified himself as an every-week fantasy TE1 and will remain so in Week 5 against the Chargers.
report: Jared Cook caught 8-of-13 targets for 110 yards and two touchdowns in the Raiders' Week 4 win over Cleveland.

impact: Cooks' six targets on the day were still encouraging despite the results. It was always plausible this day would come given his history in boom-bust performances, too. Having said that, Cook again dropped another potential touchdown inside the 10-yard line. Given the landscape (a.k.a. wasteland) of tight ends in 2018, Cook remains a weekly matchup-proof TE1.
report: Jared Cook caught 4-of-6 targets for 20 yards in the Raiders' Week 5 loss to the Chargers.

impact: We're going to get outcomes like this when Derek Carr has no time to throw and is unwilling to make difficult throws, and both scenarios played out against the Seahawks.  Cook will enter the Raiders' Week 7 bye coming off two slow games.  He remains a huge part of the passing offense as an every-week TE1.
report: Jared Cook caught 2-of-2 targets for 10 yards in the Raiders' Week 6 loss to Seattle.

impact: We're going to get outcomes like this when Derek Carr has no time to throw and is unwilling to make difficult throws, and both scenarios played out against the Seahawks.  Cook will enter the Raiders' Week 7 bye coming off two slow games.  He remains a huge part of the passing offense as an every-week TE1.
report: Jared Cook caught 2-of-2 targets for 10 yards in the Raiders' Week 6 loss to Seattle.

impact: Cook's touchdown, his third of the year, came on a 25-yard dart from Derek Carr in the second quarter. Carr shook off a defender on a play-fake to Martavis Bryant, leaving Cook one-on-one with linebacker Anthony Walker. Obviously Cook won that encounter. Cook has been Carr's go-to target all season and now that Amari Cooper has left the nest, he should see even more targets going forward. Look for him to keep the train rolling Thursday night in San Francisco.
report: Jared Cook came down with four catches for 74 yards and a touchdown on five targets Sunday in Oakland’s Week 8 loss to Indianapolis.

impact: Cook appeared on his way to a quiet day after failing to catch either of his two targets in the first half, one of which was a bad drop on third down, but he bounced back somewhat after halftime. His nine targets and 52 receiving yards led the team, and his 31-yard catch was the biggest play for the offense outside of Johnny Townsend's 42-yard run on a fake punt. Cook should continue to get targets as the No. 1 option in the passing game, but his upside is muted with the Raiders spiraling.
report: Jared Cook hauled in 4-of-9 targets for 52 yards in the Raiders' Week 10 loss to the Chargers.

impact: Cook capped off the Raiders' opening drive with a 23-yard score. He caught a slant-and-go and then put CB Jamar Taylor on skates. Cook was obviously invisible thereafter, which is disappointing considering the Raiders were down to the dregs of the roster at wide receiver. Cook will be a risk/reward TE1 for Week 12 against the Ravens.
report: Jared Cook caught 3-of-6 passes for 31 yards and a touchdown in the Raiders' Week 11 win over the Cardinals.

impact: He caught all four of his targets for 18 additional yards.  With Devonta Freeman (knee) out, Coleman got his 20 touches, while rookie RB Ito Smith chipped in with 55 yards on 10 touches.  Coleman's bug run went for 36 yards, and he also had a 19-yarder that was very close to going to the house for a long touchdown.  Coleman was unable to convert his run inside the 10-yard line for a score, getting it down to the one before Matt Ryan scored on a sneak the next play.  With Freeman expected to miss at least another game, Coleman will be an upside RB2 next week against New Orleans.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed 16 times for 107 yards in the Falcons' 31-24, Week 2 win over the Panthers.

impact: Starting for the second straight week, Coleman spent most of the afternoon running into brick walls, though he salvaged the day for fantasy owners with a late receiving touchdown. Coleman broke through for a 15-yard gain on his first touch of the second half but averaged a pathetic 1.29 yards on his other 14 carries. The 25-year-old also committed a costly mistake on the Falcons’ final drive, failing to pick up a blitz that resulted in a Matt Ryan incompletion on third down. He’ll look to redeem himself next week against Cincinnati.
report: Tevin Coleman netted just 33 yards on 15 carries while delivering two catches for 14 yards and a touchdown on three targets Sunday in the Falcons’ Week 3 loss to New Orleans.

impact: Coleman looked good when he got the touches in this game and appeared on the cusp of breaking a few long gains. Unfortunately, he ceded 10 touches to Ito Smith including what became a seven-yard touchdown on the opening drive. With Devonta Freeman looking likely to return next week, Coleman will return to the RB3/FLEX mix against the Steelers.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed 14 times for 51 yards and hauled in all three of his targets for 26 yards in the Falcons' Week 4 loss to the Bengals.

impact: Devonta Freeman started and won the touch battle, but Coleman played just one fewer snap. Ito Smith was also involved as the No. 3 back. Despite the disappointing day and the Falcons' increasingly crowded backfield, Coleman will have Week 6 FLEX appeal against the Bucs' horrific defense.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed seven times for 15 yards in the Falcons' Week 5 loss to the Steelers, adding two receptions for 15 additional yards.

impact: Coleman looked like he was going to disappoint fantasy players for most of this game. He failed to create any big plays on the ground, and he lost 11 carries and a touchdown to Ito Smith. Thankfully, he saved his fantasy day with a six-yard touchdown catch in the fourth quarter. Coleman remains a starter any time Freeman sits, but Smith's involvement means he will be more of an RB2 moving forward.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed 10 times for 35 yards and hauled in 1-of-2 targets for six yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 6 win over the Bucs.

impact: He added 32 yards through the air by catching both of his targets.  Coleman started the night off with a 14-yard run and ended it with a 30-yard touchdown run where he went untouched through the right side.  He lives off big plays and hasn't been making many of them this season.  But Coleman out-played Ito Smith by a wide margin, out-gaining him 82-45 on four more touches.  Coleman gets a bye and will remain an RB2 in Week 9 against the Redskins.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed 11 times for 50 yards and one touchdown in the Falcons' Week 7 win over the Giants.

impact: He added 32 yards through the air by catching both of his targets.  Coleman started the night off with a 14-yard run and ended it with a 30-yard touchdown run where he went untouched through the right side.  He lives off big plays and hasn't been making many of them this season.  But Coleman out-played Ito Smith by a wide margin, out-gaining him 82-45 on four more touches.  Coleman gets a bye and will remain an RB2 in Week 9 against the Redskins.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed 11 times for 50 yards and one touchdown in the Falcons' Week 7 win over the Giants.

impact: OC Steve Sarkisian made arrow and wheel routes to the perimeter a huge part of Atlanta's Week 9 plan, and Coleman exploited plus matchups against linebackers and safeties relentlessly while out-touching Ito Smith 18 to 11.  The Redskins came in playing elite run defense over the last month, yet the Falcons' offensive line won battles in the trenches all day.  Coleman will remain a volatile RB2 with big-play potential in Week 10 at Cleveland.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed 13 times for 88 yards and caught 5-of-7 targets for 68 yards and two touchdowns in the Falcons' Week 9 win over Washington.

impact: Four of Coleman's carries came inside the Browns' five-yard line, but he could not find the end zone. It was a disappointing afternoon one week after Coleman totaled 156 yards against the Redskins. Coleman has yet to have a 100-yard day on the ground and has not cleared 13 carries since September. With Ito Smith mixing in liberally, Coleman is a high-risk RB2 despite his big-play ability.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed 11 times for 44 yards in the Falcons' Week 10 loss to the Browns, adding three receptions for 19 additional yards.

impact: He ceded eight touches to Ito Smith, who did little with his.  Coleman is much better than Smith, but he can't shake loose as a true lead back, settling in as a 12-15 touches player, keeping him as a back-end RB2.  Coleman will get the Saints on Thanksgiving.  He had 47 yards against them Week 3.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed eight times for 58 yards and caught all three of his targets for 27 yards in the Falcons' Week 11 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: Cole got off to a great start with a 31-yard catch on the second play of the game, but he was mostly quiet as Blake Bortles struggled the rest of the way. He did lead the Jaguars with 54 yards, but Dede Westbrook paced the receivers with 6 targets. Cole will remain an upside WR4 play next week against the Patriots.
report: Keelan Cole hauled in 3-of-4 targets for 54 yards in the Jaguars' Week 1 win over the Giants.

impact: After a quiet Week 1, Cole delivered on his summer hype, giving him three 100-yard games over his past five regular season contests. The highlights were in the first quarter, where Cole made a one-handed, Odell Beckham-esque 22-yard catch on Eric Rowe down the sideline. He finished the job by dismantling Rowe for a 24-yard score three plays later. Cole is simply a born playmaker down the field. The Jags' receiver rotation will make him uneven in fantasy, but he's earned the right to be treated as an every-week WR3.
report: Keelan Cole caught 7-of-8 targets for 116 yards and a touchdown in the Jaguars' Week 2 win over the Patriots.

impact: Cole led the Jags in targets, but Blake Bortles' wild inaccuracies returned, and Jacksonville got nothing going in the downfield passing game.  Cole has an abundance of talent, but this offense is simply not worthy of trust for him to be viewed as anything more than a volatile WR3/flex option in Week 4 versus the Jets.
report: Keelan Cole caught 5-of-9 targets for 40 yards in the Jaguars' Week 3 loss to Tennessee.

impact: It was a quiet game for Cole with Dede Westbrook and Donte Moncrief both going over 100 yards. Cole made both of his catches in the first quarter and was a non-factor in the second half. He's now been held under 40 yards in back to back games. The Jagaurs spread it out offense is going to be dificult to predict on a week to week basis. Cole will just be a low-end WR3 for Week 5.
report: Keelan Cole caught 2-of-3 passes for 15 yards in Week 4 against the Jets.

impact: Cole played a big role in the Jaguars' only good drive of the game, hauling in a 32-yard pass to help set up a touchdown on the next play. He also drew a deep target at the end of the first half, but it was a non-descript game for Jacksonville's 1A receiver. He will be just a WR4 play next week in Dallas.
report: Keelan Cole hauled in 4-of-10 targets for 70 yards in the Jaguars' Week 5 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Three of his grabs came with Jacksonville down big in the second half. Cole was stripped by Jaylen Smith in the third quarter, resulting in a turnover. It's been a quiet stretch for the second-year wideout, who has topped 50 yards just once during his current four-game touchdown drought. Cole is just a bench stash at this point.
report: Keelan Cole collected four catches for 41 yards on five targets Sunday in the Jags’ Week 6 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: It was an inefficient day for Cole as the Jaguars benched Blake Bortles and turned to game-manager backup Cody Kessler for 30 second-half pass attempts. Even in a favorable matchup, Cole will be a low-floor WR4 option as the Jaguars head to London for Week 8 to face the Eagles.
report: Keelan Cole caught 2-of-7 targets for 21 yards in the Jaguars’ Week 7 loss to the Texans.

impact: It was an inefficient day for Cole as the Jaguars benched Blake Bortles and turned to game-manager backup Cody Kessler for 30 second-half pass attempts. Even in a favorable matchup, Cole will be a low-floor WR4 option as the Jaguars head to London for Week 8 to face the Eagles.
report: Keelan Cole caught 2-of-7 targets for 21 yards in the Jaguars’ Week 7 loss to the Texans.

impact: Cole appeared to be the receiver of choice early in this one, catching two of Blake Bortles’ six first-half completions. He fumbled after securing the second catch, however, setting the Eagles up for a touchdown just before the half. He was not heard from much after that mistake. Battling drops and fumbles, Cole could see his snap share shrink coming out of the bye. He is droppable in redraft formats.
report: Keelan Cole hauled in 2-of-3 targets for 18 yards in the Jaguars' Week 8 loss to the Eagles.

impact: The 19 touches were the most Clement has had in a game over his first two seasons, but he was out-gained by Wendell Smallwood 91-to-75 on the afternoon while Smallwood was the back who got the short yardage rushing opportunity. Clement's Week 4 fantasy status is largely dependent on the availability of Jay Ajayi and Darren Sproles Week 4 against the Titans.
report: Corey Clement rushed 16 times for 56 yards while catching 3-of-4 targets for 19 yards in Sunday's Week 3 win over the Colts.

impact: He finished second on the team in touches behind Wendell Smallwood’s 11, and Josh Adams mixed in for 4. Clement’s on-field play has been wildly inconsistent this year, and his usage isn’t much more bankable in a three-man backfield that could soon add Darren Sproles (hamstring) to the mix. Against the Jaguars in Week 8, Clement will be a low-end flex option.
report: Corey Clement rushed eight times for six yards and caught 2-of-2 targets for 16 yards in the Eagles’ Week 7 loss to the Panthers.

impact: He finished second on the team in touches behind Wendell Smallwood’s 11, and Josh Adams mixed in for 4. Clement’s on-field play has been wildly inconsistent this year, and his usage isn’t much more bankable in a three-man backfield that could soon add Darren Sproles (hamstring) to the mix. Against the Jaguars in Week 8, Clement will be a low-end flex option.
report: Corey Clement rushed eight times for six yards and caught 2-of-2 targets for 16 yards in the Eagles’ Week 7 loss to the Panthers.

impact: Clement struggled to get anything going last week, and he did not do any better in this game. He had a total of three yards on four touches in the first half, and he was limited to one carry in the second half. With Josh Adams looking good and taking on a bigger role, it would not be surprising to see Clement fall out of the rotation. He is not a must-hold in redraft formats.
report: Corey Clement rushed four times for six yards and caught one pass for negative-one yard in the Eagles' Week 8 win over the Jaguars.

impact: His only catch went for negative yards. It’s another nondescript game from Clement, who hasn’t had more than 30 total yards the last three weeks. Even with Darren Sproles not close to returning, Clement is just a low-volume third-down back.
report: Corey Clement rushed five times for 13 yards in Week 10 against the Cowboys.

impact: He was not targeted in the passing game and got out-touched by Carlos Hyde 22 to 3, but Chubb made his workload count with two monster touchdown runs from 63 and 41 yards out.  Plays like that are capable of earning Chubb more playing time going forward, although Chubb's to-date usage keeps him out of the flex-starter discussion. The Browns have stayed very committed to Hyde as their bellcow.  Chubb is a handcuff until further notice.
report: Nick Chubb rushed three times for 105 yards and two touchdowns in the Browns' Week 4 loss to the Raiders.

impact: After the Cleveland staff spent most of the week suggesting Chubb's role would expand after turning three carries into 105 yards a week ago, he remained an afterthought in the game plan. Chubb is only a bench stash as Carlos Hyde has dominated backfield touches in Cleveland.
report: Nick Chubb rushed three times for two yards in Sunday's Week 5 win over the Ravens.

impact: Chubb once again showed off his explosion with a 19-yard scamper which would have been longer had there not been a holding downfield, but once again the Browns failed to use him in the game. Chubb has now carried the ball three times or less in every game this season. He is only a bench stash at this point and needs an injury to have fantasy relevancy.
report: Nick Chubb rushed three times for 25 yards in Sunday's Week 6 loss to the Chargers.

impact: With the trade of Carlos Hyde on Friday, Chubb drew the start and out-touched Duke Johnson 18-to-5. Chubb saw two targets in the pass game, but neither one was catchable. After just 24 yards on eight carries in the first half, Chubb ran 10 times for 54 yards after the break. His touchdown was a 1-yard plunge after a pass interference in the end zone.  Chubb is now firmly on the radar as an RB2 option for fantasy next week against the Steelers, but he will still be a touchdown dependent option most weeks just as Hyde was.
report: Nick Chubb rushed 18 times for 80 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 7 loss to the Buccaneers.

impact: With the trade of Carlos Hyde on Friday, Chubb drew the start and out-touched Duke Johnson 18-to-5. Chubb saw two targets in the pass game, but neither one was catchable. After just 24 yards on eight carries in the first half, Chubb ran 10 times for 54 yards after the break. His touchdown was a 1-yard plunge after a pass interference in the end zone.  Chubb is now firmly on the radar as an RB2 option for fantasy next week against the Steelers, but he will still be a touchdown dependent option most weeks just as Hyde was.
report: Nick Chubb rushed 18 times for 80 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 7 loss to the Buccaneers.

impact: Chubb started the day well, rushing 10 times for 53 yards in the first half including a 20-yard jaunt on the first drive of the game. The second half was a much different story as the Pittsburgh defense clamped Chubb to 12 yards on eight carries. The two receptions were Chubb's first of the season. Chubb finds himself in a similar position that Carlos Hyde; he's going to need to find the end zone to overcome his low-reception totals and the Browns consistently trailing. Chubb will enter Week 9 as a RB2 option at home against the Chiefs.
report: Nick Chubb rushed 18 times for 65 yards while catching 2-of-3 targets for 10 yards in Sunday's Week 8 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Chubb ran hot in the first half while the Browns were in the game, rushing 14 times for 56 yards and a score in the first half. His long gain on the day was only 12 yards, but helped set up his own touchdown a 3-yard stop/start run where he picked out the correct hole. Chubb now has 18, 20 and 23 touches in his three games as the starting running back despite the Browns playing from behind in all three games. He still is partially a touchdown-dependent fantasy option since he has just three catches on the season, but Chubb's volume and big-play upside will keep him as a viable RB2 for the rest of the season. The Browns host the Falcons in Week 10.
report: Nick Chubb rushed 22 times for 85 yards and a touchdown while catching his lone target for five yards in Sunday's Week 9 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Chubb was already having a big game before he took a stretch zone handoff from the Browns' own eight-yard line midway through the third quarter. Chubb hit the hole, received some nice blocking from Antonio Callaway and then out-ran the Falcons' entire defense for a 92-yard score. Chubb has more than justified the Browns' decision to trade Carlos Hyde, averaging 102 yards rushing in four games since becoming starter. He is a big-play machine who can handle big workloads. Chubb will be an RB1 against the Bengals when the Browns come off bye in Week 12.
report: Nick Chubb rushed 20 times for 176 yards and a touchdown in the Browns' Week 10 win over the Falcons, adding three receptions for 33 additional yards and a second score.

impact: He had just two targets. There's not a ton of conclusion to draw in a game Buffalo managed just 100 yards of offense. Even with Josh Allen likely to start, Clay should be avoided for a Week 2 matchup with the Chargers.
report: Charles Clay was held without a catch in Buffalo's season opener.

impact: It's an improvement after Clay was held without a catch in the season opener. Clay was more involved with Josh Allen starting, but he's not on the TE2 radar.
report: Charles Clay caught 2-of-3 passes for 29 yards in Week 2 against the Chargers.

impact: Clay is averaging merely 2.6 targets through three games for the Bills. He was valuable last season if only for his high floor and consistent targets from Tyrod Taylor. With Josh Allen's tendency to spread the ball around, Clay can't be depended on. He should be dropped immediately.
report: Charles Clay caught 2-of-3 passes for 18 yards in the Bills' Week 3 win over the Vikings.

impact: That doubled Clay's season production, which is all you need to know about his fantasy value.
report: Charles Clay caught 4-of-6 targets for 40 yards in the Bills' Week 4 loss to the Packers.

impact: Battling injuries and his quarterback's ineffectiveness, Clay has been a total fantasy non-factor and will likely remain such in Week 6 at Houston.
report: Charles Clay caught his lone target for a 12-yard gain in Week 5.

impact: Clay came out of the gates "hot," catching all four of his passes in the first half. That was it for the low-upside tight end, who will remain just that next week against the Colts.
report: Charles Clay hauled in 4-of-5 targets for 20 yards in the Bills' Week 6 loss to the Texans.

impact: He also lost a fumble. Clay never had a chance in this one with Derek Anderson at QB. Even at a laughably thin fantasy position, Clay has made little noise this year, eclipsing 30 yards receiving in just one of seven games. He hasn't scored a touchdown since Week 3 of 2017. Needless to say, Clay belongs nowhere near a fantasy lineup right now.
report: Charles Clay corralled three-of-five targets for 14 yards Sunday in the Bills’ Week 7 loss to Indianapolis.

impact: He also lost a fumble. Clay never had a chance in this one with Derek Anderson at QB. Even at a laughably thin fantasy position, Clay has made little noise this year, eclipsing 30 yards receiving in just one of seven games. He hasn't scored a touchdown since Week 3 of 2017. Needless to say, Clay belongs nowhere near a fantasy lineup right now.
report: Charles Clay corralled three-of-five targets for 14 yards Sunday in the Bills’ Week 7 loss to Indianapolis.

impact: This was Cohen's best game of the season after he posted just 66 total yards on 14 touches through the opening two games. The downside is that Cohen is still just being used a spell-back and not a player the Bears are scheming as a large part of their offense. With Jordan Howard as a true workhorse, Cohen needs more consistent passing-game involvement to be considered a fantasy option moving forward.
report: Tarik Cohen rushed five times for 53 yards while catching all three of his targets for 15 yards in Sunday's Week 3 win over the Cardinals.

impact: This type of performance was always in Cohen's range of outcomes. What really stood out, though, was that Cohen out-touched Jordan Howard 20-11 and was involved early and often in the Bears' offensive game plan. Not only did he lead the club in targets, Cohen also led Chicago's backfield in carries, getting involved well before the offense erupted for a 38-3 lead heading into the half. It was admittedly a day where everything just went right for the Bears, led by Mitchell Trubisky's career-high six touchdown tosses. Everything seems to be clicking for Chicago heading into the team's Week 5 bye, and better days seem to be ahead for Cohen if kept involved. If you were thinking about dropping him, that's no longer an option.
report: Tarik Cohen rushed 13 times for 53 yards while corralling 7-of-8 targets for 121 yards and one touchdown in Sunday's Week 4 win over the Bucs.

impact: He saw two fewer touches than backfield-mate Jordan Howard (14-12) but out-gained him by over 50 yards. Cohen flashed his signature speed with a number of big plays including a 21-yard touchdown burst during the third quarter. He added a 50-yard catch-and-run later in the half and nearly scored a second touchdown, but it was called back on offensive pass interference. Cohen did hit a few rough patches, getting stuffed on a fourth-and-one opportunity and also losing a fumble in Bears territory late in the second half. After playing second fiddle early in the year, Cohen has pulled even with Howard in Chicago's backfield pecking order. Look for their timeshare to continue next week against New England.
report: Tarik Cohen contributed 31 yards and a touchdown on five carries while adding seven catches for 90 yards on nine targets Sunday in the Bears’ Week 6 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: Following a disappointing start to the season, Cohen has established himself as a big part of Chicago’s offense, and that continued in this one. Cohen finished the first half with just one fewer touch than Jordan Howard, although that total was boosted by two catches with less than 10 seconds left in the half, and dominated work after the break. He started strong in the second half, catching a six-yard touchdown on the opening drive, and he added six more catches to his total after halftime. He now has at least seven catches in each of his last three games. He will be a great PPR option and an RB3/FLEX in standard formats next week against the Jets.
report: Tarik Cohen rushed six times for 14 yards and hauled in 8-of-12 targets for 69 yards and a touchdown in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Following a disappointing start to the season, Cohen has established himself as a big part of Chicago’s offense, and that continued in this one. Cohen finished the first half with just one fewer touch than Jordan Howard, although that total was boosted by two catches with less than 10 seconds left in the half, and dominated work after the break. He started strong in the second half, catching a six-yard touchdown on the opening drive, and he added six more catches to his total after halftime. He now has at least seven catches in each of his last three games. He will be a great PPR option and an RB3/FLEX in standard formats next week against the Jets.
report: Tarik Cohen rushed six times for 14 yards and hauled in 8-of-12 targets for 69 yards and a touchdown in the Bears' Week 7 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Cohen went untouched on a screen for his touchdown in the first quarter. The Jets sold out on an all-out blitz, leaving Cohen wide open. He had a quiet second half, but it was another solid game for Cohen, who's went over 60 yards receiving in four straight games. Cohen is a strong PPR FLEX, but he's startable in all formats for Week 9 against Buffalo.
report: Tarik Cohen rushed five times for 40 yards and caught a 70-yard touchdown in Week 8 against the Jets.

impact: Cohen flopped in fantasy almost entirely due to game script, which wound up going much more in the favor of Jordan Howard as Buffalo could muster zero resistance offensively, while Chicago's defense scored twice.  Expect Cohen to bounce back quickly when the Bears host the Lions next.  Cohen is still leading the Bears in targets over their last five games (34).
report: Tarik Cohen rushed six times for five yards and caught 1-of-2 targets for eight yards in the Bears' Week 9 win at Buffalo.

impact: Cohen was featured early on, out-touching back-field mate Jordan Howard by a noticeable 11-2 margin during the first half. Obviously the 23-year-old didn't find much running room on Sunday (2.14 yards per carry) but he helped his fantasy cause nonetheless by punching in a goal-line touchdown. Cohen has cooled off some since his hot start, but he's still been a helpful fantasy presence by hitting pay-dirt in five of his last six games. He'll try to keep the touchdowns coming next week when the Bears host Minnesota on SNF.
report: Tarik Cohen tallied 15 yards and a touchdown on seven carries while snagging six-of-seven targets for an additional 29 yards Sunday in the Bears’ Week 10 win over Detroit.

impact: Cohen got the start with Chicago opening in a pass formation. This wasn't of his better games, finishing with 50 total yards and a late fourth-quarter fumble.  Cohen has been held under 30 yards receiving the last three weeks. He's a FLEX play against Detroit on Thanksgiving.
report: Tarik Cohen rushed seven times for 27 yards and caught 3-of-4 targets for 23 yards in Week 11 against the Vikings.

impact: Chark’s role has been growing in recent weeks, and that continued in this game. The rookie only caught one pass in the first half, but he came down with three catches on the Jaguars’ first two scoring drives after the break. He also got open in the end zone in the fourth quarter, but he could not come down with a pass which was thrown slightly behind him. With Keelan Cole struggling, Chark could start to see more work following the bye.
report: D.J. Chark hauled in 4-of-5 targets for 41 yards in the Jaguars' Week 8 loss to the Eagles.

impact: Even with Keelan Cole out of the picture, Chark was not able to make anything happen in the passing game. He did have a couple nice returns, but he is not a viable option in redraft formats right now. He remains a hold in Dynasty.
report: D.J. Chark did not catch either of his two targets Week 10 against the Colts.

impact: Chark led the team in targets on Sunday after failing to catch a pass in Week 10. The second-round pick this year has surpassed Keelan Cole on the depth chart, but is not a fantasy option on his own merit at this time.
report: D.J. Chark caught 2-of-5 targets for 15 yards in Sunday's Week 11 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Not a bad day at the office for Carson, who out-touched backfield-mate Rashaad Penny by an overwhelming 34-3 margin. Penny found himself in Pete Carroll’s doghouse after botching a handoff in the first half and Carson took full advantage of the opportunity, becoming the first Seahawk to rush for 100 yards in a regular season game since Thomas Rawls in Week 13 of 2016. The 24-year-old scored his first career rushing touchdown on a five-yard scamper early in the fourth quarter. Obviously, Carson wasn’t very efficient on Sunday—he averaged a mere 3.2 yards per carry—though the 24-year-old remains ahead of Penny in the Seahawks' backfield pecking order. He should be in play as a back-end RB2 next week against the Cardinals.
report: Chris Carson tallied 102 yards and a touchdown on 32 carries while also earning two catches for 22 yards on two targets Sunday in the Seahawks’ Week 3 win over Dallas.

impact: Carson started and operated as the lead back, but he lost key carries including a touchdown opportunity to Mike Davis. Even with the split, Carson rewarded his fantasy backers with 127 yards from scrimmage as he consistently gashed the Rams' defense for big gains on the ground. Carson has now topped 120 yards from scrimmage each of his last two games. Even with concerns about his workload, he will be a RB3 next week against the Raiders in London.
report: Chris Carson rushed 19 times for 116 yards and caught his only target for 11 yards in the Seahawks' Week 5 loss to the Rams.

impact: Carson was Seattle's backfield leader, but Mike Davis mixed in for seven touches, and Rashaad Penny even contributed 11 touches as the Seahawks nursed a comfortable lead for three-plus quarters.  Still, the possibility of a three-way RBBC will loom during Seattle's Week 7 bye.  Carson is an RB2 hold, albeit a shaky one.
report: Chris Carson rushed 14 times for 59 yards in Seattle's Week 6 victory.

impact: Carson's night got off to the worst possible start after he lost a fumble at the Seahawks' own 29-yard on the first play scrimmage. Thankfully for fantasy owners, coach Pete Carroll stuck with him and he delivered with another solid performance. Carson ceded "only" 14 combined touches to Rashaad Penny and Mike Davis. That would be a lot in a normal offense, but not the Seahawks' run-heavy attack. Operating as a legitimate RB2, Carson has 10 days to rest up for the Panthers in Week 12.
report: Chris Carson rushed 17 times for 83 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 11 win over the Packers.

impact: Carr was borderline flawless all afternoon, throwing just one incompletion in the first half and just three all game while averaging 8.3 yards per pass attempt. His lone touchdown was a 20-yard touchdown strike to Seth Roberts that put the Raiders up 19-7 in the 3rd quarter. Carr's Week 2 game was a big step forward after a lackluster open to the season, but will remain in the QB2 mix as Oakland heads to Miami in Week 3.
report: Derek Carr completed 29-of-32 passes for 288 yards and one touchdown in Sunday's Week 2 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Carr was awful in Week 1, solid in Week 2 and adequate today. His first interception was an end zone arm punt on a play where he had a miscommunication with Amari Cooper. His second was an inadvisable throw to a blanketed Martavis Bryant in the end zone late. Carr would have had a bigger fantasy day, but a Jared Cook touchdown came off the board when it was revealed he was down at the one-yard line. Cooper also committed an inexplicable drop. It has not been elite stuff from Carr, but he has put his brutal opener behind him. He's playing solid enough football. The Raiders just don't have much talent. The Browns will be a tough Week 4 opponent.
report: Derek Carr completed 27-of-39 passes for 345 yards, one touchdown and two interceptions in the Raiders' 28-20, Week 3 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: In a barnburning 45-42 shootout, Carr turned in his best game of the Jon Gruden era with red-zone scores to Amari Cooper, Jared Cook (two), and Jordy Nelson as Oakland shredded Cleveland's previously-stingy pass defense.  Carr has thrown for at least 288 yards in each of the Raiders' first four games, although this was his first big-time fantasy performance.  The Raiders go on the road to face the Chargers in Week 5.  In another potential shootout, Carr will be a solid two-quarterback league play with some low-end QB1 streamer appeal for fantasy leaguers in bye-week binds.
report: Derek Carr completed 35-of-58 passes for 437 yards, four touchdowns, and two interceptions in the Raiders' Week 4 overtime win over the Browns.

impact: Carr had less than 200 yards and one pick with 10 minutes remaining in the fourth quarter. A 47-yard completion to Martavis Bryant (3-91) and eventual touchdown toss to a wide-open Jordy Nelson (due to a complete breakdown in the Chargers' secondary) allowed Carr to turn an outright miserable day into one that was simply miserable. Carr has undoubtedly been poor in engineering coach Jon Gruden's otherwise efficient offense this season, but his weekly fantasy finishes are still that of a low-end QB2 with QB1 streaming appeal. The Raiders host the Seahawks in Week 6.
report: Derek Carr managed to complete 24-of-33 passes for 268 yards, one touchdown, and one interception in the Raiders' Week 5 loss to the Chargers.

impact: Carr took six sacks and lost two fumbles, and he suffered an apparent left-arm injury in the fourth quarter.  The Raiders opted to let A.J. McCarron finish out the game down 27-3.  Carr has had one productive fantasy performance out of six so far this year while repeatedly earning the ire of first-year coach Jon Gruden.  As the Raiders head into their Week 7 bye, Carr has long been droppable in 14- and even 16-team fantasy leagues.
report: Derek Carr completed 23-of-31 passes for 142 yards and rushed four times for 31 yards in the Raiders' Week 6 loss to Seattle.

impact: Carr rushed twice for no gain. It's been a turbulent week for Carr, who has been the subject of trade rumors and has also had the media question his toughness (not to mention the Raiders traded away his top receiver, Amari Cooper, on Monday). But none of those distractions had any bearing on Sunday's outcome as the 26-year-old went out and had arguably his best game of the season. He distributed touchdowns to three different receivers (Jared Cook, Brandon LaFell and Seth Roberts) while also adding his first career rushing touchdown on a quarterback sneak. Carr was so accurate that at one point he strung together 17 straight completions. He'll get another favorable draw Thursday at San Francisco.
report: Derek Carr completed 21-of-28 passes for 244 yards and three touchdowns while rushing for another touchdown Sunday in the Raiders’ Week 8 loss to Indianapolis.

impact: This is a new low for the 1-7 Oakland Raiders. Tom Cable's offensive line wasn't able to give Carr a lot of time, but Carr also kept stepping into pressure, which led to six sacks. After three quarters of bad football, Gruden stepped in and replaced Carr with backup A.J. McCarron, who also did nothing. The Raiders offense is built to be high completion, but the Raiders don't have the weaponry to pick up consistent yards after catch, so Carr is prone to some ugly games. The Raiders get extended time to develop a game plan for the Week 10 game against the Chargers.
report: Derek Carr completed 16-of-22 passes for 171 scoreless yards in the Raiders' Week 9 loss to the 49ers.

impact: As has been the case most of the season, Carr's stat line actually looks fine, but it is nothing but empty calories. The offense did not really move outside of a fake field goal in the first half, and their production in the second half came in garbage time. On one of those late drives, Carr threw the ball away on fourth-and-five. He also should have been intercepted on an ill-advised throw near the goal line. The quarterback has now thrown one or fewer touchdowns in seven of nine games. He is unlikely to do much better next week against the Cardinals, who will be a great streaming defense.
report: Derek Carr completed 24-of-37 passes for 243 yards in the Raiders' Week 10 loss to the Chargers.

impact: It can hardly be said that the Raiders played well, but the Cardinals were measurably worse, especially as they attempted to close things out late with a 21-20 lead. Carr nearly tossed a ghastly pick from his own end zone that would have essentially ended the game, but the Cards dropped the pass. Playing with a no-name receiver corps — even Brandon LaFell failed to finish the game after injuring his Achilles' — Carr took four sacks and was in frequent disagreement with coach Jon Gruden. The duo had to be separated by TE Lee Smith at one point. The low point was when Carr called back-to-back first half timeouts, drawing a penalty. But Carr made just enough throws for the Raiders to eke out an ugly road win. Playing with laughably few weapons and struggling in his own right, Carr will remain outside the QB2 range for next week's trip to Baltimore.
report: Derek Carr completed 19-of-31 passes for 192 yards and two touchdowns in the Raiders' 23-21, Week 11 win over the Cardinals.

impact: With Bilal Powell suffering a first-half neck injury, Cannon was elevated to Isaiah Crowell's change-of-pace.  Cannon's 73 yards led the team while his 69 yards receiving were also a team-best.  He did a bit of work on the final meaningless drive.  But if Powell remains out, Cannon could play a bigger role next week in Chicago.  He won't be a recommended fantasy play.
report: Jets rookie RB Trenton Cannon rushed two times for four yards and caught 4-of-5 targets for 69 yards in the Week 7 loss to the Vikings.

impact: With Bilal Powell suffering a first-half neck injury, Cannon was elevated to Isaiah Crowell's change-of-pace.  Cannon's 73 yards led the team while his 69 yards receiving were also a team-best.  He did a bit of work on the final meaningless drive.  But if Powell remains out, Cannon could play a bigger role next week in Chicago.  He won't be a recommended fantasy play.
report: Jets rookie RB Trenton Cannon rushed two times for four yards and caught 4-of-5 targets for 69 yards in the Week 7 loss to the Vikings.

impact: Cannon played the Bilal Powell role but wasn't a factor after totaling 73 yards in relief of Powell last week. Now Cannon faces the specter of Elijah McGuire returning this week. The Jets play Miami in Week 9.
report: Trenton Cannon rushed six times for 12 yards and caught 3-of-4 targets for 12 yards in Week 9 against Chicago.

impact: Callaway replaces Josh Gordon opposite Jarvis Landry. The Browns surprisingly gave Rashard Higgins more snaps than Callaway in Week 1, but with Gordon gone, Callaway will take over in two-wide sets. Callaway has a tough matchup against Marshon Lattimore this week, but his season outlook is on the rise.
report: Antonio Callaway is starting Week 2 against the Saints.

impact: Starting for Josh Gordon, Callaway failed to draw a target in the first half Sunday, but made his presence felt in the second half when he had catches of 18, 47 and 16 yards. The highlight of his day was reeling in a 47-yard vertical shot on 4th down to tie the game late in the 4th quarter. Callaway will provide uneven production moving forward as a secondary option in the Cleveland passing game, but his season is trending upwards with the Browns moving on from Josh Gordon and should be looked at in deeper leagues. The Browns will host the Jets on Thursday Night in Week 3.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 3-of-4 targets for 81 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 2 loss to the Saints.

impact: Callaway should have had a much bigger night, but Tyrod Taylor missed him on a gimme 75-yard touchdown in the first half. He also committed a few drops and quit on a route that might have resulted in a catch. It was a decidedly mixed effort from the Browns' new starting wideout, but his easy speed was on prominent display. With Baker Mayfield taking over at quarterback, Callaway could quickly push for WR3 status in fantasy leagues.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 4-of-10 targets for 20 yards in the Browns' Week 3 win over the Jets.

impact: It was an eventful day at the office for Callaway, who committed several drops and nearly lost a fumble on a fourth-quarter punt return, but Cleveland recovered.  Callaway nearly hit pay dirt on a 51-yard reception, only to be tackled down at the one-yard line before Carlos Hyde punched it in.  The good news is Callaway has commanded nine and ten targets in the last two games; the bad news is he has only 74 scoreless yards to show for it.  Callaway will remain an exciting-if-volatile WR4/flex option in Week 5 against the Ravens, who are getting back suspended top CB Jimmy Smith.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 3-of-9 targets for 54 yards in the Browns' Week 4 loss to the Raiders.

impact: After a dreadful performance a week ago, Callaway once again struggled on Sunday, dropping a crucial pass. Callaway entered the week dealing with a knee issue and the coaching staff mentioned dialing back his workload, which they did after he received nine and 11 targets over the two games prior. Callaway now has four or fewer receptions in every game this season and is still only a bench stash at this stage of the season. The Browns host the Chargers in Week 6.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 3-of-5 targets for 22 yards in Sunday's Week 5 win over the Ravens.

impact: Callaway once again struggled with missed opportunities as he lost a potential 45-yard touchdown in the sun in the first quarter and then had another straight drop on a potential long-gainer in the second half. He did secure a two-point conversion after the Browns' lone touchdown on the day. Callaway will continue to be force-fed targets as Cleveland has limited healthy bodies available at the wide receiver position, but he has caught just 8-of-24 targets over the past three weeks for 85 yards. Callaway will be an all-or-nothing option against a giving Tampa Bay defense in Week 7.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 2-of-10 targets for nine yards in Sunday's Week 6 loss to the Chargers.

impact: The two targets were the fewest that Callaway has received in a game since Week 1. He now has three or fewer receptions in every game on the season but one. Callaway has now reeled in just 9-of-23 targets for 99 yards over Baker Mayfield's four starts. Callaway is not a fantasy option heading into Week 8 against the Steelers.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 1-of-2 targets for 14 yards in Sunday's Week 7 loss to the Buccaneers.

impact: The two targets were the fewest that Callaway has received in a game since Week 1. He now has three or fewer receptions in every game on the season but one. Callaway has now reeled in just 9-of-23 targets for 99 yards over Baker Mayfield's four starts. Callaway is not a fantasy option heading into Week 8 against the Steelers.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 1-of-2 targets for 14 yards in Sunday's Week 7 loss to the Buccaneers.

impact: Callaway managed to find the end zone for the second time this season, catching a 1-yard touchdown in the third quarter as he battled through a defensive pass interference. Callaway has had an up-and-down rookie season, catching 21-of-48 targets for 236 yards and two scores through eight games. Callaway is not a fantasy option heading into Week 9 against the Chiefs.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 5-of-6 targets for 36 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 8 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Callaway was tied for fourth on the team in targets and his 51 yards were the most he's had in a game since Week 4 in Baker Mayfield's first career start. The bull of Callaway's yardage came on a 38-yard sideline grab when Mayfield found him in stride. Callaway has now caught 17-of-38 targets for 186 yards and one touchdown over his six starts with Mayfield.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 3-of-5 targets for 51 yards in Sunday's Week 9 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Callaway also made his presence felt with some down-field blocking on Nick Chubb's 92-yard touchdown. With the Browns expanding the target tree under new OC Freddie Kitchens, Callaway's WR5 value is even more tenuous.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 2-of-2 targets for 39 yards in the Browns' Week 10 win over the Falcons.

impact: This was Doyle's first appearance since Week 2 after missing five games with a hip injury. Doyle did almost all of his damage on one possession, catching four balls for 52 yards and a touchdown on a six-play drive during the fourth quarter. His 10-yard touchdown grab broke a 28-28 tie, putting Indy ahead for good with 5:28 remaining. There was some concern that Doyle would take a backseat to Eric Ebron, who dominated during his absence, but it looks like both players are going to have a role in the Colts' offense. The Colts are off next week but return against the Jaguars in Week 10.
report: Jack Doyle registered six catches for 70 yards and a touchdown on seven targets Sunday in the Colts’ Week 8 win over Oakland.

impact: The Jaguars could not keep track of Colts tight ends early in this game, and Doyle got loose for a 20-yard catch of his own on the first play of the second series. Unfortunately, he could not get in on the tight end scoring spree in the first half. He came close when he was tackled at the one-yard line in the second quarter, but Mo Alie-Cox got the score on the next play. Doyle should have better days moving forward, but Eric Ebron will be a touchdown threat all season.
report: Jack Doyle caught all three of his targets for 36 yards in the Colts' Week 10 win over the Jaguars.

impact: It was a disappointing day seeing as the Colts scored 38 points and Eric Ebron was not targeted. Doyle did have to watch as Mo Alie-Cox drew a red zone look. Doyle has the occasional mindmeld with Andrew Luck, but Luck is spreading the ball around as much as any quarterback in football. Doyle will nevertheless remain a TE1 for Week 12 against a Dolphins defense that's been routinely embarrassed by opposing seam stretchers.
report: Jack Doyle caught 4-of-4 targets for 43 yards in the Colts' Week 11 win over the Titans.

impact: The good news is Drake handled 17 touches to Frank Gore's 9.  The bad news is Gore showed a ton of burst and was highly effective in his role, averaging 6.8 yards per carry to Drake's 3.4.  Drake is a more talented back, but Gore is a coaches' pet who doesn't make mistakes.  Expect a similar split in Week 2 at the Jets.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed 14 times for 48 yards and caught 3-of-4 targets for 18 yards in Miami's Week 1 win over Tennessee.

impact: Drake's touchdown came from six yards out on a perfectly-blocked inside-zone run in the first half.  Leading by one score late in the fourth quarter, it was notable that Frank Gore operated as Miami's clock killer over Drake.  Drake out-touched Gore 15 to 10, but this remains a committee and will stay one so long as Gore maintains effectiveness.  Drake will be an RB2 in Week 3 versus Oakland.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed 11 times for 53 yards and a touchdown and caught 4-of-4 targets for 17 yards in the Dolphins' Week 2 win over the Jets.

impact: It was a nightmare fantasy day in a golden matchup, but the Dolphins ran an absurdly low 39 plays. It was just bizarre game flow. Drake did watch as Frank Gore got the "start," though he out-touched his veteran teammate 7-6. We've been expecting — hoping? — Drake to banish Gore to the bench but through three games it is not looking imminent. Drake might be best downgraded to the RB2/3 borderline until he has a breakout game or officially renders Gore a non-factor. The Patriots will present another opportunity for a strong fantasy day in Week 4.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed five times for three yards in the Dolphins' Week 3 win over the Raiders, adding two catches for seven additional yards.

impact: It was Drake's second-straight usage disaster. Like last week, the Dolphins struggled to possess the ball, running only 45 total plays. Even that number was goosed by a marathon garbage time drive. The Dolphins have now run just 84 players over their past two weeks, which is almost inconceivable. Incredibly, it was Frank Gore, not Drake, who was in as the Dolphins killed the clock with Brock Osweiler down 38-0. It's getting difficult to call Drake an RB2 with a straight face. The Bengals' struggling defense is on tap for Week 5.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed three times for three yards in the Dolphins' Week 4 loss to the Patriots, adding a 13-yard reception.

impact: Drake was the only thing working in Miami's offense. He led the Dolphins in receiving in a game Ryan Tannehill threw for 185 yards. Drake didn't do much on the ground -- he was gifted a 25-yard run against prevent defense on the final play -- but it's a solid rebound after getting only four touches last week. Drake will be an RB3/FLEX in Week 6 against Chicago.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed six times for 46 yards and caught 7-of-11 targets for 69 yards and a touchdown in Miami's Week 5 loss to the Bengals.

impact: He out-touched Frank Gore (barely) but was significantly out-gained by the veteran. Drake was near tears after losing a goal-line fumble in overtime but he redeemed himself later by gaining 22 yards on the Dolphins' game-winning drive. This marked Drake's largest workload of the season both in terms of carries and total touches. He'll look to build off Sunday's performance next week against the Lions.
report: Kenyan Drake totaled 57 yards on 13 carries while adding four catches for 21 yards on six targets Sunday in Miami’s Week 6 win over the Bears.

impact: 62 percent of Drake's yardage came on his 54-yard touchdown in the third quarter. Drake exploded through the hole and was not touched until he shed some tackles near the goal line. Although he got out-touched 11-10 by Frank Gore, Drake out-gained his backfield mate 87-33. Everyone knows Drake is the more explosive player, but Gore isn't going anywhere. Drake will remain a risk/reward FLEX for Week 8's Thursday night tilt with the Texans.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed six times for 72 yards and a touchdown in the Dolphins' Week 7 loss to the Lions, adding four receptions for 15 additional yards.

impact: Drake’s frustrating usage continued in this game. He did not see his first carry until the second quarter, at which point Frank Gore already had eight attempts, and he did not register a carry in the second half. Meanwhile, Frank Gore finished with just 53 yards on 20 carries. Drake did do good work in the passing game including a fourth-down conversion in the second quarter, but he was targeted just once in the second half. Drake could certainly bounce back next week in Green Bay, but Miami's offensive ineptitude and insistence on using Gore will keep him a risky fantasy option.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed three times for nine yards and caught 4-of-6 targets for 26 yards in the Dolphins' Week 9 win over the Jets.

impact: Drake exited early with a shoulder injury, but had only received four touches to Gore's 10 to that point. It obviously doesn't make sense for the Dolphins to keep using Gore on early downs over the younger and more athletic Drake, but that's clearly coach Adam Gase's intention moving forward. Drake isn't anything more than a hold-your-nose FLEX unless Gore misses time.
report: Kenyan Drake received eight carries for 27 yards, additionally hauling in two catches for 11 yards in the Dolphins' Week 10 loss to the Packers.

impact: He was essentially invisible on Sunday as the third-year wideout was out-targeted by teammates Chris Thompson, Paul Richardson, Jordan Reed and Jamison Crowder. Doctson definitely has rebound potential next week against a sluggish Indy secondary, but at this point, it’s hard to trust the former first-round pick as anything more than a last-ditch WR4/5.
report: Josh Doctson totaled just one catch for 11 yards on three targets Sunday in Washington’s Week 1 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Doctson committed a head-scratching drop in the first quarter but redeemed himself somewhat by beating Pierre Desir for a 14-yard grab down the sideline later in the afternoon. He almost came down with a touchdown about midway through the third quarter, but couldn’t quite pull it in. Doctson’s Week 2 wasn’t anything to write home about, though at least he saw seven targets, good for third-most on the team behind only Chris Thompson (13) and Jordan Reed (eight). The 2016 first-rounder gets the Packers at home in Week 3.
report: Josh Doctson nabbed four-of-seven targets for 37 yards Sunday in the Redskins’ Week 2 loss to Indianapolis.

impact: Doctson's only production came on two first quarter DPIs totaling 15 yards. Doctson has been an every-down player this season but predictably has zero chemistry with Alex Smith. He's caught five balls for 48 yards in three games. You can safely cut bait in re-draft leagues if you haven't already.
report: Josh Doctson was held without a catch on three targets in the Redskins' Week 3 win over the Packers.

impact: Doctson was playing through a questionable tag for a heel injury. The first-round bust has 68 yards this season.
report: Josh Doctson caught 3-of-6 targets for 20 yards in the Redskins' Week 6 win over the Panthers.

impact: His 42 yards were a season-high, but it doesn't make him any more fantasy relevant than he was prior to kick-off. Doctson is a candidate to fade away completely once Jamison Crowder and Paul Richardson return.
report: Josh Doctson hauled in 3-of-6 targets for 42 yards in Washington's Week 7 victory over the Cowboys.

impact: His 42 yards were a season-high, but it doesn't make him any more fantasy relevant than he was prior to kick-off. Doctson is a candidate to fade away completely once Jamison Crowder and Paul Richardson return.
report: Josh Doctson hauled in 3-of-6 targets for 42 yards in Washington's Week 7 victory over the Cowboys.

impact: The five catches were Doctson's single-game career high.  He still does not have a touchdown on the season.  Doctson will be a WR4/5 in Week 9 vs. Atlanta.
report: Josh Doctson caught 5-of-5 targets for 49 yards in the Redskins' Week 9 win over the Giants.

impact: Doctson opened the game with back-to-back drops, then beat Falcons rookie RCB Isaiah Oliver for a short touchdown on a fade route.  Dating back to last season, Doctson has been held below 50 yards in 12 of his last 13 games.  Doctson will be a touchdown-dependent WR4/flex option in Week 10 at Tampa Bay.
report: Josh Doctson caught 3-of-6 targets for 31 yards and a touchdown in the Redskins' Week 9 loss to the Falcons.

impact: He has a touchdown in back-to-back games, even if the volume isn't there.  Doctson's short score in the red zone was the only touchdown of this game.  He'll be a WR4 next week when the Redskins host the Texans.
report: Josh Doctson caught all four of his targets for 46 yards and one touchdown in the Redskins' Week 10 win over the Bucs.

impact: Doctson hasn't gotten to the 50-yard plateau in a single game all season, so he has only been relevant whenever he has caught touchdowns.  He caught a touchdown in Weeks 9 and 10, but otherwise has gone scoreless in eight of Washington's ten games.  With popgun-armed Colt McCoy at quarterback, Doctson's fantasy outlook will stay the same on Thanksgiving against the Cowboys.
report: Josh Doctson caught 3-of-7 targets for 32 yards in Washington's Week 11 loss to Houston.

impact: We will give you a second to look him up. A fourth-round rookie, Dissly was expected to be more of a blocker in the NFL, but he opened the scoring with a 15-yard touchdown on play action and bounced off several defenders on a 66-yard catch-and-run to end the first quarter. He did not do much damage after that, and it is likely this is easily his biggest game of the season. Still, he is worth a look in deeper TE premium leagues with Ed Dickson out at least five more weeks.
report: Will Dissly hauled in 3-of-5 targets for 105 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 1 loss to the Broncos.

impact: The rookie has predictably come back to Earth, managing a mere four catches for 46 yards in the two games since his breakout Week 1. Even against the lowly Cardinals, Dissly makes for a poor streamer in Week 4.
report: Will Dissly secured one-of-three targets for four yards Sunday in the Seahawks’ Week 3 victory over Dallas.

impact: Dissly's rookie season comes to an end catching 8-of-14 targets for 156 yards and two touchdowns in just three-plus game's worth of action. Nick Vannett will take over as the lead tight end for the Seahawks for the remainder of the season.
report: Seahawks TE Will Dissly suffered a torn patella tendon in Sunday's Week 4 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Diggs beat Richard Sherman for a nice gain on his first catch of the day and then bested Ahkello Witherspoon for a 22-yard touchdown on a perfectly-placed ball by Kirk Cousins down the left sideline.  It was put only where Diggs could catch it.  Diggs' day was pretty quiet after the early second-quarter score.  Diggs will be on the WR1/2 borderline next week in Green Bay.
report: Stefon Diggs caught 3-of-6 targets for 43 yards and one touchdown in the Vikings' Week 1 win over the 49ers.

impact: Diggs already was having a fine fantasy day heading into the fourth quarter after converting a well-designed play at the goal line into his second touchdown of the season, but he did not settle for fine. With the Vikings trailing in the fourth, Diggs got loose down the field, and Kirk Cousins hit him with a beautiful pass for a 75-yard touchdown. He also absolutely worked the corner to get wide open on the game-tying two-point conversion late in the fourth quarter, and he added three more catches in overtime. Up to three scores on 19 targets through two games, Diggs will be a locked-in WR1 next week against the Bills.
report: Stefon Diggs hauled in 9-of-13 targets for 128 yards and two touchdowns in the Vikings' Week 2 tie with the Packers.

impact: Unlike teammates Adam Thielen (14-105) and Kyle Rudolph (5-48-1), Diggs was unable to benefit from the Vikings' second-half blitzkrieg following their 27-0 first half deficit. He's seen 29 targets through three games, highlighted by his Week 2 overtime performance (9-128-2) against the Packers. Kirk Cousins was unable to keep his eyes downfield as the Bills' defensive line completely surprised and crushed Minnesota's pass protection throughout the afternoon. There are better days ahead for Diggs, including more top-ten scoring weeks, as long as he stays healthy.
report: Stefon Diggs caught 4-of-10 targets for 17 yards in the Vikings' Week 3 loss to the Bills.

impact: The 10-catch game was Diggs' second straight, while he's now drawn 10 targets in four straight games after a disappointing Week 1. He's cleared 90 yards in 3-of-5 contests. It has been Adam Thielen making the splash plays in the Vikings' receiver corps thus far, but it is only a matter of time before Diggs has a true blow-up game. He has stayed healthy and is seeing the requisite volume. The Vikings host the bottom-three Cardinals in Week 6.
report: Stefon Diggs caught 10-of-11 targets for 91 yards in the Vikings' Week 5 win over the Eagles, adding two carries for 25 additional yards.

impact: Diggs took a backseat to Adam Thielen, who accounted for over half of Kirk Cousins' yards. The five targets were the lowest he's seen all year. Diggs should rebound in a matchup with the Jets in Week 7.
report: Stefon Diggs caught 3-of-5 passes for 33 yards in Week 6 against the Cardinals.

impact: Adam Thielen hung a 9-110-1 day up on 10 targets while Diggs struggled in Morris Claiborne's coverage much of the afternoon.  Diggs was getting targets close to the line of scrimmage and had trouble getting anything after the catch.  The 14 targets were his second-most of the season.  Diggs will look to get back on track next week in a home game against the Saints.  The last time he saw them, in the playoffs, Diggs became a legend with the Minnesota Miracle.
report: Stefon Diggs caught 8-of-14 targets for 33 yards in the Vikings' Week 7 win over the Jets.

impact: Dickson was making his 2018 debut. Dickson memorably went 5/175 in Detroit as a member of the Panthers last season. This wasn't as dramatic, but the Lions seemed to once again forget he existed. Dickson will catch some passes and score touchdowns, but with Nick Vannett still in the picture, Dickson is merely a last-gasp TE2.
report: Ed Dickson caught 2-of-2 targets for 52 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 8 win over the Lions.

impact: The score was Davis' first of the season. He was left uncovered on a 22-yarder. Davis will pop up for the occasional big play but won't see enough volume for fantasy relevance in the Redskins' Alex Smith-led offense.
report: Vernon Davis caught 3-of-3 targets for 48 yards and a touchdown in the Redskins' Week 6 win over the Panthers.

impact: Davis dominated Sunday's game for short stretches and significantly outproduced Jordan Reed (34 yards) on the same number of targets.  Davis' week-to-week usage has been far less stable, however; Davis had one catch combined over Washington's previous two games.  Next Sunday's cupcake matchup against Tampa Bay does put Davis onto the streamer radar for Week 10.
report: Vernon Davis caught 5-of-6 targets for 62 yards in Washington's Week 9 loss to the Falcons.

impact: The two teams combined for 19 points.  Davis should have caught a 59-yard touchdown on his target, but Alex Smith badly missed him running wide open down the field.  He could have walked into the end zone.
report: Vernon Davis failed to catch his lone target in the Week 10 win over the Bucs.

impact: Even with the Packers' injury issues at receiver, third-year pro Davis should mostly contribute as a return man on special teams. He is not worth a flier in fantasy leagues.
report: Packers activated WR Trevor Davis (hamstring) from injured reserve.

impact: Drawing the start for the injured Chris Carson, Davis dominated the Seattle backfield on Sunday, handling 25-of-34 backfield touches. Davis gave Seattle the lead with a 20-yard touchdown in the 1st quarter and then scored their second and final touchdown on a 1-yard plunge in the 3rd quarter. Davis' fantasy viability will be contingent on the availability of Carson in Week against the Rams.
report: Mike Davis rushed 21 times for 101 yards and two touchdowns while catching four passes for 23 yards in Sunday's Week 4 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Davis ceded the starting job and many of the early carries to Chris Carson, but his role in the offense grew as the game went along. Most importantly, he received the most valuable carry of the afternoon. After Carson drove the offense down the field with some big runs, Davis took over, converted a third-and-two, and then scored from six yards out on the next play. Davis looks like he is the No. 2 option in the backfield -- Carson ended with 20 touches to 14 for Davis -- but the Seahawks' running game has been good enough to support multiple fantasy players the last several weeks. His workload could prove shaky, but Davis will be worth a look in FLEX spots next week against the Raiders in London.
report: Mike Davis rushed 12 times for 68 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 5 loss to the Rams.

impact: It was surprising to see Davis handle only seven touches while Rashaad Penny came back to life for 11, although the blowout nature of the game skewed usage a bit, and it was an opportunity for the Seahawks' coaching staff to give Penny more chances.  Davis is worth rostering as an RB4/5, but he won't become a consistent flex option barring injury to Carson and/or Penny.
report: Mike Davis rushed six times for 21 yards and caught 1-of-3 targets for five yards in Seattle's Week 6 London win over Oakland.

impact: It was surprising to see Davis handle only seven touches while Rashaad Penny came back to life for 11, although the blowout nature of the game skewed usage a bit, and it was an opportunity for the Seahawks' coaching staff to give Penny more chances.  Davis is worth rostering as an RB4/5, but he won't become a consistent flex option barring injury to Carson and/or Penny.
report: Mike Davis rushed six times for 21 yards and caught 1-of-3 targets for five yards in Seattle's Week 6 London win over Oakland.

impact: Davis re-established himself as the Seahawks' clear No. 2 back on an afternoon where Rashaad Penny did not touch the ball on offense. He still got out-touched 27-11 by Chris Carson. Davis is seeing a lot of work for a backup running back, but it's still not enough for standalone FLEX value.
report: Mike Davis rushed 10 times for 33 yards in the Seahawks' Week 8 win over the Lions, adding a two-yard reception.

impact: Davis took over as lead back after a thigh issue knocked out Chris Carson in the second quarter. It was all Davis after Carson went down, as he out-touched Rashaad Penny 22-7 on the day. The Seahawks stayed with the run even as they were playing from behind. Davis will need that to remain the case for Week 10 if Carson remains sidelined, as negative game script will be a distinct possibility against the Rams.
report: Mike Davis rushed 15 times for 62 yards in the Seahawks' Week 9 loss to the Chargers, adding seven receptions for 45 additional yards.

impact: Davis got the start in Chris Carson's absence, ripping a 12-yard gain on the Seahawks' first play from scrimmage. He quickly gave way to a committee with Rashaad Penny, however, and the rookie back stole the show with explosive running. Davis was out-carried 12-11, though he narrowly won the touch battle 15-12. If Carson can't get cleared to face the Packers for Thursday Night Football, Davis will be an uncertain FLEX option with Penny showing so well in Los Angeles.
report: Mike Davis rushed 11 times for 58 yards in the Seahawks' Week 10 loss to the Rams, adding four receptions for 22 additional yards and a touchdown.

impact: Playing primarily third downs, Davis' six touches were third in the Seahawks' backfield behind Chris Carson and Rashaad Penny. Carson returned from his thigh/hip injuries to operate as the clear lead back, with Penny offering an explosive change of pace. Davis has shown well when give the opportunity this season, but he can't be trusted as a FLEX option when both Carson and Penny are healthy.
report: Mike Davis rushed four times for 26 yards in the Seahawks' Week 11 win over the Packers, adding two receptions for 24 additional yards.

impact: Darnold, the youngest starting quarterback in the Super Bowl era, started off about as miserably as one could, having his first pass of the game picked off and returned for a touchdown by S Quandre Diggs.  But the rookie had nowhere to go but up from that point, and up he went.  Darnold showed the poise of a 10-year veteran and bounced back with a 21-yard touchdown to Quincy Enunwa and a perfect deep ball to Robby Anderson for another score from 41 yards out.  Darnold and Enunwa had a real connection, with Enunwa seeing a team-high 10 targets.  (The next closes Jet had three.)  Darnold should pick up right where he left off at home in Week 2 against Miami.
report: Making his NFL debut, Sam Darnold completed 16-of-21 passes for 198 yards, two touchdowns, and one interception in the Jets' 48-17, Week 1 win over the Lions.

impact: Darnold averaged over eight yards per attempt for the second straight week, but his two picks were costly in a one-score game.  The second wasn't necessarily Darnold's fault; Terrelle Pryor appeared to cut off his route in the back of the end zone, allowing Xavien Howard to catch it.  Darnold also missed a would-be game-changing play when he overthrew wide-open Quincy Enunwa in the back of the end zone in the second half.  Darnold will be a QB2 when the Jets visit Cleveland on Thursday Night Football in Week 3.
report: Sam Darnold completed 25-of-41 passes for 334 yards, one touchdown, and two interceptions in the Jets' Week 2 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: Whereas Baker Mayfield stole the show, Darnold stunk up the joint. He might as well have had "rookie" tattooed on his forehead. For their part, the Jets were terrified of Darnold making a mistake, calling a horizontal passing offense. It resulted in some nice catch-and-runs for Quincy Enunwa but severely capped the Jets' point ceiling for the evening.
