Drew Brees is averaging just 30 attempts in two games since Mark Ingram's return, and the Saints are headed on the road to take on the Vikings' tough defense in Week 8. It could be a minute before Smith becomes a legitimate WR4.
report: Tre'Quan Smith caught 3-of-6 targets for 44 yards in the Saints' Week 7 win over the Ravens.

impact: It was another quiet game for Smith after getting held to 44 yards last week. Smith continued to outsnap Cameron Meredith, but there wasn't much volume for him in a game Drew Brees threw for only 120 yards. There’s still a lot to like with Smith’s ROS outlook. He’s in the WR4 conversation for a potential Week 9 shootout with the Rams.
report: Tre'Quan Smith caught 3-of-4 targets for 18 yards in Week 8 against the Vikings.

impact: Smith has disappointed a bit following Ted Ginn’s season-ending injury, and he did not have the break out many were hoping to see in this one. That said, he did manage a good fantasy day with his two catches. The first was a nice back-shoulder grab in the first quarter which went for 19 yards, and he got open at the goal line for a four-yard score in the second. He was targeted down the left sideline in the fourth quarter, but he could not come up with a slightly overthrown pass. Next week’s game in Cincinnati could be another shootout, but Smith has not seen enough targets to be considered anything but a risky FLEX.
report: Tre'Quan Smith caught 2-of-3 targets for 23 yards and a touchdown in the Saints' Week 9 win over the Rams.

impact: Coming off a zero target game against the Bengals, Smith exploded in this matchup. He was not able to come up with an end-zone target in the first quarter, but he corralled three quick catches on the next drive and just kept building from there. He got the two-minute drive started with a 22-yard catch, and he capped that drive with a gutsy 15-yard touchdown in which he absorbed a big hit. He kept things going after the break, working back to the ball on an 18-yard grab on the opening drive of the third quarter and closing out the period with a spectacular diving catch for 38 yards. Smith could not build on his last breakout, but he will have a better chance this time around with the Falcons up next. He will be an upside WR3 on Thanksgiving.
report: Tre'Quan Smith hauled in 10-of-13 targets for 157 yards and a touchdown in the Saints' Week 11 win over the Eagles.

impact: Smith-Schuster won in the slot often when faced off against Briean Boddy-Calhoun with the highlight of his day being a 67-yard catch and run that set up a Steelers touchdown in the 3rd quarter. Building off an impressive rookie season, Smith-Schuster will be a starting option next week at home versus the Chiefs.
report: Steelers WR JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 5-of-8 targets for 119 yards in Sunday's Week 1 game versus the Browns.

impact: With Antonio Brown gutting out a calf injury, Smith-Schuster set new career highs in both targets and catches. He benefitted from the Steelers spending literally the entire game in comeback mode. Smith-Schuster's touchdown was a two-yarder where he displayed ridiculously strong hands while getting tackled in tight coverage. He drew another end zone target later in the game but could not hook up with Ben Roethlisberger. The Steelers' No. 2 wideout is now sitting at 18/240/1 through two games. He's flirting with every-week WR1 value.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 13-of-19 targets for 121 yards and a touchdown in the Steelers' Week 2 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: With Ben Roethlisberger (successfully) fixated on getting Antonio Brown going, Smith-Schuster had his quietest game of the season. Thankfully for fantasy owners, it included a touchdown. With just eight catches over his past two games, Smith-Schuster will look to get cooking again in Week 6 against the Bengals.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 4-of-4 targets for 34 yards and a touchdown in the Steelers' Week 5 win over the Falcons.

impact: His 10 targets led the team.  JuJu made an incredible catch over the top of CB Darqueze Dennard at the goal line and was ruled down at the one, setting up a second one-yard touchdown for James Conner.  This was Smith-Schuster's fourth 100-yard game of the season as the Steelers head into their bye before hosting the Browns in Week 8.  JuJu went 5-119 in Week 1 vs. Cleveland.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 7-of-10 targets for 111 yards in the Steelers' Week 6 win over the Bengals.

impact: His 10 targets led the team.  JuJu made an incredible catch over the top of CB Darqueze Dennard at the goal line and was ruled down at the one, setting up a second one-yard touchdown for James Conner.  This was Smith-Schuster's fourth 100-yard game of the season as the Steelers head into their bye before hosting the Browns in Week 8.  JuJu went 5-119 in Week 1 vs. Cleveland.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 7-of-10 targets for 111 yards in the Steelers' Week 6 win over the Bengals.

impact: The 33 yards were a season-low for Smith-Schuster. He only received one target in the second half as the Steelers put the game away as he now has games of 34 and 33 yards in two of his past three games in Pittsburgh blowout wins. Despite the down day, Smith-Schuster will be a WR2 option in Week 9 on the road against the Ravens.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 4-of-6 targets for 33 yards in Sunday's Week 8 win over the Browns.

impact: On a day where the Ravens sold out to stop Antonio Brown, JuJu made a number of clutch catches. His highlights included a second-quarter, fourth-down conversion and a timely seven-yard catch that kept the clock running late in the fourth quarter. Smith-Schuster did have one bad drop, taking his eye off the ball before he had possession. JuJu was checked for a concussion in the third quarter after taking a big hit from safety Eric Weddle but only missed a couple plays. The second-year USC product owns an impressive 53-672-2 receiving line at the season's halfway mark. JuJu and the surging Steelers will take a four-game winning streak into Thursday night's battle with Carolina.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster tallied seven catches for 78 yards on nine targets Sunday in the Steelers’ Week 9 win over Baltimore.

impact: Smith-Schuster scored a 75-yard touchdown on the Steelers' first play from scrimmage. James Bradberry got confused in coverage and Smith-Schuster exploded down the left sideline. He didn't do much thereafter as Ben Roethlisberger spread the ball around on a night where he posted a perfect quarterback rating, but the damage was already done. The sledding will be tougher in Week 11 against the Jaguars.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 3-of-5 targets for 90 yards and a touchdown in the Steelers' Week 10 win over the Panthers, adding a 13-yard reception.

impact: Like the entire Steeler offense, Smith-Schuster was limited in the first half, catching just two passes for 16 yards before the break. His biggest play of the game was a 35-yard catch over A.J. Bouye with 1:39 left to get the Steelers into position for the game-winning touchdown. Smith-Schuster finally turns just 22-years old this Thursday, having amassed the most receptions (122) and receiving yards (1,783) before turning 22-years old in NFL history. The Steelers head to Denver in Week 12.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster caught 8-of-10 targets for 104 yards in Sunday's Week 11 win over the Jaguars.

impact: With Devonta Freeman (knee) out, Smith was part of the game plan behind Tevin Coleman.  Coleman essentially took Freeman's role, with Smith elevated into Coleman's normal one.  Smith's best series was one where he piled up 31 yards on back-to-back carries to set up a Matt Ryan one-yard touchdown run.  Smith added one catch for eight yards on his lone target.  He'll play the same role next week against the Saints with Freeman still likely to be out.
report: Falcons fourth-round RB Ito Smith rushed nine times for 46 yards in the Week 2 win over the Panthers.

impact: Smith was bottled up on the ground but peppered in a few nice gains on screen passes from Matt Ryan. Tevin Coleman out-touched Smith by a commanding 17-5 margin on Sunday. Assuming Devonta Freeman (knee) remains sidelined, we’d expect a similar distribution next week against the Bengals.
report: Ito Smith lost six yards on two carries while snaring three-of-four targets for 41 receiving yards Sunday in Atlanta’s Week 3 loss to the Saints.

impact: He added another 13 yards on three catches. A week after touching the ball just five times, Smith took 10 touches away from Tevin Coleman including what turned into a seven-yard touchdown run on the opening drive. With Devonta Freeman looking likely to return next week, Smith should return to the No. 3 job, but he has shown well when given the opportunity. He should be rostered in all Dynasty formats.
report: Ito Smith rushed seven times for 35 yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 4 loss to the Bengals.

impact: Smith added a five-yard reception. #AsExpected, Smith was third on the depth chart with Devonta Freeman (knee) back in the mix, but he still played 12 snaps by Pro Football Focus' count. Smith will be without re-draft value for however long Freeman and Tevin Coleman stay healthy, but he's a nice stash in Dynasty leagues.
report: Ito Smith rushed three times for five yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 5 loss to the Steelers.

impact: He "added" negative-one yard on two catches. Smith mostly went backward against Tampa, but he got loose on a wonderfully blocked play for a 14-yard touchdown in the second quarter. He now has three touchdowns in as many games. He will be in the FLEX conversation next week if Devonta Freeman sits.
report: Ito Smith rushed 11 times for 22 yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 6 win over the Bucs.

impact: He added two catches for 29 yards on two targets and was out-touched 13-9 by Tevin Coleman, who amassed 82 yards and scored a touchdown.  Smith's biggest play was a 20-yard catch on a blitz-beater.  Smith will remain on the FLEX map as Coleman's 1B coming out of the bye in Week 9.
report: Ito Smith rushed seven times for 16 yards in the Falcons' Week 7 win over the Giants.

impact: He added two catches for 29 yards on two targets and was out-touched 13-9 by Tevin Coleman, who amassed 82 yards and scored a touchdown.  Smith's biggest play was a 20-yard catch on a blitz-beater.  Smith will remain on the FLEX map as Coleman's 1B coming out of the bye in Week 9.
report: Ito Smith rushed seven times for 16 yards in the Falcons' Week 7 win over the Giants.

impact: Smith scored the Falcons' lone rushing touchdown; their other four TDs came in the air with two to Tevin Coleman, one to Calvin Ridley, and one to Julio Jones.  Coleman out-touched Smith 18 to 11, but Smith ran physically inside the tackles and hurdled a defender on his 12-yard rushing score.  Smith will remain a workable flex play on 9-13 touches when Atlanta visits Cleveland next.
report: Ito Smith rushed 10 times for 60 yards and a touchdown and caught 1-of-2 targets for four yards in Atlanta's Week 9 win at Washington.

impact: Smith's 26 yards were his fewest in four games. Smith is mixing in for 8-12 touches on a weekly basis but has proven to be little more than a low-end FLEX option. He gets the Cowboys for Week 11.
report: Ito Smith rushed four times for 11 yards in the Falcons' Week 10 loss to the Browns, adding four receptions for 15 additional yards.

impact: Smith lucks into a touchdown here and there but has otherwise been a disappointment while stealing touches from Tevin Coleman.  Smith is averaging a pitiful 3.4 YPC on the year.  He's a TD-or -bust RB3/4.
report: Ito Smith rushed six times for 10 yards and caught both of his targets for 12 yards in the Falcons' Week 11 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: Smith is a "starter," but he has no fantasy value.  During their Week 4 bye, the Panthers need to find a way to cut Smith's snaps in favor of D.J. Moore.
report: Torrey Smith caught 3-of-6 targets for 19 yards in the Panthers' Week 3 win over the Bengals.

impact: Smith was completely anonymous despite seeing the field on 45-of-71 offensive snaps, but at least he got in some good cardio. Cam Newton must have either forgotten he existed or just chose not to acknowledge him. Either way, the well-traveled 29-year-old can be safely ignored in all fantasy formats.
report: Torrey Smith came up empty on his lone target Sunday in the Panthers’ Week 5 victory over New York.

impact: Smith, whose touchdown came on a goal line look, also converted a two-point attempt. The score was Smith's second as a Panther. Smith just crossed the 100-yard threshold for the season this afternoon. He's miles from fantasy relevance.
report: Torrey Smith caught 5-of-5 targets for 43 yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 6 loss to the Redskins.

impact: He was seen limping to the X-ray room after the game.  Smith contributed a massive 35-yard catch on fourth down with only a few minutes remaining to keep alive what wound up being the game-winning drive. Smith finished with four catches for 61 yards on six targets. If he can’t play in Week 8 against the Ravens, D.J. Moore and Curtis Samuel could get more playing time.
report: Torrey Smith needed X-rays following Sunday’s Week 7 win over Philadelphia.

impact: He was sacked three times for a loss of eight yards. Smith was surgical in his Washington debut, cutting up the Cardinals with his usual precision on short and intermediate passes. The former Chief was so accurate, he completed 13 passes in a row at one point. Smith's favorite target seemed to be receiving back Chris Thompson, who he hooked up with six times for 63 yards and a touchdown. His longest completion came on a 52-yard screen to Adrian Peterson late in the fourth quarter, though AD admittedly did most of the work on that one. With the Redskins up big, Smith only attempted 10 passes after halftime. The 34-year-old could have some streaming appeal against a lackluster Colts secondary in Week 2.
report: Alex Smith completed 21-of-30 passes for 255 yards and a pair of touchdowns while adding 14 yards on eight carries Sunday in Washington’s Week 1 win over the Cardinals.

impact: Smith also lost 23 yards on three sacks. The Redskins’ offense was cooking against the Cardinals last week, but they never got going on Sunday, managing just three field goals in a home loss to Indy. Smith had a quiet first half but let it rip after halftime, tallying 195 of his 292 yards in the second half. Most of it came in garbage time on check-downs to Chris Thompson, though he did connect on a handful of deep balls. Smith and the Redskins will take a 1-1 record into next week’s home matchup against the Packers.
report: Alex Smith completed 33-of-46 passes for 292 yards with no touchdowns or interceptions while supplying 14 yards on four carries Sunday in Washington’s Week 2 loss to the Colts.

impact: He added seven rushes for 20 additional yards. Smith's lone highlight was his 46-yard touchdown strike to Paul Richardson in the first quarter. Smith and Richardson split the defense and Richardson made a diving catch between two defenders near the goal line. Untouched, Richardson got up and finished the job. After that, Smith was dinking and dunking and doing his signature take off and run on nearly every third down. Unable to hit any big plays, Smith and the Redskins kept the Packers in the game. Thankfully for the Redskins, the Packers ruined themselves with drops and penalties. Smith is off to a highly Smith-ian start so far this season but has an attackable Week 5 matchup in the Saints.
report: Alex Smith completed 12-of-20 passes for 220 yards, two touchdowns and an interception in the Redskins' 31-17, Week 3 win over the Packers.

impact: He added a four-yard rushing score, but Smith was far worse than his pedestrian numbers even suggest.  He did some stat-padding late in the blowout loss.  Smith threw multiple hospital balls to his targets in the pass game, getting both Adrian Peterson (knee) and Chris Thompson (ribs) injured, while also spiking numerous passes into the turf well short of his receivers.  Smith lost a hilariously-bad fumble that went about 20 feet into the air and backwards for an easy scoop for the Saints.  It's hard to believe how terrible the Redskins were coming out of their bye.  They're now on a short week ahead of a home game against Carolina.  Smith won't be a fantasy option.
report: Alex Smith completed 23-of-39 passes for 275 yards, no touchdowns, and one interception in the Redskins' 43-19, Week 5 loss to the Saints.

impact: He added five carries for 14 yards. Averaging an inexcusable 4.53 yards per attempt, Smith was mostly dreadful, but the Panthers could never make him pay by creating a turnover. The Redskins won on the back of their running game. Vernon Davis was schemed completely wide open on Smith's first score, though his second was a nice throw to Paul Richardson in the back of the end zone. With seven total touchdowns through five games, Smith will be a last-gasp QB2 against the Cowboys in Week 7.
report: Alex Smith completed 21-of-36 passes for 163 yards and two touchdowns in the Redskins' 23-17, Week 6 win over the Panthers.

impact: In vintage Smith fashion, his only score on the day came on a 23-yard screen pass to change-of-pace back Kapri Bibbs. No receiver topped 43 yards for Washington. Dallas' secondary admittedly presents a tough matchup, but it is the second straight week Smith's failed to exceed 175 passing yards. Given the club's run-first grind-it-out style of play, Smith should only be used in terrific matchups on paper -- like the one the Redskins face in Week 8 against the Giants.
report: Alex Smith completed 14-of-25 passes for 178 yards and one touchdown in Washington's Week 7 win over the Cowboys.

impact: In vintage Smith fashion, his only score on the day came on a 23-yard screen pass to change-of-pace back Kapri Bibbs. No receiver topped 43 yards for Washington. Dallas' secondary admittedly presents a tough matchup, but it is the second straight week Smith's failed to exceed 175 passing yards. Given the club's run-first grind-it-out style of play, Smith should only be used in terrific matchups on paper -- like the one the Redskins face in Week 8 against the Giants.
report: Alex Smith completed 14-of-25 passes for 178 yards and one touchdown in Washington's Week 7 win over the Cowboys.

impact: Smith has settled into a low-volume, game-manager role with Adrian Peterson as Washington's offensive centerpiece.  Smith has not finished as a top-12 fantasy quarterback in any of the first seven weeks.  Smith will be a low-ceiling two-quarterback-league play in Week 9 against Atlanta.
report: Alex Smith completed 20-of-32 passes for 178 yards and a touchdown and rushed three times for 13 yards in Washington's Week 8 win over the Giants.

impact: He rushed once for 22 yards and got absolutely leveled by Falcons DB Brian Poole at the end of the sideline scramble.  Sunday's game script did not go in the favor of Washington, which aims to control games and win with strong run defense and a high-volume rushing attack.  The Redskins fell behind the Falcons and couldn't stop the run, so Smith dropped back to pass 49 times with three sacks taken.  Even against the Bucs in Week 10, Smith will remain a two-quarterback-league play only.
report: Alex Smith completed 30-of-46 passes for 306 yards, one touchdown, and one interception in Washington's Week 9 loss to Atlanta.

impact: The Tampa Bay offense thoroughly outplayed the Redskins' unit between the 20s, but the Bucs consistently shot themselves in the foot with horrid turnovers at the goal line and deep in Washington territory.  Smith's lone score was a short hookup with Josh Doctson, while Maurice Harris led the team in receiving with a 5-52 day.  The 6-3 Skins host the Texans in Week 11.
report: Alex Smith completed 19-of-27 passes for 178 yards and one touchdown in the Redskins' 16-3, Week 10 win over the Bucs.

impact: The compound leg fracture occurred in the third quarter of Week 11's loss to Houston.  Colt McCoy will close out the year as Washington's starting quarterback.  Previously, McCoy and Smith were the only two signal callers on the Redskins' roster.  Smith, who turns 35 next May, will have a long road back from this gruesome injury.  It's fair to wonder whether he'll be ready for Week 1 in 2019.
report: Alex Smith is done for the season with a fractured fibula and tibia.

impact: Smallwood's usage increased because Jay Ajayi missed almost the entire first half and Darren Sproles (hamstring) was out.  Unfortunately, Smallwood lost a fumble and Ajayi returned.  Smallwood shouldn't have a Week 3 role versus the Colts.
report: Wendell Smallwood rushed seven times for 28 yards and caught his lone target for a gain of two in the Eagles' Week 2 loss to Tampa Bay.

impact: Smallwood drew the start and out-gained Corey Clement despite receiving just 13 touches. His 4-yard touchdown rush with 3:02 left in the 4th quarter put the Eagles up for good. If both Jay Ajayi and Darren Sproles remained sidelined in Week 4, Smallwood will be in the mix as a FLEX option next week against the Titans.
report: Wendell Smallwood rushed 10 times for 56 yards and a touchdown while catching 3-of-5 targets for 35 yards in Sunday's Week 4 win over the Colts.

impact: With both Corey Clement and Darren Sproles sidelined, Smallwood served as the No. 2 back behind Jay Ajayi. It was not always pretty -- he missed a blitz pickup in the two-minute drill -- but he was able to provide a couple nice runs. With Clement's and Sproles' availability up in the air, Smallwood is worth a look in deeper leagues.
report: Wendell Smallwood rushed five times for 39 yards and hauled in 3-of-5 targets for 15 yards in the Eagles' Week 4 loss to the Titans.

impact: Corey Clement (quad) was announced as active but ended up playing zero snaps. Smallwood drew Jay Ajayi to a playing time standstill and out-gained him 71-34. He did have a first half lowlight with a red zone drop. Smallwood has shown signs of life the past three weeks but is still an uninspiring FLEX option in PPR leagues. He's a bye week "if you must" play.
report: Wendell Smallwood rushed three times for 27 yards in the Eagles' Week 5 loss to the Vikings, adding three catches for 44 additional yards and a touchdown.

impact: Smallwood’s 11 touches led the Eagles’ backfield; Corey Clement logged 10 and Josh Adams 4. Smallwood had multiple big plays nullified by penalties, including a monster screen pass of 50-plus yards that came about partly because of RG Brandon Brooks’ holding flag. Entrenched in a three-man backfield, Smallwood will be a sub-par Week 8 flex option against the Jags.
report: Wendell Smallwood rushed nine times for 32 yards and caught 2-of-2 targets for five yards in the Eagles’ Week 7 loss to the Panthers.

impact: Smallwood’s 11 touches led the Eagles’ backfield; Corey Clement logged 10 and Josh Adams 4. Smallwood had multiple big plays nullified by penalties, including a monster screen pass of 50-plus yards that came about partly because of RG Brandon Brooks’ holding flag. Entrenched in a three-man backfield, Smallwood will be a sub-par Week 8 flex option against the Jags.
report: Wendell Smallwood rushed nine times for 32 yards and caught 2-of-2 targets for five yards in the Eagles’ Week 7 loss to the Panthers.

impact: Smallwood could not get anything going in the first half, but he made his presence known after the break, taking a perfectly executed screen pass 36 yards for a touchdown on the Eagles’ first drive of the second half. Most of his damage was done in the passing game, but Smallwood had his best run of the game to pick up a game-ending first down just before the two-minute warning. It seems likely Josh Adams takes on a bigger role coming out of the bye, but Smallwood is a better bet to keep his spot than Corey Clement, making him a hold in most formats.
report: Wendell Smallwood rushed eight times for 24 yards and caught 2-of-3 targets for 42 yards and a touchdown in the Eagles' Week 8 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Smallwood got most of his snaps in the two-minute offense. He’s been passed on the depth chart by Josh Adams. Smallwood is droppable in standard leagues.
report: Wendell Smallwood had two carries for four yards in Week 10 against the Cowboys.

impact: Smith is a promising talent in theory, but the dysfunctional nature of the passing game in which he plays strips Smith of any streamer appeal in re-draft leagues.
report: Jonnu Smith caught 1-of-2 targets for nine yards in the Titans' Week 3 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Smith continues to play the majority of snaps, but he now has just two catches on seven targets this season. One of his missed connections in this game was a bad drop on third down. He is not an option in redraft leagues.
report: Jonnu Smith did not haul in either of his targets in the Titans' Week 4 win over the Eagles.

impact: Smith has been targeted five times by Marcus Mariota this year, catching none.
report: Titans TE Jonnu Smith was held catch-less on two targets in Week 5.

impact: Smith was tackled just short of the end-zone on one of his catches. He had only three targets, but he's been more involved the last few weeks. The Titans are on a bye in Week 8.
report: Jonnu Smith caught two passes for 11 yards in Week 7 against the Chargers.

impact: Smith was tackled just short of the end-zone on one of his catches. He had only three targets, but he's been more involved the last few weeks. The Titans are on a bye in Week 8.
report: Jonnu Smith caught two passes for 11 yards in Week 7 against the Chargers.

impact: Smith entered Week 9 with five catches for 44 scoreless yards despite being the starter since Delanie Walker's Week 1 injury.  Smith's score was from seven yards out on a shovel pass after Marcus Mariota faked the handoff to Dion Lewis.  Smith will not be a fantasy option next week.
report: Jonnu Smith caught both of his targets for 33 yards and one touchdown in the Titans' Week 9 win over the Cowboys.

impact: He still hasn't topped three targets in a game all year, but the Titans are designing plays for Smith in scoring position, and he now has red-zone TDs in consecutive weeks.  Even in a plus Week 11 matchup against the Colts, Smith will remain a touchdown-or-bust streamer option on low volume.
report: Jonnu Smith caught 3-of-3 targets for 45 yards and a touchdown in the Titans' Week 10 win over the Patriots.

impact: The catches were a new career high, while the 44 yards were his second-most after last week's 45. Finally becoming a part of the Titans' offense, Smith will offer TE2 appeal down the stretch. How useable he is in Week 12 will depend on who is under center after Marcus Mariota re-injured his throwing elbow against the Colts.
report: Jonnu Smith caught 6-of-8 targets for 44 yards in the Titans' Week 11 loss to the Colts.

impact: Sharpe worked behind Taywan Taylor in the first game without Rishard Matthews, but he made his presence known with an 11-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter on which he ran a great route. Even so, he is not a redraft option outside of deep leagues.
report: Tajae Sharpe hauled in 2-of-3 targets for 27 yards and a touchdown in the Titans' Week 4 win over the Eagles.

impact: Sharpe is a low-upside possession receiver in a struggling passing offense.  We wouldn't bet on him becoming fantasy relevant anytime soon.
report: Tajae Sharpe caught 3-of-4 targets for 30 yards in the Titans' Week 5 loss to the Bills.

impact: Sharpe just won't go away, leading the Titans' struggling pass offense in receiving Sunday. Second-year pro Taywan Taylor, who's seemingly been blocked by Sharp's presence, caught just one ball for 13 yards. Sharpe shouldn't be owned in fantasy, but still remains the Titans' No. 2 wideout behind Corey Davis (1/24) for whatever reason.
report: Tajae Sharpe caught both of his targets for a team-high 33 yards in the Titans' Week 6 loss to the Ravens.

impact: It's a career high in yards for Sharpe, who also paced the Titans with nine targets. He's now led Tennessee in receiving in consecutive weeks. Sharpe has a strong rapport with Marcus Mariota going back to their rookie seasons. He's worth stashing through the Titans Week 8 bye.
report: Tajae Sharpe caught 7-of-9 passes for 101 yards in Week 7 against the Chargers.

impact: The yards were Sharpe's first in four weeks. His touchdown came in the deepest recesses of garbage time. Even if Taywan Taylor (foot) remains sidelined for Week 12, Sharpe will not be a compelling WR5.
report: Tajae Sharpe caught 5-of-7 targets for 37 yards and a touchdown in the Titans' Week 11 loss to the Colts.

impact: Shepard looked on his way to a good game with four catches for 38 yards at the half, but he only managed one reception after the break. Odell Beckham is going to dominate targets in this offense -- he had 15 in this game -- but Shepard should find more success in easier matchups. He gets one next week in Dallas.
report: Sterling Shepard hauled in 5-of-7 targets for 48 yards in the Giants' Week 1 loss to the Jaguars.

impact: Shepard finished behind Odell Beckham, Evan Engram, and Saquon Barkley in targets. He missed some time this week with a back injury, but it wasn't a factor in his quiet night. Shepard won't be more than a WR4 for next week's game against the Texans.
report: Sterling Shepard caught 3-of-5 passes for 24 yards in Week 2 against the Cowboys.

impact: It's a nice rebound after a down Week 2. The Giants got better pass protection from their offensive line with RT Ereck Flowers benched, allowing Shepard and Odell Beckham to get open. Shepard's touchdown came late on a short seven-yard pass in the fourth quarter. His red-zone role could be expanded if Even Engram misses time with a knee injury. Shepard is a WR3 for Week 4's matchup with the Saints.
report: Sterling Shepard caught 6-of-7 yards for 80 yards and a touchdown in Week 3 against the Texans.

impact: He also nabbed a two-point conversion following a Saquon Barkley touchdown run.  Shepard beat CB Ken Crawley with ease on his short touchdown in the first quarter.  This was a prime spot for Shepard, and he answered with his best game of September.  Shepard has touchdowns in back-to-back games but will find tougher sledding next week on the road against the Panthers.
report: Sterling Shepard caught all 10 targets for 77 yards and one touchdown in the Giants' Week 4 loss to the Saints.

impact: The bulk of his yards (54 of his 75) came with New York trailing in the second half. Shepard was visibly frustrated on Sunday, throwing a trash can in anger during a third-quarter sideline tantrum. It’s just been that kind of year for the Giants, who have now dropped four of five including two straight. Shepard has done his part, however, eclipsing 70 yards in each of his last three contests. He’ll be in play as a WR3 Thursday against the Eagles’ funnel defense.
report: Sterling Shepard contributed four catches for 75 yards on seven targets Sunday in the Giants’ Week 5 loss to the Panthers.

impact: Shepard had monster gains of 53 and 58 to aid his huge evening against this porous defense.  It was Shepard's first 100-yard game of the season and the most of his career after topping 100 yards just four times his first two seasons.  Shepard will be a solid if unspectacular WR3 next week against the Skins.
report: Sterling Shepard caught 5-of-8 targets for 167 yards in the Giants' Week 7 loss to the Falcons.

impact: Shepard had monster gains of 53 and 58 to aid his huge evening against this porous defense.  It was Shepard's first 100-yard game of the season and the most of his career after topping 100 yards just four times his first two seasons.  Shepard will be a solid if unspectacular WR3 next week against the Skins.
report: Sterling Shepard caught 5-of-8 targets for 167 yards in the Giants' Week 7 loss to the Falcons.

impact: Redskins rookie RCB Greg Stroman knocked a would-be monster gain out of Shepard's hands in the first half, and the Giants' slot receiver was quiet the rest of the way.  Shepard's fantasy owners need the Giants to stay with Eli Manning and not turn to rookie Kyle Lauletta during their forthcoming Week 9 bye.
report: Sterling Shepard caught 4-of-8 targets for 34 yards in the Giants' Week 8 loss.

impact: Much like the rest of the Giants' receivers, Shepard wasn't needed on a day that saw Saquon Barkley carry the load for 27/142/2. Odell Beckham actually led with a relatively low four targets. Shepard and Beckham will be called upon in Week 12 against the divisional foe Eagles. Consider Shepard a low-end WR3 in that matchup given that he's still coming off consecutive letdowns in what were actually plus matchups against the Niners and Bucs.
report: Sterling Shepard caught both of his targets for 22 yards in the Giants' Week 11 win over the Bucs.

impact: Seferian-Jenkins suffered from awful touchdown luck last season in New York, and it seems to have followed him to Jacksonville. ASJ got open for a 10-yard touchdown early in the second quarter, but the play was called back on a penalty. It is a tough break, but such is life with a touchdown-or-bust fantasy option. That is what Seferian-Jenkins will be next week against the Patriots.
report: Austin Seferian-Jenkins hauled in 3-of-5 targets for 25 yards in the Jaguars' Week 1 win over the Giants.

impact: The rarest of rarities — an ASJ touchdown that was not called back. ASJ was freed by a pick play in the end zone on his four-yard score in the second quarter. The catch-and-fall specialist is averaging eight yards through his first six Jaguars receptions. He's a low-end TE2.
report: Austin Seferian-Jenkins caught 3-of-5 targets for 23 yards and a touchdown in the Jaguars' Week 2 win over the Patriots.

impact: ASJ never logs big yardage numbers and is always a touchdown-or-bust streamer option. He will draw a "revenge" matchup in Week 4 against the Jets.
report: Austin Seferian-Jenkins caught 3-of-5 targets for 18 yards in the Jaguars' Week 3 loss to Tennessee.

impact: Seferian-Jenkins wasn't much of a factor playing against his former team. He's been an afterthought in Jacksonville's offense this year, failing to go over 25 yards in any game. Seferian-Jenkins gets a matchup against the Chiefs in Week 5.
report: Austin Seferian-Jenkins caught 2-of-4 passes for 24 yards in Week 4 against the Jets.

impact: Seferian-Jenkins could not come up with the pass on a fourth-and-two target in the second quarter. That was his last involvement in the game, and he did not play many snaps if any at all in the second half. Seferian-Jenkins has been struggling with a core-muscle injury all season, and it is possible that issue flared up against Kansas City. Niles Paul, who finished with 65 yards on seven catches, would be next up at tight end.
report: Austin Seferian-Jenkins did not catch his only target in the Jaguars' Week 5 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Sanu's score was a 43-yarder. It was a short pass Matt Ryan delivered perfectly into traffic, hitting Sanu with a head of steam. The Falcons' No. 3 receiver now has 184 yards over his past two games. He will be in the WR4 mix for next week's plus matchup with the Bucs.
report: Mohamed Sanu caught 4-of-7 targets for 73 yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 5 loss to the Steelers.

impact: Sanu had no issues with his hip injury; he just didn't see many targets as Julio Jones garnered 12 and deep reserve WR Marvin Hall also caught a 47-yard score.  Sanu will be a WR4 in Week 9 at the Redskins after the bye.
report: Mohamed Sanu caught both of his targets for 21 yards in the Falcons' Week 7 win over the Giants.

impact: Sanu was seen blocking on highlight reels far more often than making the big plays himself. He did score an 11-yard fourth-quarter TD, only for the play to be negated by a holding penalty.  In a crowded Falcons pass-catcher corps, Sanu will remain a touchdown-reliant WR4/flex in Week 10 at Cleveland.
report: Mohamed Sanu caught 4-of-5 targets for 45 yards in the Falcons' Week 9 win over Washington.

impact: Sanu also lost an extremely soft fumble. Sanu has exceeded 50 yards twice in nine games. He provides zero upside as a WR4.
report: Mohamed Sanu caught 6-of-8 targets for 47 yards in the Falcons' Week 10 loss to the Browns.

impact: Sanu's 56 yards were his most since Week 5.  He also hasn't scored since Week 6.  Sanu will get a nice draw against the Saints on Thanksgiving night as a WR4.  He went 4-36-1 versus New Orleans in Week 3.
report: Mohamed Sanu caught 4-of-6 targets for 56 yards in the Falcons' Week 11 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: It looked like Sanders would be Case Keenum’s favorite target during the preseason, and that is exactly what happened in Week 1. Sanders was involved early, but he really made his presence known on a 43-yard, catch-and-run touchdown in the second quarter. He finished the first half with 115 yards and that score on seven catches. He was quieter after the break, but he still consistently got open. With the Raiders up next, Sanders will be a clear top-20 receiver in Week 2.
report: Emmanuel Sanders hauled in 10-of-11 targets for 135 yards and a touchdown in the Broncos' Week 1 win over the Seahawks.

impact: Sanders wasn't even targeted in the first half as Oakland played keep away, but still almost hit the century mark in yardage after the break. Sanders now has 231 yards receiving yards through two weeks compared to 81 yards for Demaryius Thomas. Sanders will be a WR2 option in Week 2 when the Raiders head to Baltimore.
report: Emmanuel Sanders caught 4-of-4 targets for 96 yards in Sunday's Week 2 win over the Raiders.

impact: Sanders struggled to get much going through the air, but he saved his fantasy day with a 35-yard touchdown on an end around in the first quarter. Despite the down receiving day, he still led the team in targets and tied for the team lead in catches. He should bounce back next week against the Chiefs.
report: Emmanuel Sanders hauled in 5-of-8 targets for 38 yards and rushed once for a 35-yard touchdown in the Broncos' Week 3 loss to the Ravens.

impact: Sanders made a huge catch on 4th-and-11 on the final drive with the Broncos trailing by four points, but the offense later stalled and ran out of time.  Sanders also had an 18-yard carry on an end-around.  Case Keenum hasn't been getting the job done of late, putting Sanders on the WR3 map next week for a road date with the Jets.  Sanders, however, has been Denver's best wideout.
report: Emmanuel Sanders caught 5-of-7 targets for 45 yards in the Broncos' Week 4 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Sanders set season highs in catches and yards in a game where the Broncos were forced to abandon the running game after falling behind.  Sanders also saw his first red-zone target of the season.  In a Week 6 matchup with the Rams, Sanders' outlook will be improved by the game's shootout potential.  Sanders has earned every-week WR3 treatment but will be a legit WR2 against Los Angeles.
report: Emmanuel Sanders caught 9-of-14 targets for 72 yards in the Broncos' Week 5 loss to the Jets.

impact: Sanders nearly had a two-score day but got ruled down at the one-yard line on a 43-yard grab in the first quarter. Celebrating what he thought was a touchdown, Sanders was then called for taunting, pushing the Broncos back to the 16-yard line for 1st-and-goal. They had to settle for a field goal in a game they went on to lose 23-20. Sanders has come alive over the past two weeks even as Case Keenum continues to struggle, catching 16 passes for 187 yards and a touchdown. He could have a hard time staying hot in Week 7, as the Broncos will be traveling to Arizona on a short week. The Cardinals have held receiver fantasy production reasonably in check thus far.
report: Emmanuel Sanders caught 7-of-10 targets for 115 yards and a touchdown in the Broncos' Week 6 loss to the Rams.

impact: Sanders nearly overthrew Courtland Sutton on his wide-open touchdown throw in the first quarter, but the rookie was able to extend and make the catch. Sanders was left completely wide open on his 64-yard receiving score in the second quarter, as reserve S Rudy Ford seemed to have no idea what was going on. Sanders has now cleared 100 yards receiving in back-to-back games and 3-of-7 on the year. Case Keenum's play has often been ugly, but he has no qualms about looking Sanders' way. The Chiefs' burnable defense is on deck for a mouthwatering Week 8 matchup.
report: Emmanuel Sanders caught 6-of-7 targets for 102 yards and a touchdown in the Broncos' Week 7 win over the Cardinals, adding a 28-yard touchdown pass.

impact: Sanders came down with a 49-yard catch on the opening drive but wasn't heard from much after that. The veteran exited with a right shoulder injury early in the second half but only missed a few snaps. There have been rumblings that Sanders could be dealt ahead of Tuesday's trade deadline, so this could potentially be the last game of his Broncos tenure. If not, he'll be in the WR2/3 mix when the Broncos host Houston in Week 9.
report: Emmanuel Sanders snagged four catches for 66 yards on four targets while losing six yards on his lone carry Sunday in Denver’s Week 8 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Only Jeff Heuerman (10/83/1) saw more targets than Sanders in Denver's first game without Demaryius Thomas. Unfortunately, his nine targets amounted to just 47 yards on the day. Courtland Sutton totaled 3/57 on six fewer catches than Sanders. It was an underwhelming outing given the surrounding situation, but owners need not lose hope in him yet. Sanders will stay a WR2/3 when the Broncos return in Week 11 against the Chargers.
report: Emmanuel Sanders corralled 6-of-9 targets for 47 yards in the Broncos' Week 9 loss to the Texans.

impact: L.A.'s elite secondary showed little resistance early on, limiting the Broncos' star receiver to a single first-half catch. Sanders livened up in the second half, delivering a pivotal 38-yard catch on Denver's game-winning drive. The nine-year vet initially lost a fumble after taking a monster hit from Casey Hayward during the fourth quarter, though the play was later changed to an incompletion on review. Fantasy owners were hoping Sanders would see a boost from Demaryius Thomas' departure, but that hasn't exactly been the case as the 31-year-old has totaled just 10 catches for 103 yards and no touchdowns in his two games without Demaryius. He'll try to reverse that trend next week against his former team, the Steelers.
report: Emmanuel Sanders pulled in four catches for 56 yards on six targets Sunday in Denver’s Week 11 victory over the Chargers.

impact: Samuel turned a simple Cam Newton screen into a 25-yard touchdown, which gave Carolina its first points of the afternoon with 4:38 left in the first quarter. He broke multiple tackles on his way to the end zone and also got a great block from teammate Devin Funchess, who leveled Janoris Jenkins at the line of scrimmage. That play marked the first touchdown of Samuel’s two-year career. The 22-year-old was making his season debut after missing the Panthers’ first three games with an irregular heartbeat. Samuel isn’t in the fantasy discussion yet, but he’ll be a name to monitor on the waiver wire throughout the season.
report: Curtis Samuel grabbed two catches for 37 yards and a touchdown on four targets Sunday in Carolina’s Week 5 win over the Giants.

impact: He scored a 14-yard touchdown on an end-around, but lost five yards on his other rushing attempt and was only targeted once. A low-volume gadget player, Samuel’s fantasy value is limited to deeper Dynasty leagues.
report: Curtis Samuel rushed twice for nine yards and a touchdown and caught a 16-yard pass in the Panthers’ Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: He scored a 14-yard touchdown on an end-around, but lost five yards on his other rushing attempt and was only targeted once. A low-volume gadget player, Samuel’s fantasy value is limited to deeper Dynasty leagues.
report: Curtis Samuel rushed twice for nine yards and a touchdown and caught a 16-yard pass in the Panthers’ Week 7 win over the Eagles.

impact: Samuel and D.J. Moore picked up more reps with Torrey Smith (knee) out, but it was Moore who did the bulk of the damage with a team-high six targets and 129 total yards on seven touches.  Samuel isn't on the redraft map.
report: Curtis Samuel caught all three of his targets for 28 yards in the Panthers' Week 8 win over the Ravens.

impact: Coming off a complete dud of a Week 8, Samuel surprisingly had the most impressive game of his career. Samuel's winding 33-yard rushing score covered an astonishing 103 yards of turf. Samuel got the ball on a double reverse and ended up completely reversing fields. It was something to see. Highly volatile and fighting for gadget targets with D.J. Moore, Samuel remains off the re-draft radar.
report: Curtis Samuel caught 2-of-4 targets for 25 yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 9 win over the Bucs, adding a 33-yard rushing touchdown.

impact: Samuel also committed a costly special teams turnover, losing the ball deep in his own territory. Samuel has been heavily involved on offense during Torrey Smith's (knee) three-game absence but has not made enough big plays for it to translate to fantasy value. Smith's health for Week 11 is uncertain.
report: Curtis Samuel caught 4-of-4 targets for 18 yards in the Panthers' Week 10 loss, adding a one-yard rush.

impact: Samuel was mostly a non-factor early, and he was unable to wrestle the ball out of Tracy Walker’s hands on Cam Newton’s interception at the end of the half. Following a quiet third quarter, Samuel got things going in a big way in the fourth. All five of his catches came in the final period including a spectacular, leaping catch for a 12-yard touchdown to tie the game. After the Lions retook the lead, Samuel helped keep another touchdown drive alive with a catch along the sideline. The seven targets were a season-high for Samuel as were the 55 receiving yards. Even so, Samuel will not be an option outside of deep leagues next week.
report: Curtis Samuel hauled in 5-of-7 passes for 55 yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 11 loss to the Lions.

impact: Donte Moncrief caught a 29-yard pass to the one-yard line.  Bills CB Levi Wallace wouldn't let go of the ball, and several players on both sides jumped in and began to fight.  In addition to Fournette, Bills DE Shaq Lawson got kicked out of the game.  Fournette may be subject to further discipline in Week 13.  Fournette finished Week 12 with 108 total yards and two rushing TDs.
report: Leonard Fournette was ejected in the third quarter of Sunday's Week 12 game against the Bills for throwing punches.

impact: Ivory’s most notable play was when he tripped on a blade of grass and fumbled in the second quarter. He is not even an exciting handcuff.
report: Chris Ivory rushed six times for four yards in the Bills' Week 13 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: Murray had more carries and yards than Dalvin Cook, but most of them came in clock-killing mode late in the fourth quarter. He remains a distant second in line for touches behind Cook. Murray is just a short yardage change-of-pace.
report: Latavius Murray had 11 carries for 33 yards in Week 12 against the Packers.

impact: Murray converted a crucial fourth-and-one opportunity in the fourth quarter (barely) but other than that, he didn't have much impact on Sunday's proceedings. Lead back Dalvin Cook out-touched Murray by a convincing 17-6 margin while out-producing him by over 90 yards from scrimmage. Unless you're stashing him as a handcuff, Murray is probably best left on the waiver wire.
report: Latavius Murray chewed up 11 yards on four carries while securing both of his targets for an additional three yards Sunday in Minnesota’s Week 13 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Njoku did nearly all of his damage on one drive, catching three passes for 51 yards on the third drive of the game that was a capped with a 6-yard touchdown. On his score, Njoku attempted to leap over a defender from the 5-yard line, but was caught in mid-air, only to not go down. His teammates then shoved him into the end zone for his third touchdown of the season. Njoku will enter Week 13 as an upside option at tight end against the Texans.
report: David Njoku caught all five his targets for 63 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 12 win over the Bengals.

impact: Njoku has been tough to nail down as of late, having games with zero, 18 and eight yards receiving over the past five weeks to go along with games of 53 and 63 yards. Njoku does have six games with at least 50-yards receiving, but only a season-high of 69 yards on the year. Despite his down game and lack of showing a high ceiling this season, Njoku will still be a option at a depressed tight end position to take a chance on in Week 14 against a giving Panthers defense.
report: Davis Njoku caught 3-of-6 targets for eight yards in Sunday's Week 13 loss to the Texans.

impact: Prescott added 18 yards and a third touchdown on the ground.  His five-yard rushing score was a thing of magic, escaping two sacks deep in the backfield close to the 20-yard line and then front-flipping into the end zone.  His two passing scores were 40- and 90-yard strikes to Amari Cooper, who went for 180 yards.  The 289 pass yards is a new season-high for Prescott, and he's topped 200 yards passing in all four games with Cooper after failing to reach that mark several times before the deal.  Prescott will be a borderline QB1 next Thursday versus the Saints.
report: Dak Prescott completed 22-of-31 passes for 289 yards and two touchdowns in the Cowboys' 31-23, Week 12 win over the Redskins.

impact: Prescott added five rushes for 22 yards. He also fumbled twice, losing one. It was a horrible red zone mistake late in the fourth quarter, but Drew Brees ended up "answering" just moments later with an even worse interception. One of Prescott's four incompletions was a should-have-been 55-yard touchdown to Michael Gallup, who was wide open after putting a double move on Eli Apple. Prescott just missed him. Otherwise, Prescott played excellent ball as the Cowboys sprung the massive home upset. He now has 10 days to rest up for a critical divisional matchup with the Eagles.
report: Dak Prescott completed 24-of-28 passes for 248 yards and a touchdown in the Cowboys' 13-10, Week 13 win over the Saints.

impact: Pettis was the 49ers' biggest passing-game bright spot, showing elite route-running chops as he created separation at will against Tampa Bay's overmatched secondary.  Pettis quietly now has 13 targets over the last two games, although Marquise Goodwin (personal) and Pierre Garcon's (knee) absences have helped his volume.  Their statuses are uncertain entering Week 13 at Seattle, as is struggling quarterback Nick Mullens' job security.
report: Dante Pettis caught four passes for 77 yards and a touchdown on seven targets in the 49ers' Week 12 loss to Tampa Bay.

impact: The 49ers were blown out in this one, but they were actually able to move the ball in large part because of Pettis, who flashed his great after catch ability on both of his touchdowns. On the first, he was able to escape a tackle attempt, utilize a great block, and dash into the end zone. On the second, he was able to skip out of a tackle attempt and outrun everyone to the end zone for a 75-yard score. With Marquise Goodwin and Pierre Garcon out indefinitely, Pettis is worth an add in most leagues.
report: Dante Pettis hauled in 5-of-7 targets for 129 yards and two touchdowns in the 49ers' Week 13 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: He wasn't targeted in the passing game.  Peterson scored a 90-yard touchdown on a handoff from Mark Sanchez on Sanchez's first snap of the game after replacing Colt McCoy following a broken fibula.  Peterson did nothing on the rest of his touches.  The nine carries tied an eight-game-low.  Peterson will be faced with stacked boxes the rest of the way with Mark Sanchez at quarterback.  Blowouts will be almost certain.  Peterson will be a very risky RB2 the final month.
report: Adrian Peterson rushed nine times for 98 yards and one touchdown in the Redskins' 28-13, Week 13 loss to the Eagles on Monday night.

impact: With Chris Carson working as the clear lead back, Penny did not get many opportunities in this one. He finished the first half with just two carries for three yards, and he did even worse after the break. With Carson working as the clear lead back, Penny is just a handcuff at this point.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed four times for four yards in the Seahawks' Week 12 win over the Panthers.

impact: Penny still worked as the clear No. 2 to Chris Carson for most of this game, but he had several explosive runs including a 20-yard touchdown on the opening play of the second half – Tyler Lockett set up the offense with a long kickoff return. It is notable, however, that Carson left this game in the fourth quarter with a finger injury. Coach Pete Carroll said Carson should be fine, but if he is forced to miss time, Penny will be on the RB2 map.
report: Rashaad Penny rushed seven times for 65 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 13 win over the 49ers.

impact: Taking four sacks, Mullens continued to have the same happy feet in the pocket he showed in San Francisco's pre-bye loss to the Giants.  This contributed to Mullens' inaccuracy, and he committed multiple turnovers for the second straight start.  We would not be surprised if coach Kyle Shanahan reconsidered his quarterback situation entering Week 13 against the Seahawks.  The 49ers invested a third-round pick into C.J. Beathard and nothing into Mullens.
report: Nick Mullens completed just 18-of-32 passes for 221 yards, one touchdown, and two interceptions in the 49ers' Week 12 loss to Tampa Bay.

impact: A week after busting against the Bucs, Mullens was able to consistently move the ball in Seattle even if garbage time helped pad his numbers. After hooking up with Dane Pettis for 77 yards and a touchdown last week, Mullens found the rookie for 129 yards and both of his touchdowns in this one. Pettis did much of the hard work on both scores, but Mullens threw a nice pass on the 75 yarder. He did throw a pick-six when the 49ers looked headed for a touchdown in the fourth quarter, but this was overall a solid display. Despite this surprising showing, Mullens will not be anything more than a two-quarterback option next week against the Broncos.
report: Nick Mullens completed 30-of-48 passes for 414 yards, two touchdowns, and an interception in the 49ers' Week 13 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: Never exactly known for his chemistry with Ryan Tannehill, Parker was invisible as coach Adam Gase employed a smoke-and-mirrors game plan for his quarterback's return. Although he's had two nine-target games over his past four contests, Parker has showed few signs of becoming a reliable WR4. He figures to see plenty of Tre'Davious White in Week 13 against the Bills.
report: DeVante Parker caught 3-of-3 targets for 10 yards in the Dolphins' Week 12 loss to the Colts.

impact: Parker struggled playing through a shoulder injury last week, but he started out this game on the right foot. He capped a good opening drive from the Dolphins with an 18-yard touchdown, taking a big hit and still holding onto the ball at the goal line. It was his first touchdown since September of 2017. He almost scored again in the second quarter, but he was stopped at the three-yard line. He was held without a catch in the second half with the Dolphins struggling to move the ball, but this was still a solid performance. Assuming Danny Amendola continues to sit, Parker will be a WR4 option next week against the Patriots.
report: DeVante Parker hauled in 4-of-7 targets for 43 yards and a touchdown in the Dolphins' Week 13 win over the Bills.

impact: Christian McCaffrey was the main target in the passing game, but Moore operated as the No. 1 receiver with Devin Funchess on the sidelines. That did not result in much work in the first half, but he caught six passes for 54 yards after the break and continued to look dangerous with the ball in his hands. If Funchess sits again, Moore will be an upside WR3 in a great matchup against the Bucs next week.
report: D.J. Moore hauled in 8-of-9 targets for 91 yards in the Panthers' Week 12 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: It's a step back after Moore went off the last two weeks. Devin Funchess was active but didn't play a full complement of snaps. Moore takes a hit with Funchess healthy, but the potential loss of Greg Olsen (foot) is a boost to his target share.
report: D.J. Moore caught 4-of-8 targets for 44 yards in Week 13 against the Bucs.

impact: Miller was peeling off big runs the entire first half, with gains of 21, 12, and 15 before Demaryius Thomas caught a 12-yard score a couple plays later.  He then wrecked the game for the Titans with a 97-yard touchdown run one play after Tennessee went for it on fourth down from the three-yard line only to get stuffed for no gain.  Miller took it easy in the second half with Alfred Blue getting more work.  Miller has 100 total yards and/or a touchdown in four of the last five games.  He's established himself as a volume RB2 heading into Week 13 against the Browns.
report: Lamar Miller rushed 12 times for 162 yards and one touchdown in the Texans' 34-17, Week 12 win over the Titans on Monday night.

impact: This was Miller's second 100-yard rushing game in a row and the fourth that he's had over his past six games. With the Texans continuing to control games, Miller has turned his season around and worked his way into weekly RB2 status. Miller will be a solid option once again next week at home when the Texans host the Colts.
report: Lamar Miller rushed 19 times for 103 yards while catching one pass for 12 yards in Sunday's Week 13 win over the Browns.

impact: Moncrief's reception initially was ruled a 30-yard touchdown, then overturned by replay as reviews showed he was tackled at the one-yard line.  A brawl ensued after that very play, and Leonard Fournette was appropriately ejected for throwing several haymakers.  Moncrief remains one of fantasy's most boom-bust wide receiver plays.  He will continue to be in Week 13 against the Colts.
report: Donte Moncrief caught 1-of-4 targets for 29 yards in the Jaguars' Week 12 loss to Buffalo.

impact: He was out-targeted by T.J. Yeldon (8) and Dede Westbrook (5).  Game-managing fill-in QB starter Cody Kessler attempted just 24 throws and passed for 150 yards.  We wouldn't expect much more passing-game production in Week 14 at Tennessee, rendering Moncrief a low-floor WR4 option at best.
report: Donte Moncrief caught 3-of-4 targets for 40 yards in the Jaguars' Week 13 win over the Colts.

impact: Mixon's 155 yards were his most in a game in three weeks and his seven catches and 66 yards were a season-high. Even trailing by 28 points early, Mixon remained the bellcow, never coming off the field, something he had struggled with in previous Bengals losses. Mixon will enter Week 13 as a lower-end RB1 at home against the Broncos.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 14 times for 89 yards while catching all seven of his targets for 66 yards in Sunday's Week 12 loss to the Browns.

impact: It was an efficient day for Mixon (6.8 YPC), but he was ultimately game-scripted out of play as the Broncos took possession after possession and milked the clock behind Phillip Lindsay's breakout 19/157/2 performance. Unlike previous weeks, though, the second-year pro actually did lose touches down the stretch to Giovani Bernard, who finished tied with Tyler Boyd for the team-lead in targets (8). The Bengals will have to run the ball if they stand any chance at competing with the Chargers next week, keeping Mixon a low-end usage-based RB1 despite Jeff Driskel's shortcomings.
report: Joe Mixon rushed 12 times for 82 yards in the Bengals' Week 13 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Nearly all of TyMont's production including all eight of his carries came in the second half. His biggest gain of the afternoon came on a 15-yard burst, which set up a five-yard touchdown dash by Lamar Jackson early in the third quarter. Montgomery impressed as a change-of-pace/passing-down complement to power back Gus Edwards on Sunday, though his role will probably be scaled back when Alex Collins (foot) returns from injury. TyMont and the 6-5 Ravens will travel to Atlanta for a date with the Falcons in Week 13.
report: Ty Montgomery delivered 51 yards on eight carries while also securing three catches for 13 yards on three targets Sunday in the Ravens’ Week 12 win over Oakland.

impact: Montgomery's 55 yards from scrimmage were a new Ravens high after he gained 54 in Week 12. Kenneth Dixon mixed in for nine touches in his return, making Montgomery further volatile as a potential PPR FLEX option going forward.
report: Ty Montgomery caught 5-of-7 targets for 42 yards in the Ravens' Week 13 win over the Falcons, adding three carries for 13 additional yards.

impact: Miller now has just seven targets over his past two games. He will still offer some WR4 appeal for Week 13 against the Giants if Mitchell Trubisky (shoulder) can get cleared.
report: Anthony Miller caught 3-of-4 targets for 41 yards in the Bears' Week 12 win over the Lions.

impact: Miller made his catch count by securing the one-yard score on a trick play from Tarik Cohen as time expired in regulation to tie the game at 27-27 and force overtime.  Miller will be a WR4/5 next week against the Rams.
report: Anthony Miller caught a one-yard touchdown on two targets in the Bears' Week 13 loss to the Giants.

impact: The 133 yards on the ground were a new career high. Michel almost didn't get there after tweaking his back early in the third quarter. He remained down for several moments before walking very gingerly to the sidelines. He never popped into the medical tent, however, and ended up missing only one series. Michel could have had an even-bigger game but had 25- and 15-yard runs called back by penalty. He also had a touchdown overturned on review but managed to punch it in one play later. Michel will remain a volume-based RB2 for Week 13 against the Vikings.
report: Sony Michel rushed 21 times for 133 yards and a touchdown in the Patriots' Week 12 win over the Jets, adding two receptions for 12 additional yards.

impact: Michel spent much of the first half running into brick walls, contributing just 19 yards on seven carries before the break. He had somewhat better luck in the second half, though Michel's day (at least in fantasy) was ruined by fullback James Develin, who trolled fantasy owners by vulturing a pair of touchdowns. Michel still worked as the lead back, but ceded seven carries to Rex Burkhead, who returned from an eight-game absence on Sunday. With Burkhead back in the rotation and James White occupying his usual role on passing-downs, Michel will be a risky RB2 when the Patriots visit Miami in Week 14.
report: Sony Michel racked up 63 yards on 17 carries while converting his lone target for a seven-yard pickup Sunday in the Patriots’ Week 13 win over Minnesota.

impact: McGuire could have had a second reception but committed an awful drop. McGuire was out-touched and out-gained by Isaiah Crowell but was charted as out-snapping his backfield mate 35-26. McGuire has slid seamlessly into Bilal Powell's old role but has yet to turn it into viable FLEX numbers.
report: Elijah McGuire rushed six times for 19 yards in the Jets' Week 12 loss to the Patriots, adding a seven-yard reception.

impact: McDonald had a fine first half, but it could have been much better if he did not allow a touchdown to slip through his hands just before halftime. Unfortunately, that was his only real opportunity at a big fantasy day as he went without a target after the break. McDonald did leave for a bit with a hip injury, but he was able to reenter the game. Assuming he avoided a major injury, McDonald will be a back-end TE1 next week against the Chargers.
report: Vance McDonald hauled in 3-of-5 targets for 27 yards in the Steelers' Week 12 loss to the Broncos.

impact: The touches were there, but Josh Allen's dominant rushing day (12/100/1) ate into McCoy's production, and Buffalo's porous interior run blocking did him no favors. McCoy had touchdown opportunities in clock-killing mode, but Allen opted for multiple quarterback keepers, and McCoy never got a goal-line chance.  McCoy will remain a volatile RB2 option when Buffalo visits Miami next.
report: LeSean McCoy rushed 17 times for 46 yards and caught his lone target for a gain of seven in Buffalo's Week 12 win over Jacksonville.

impact: There was not much to like about McCoy’s first quarter, but he ended it with a great move in the backfield to shake a safety and pick up a third down, helping spark a touchdown drive. He also finished the second quarter with a flourish, gaining 18 yards to give the Bills a chance for points before the half. McCoy was mostly shut down in the second half before adding a couple catches on Buffalo's failed final drive. McCoy continues to see good volume, but he has struggled to produce. He will be just an RB3/FLEX option next week against the Jets.
report: LeSean McCoy rushed 15 times for 52 yards and caught all four of his targets for 12 yards in the Bills' Week 13 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: McCown's touchdown was a 16-yarder to Jermaine Kearse on a quick snap. His interception was a deep ball arm punt into Stephon Gilmore's coverage. McCown was hurt by a few drops but was in full game-manager mode. A bizarrely-constructed offense is spinning its wheels with McCown under center. Hopefully Sam Darnold (foot) can finally return for Week 13 against the Titans' tough defense.
report: Josh McCown completed 26-of-45 passes for 276 yards, one touchdown and an interception in the Jets' 27-13, Week 12 loss to the Patriots.

impact: The Jets didn't score an offensive touchdown, instead settling for five Jason Myers field goals and a pick-six from Trumaine Johnson for their points.  McCown will head back to the bench in Week 14 with Sam Darnold expected back to face the Bills after missing the last three games with a foot injury.
report: Josh McCown completed 17-of-30 passes for 128 scoreless yards and an interception in the Jets' Week 13 loss to the Titans.

impact: The Panthers struggled in the red zone on Sunday, which ultimately cost them the game, but they marched up and down the field in part because of McCaffrey’s work in the passing game. He caught eight of Cam Newton’s 14 passes in the first half for 79 yards, and he just kept on eating in the second half. After Seattle took the lead, McCaffrey helped set up his own one-yard touchdown run with a 23-yard catch on a screen pass, a play which put him over 100 yards through the air. He made it happen on the ground the next drive, bursting through a hole for 59 yards on the opening play. He almost lost a fumble at the goal line a couple plays later, but he finished off the series with a two-yard touchdown catch. This is the first 100/100 game of McCaffrey's career, and he is just the 31st player in NFL history to manage the feat. McCaffrey will be a high-end RB1 next week against the Bucs.
report: Christian McCaffrey rushed 17 times for 125 yards and a touchdown and hauled in all 11 of his targets for 112 yards and another score in the Panthers' Week 12 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: McCaffrey was Carolina's entire offense with Greg Olsen leaving early and Devin Funchess at less than 100 percent. He set up his TD catch after a 53-yard run that put the Panthers inside the red-zone. McCaffrey has been locked in down the stretch and leads the league with 10 touchdowns over the last six weeks. He'll remain a high-end RB1 for Week 13 against the Browns.
report: Christian McCaffrey had 10 carries for 106 yards and caught 9-of-10 targets for 55 yards and a touchdown in Week 13 against the Bucs.

impact: Mayfield came out of the gates blazing, completing 6-of-6 passes of 71 yards on the opening drive and went on to complete 17-of-22 passes for 245 yards and three scores in the first half. Up 35-7 early in the third quarter, the Browns took their foot off the gas, but Mayfield had already done his damage. Mayfield has now thrown multiple touchdowns in five straight games, the first Cleveland quarterback to have such a streak in the same season since Frank Ryan in 1967. Mayfield will enter Week 13 as a high-end QB2 in Week 13 on the road versus the Texans.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 19-of-26 passes for 258 yards and four touchdowns in Sunday's Week 12 win over the Bengals.

impact: After a strong stretch that was aided by soft opponents, Mayfield played like a rookie Sunday. His passing yardage was a season-high, but the bulk of those yards were of the empty-calorie variety playing from a self-induced hole in the second half. The Browns trailed 23-0 at the half with Mayfield completing just 5-of-13 passes with three interceptions prior to the break, one of which was returned for a touchdown. Mayfield will look to get back on track at home against a reeling Panthers team in Week 14.
report: Baker Mayfield completed 29-of-43 passes for 397 yards with one touchdown and three interceptions in Sunday's Week 13 loss to the Texans.

impact: Martin staked the Raiders to an early lead with a one-yard touchdown scamper in the first quarter. The play was originally ruled a lost fumble, but replay showed Martin crossed the plane before coughing it up. That touchdown was Martin's first since Week 14 of last season. Game script was Martin's undoing as the Muscle Hamster was held to just one second-half carry with Oakland in catch-up mode. The 29-year-old was limited by an ankle injury at practice this week but didn't show any ill effects in Sunday's defeat. Martin and the 2-9 Raiders will host Kansas City in Week 13.
report: Doug Martin contributed 51 yards and a touchdown on 11 carries while adding three grabs for 21 yards on four targets Sunday in the Raiders’ Week 12 loss to Baltimore.

impact: Martin was one of
report: Doug Martin rushed 18 times for 61 yards and a touchdown in the Raiders' Week 13 loss to the Chiefs, also losing a fumble.

impact: Manning was cooking early, guiding the Giants down the field for four-straight scoring drives, including a touchdown pass to Saquon Barkley on a 13-yard screen.  But the Giants did nothing after the half, with Manning throwing for just 58 scoreless yards the final 30 minutes.  Barkley got just five touches in the second half.  Manning won't be a fantasy option next week against the Bears.
report: Eli Manning completed 25-of-36 passes for 294 yards, one touchdown, and one interception in the Giants' 25-22, Week 12 loss to the Eagles.

impact: Manning was being harassed by the Bears' pass rush much of the day but was also terrible even when he did have time to throw, missing receivers.  His interception was thrown right to CB Kyle Fuller.  Manning's score was a blind heave into the air from the on-yard line in the face of pressure, and a wide-open Odell Beckham was able to run under it in the end zone.  Manning is a bottom-five fantasy option heading into a road date against the Redskins in Week 14.
report: Eli Manning completed 19-of-35 passes for 170 yards, one touchdown, and one interception in the Giants' Week 13 win over the Bears.

impact: Mariota completed his first 19 passes of the night, channeling his inner Philip Rivers who set the record with 25 straight completions on Sunday  Mariota didn't have his first incompletion until there was 1:06 left in the fourth quarter.  He finished with a near-perfect 147.7 passer rating and threw 61- and 48-yard touchdown passes to Jonnu Smith and Corey Davis, respectively.  Smith did all the work on his, racking up a ton of YAC as he went almost untouched to the end zone after not being covered.  Davis' ball was a deep shot down the right side.  He was wide open.  Mariota added 28 rushing yards.  One of the most unpredictable players at the position, Mariota can pop up for big games in random spots and totally bottom out in perceived good matchups.  This offense is bipolar as a whole.  Mariota will get the Jets at home in Week 13.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 22-of-23 passes for 304 yards and two touchdowns in the Titans' 34-17, Week 12 loss to the Texans on Monday night.

impact: Mariota was also the team's leading rusher with 42 yards on five attempts.  The Titans were getting creamed early, losing 16-0 at one point deep into the second quarter.  But Mariota ended up hitting Anthony Firkser for a 12-yard score with 57 second to half to get the Titans on the board.  The teams continued to trade field goals, but Mariota then hit Corey Davis for an 11-yard score on 3rd-and-6 with 36 ticks left in regulation to win the game.  Mariota has now strung together back-to-back good games after his injury-aided dud in Indy three weeks back.  Tennessee will host the Jaguars in Week 14.  Mariota will be more of a mid-range QB2 with upside.
report: Marcus Mariota completed 20-of-35 passes for 282 yards, two touchdowns, and one interception in the Titans' 26-22, Week 13 win over the Jets.

impact: Mahomes was not particularly crisp today — he struggled to get on the same page with Tyreek Hill and nearly broke some of Travis Kelce's ribs with a hospital ball — but he still managed to cruise by 40 touchdowns on the season. His 41 scores are already tied for ninth all time. Mahomes has arguably been a little too frisky with the ball of late, risking unnecessary turnovers, but his play-making ability is simply out of this world. He should be considered the frontrunner for MVP honors. The Ravens' elite defense is on deck for Week 14.
report: Patrick Mahomes completed 23-of-38 passes for 295 yards and four touchdowns in the Chiefs' 40-33, Week 13 win over the Raiders, adding nine carries for 52 additional yards.

impact: Mack was ruled out late in the fourth quarter. He was having a strong game before going down, rushing 15 times for 85 yards while adding two receptions. He will have the full seven days to get cleared for Week 13 against the Bills. Jordan Wilkins would be the next man up on early downs.
report: Marlon Mack was forced from Sunday's game against the Dolphins with a concussion and will not return.

impact: He got out-touched by Nyheim Hines 13 to 9 in a game where the Colts played from behind and couldn't run efficiently, resorting to short passes to move the chains.  In that approach, versatile Hines is a superior option to Mack, who primarily focuses on early-down rushing.  Mack has settled in as a low-end RB2 entering the Colts' Week 14 date with a stout Texans run defense.
report: Marlon Mack rushed eight times for 27 yards and caught his lone target for six yards in the Colts' Week 13 loss to the Jaguars.

impact: Olsen also caught just two passes last week against the Lions, but he managed to save his fantasy day with a touchdown. He came close to doing the same thing in the fourth quarter, but he just could not come up with the goal-line target. His usage the last couple games has been troubling, but Olsen will remain a TE1 option in a great matchup against the Bucs next week.
report: Greg Olsen hauled in 2-of-4 targets for 11 yards in the Panthers' Week 12 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: Nelson returned from a one-week absence but didn't do anything. Derek Carr seemed to favor Marcell Ateman, targeting him a team-high 10 times while only looking Nelson's way on one occasion. Oakland's offense is in shambles and the aging Nelson has done very little to help the cause. Even against a Chiefs defense that gave up 54 points and over 400 yards of offense last week, Nelson won't be of much use to fantasy owners in Week 13.
report: Jordy Nelson came up empty on his lone target Sunday in the Raiders’ Week 12 loss to the Ravens.

impact: Taking advantage of a mouthwatering matchup, Nelson set a new season high for catches. The yards were his second most. It was just the second time all year Nelson cleared 50 yards. It's encouraging, and proved that Nelson is back to full health, but he will find the sledding tougher in Week 14 against the Steelers.
report: Jordy Nelson caught 10-of-11 targets for 97 yards in the Raiders' Week 13 win over the Chiefs.

impact: Newton started this game hot, completing all 14 of his first-half passes, but the Panthers consistently left points on the board in the red zone. Newton was stuffed on fourth down on the opening drive, and another good drive bogged down in the red zone later in the first quarter. The Panthers finally found the end zone when Newton hit Curtis Samuel with a seven-yard strike midway through the second quarter, but it was not the start of a trend. Carolina had to settle for a field goal at the end of the first half, and Newton threw an interception on the first drive of the second half. The Panthers scored touchdowns on back-to-back drives from there, but those missed opportunities along with a missed field goal allowed the Seahawks to steal the win. Coming off two games they should not have lost, Newton will try to get things back on track in a great matchup against the Bucs next week.
report: Cam Newton completed 25-of-30 passes for 256 yards, two touchdowns, and an interception in the Panthers' Week 12 loss to the Seahawks, adding 63 yards on the ground.

impact: Newton got off to a fast start with a first quarter touchdown to Christian McCaffrey.  He went off the rails in the second half, stalling the Panthers' drives with interceptions. It's a letdown against a Bucs secondary that was playing without their top three corners, though Newton salvaged his fantasy day with 33 rushing yards and a late TD to Devin Funchess. Newton will try to rebound with a Week 14 matchup against the Browns.
report: Cam Newton completed 28-of-41 passes for 300 yards with two touchdowns and four interceptions in the Panthers' Week 13 loss to the Bucs.

impact: It's easy to forget that Jones caught eight balls for 93 yards and a touchdown in the Bills' Week 10 blowout win over the Jets.  That came with Matt Barkley at quarterback.  Jones has been a non-factor with Josh Allen under center.
report: Zay Jones went catch-less on one target in the Bills' Week 12 win.

impact: Following his zero-catch performance last week, Jones had a slightly better day on Sunday. He started it off by getting open in the back of the end zone in the second quarter for a 15-yard touchdown from a scrambling Josh Allen. Jones was wide open again in the end zone on the first drive of the third quarter, but Allen expected him to break off his route and threw behind him. Allen was able to find him along the sideline on the next drive, and Jones scored for the second time when Allen threaded a pass to him in coverage in the fourth quarter. He followed up that touchdown with a two-point conversion. Jones appeared to set the Bills up with first-and-goal late in the fourth, but the catch was reversed on review. Jones has now posted two great fantasy games in his last three, but he sandwiched those around a zero-catch effort. In an inconsistent passing attack, Jones is still not a fantasy option.
report: Zay Jones hauled in 4-of-9 targets for 67 yards and two touchdowns in the Bills' Week 13 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: The Saints surprisingly utilized former No. 10 overall pick Eli Apple in shadow coverage on Jones, allowing the stud receiver to dominate on a team-high 14 targets. Even so, Jones was responsible for one of Atlanta's three lost fumbles in the red zone Thursday.
