Another fumble occurred when Matt Ryan lost the ball while waiting on Julio to separate on a designed play for him inside the 10. Although Atlanta's offense as a whole leaves much to be desired, Jones has benefitted from a concerted effort to get him involved in the red zone since the team's bye. He's now on pace for a whopping 122/1,898/4, which would slot his 2018 campaign at No. 2 all-time in single-season receiving yards. He's a weekly WR1 whether he hits pay dirt or not.
report: Julio Jones hauled in 11-of-14 targets for 147 yards in Atlanta's Week 13 loss to the Saints.

impact: Jones was seen getting his right hand taped early in the game but was never announced with an injury. The Falcons simply could not sustain drives against the Ravens' elite defense. Jones was dealing with sticky coverage on nearly every play. Even if Jones sees a heavy dose of impressive rookie Jaire Alexander in Week 14, he will bounce back as an elite WR1 against the Packers.
report: Julio Jones caught 2-of-8 targets for 18 yards in the Falcons' Week 13 home loss to the Ravens.

impact: Jones continued to be a bright spot for a Packers offense that's taken a step back the last couple weeks. He went untouched from six yards out on his touchdown, but most of his yards came after contact. Jones remained involved in the pass game with 21 yards on three catches. Jamaal Williams barely saw the field behind Jones, getting just one carry. Jones will be a locked-in RB1 for Week 13 against the Cardinals.
report: Aaron Jones rushed 17 times for 72 yards and a touchdown in the Packers' Week 12 loss to the Vikings.

impact: The entire Green Bay offense bombed in what looked like a great spot for them to get on track at home against Arizona.  Jamaal Williams got way too many touches (11, for 27 yards), and Jones only turned in a usable fantasy performance because of his late-game touchdown from eight yards out, set up by Davante Adams' toe-tapping 19-yard sideline catch on the previous play.  Jones will remain a quality RB1/2 when the Packers host the Falcons next week, but coach Mike McCarthy really needs to get over his obsession with weekly black hole Williams.
report: Aaron Jones rushed 11 times for 36 yards and a touchdown and caught 4-of-4 targets for 16 yards in Green Bay's Week 13 loss to Arizona.

impact: Johnson's volume was terrible in a game the Cardinals played behind in the second half, but he didn't do much with his touches. It's the first time in the last four weeks Johnson has been held either under 100 total yards or a touchdown. Johnson has a good rebound spot against the Packers in Week 13.
report: David Johnson rushed 17 times for 63 yards and caught two passes for 16 yards in Week 12 against the Chargers.

impact: This was an incredibly frustrating game if you had any fantasy exposure to Johnson at all.  In a game where the Cardinals rushed for 182 yards and two touchdowns as a team, Johnson was held scoreless while rookie backup Chase Edmonds scored twice inside the ten-yard line.  Johnson's lack of passing-game usage was also befuddling.  Johnson did blow a blitz protection to get Josh Rosen sacked in the first quarter.  Returning home for Week 14 against the Lions, Johnson will remain a high-volatility RB2 play.
report: David Johnson rushed 20 times for 69 yards and caught 1-of-2 targets for three yards in Arizona's Week 13 win over Green Bay.

impact: With the Browns controlling the game from the opening drive, Johnson was hardly needed on the day. He now has just seven and three touches over his past two games after receiving 10 touches in his first game under Freddie Kitchens as offensive coordinator. Johnson will likely find game script more in his favor in Week 13 at the Texans, but will only be a lower-end FLEX play.
report: Duke Johnson rushed two times for 16 yards while catching 1-of-2 targets for 23 yards in Sunday's Week 12 win over the Bengals.

impact: Even with the Browns trailing by 23 points, Johnson wasn't used at all, managing just two touches. Johnson now has just 12 touches over the past three games and is an afterthought in the weekly game planning for the Browns.
report: Duke Johnson caught 2-of-3 targets for 12 yards in Sunday's Week 13 loss to the Texans.

impact: Jeffery has had back-to-back quiet games with just seven total grabs for 72 scoreless yards against the Saints and G-Men.  Jeffery hasn't topped 48 yards in four-straight games.  He'll be a WR2/3 next week against the Redskins, who just got torched by Amari Cooper for two scores on Thursday.
report: Alshon Jeffery caught all three of his targets for 39 yards in the Eagles' Week 12 win over the Giants.

impact: Jeffery has seen five targets or less in four of the last five games and three of the four since the Golden Tate trade.  He hasn't scored since Week 7 and hasn't topped 48 yards since then.  Jeffery has been the biggest loser since the Tate deal.  He's a tough sell as a WR3 next week at Dallas.
report: Alshon Jeffery caught 3-of-5 targets for 31 yards in the Eagles' Week 13 win over the Redskins.

impact: He was sacked once for a four-yard loss. Jackson rarely looked to run in the first half, accruing just 11 yards on two carries. He adopted a new philosophy after halftime, however, showing off his signature speed with a number of impressive scrambles including a 39-yard burst late in the fourth quarter. L-Jax also added his second career rushing touchdown, cramming it in from five yards out with 8:10 remaining in the third quarter. Jackson looked green at times, struggling to get the play off on numerous occasions while also taking an inexcusable delay of game penalty. Both of his interceptions came on tipped passes. Jackson showed off his arm strength in the second quarter by threading the needle to tight end Mark Andrews for a 74-yard pick-up. With Joe Flacco (hip) expected to resume practicing on Wednesday, it will be interesting to see if the Ravens turn back to their long-time starter or give Lamar another look next week against Atlanta.
report: Lamar Jackson completed 14-of-25 passes for 178 yards and a touchdown with two interceptions while adding an additional 71 yards and a touchdown on 11 carries Sunday in the Ravens’ Week 12 win over the Raiders.

impact: Jackson is a low-end QB1 as he makes his first road start in Atlanta.
report: Lamar Jackson is officially the Ravens' Week 13 starter at quarterback.

impact: Jackson was injured running into LT Ronnie Stanley on a failed red zone run. His status for the rest of the game is unclear.
report: Lamar Jackson was forced from Sunday's game against the Falcons with a potential concussion.

impact: Jackson was evaluated for nearly 20 minutes but was cleared to return after a long visit to the locker room. There is one quarter of play to go.
report: Lamar Jackson (concussion) has been cleared to return to Sunday's game against the Falcons.

impact: Jackson fumbled twice, losing one that was returned for a touchdown. Jackson missed nearly 20 minutes of real time in the second half as he was evaluated for a concussion but was finally cleared to return for the fourth quarter. His 13-yard rushing score was a true option where he took a big hit near the goal line but managed to clear the plane. Jackson missed a few easy throws, none easier than what should have been a long touchdown to John Brown early in the second quarter. Jackson had his feet set but just couldn't hit his wideout. With Joe Flacco (hip) likely returning for Week 14, it is unclear what the Ravens plan to do at quarterback. The team has hinted at a college-style timeshare. Harbaugh did say after the game that Jackson has "done enough" to keep the starting job.
report: Lamar Jackson completed 12-of-21 passes for 125 yards in the Ravens' 26-16, Week 13 win over the Falcons, adding 17 carries for 75 yards and a touchdown.

impact: Jackson was held without a carry in the first half. He stole the show after halftime, helping fuel the Chargers to a comeback win. Jackson's night was highlighted on an explosive go-ahead 18-yard touchdown late in the fourth quarter. Melvin Gordon has a chance to return against the Bengals, but Jackson should be this week's top waiver add.
report: Justin Jackson rushed eight times for 63 yards and a touchdown in the Chargers' Week 13 win over the Steelers.

impact: Mike Evans (116 yards) did the heavy lifting in Tampa Bay's Week 12 passing game, as no other Bucs pass catcher topped 54 yards.  Still, the eight targets were promising for Jackson, who draws a burnable Carolina secondary next.  The Panthers may be without No. 2 CB Donte Jackson (quad) in that game.
report: DeSean Jackson caught 3-of-8 targets for 19 yards in the Bucs' Week 12 win over the 49ers.

impact: Luck is now just the third player in NFL history to throw for at least three touchdowns in eight-consecutive games. With another three-score day in Week 13 against the collapsed Jaguars, Luck can join 2007 Tom Brady as only the second player with a nine-game streak. Although he was sacked for the first time since Week 5 today, Luck was perfect outside of throwing two picks in 14 seconds near the end of the first half. He once again featured his tight ends in the red zone, finding Eric Ebron for two more scores. Luck has begun to look scarily good in recent weeks, combining his 2018 efficiency with his pre-2018 big-play ability.
report: Andrew Luck completed 30-of-37 passes for 343 yards, three touchdowns and two interceptions in the Colts' 27-24, Week 12 win over the Dolphins.

impact: He added 16 yards on a pair of scrambles in a game where Colts pass catchers struggled to get open and Jacksonville's previously-dead defense came alive for its best performance all year.  Luck took three sacks and was hit nine times, with Yannick Ngakoue particularly standing out as a pass rusher.  Luck entered this game with three or more passing touchdowns in eight straight contests.  Expect him to get back on track in Week 14 at Houston.
report: Andrew Luck completed 33-of-52 passes for 248 yards and an interception in the Colts' Week 13 shutout loss to Jacksonville.

impact: Like the rest of the pass catchers, Lockett did not see many targets in the first half, but he made the most of them including a 27-yard catch-and-run to help spark a touchdown drive late in the second quarter. He scored himself after halftime, finding the end zone from 12 yards out to cap a long scoring drive. That score was his eighth of the season, and he has now scored in all but three games this year. His most impactful play was not a touchdown, however. With the game tied, Lockett worked open down the right sideline, and Russell Wilson found him for a 43-yard gain to set up the game-winning field goal. Seemingly scoring every week, Lockett will remain an upside WR3 next week against the 49ers.
report: Tyler Lockett hauled in all five of his targets for 107 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 12 win over the Panthers.

impact: It was a game of big plays for Lockett. His only catch was a 52-yard touchdown in which he did a great job shielding off the defenders and creating space for the catch in the first half. It was Lockett’s ninth touchdown of the season, and he has scored in all but three games this year. He made a splash again after halftime, taking the opening kick 84 yards to set up a Rashaad Penny touchdown run. He added a long defensive pass interference later in the game for good measure. The matchup next Monday against the Vikings is not great, but Lockett has earned weekly upside WR3 status with his touchdown prowess this season.
report: Tyler Lockett hauled in 1-of-2 targets for 52 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 13 win over the 49ers.

impact: Lewis' touches have been down the last two weeks in back-to-back blowout losses.  In this one, he was constantly getting hit behind the line and running into his own blockers, who were getting destroyed up front by the Texans' front seven.  Derrick Henry wasn't any better with 49 scoreless yards and a lost fumble on 10 touches.  Lewis will be an RB2 next week against the Jets.
report: Dion Lewis rushed seven times for eight yards and caught all seven of his targets for 33 yards in the Titans' Week 12 loss to the Texans.

impact: Lewis was a total non-factor in the second half, getting just two carries and an empty target after the break.  Marcus Mariota and Derrick Henry were moving the ball, with Henry scoring a short touchdown and Mariota amassing nearly 250 yards after half while tossing a game-winning score to Corey Davis with 36 seconds left.  Lewis will be an RB2/3 next week against the Jaguars.
report: Dion Lewis rushed six times for 36 yards and caught 2-of-3 targets for -2 yards in the Titans' Week 13 win over the Jets.

impact: Denver’s offense was mostly held in check in the first half, but Lindsay broke things open with a 32-yard explosion to kick-start a touchdown drive at the end of the second quarter. Lindsay stayed hot after the break, ripping off 12- and 14-yard runs on the opening drive of the third quarter. He also opened the fourth with a flurry of big plays, and he gave the Broncos the lead in the final quarter with a two-yard score. The only thing holding Lindsay back right now is a lack of carries -- for some reason, he has just 25 in the last two games despite averaging 7.6 per carry. He will be a borderline RB1 in a great matchup with the Bengals next week.
report: Phillip Lindsay rushed 14 times for 110 yards and a touchdown in the Broncos' Week 12 win over the Steelers.

impact: The Broncos always had a good shot to follow in the footsteps of other opposing offenses and paste the Bengals' defense for numerous points, but Lindsay made it look easy throughout the day. Not only did he outrun Cincinnati's entire secondary to put the Broncos on the board with a 65-yard touchdown sprint, he later showed patience in waiting for his blocking from six yards out and running up the middle for his second score of the day. Lindsay's now out-touched teammate Royce Freeman 34-18 in the last two games, efficiently rushing for a total of 267 yards (8.09 YPC) and three scores in that stint. Clearly the team's leading back for the rest of the season, he'll again be an RB1 in San Francisco next week.
report: Phillip Lindsay rushed 19 times for 157 yards and two touchdowns in the Broncos' Week 13 win over the Bengals.

impact: Landry was a victim of not being a part of the Browns offensive explosion in the first half and then buried by the team attempting just four passes in the second half. Landry has now received just 17 targets over his three games since the Browns coaching shake up, catching just 10 passes over that span for 102 yards. Landry has now posted 50 or fewer receiving yards in 6-of-8 starts by Baker Mayfield. He has to now be treated as a lower-end WR3 option moving forward. The Browns play at Houston in Week 13.
report: Jarvis Landry caught 3-of-5 targets for 30 yards in Sunday's Week 12 win over the Bengals.

impact: After being held to 50 or fewer yards in four straight games, Landry led the team in targets, catches and yards on Sunday. His overall production wasn't entirely aided by the Browns in catch-up mode in the second half as he caught three passes for 45 yards in the first half. Landry has has an up-and-down first season in Cleveland, but is still a WR3 option based on target potential each week. He gets another matchup in Week 14 against a struggling Panthers secondary, but still comes along with a pedestrian floor paired with a marginal ceiling.
report: Jarvis Landry caught 6-of-9 targets for 103 yards in Sunday's Week 13 loss to the Texans.

impact: Kirk led the Cardinals in receiving, but there wasn't much he could do in a game Josh Rosen threw for only 105 yards. He also had the team high in targets. Kirk is having a solid rookie year despite league worst quarterback play. He'll be on the FLEX radar for Week 13.
report: Christian Kirk caught 4-of-6 targets for 41 yards in Week 12 against the Chargers.

impact: He added a 23-yard gain on the ground.  Kirk has shown promise as a rookie wideout and punt returner, but Arizona's passing game isn't capable of supporting much fantasy-caliber production in the air.  Kirk will be a WR4/flex option when the Cardinals square off with Darius Slay's Lions in Week 14.
report: Christian Kirk caught 3-of-8 targets for 54 yards in the Cardinals' Week 13 upset win over Green Bay.

impact: Nick Mullens entered this game 13-of-14 when targeting Kittle on the season.  As Mullens took a significant step back with happy feet and inaccuracy, so too did Kittle's box-score production.  Kittle will remain a TE1 when the 49ers visit Seattle next, but his quarterback play is becoming a concern.
report: George Kittle caught 6-of-12 targets for 48 yards in the 49ers' Week 12 loss to Tampa Bay.

impact: Coming off something of a down week, Kittle bounced back with a solid if not spectacular showing in this one. His biggest play of the game was a 28-yard grab in the third quarter. Kittle will remain a solid TE1 next week against the Broncos.
report: George Kittle hauled in 6-of-9 targets for 70 yards in the 49ers' Week 13 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: Kearse's 66 yards were his most since Week 6 while the targets were a new season high. The Titans' secondary allows a healthy amount of receiver yardage, but Kearse will not be a recommended WR4 for Week 13.
report: Jermaine Kearse caught 6-of-12 targets for 66 yards and a touchdown in the Jets' Week 12 loss to the Patriots.

impact: The 72 yards from scrimmage were Kamara's fewest since Week 5, though the eight receptions were his most since Week 3. The Saints' offense was gasping for air against a Cowboys defense that came out swinging. There was a scary moment in the fourth quarter where Kamara took an obvious, unflagged helmet-to-helmet hit from Jaylon Smith. He was woozy but was ultimately cleared to return. Kamara should bounce back with a Week 14 rampage in Tampa Bay.
report: Alvin Kamara rushed 11 times for 36 yards in the Saints' Week 13 loss to the Cowboys, adding eight receptions for 36 additional yards.

impact: Keenum did not have much success early in this one and missed Emmanuel Sanders on what should have been a big gain, but he was able to find Matt LaCosse on back-to-back throws late in the second quarter for the Broncos first touchdown of the game. Following a slow start in the second half, Keenum made the most of his defense gifting him a short field off an interception, hitting Sanders for a 38-yard catch before finding him one play later for a five-yard touchdown. Following another Pittsburgh turnover, Keenum led a long scoring drive to give the Broncos the lead in the fourth quarter. He did not have to do much, but he did enough to secure an important win. With the Bengals on deck next week, Keenum will be a viable streaming option.
report: Case Keenum completed 15-of-28 passes for 197 yards and two touchdowns in the Broncos' Week 12 win over the Steelers.

impact: Despite being in a plus matchup against Cincinnati's injury-riddled secondary, Keenum ultimately wasn't asked to do much as the Broncos rode Phillip Lindsay (19/157/2) and Royce Freeman (12/48) to victory. Keenum didn't even look to Emmanuel Sanders (4/19) all too often, instead chunking high-upside grenades to explosive rookie Courtland Sutton (4/85/1) down the sidelines and into the end zone. Keenum has another tasty matchup against San Francisco's secondary next week, but it's clear the Broncos prefer to take the weight off his shoulders and back Lindsay as they continue to push for the postseason. Keenum is merely a borderline QB2 in 2-QB leagues in Week 14.
report: Case Keenum completed 12-of-21 passes for 151 yards and one score as the Broncos defeated the Bengals handily in Week 13.

impact: Drake's 33-yard receiving score on a free play first quarter screen was the Dolphins' first offensive touchdown in 27 possessions. He was barely touched on his 14-yard ground score in the fourth quarter. It was the fourth where Drake went down in a heap of pain at the end of a negative run. It appeared he had maybe broken his arm. He was announced with a shoulder injury before returning for the Dolphins' final series. Although Drake returned in Indy, his practice status will be worth monitoring ahead of next Sunday's game against the Bills.
report: Kenyan Drake caught 5-of-6 targets for 64 yards and a touchdown in the Dolphins' Week 12 loss to the Colts, adding eight carries for 32 yards and an additional score.

impact: Drake is still behind Frank Gore in the pecking order and Miami is using Kalen Ballage in Wildcat formations, but touchdowns have kept him in the fantasy conversation this season. That continued in this game. Just before the half, Drake was left alone in the flat, and Ryan Tannehill hit him for a three-yard score. It was his eighth touchdown of the season. Drake added a 20-yard run on what ended up being the game-winning drive. He will be a volatile FLEX option next week against the Patriots.
report: Kenyan Drake rushed seven times for 31 yards and hauled in 2-of-4 targets for 13 yards and a touchdown in the Dolphins' Week 13 win over the Bills.

impact: Driskel also added nine rushing yards and a touchdown on the ground after taking over for Andy Dalton early in the third quarter. Entering the game down 35-7, Driskel found Cleveland coasting to win, passing for just 5.3 yards per pass attempt despite the lofty volume. Dalton's Week 13 status will surely be up in the air to start Week 13, but Driskel will only be a lower-end QB2 option with no teams on bye if he is forced into a starting job against the Broncos.
report: Jeff Driskel completed 17-of-29 passes for 155 yards with one touchdown in Sunday's Week 12 loss to the Browns.

impact: The score was Doyle's second in four contests since returning from his hip injury, though he got out-targeted 7-4 by Eric Ebron, who had yet to draw more looks in a game since Doyle's return. Ultimately, Doyle should continue to see heavier usage even if Ebron is the preferred target in the red zone. Doyle will maintain TE1 appeal for Week 13 against the Jags' leaky tight end defense.
report: Jack Doyle caught 4-of-4 targets for 16 yards and a touchdown in the Colts' Week 12 win over the Dolphins.

impact: Doctson's yards and targets led the team on a day Mark Sanchez completed 13-of-21 passes for 100 yards and no scores in relief of Colt McCoy, who broke a leg in the first half.  McCoy was 4-of-4 for 50 yards before leaving, including a 32-yard hookup to Doctson.  Doctson will go back to irrelevancy the rest of the season with Sanchez starting Week 14 against the Giants.
report: Josh Doctson caught 3-of-5 targets for 51 yards in the Redskins' Week 13 loss to the Eagles.

impact: Dixon was the Ravens' clear-cut No. 2 back, though a distant No. 2 to Gus Edwards, who ran the ball 21 times. Ty Montgomery also mixed in for five catches. Barring missed time for Edwards, who seemed to tweak his ankle late in Atlanta, Dixon will lack Week 14 fantasy value against the Chiefs.
report: Making his first appearance since Week 1, Ravens RB Kenneth Dixon rushed eight times for 37 yards in Baltimore's Week 13 win over the Falcons, adding a six-yard reception.

impact: Diggs didn't look limited at all despite being a game-time decision due to a nagging knee injury. As expected, he saw a fair amount of Stephon Gilmore while Jason McCourty spent the afternoon chasing Adam Thielen. The 49 yards were Diggs' fewest since Week 7. Sunday also snapped a three-game touchdown streak for the talented 25-year-old. Diggs will try to do better when the Vikings travel to Seattle for Monday Night Football in Week 14.
report: Stefon Diggs absorbed all five of his targets for 49 yards Sunday in Minnesota’s Week 13 loss to New England.

impact: He logged a career-high in targets despite being in on just 19 of the Ravens' 70 offensive snaps. That was one more than fellow rookie Mark Andrews and 32 fewer than blocking tight end Nick Boyle. The 2018 first-rounder has yet to clear 30 yards receiving in a game this year and won't be a recommended streamer next week, even against the Falcons' anemic secondary.
report: Hayden Hurst compiled three catches for 25 yards on four targets Sunday in Baltimore’s Week 12 victory over the Raiders.

impact: Hyde was a predictable bust filling in for suspended Leonard Fournette, doing his best to keep the Colts in the game.  The Jags wound up winning with defense and T.J. Yeldon, who led the team in receiving.  Hyde will go back to the bench when Fournette returns for Week 14 against the Titans on Thursday Night Football.
report: Carlos Hyde rushed 13 times for 36 yards, caught his lone target for a gain of one, and lost a fumble in the Jaguars' Week 13 win over the Colts.

impact: The Bucs' slot receiver has now caught a touchdown from Jameis Winston in back-to-back games.  Humphries' week-to-week usage is never reliable, but his outlooks have been betteer when Winston plays than with Ryan Fitzpatrick.  Humphries will be a volatile WR3 option when the Bucs host Carolina next.
report: Adam Humphries caught 6-of-6 targets for 54 yards and a touchdown in the Bucs' Week 12 win over the 49ers.

impact: Matt Ryan seeded a ball through a tight window for Hooper's one-yard score in the fourth quarter. The touchdown was Hooper's fourth of the season. Reliably catching 4-5 weekly passes, Hooper has settled in as a borderline TE1. Blowup weeks will be rare, but the same is true of zeros. The Falcons are headed to Green Bay for Week 14.
report: Austin Hooper caught 5-of-5 targets for 44 yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' Week 13 loss to the Ravens.

impact: Brutal. With Chase Daniel presenting zero down-field threat, the Bears could not get anything on the ground against the Lions' improving run defense. The 15 yards from scrimmage were by far Howard's fewest of the season, though he was also head to 32 two weeks ago. Completely touchdown-or-bust as a run-only running back, Howard is a low-upside RB2/3.
report: Jordan Howard rushed seven times for 13 yards in the Bears' Week 12 win over the Lions, adding a two-yard reception.

impact: Howard was impressive in the first half, gaining 68 yards on the ground before the break.  He had pickups of 21 and 25 yards to set up a touchdown to Adam Shaheen.  Howard disappeared after that as Tarik Cohen took over and totaled 186 yards with a passing score.  Howard will be a TD-or-bust RB2/3 next week at home against the Rams.  He's a tough sell every week.
report: Jordan Howard rushed 16 times for 76 yards in the Bears' Week 13 loss to the Giants.

impact: Hopkins came into Monday night having registered 100 yards and/or one touchdown in seven-straight games and 8-of-10 times on the year.  His six targets still led the team on a night Deshaun Watson again attempted fewer than 25 passes.  Watson has attempted 25-or-fewer passes in six-straight games.  Hopkins was the target on a deep ball into the end zone from 47 yards out, but Adoree Jackson covered it well.  Demaryius Thomas was the red-zone beneficiary tonight with 12- and 10-yard scores.  Hopkins will get Denzel Ward of the Browns next week.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 5-of-6 targets for 74 yards in the Texans' 34-17, Week 12 win over the Titans on Monday night.

impact: Hopkins was once again the most-targeted player in the Houston passing game, turning in his typical game of making contested catches with multiple toe-dragging receptions. Hopkins has now cleared 100-yards just once over his past seven games, but remains a high-end WR1 option in Week 14 at home against the Colts.
report: DeAndre Hopkins caught 7-of-12 targets for 91 yards in Sunday's Week 13 win over the Browns.

impact: Davis continued to work as the passing-down option in this one, but he was actually out-targeted 2-to-1 by Chris Carson. With Rashaad Penny also getting touches, Davis can be left on the wire.
report: Mike Davis rushed four times for 14 yards in the Seahawks' Week 12 win over the Panthers.

impact: He added 39 yards on an end-around rushing attempt, giving him 135 total yards on the night.  The Titans were working it to Davis early and often, as he was smoking Johnathan Joseph in coverage while also drawing a 33-yard DPI penalty on another DB, but the offense mysteriously went away from him much of the second half.  With one of his two second-half looks, Davis roasted Joseph for a 48-yard TD grab down the right side.  One of the most unpredictable players in a totally unpredictable offense, boom-or-bust Davis will be a WR2 next week against the Jets.
report: Corey Davis caught all four of his targets for 96 yards and a touchdown in the Titans' 34-17, Week 12 loss to the Texans on Monday night.

impact: Davis' 11-yard touchdown with 36 seconds left on the clock on 3rd-and-6 in the fourth quarter proved to be the game-winner with the Titans trailing 22-19.  Davis has scored in three of the last four games and continues to pace the Titans in targets.  He'll be a WR3 next week against the Jags.
report: Corey Davis caught 3-of-7 targets for 42 yards and one touchdown in the Titans' Week 13 win over the Jets.

impact: It's the best possible news after Dalton departed Sunday's loss early, but his Week 13 status remains unclear. Even a sprain could keep a quarterback out multiple games. The Bengals may also not be in a hurry after Jeff Driskel looked competent against the Browns. Dalton's status will be updated no later than Wednesday, when the Bengals return to practice.
report: Andy Dalton has been diagnosed with a sprained thumb and is day to day.

impact: A trendy WR3 selection in fantasy leagues over the summer, Hogan has been among this year's biggest disappointments. He's seen a combined 10 targets over his last five games and hasn't scored a touchdown since Week 2. Even in deeper leagues, Hogan remains glued to the waiver wire.
report: Chris Hogan produced two catches for 20 yards on two targets Sunday in the Patriots’ Week 13 win over the Vikings.

impact: Just like that, Hilton has now posted back-to-back 125-yard games after he entered Week 11 with a 2018 high of 115. Hilton was the intended target on Andrew Luck's first interception, essentially having his route run for him by Xavien Howard. Otherwise, he was the player we came to know before Luck's shoulder woes. Although he's once again locked in as an every-week WR1 at home, Hilton will have to contend with Jalen Ramsey on the road in Week 13.
report: T.Y. Hilton caught 7-of-10 targets for 125 yards in the Colts' Week 12 win over the Dolphins.

impact: Hilton had his fair share of wins, but this was an epic battle against Jalen Ramsey that Ramsey ultimately won in the Jaguars' 6-0 shutout upset victory.  Hilton got shaken up on a tough fourth-quarter catch in Ramsey's coverage but only missed one play.  Hilton will get a better Week 14 matchup against the Texans, who lost CB Johnathan Joseph to a neck injury on Sunday.
report: T.Y. Hilton caught 8-of-13 targets for 77 yards in the Colts' Week 13 loss to Jacksonville.

impact: Hill has averaged 12.3 targets with Watkins hurt and 7.1 targets in Kansas City's other eight games.  Although we can't expect this small-sample split stat to carry over directly to Week 13, it does suggest Hill has an elevated target expectation with Watkins on the shelf.  (Watkins is ruled out for Week 13 at Oakland with a foot injury.)  You can read more splits and game-specific tidbits in Evan Silva's Week 13 Matchups column, accessible at the link below.
report: Tyreek Hill has drawn double-digit targets in all three games in which Sammy Watkins has either played fewer than 15 snaps or missed entirely.

impact: If you were watching live, this was quite a tilting experience. Hill committed two drops, one of which was stunningly bad on what should have been a 52-yard touchdown late in the third quarter. The next period, Patrick Mahomes had Hill for a 57-yard score, but he underthrew the pass. Hill still had a chance to corral it but could not make the necessary mid-air adjustment. Hill was so close to a monster day in the final week of the fantasy regular season and just could not convert. He has a tough Week 14 matchup in the Ravens at home.
report: Tyreek Hill caught 1-of-6 targets for 13 yards in the Chiefs' Week 13 win over the Raiders, adding two rushes for 37 additional yards.

impact: The eight touches were Hines' most in three games. Hines could have some Week 13 FLEX appeal against the Jaguars if Marlon Mack (concussion) can't get cleared, though Jordan Wilkins would be the favorite for early-down work.
report: Nyheim Hines rushed nine times for 28 yards in the Colts' Week 12 win over the Dolphins, adding two receptions for 22 additional yards.

impact: The Colts got nothing going on the ground and resorted to short passes, an approach that favored Hines over lead back Marlon Mack.  Andrew Luck wound up with 52 pass attempts.  Hines now has averaged nine touches per game since the Colts' Week 9 bye. He will be a low-end flex option specific to PPR leagues when Indianapolis travels to Houston for Week 14.
report: Nyheim Hines rushed four times for five yards but caught 9-of-9 targets for 50 yards in the Colts' Week 13 loss to Jacksonville.

impact: Heuerman helped set up a first-quarter field goal with a 29-yard catch, but he had to watch as Matt LaCosse caught two quick passes at the end of the second quarter including a ten-yard touchdown. Heuerman added a 15-yard catch in the second half, enough to give him the second-most yards on the team, but he left in the fourth quarter with a back injury. If that injury ends up being minor, he will be a streaming option next week against the spiraling Bengals.
report: Jeff Heuerman hauled in 2-of-3 targets for 44 yards in the Broncos' Week 12 win over the Steelers.

impact: Henry was the target on Marcus Mariota's lone incompletion on 23 attempts.  He also lost a fumble at the end of a 12-yard catch-and-run on the final Mariota completion in the fourth quarter.  Henry out-produced Dion Lewis, but neither was good in this one.  Henry isn't a glowing fantasy option heading into Week 13 against the Jets, though he's always a candidate for a short score.
report: Derrick Henry rushed eight times for 30 yards and caught 2-of-3 targets for 19 yards in the Titans' Week 12 loss to the Texans.

impact: He caught his two targets for five yards.  This has become the new norm for Henry -- minimal yards and a short touchdown.  He's a boom-bust RB3/FLEX in standard leagues.  The same will be the case next week vs. Jacksonville.
report: Derrick Henry rushed 10 times for 40 yards and one touchdown in the Titans' Week 13 win over the Jets.

impact: In addition to the sluggish stat line, Burton lost a fumble and committed a costly offensive pass interference penalty. In Burton's defense, the fumble call seemed borderline. Burton is occasionally blowing up but mostly producing as a fringe TE1. The Bears are headed to New Jersey to take on the Giants in Week 13.
report: Trey Burton caught 4-of-7 targets for 28 yards in the Bears' Week 12 win over the Lions.

impact: The Giants came into Week 13 giving up the seventh-most catches for the seventh-most yards to tight ends.  Burton was nowhere to be found as Adam Shaheen came off I.R. and scored a two-yard TD on his lone target.  Burton has been extremely boom-bust year one in Chicago.  He has five touchdowns, but Burton hasn't topped 40 yard since Week 7 and has just one score in that span.  Burton will again be on the TE1 borderline next week at home against the Rams.
report: Trey Burton failed to catch his lone target in the Bears' Week 13, 30-27 overtime loss to the Giants.

impact: Making his return from an eight-game absence, Burkhead was in on 17 of New England's 74 offensive snaps. With Sony Michel entrenched as New England's lead back and James White continuing his superb work on passing downs, Burkhead will probably be limited to change-of-pace duties down the stretch. The Dolphins are up next for the 9-3 Patriots.
report: Rex Burkhead chipped in with 20 yards on seven carries while also contributing two catches for 21 yards on two targets Sunday in the Patriots’ Week 13 victory over the Vikings.

impact: Brown is well-known for his boom-or-bust tendencies and obviously Sunday's clunker falls squarely in the "bust" category. Smokey got off to a strong start, nabbing a 25-yard dart from Lamar Jackson early in the first quarter. That marked Brown's eighth catch of at least 25 yards this season. He committed a head-scratching drop later in the quarter, though Jackson probably could have put more mustard on it. Brown also had a 48-yard grab come off the board due to a holding penalty on the offensive line. The fifth-year deep threat has pulled in just eight-of-21 targets during his current four-game touchdown drought. We'll see what he can cobble together against Atlanta in Week 13.
report: John Brown managed just one catch for 25 yards on seven targets Sunday in the Ravens’ Week 12 victory over Oakland.

impact: Brown should have had a 51-yard touchdown early in the second quarter, but Lamar Jackson flat missed him despite having time to set his feet and uncork a deep ball. The Ravens ran the same play later in the game, but the Falcons were ready for it that time. Brown now has just two catches in three games with dual-threat Jackson under center. Joe Flacco could be returning for Week 14, though Jackson is not going to be outright benched. Brown cannot be trusted for the fantasy playoffs.
report: John Brown was held without a catch on four targets in the Ravens' Week 13 win over the Falcons.

impact: The Broncos were allowing the Steelers to dink and dunk all game, but unlike JuJu Smith-Schuster, Brown was not able to break off the big play to help boost his catch average. He should have had a long gain near the sideline in the fourth quarter, but he was not able to get both feet down. This game ended Brown's eight-game touchdown streak, but he still came through in a big way in PPR leagues. Even with a tough matchup against the Chargers up next, Brown will remain a solid WR1.
report: Antonio Brown hauled in 9-of-13 targets for 67 yards in the Steelers' Week 12 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Breida opened the contest with a 33-yard burst and ripped off chunk-yardage gains all day long, but the 49ers fell behind and never caught up as Nick Mullens struggled, throwing two picks for the second straight start.  The good news is Breida's health has largely returned after he battled myriad early-season injuries.  Breida will remain a quality RB2 play in Week 13 at Seattle.
report: Matt Breida rushed 14 times for 106 yards and caught 3-of-4 targets for 34 yards in the 49ers' Week 12 loss to Tampa Bay.

impact: His total yardage wasn't too impressive, but Brees hit four different UDFAs (Tommylee Lewis, Dan Arnold, Austin Carr, Keith Kirkwood) for touchdowns Thursday as the Saints stayed efficient on offense throughout the night. Brees' lone flaw of the evening occurred because Kirkwood slipped at the end of a route. Even Michael Thomas (4/38) essentially had the night off as New Orleans forced five fumbles and coasted behind stellar defense and explosiveness up the middle from Alvin Kamara (14/89) and Mark Ingram (11/52). Brees tied an NFL record by hitting 13 different receivers for pay dirt this season, all but securing his late-season run as league MVP. He'll be an easy QB1 despite having his work cut out for him against Dallas' stout pass rush in Week 13.
report: Drew Brees completed 15-of-22 passes for 171 yards, four touchdowns, and one pick in the Saints' Week 12 rout of the Falcons.

impact: Brees entered halftime 7-of-13 for 39 yards and was scarcely better after the break. His touchdown was a 30-yarder to Keith Kirkwood in a crowded part of the end zone. His pick was a truly inexplicable miss to Alvin Kamara. Brees unloaded the ball behind his running back as pressure was in his face. It ended up being the Saints' final play of the night. The Cowboys played absolutely lights-out defense, but Brees needed to be better. He undoubtedly will be in Week 14 when the Saints travel to Tampa Bay to take on the Bucs' barely-there defense.
report: Drew Brees completed 18-of-28 passes for 127 yards, one touchdown and one interception in the Saints' 13-10, Week 13 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: All of his production occurred in the first half, including a first-quarter score from six yards out.  Brate's lone missed target was a pass from Jameis Winston to him in the end zone that fell incomplete.  Brate will remain a touchdown-or-bust streamer when Tampa Bay hosts Carolina next.
report: Cameron Brate caught 3-of-4 targets for 26 yards and a touchdown in the Bucs' Week 12 win over San Francisco.

impact: He was unable to take advantage of Marquise Goodwin and Pierre Garcon's absences, as Dante Pettis and George Kittle did the heavy lifting in San Francisco's passing game.  Bourne is a complementary role player in an offense with major quarterback question marks with Nick Mullens getting worse each week.
report: Kendrick Bourne caught 2-of-3 targets for 27 yards in the 49ers' Week 12 loss to Tampa Bay.

impact: Going by the "eye test," Brady did not look great, throwing some turf missiles and an early third down hospital ball. Nevertheless, the box score was solid, producing Brady's first multi-score game in four starts. His best throw was his 34-yard first quarter touchdown strike to Rob Gronkowski, where the gargantuan tight end split two-deep coverage. Brady has just four scores over his past four games heading into a tough Week 13 matchup with the Vikings.
report: Tom Brady completed 20-of-31 passes for 283 yards and two touchdowns in the Patriots' 27-13, Week 12 win over the Jets.

impact: Brady wasn't sacked in this one. Touchdown Tom spent the bulk of his afternoon dishing out screen passes to running back James White, though he did find time to hit Josh Gordon for a wide-open 24-yard touchdown, which broke a 10-all tie with 35 seconds left in the third quarter. Brady's interception, his eighth of the year, came in the fourth quarter on a play where he was hit by blitzing safety Harrison Smith. The 41-year-old achieved two more milestones on Sunday, tying Brett Favre for third on the NFL's all-time touchdown list while also reaching 1,000 yards rushing for his career. It only took him 265 games to climb that mountain. The Pats will take a 9-3 record into next week's game in Miami, a place where Brady has struggled throughout his career.
report: Tom Brady completed 24-of-32 passes for 311 yards with a touchdown and an interception while adding five yards on two rushes Sunday in New England’s Week 13 win over the Vikings.

impact: Boyd bounced back in a loss with his most catches and yards since A.J. Green was sidelined. Boyd managed just two catches for 23 yards in the first half, but then was peppered with opportunity in the second half with Cincinnati trailing huge. Boyd caught a 26-yard score from backup quarterback Jeff Driskel to make the score 35-14 in the third quarter. Boyd will enter Week 13 as WR3 option if Driskel is forced to start next week against the Broncos.
report: Tyler Boyd caught 7-of-8 targets for 85 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 12 loss to the Browns.

impact: A.J. Green (foot) was carted off mid-game, allowing Boyd to finish with a team-high 97 yards through the air. He nearly tripled-up Cincinnati's next closest receiver in yardage (C.J. Uzomah, 33). Even with Green presumably out for the rest of the season, Boyd's ceiling will be extremely limited moving forward as long as he's catching passes from Jeff '6.2 YPA' Driskel. He'll still be a usage-based borderline WR2 next week as the Bengals attempt to keep pace with the Chargers.
report: Tyler Boyd soaked up 6-of-8 targets for 97 yards in the Bengals' Week 13 loss to the Broncos.

impact: He rushed six times for 28 yards.  The Jags' passing game was a nightmare with Bortles as the biggest culprit to the extent we were slightly surprised he didn't get benched for Cody Kessler.  Jacksonville has now lost seven straight games.  Even against the Colts, Bortles will remain a high-risk QB2 in Week 13 at risk of in-game benchings should he continue to give the other team the ball.
report: Blake Bortles completed 12-of-23 passes for 127 yards, one touchdown, and two interceptions in the Jaguars' Week 12 loss to Buffalo.

impact: He added a 13-yard catch on his lone target.  Blue's 14 touches were actually one more than Lamar Miller, but Miller easily out-gained him with 167 yards, including a 97-yard touchdown.  Miller got most of the second half off in the comfortable win, so we wouldn't read too much into Blue out-touching his backfield mate.  Blue isn't a fantasy option with Miller healthy and playing well.
report: Alfred Blue rushed 13 times for 49 yards in the Texans' Week 12 win over the Titans.

impact: Happy Thanksgiving. The ultimate fantasy troll was in rare form today, running in straight lines but dragging tacklers in the process. It was a classic "gets better as the game goes on" performance against the Bears' otherwise swarming defense. Blount will be a touchdown-based FLEX for Week 13 against the Rams if Kerryon Johnson (knee) misses another game.
report: LeGarrette Blount rushed 19 times for 88 yards and two touchdowns in the Lions' Week 12 loss to the Bears, adding a 15-yard reception.

impact: Predictably, Blount dropped his lone target. That one really hurt as Blount was wide open on a screen pass that surely would have gone for a big gain. Blount snoozed through the first half (11 yards on six carries) but livened up after halftime, rolling to 50 yards on 10 second-half totes. With Kerryon Johnson (knee) still not practicing, Blount could be in for another start next week when the Lions travel to Arizona.
report: LeGarrette Blount rushed for 61 yards on 16 carries and was unable to reel in his lone target Sunday in Detroit’s Week 13 loss to Los Angeles.

impact: Bernard now has just five carries for 21 yards and seven catches for 62 yards over his three games since returning to the lineup. Bernard is nothing more than a handcuff and not a fantasy option in Week 13 against the Broncos.
report: Giovani Bernard rushed one time for 10 yards while catching one pass for 12 yards in Sunday's Week 12 loss to the Browns.

impact: Unlike previous weeks, Bernard was actually involved over teammate Joe Mixon down the stretch. Mixon still led the Bengals with 12 carries to Bernard's five, but Gio quietly tied Tyler Boyd with a team-high eight targets as Cincinnati went into catch-up mode early. It would make sense the Bengals utilize both Mixon and Bernard against the Chargers next week, but the latter is still just a handcuff at this point of the season.
report: Giovani Bernard rushed five times for 14 yards, tacking on six catches for 32 yards in the Bengals' Week 13 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Since the acquisition of Amari Cooper, Beasley has just 13 grabs for 109 scoreless yards in four games.  Beasley has taken a big step back and is no longer worth rostering in redraft formats ahead of Week 13 against the Saints.
report: Cole Beasley caught 1-of-2 targets for five yards in the Cowboys' Week 12 win over the Redskins.

impact: One of Beasley's catches was a huge fourth quarter first down that was actually just a miserably-bad spot. The Saints were out of challenges. Beasley's already limited fantasy value has been fading to black since Amari Cooper's arrival.
report: Cole Beasley caught 2-of-3 targets for nine yards in the Cowboys' Week 13 win over the Saints.

impact: Baldwin entered this game nursing a groin injury, but he appeared to be healthy in this one, getting a deep target on the second drive. He should have had a wide-open touchdown in the second quarter, but Russell Wilson missed him in the end zone for the second week in a row. Baldwin did tack on four catches in the second half, but he gained just 23 yards on them and is now averaging just 7.6 yards on his last 17 catches. Just a touchdown-or-bust option at this point, Baldwin will be just a FLEX option next week against the 49ers.
report: Doug Baldwin hauled in 5-of-7 targets for 39 yards in the Seahawks' Week 12 win over the Panthers.

impact: There were not many targets to go around in this one, but Baldwin made his count. After drawing a defensive pass interference penalty to set the Seahawks up at the one, Baldwin lost his defender in traffic and hauled in a short touchdown. It was his second touchdown in three games after failing to score in the first ten weeks. Baldwin has not flashed much yardage upside this season, but hopefully he can regularly find the end zone down the stretch.
report: Doug Baldwin caught 2-of-4 targets for 22 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 13 win over the 49ers.

impact: Barkley did all of his damage in the first half, curiously receiving just four carries and five touches total after the break.  He wasn't injured, but the Giants sat him out the second series of the third quarter, and the offense never moved the ball the rest of the way.  Barkley started out hot with a 13-yard touchdown catch on a screen before then breaking off a 51-yard rushing score late in the second quarter to stake the G-Men to a 19-3 lead they'd eventually blow.  The 13 carries were Barkley's fewest since Week 4.  He'll get a tough draw against the Bears next week.
report: Saquon Barkley rushed 13 times for 101 yards and one touchdown and caught 7-of-8 targets for 41 yards and an additional touchdown in the Giants' 25-22, Week 12 loss to the Eagles.

impact: Barkley got off to an extremely slow start with the Bears defense keying on him and the Giants going three-and-out on four of their first five possessions with the other one ending in an interception.  Barkley, however, was able to break off a 22-yard run on 3rd-and-23 at the end of the half to set up a 57-yard field goal.  He later started OT with a 29-yarder to set up the eventual winning kick.  Barkley did leave the game at one point with a shoulder injury but later returned.  He may miss some practice reps ahead of next week at the Redskins.
report: Saquon Barkley rushed 24 times for 126 yards and caught 3-of-4 targets for 21 yards in the Giants' Week 13 overtime win over the Bears.

impact: He out-touched Jacquizz Rodgers 20 to 9, earning more work as Tampa Bay operated in positive game script while protecting their lead in Sunday's 27-9 victory.  Not flashy or capable of ripping frequent big plays, Barber will remain a touchdown-dependent, volume-based RB2 option when the Bucs host the Panthers' swiss-cheese defense next.
report: Peyton Barber rushed 18 times for 47 yards and a touchdown and caught 2-of-2 targets for 16 yards in the Bucs' Week 12 win over the 49ers.

impact: Barber had good volume early but wasn't effective with his carries. He didn't make any notable plays, with his touchdown coming on a goal-line conversion. Ronald Jones saw just four carries behind Barber and remained a non-factor in his return from injury. Barber is a touchdown-dependent RB3 for Week 14.
report: Peyton Barber rushed 16 times for 45 yards and a touchdown in Week 13 against the Panthers.

impact: Gronk's first target was a third down hospital ball from Tom Brady on the Pats' opening possession. The quarterback atoned one series later, delivering a perfect 34-yard touchdown strike as Gronk split two-deep coverage. Gronk still did not seem to be moving terribly well. It's going to be a gut-it-out stretch run for the 29-year-old All-Pro. The Vikings are on deck for Week 13.
report: Rob Gronkowski caught 3-of-7 targets for 56 yards and a touchdown in the Patriots' Week 12 win over the Jets.

impact: His longest gain of the afternoon came on a 15-yard dart from Tom Brady, which keyed a Patriots scoring drive late in the third quarter. We knew injuries would catch up to Gronk sooner or later and it seems his decline has finally begun. The 29-year-old doesn't move well and can't create separation liked he used to. Despite his struggles, Gronk remains an every-week starter at a thin fantasy position. We'll see what he can muster against the Dolphins in Week 14.
report: Rob Gronkowski came down with three grabs for 26 yards on four targets Sunday in the Patriots’ Week 13 victory over Minnesota.

impact: The Rams as a whole looked sluggish coming off last week's bye, but Gurley sure didn't. After mostly taking a backseat in L.A.'s entertaining win over Kansas City two weeks ago (an ankle injury hampered him in that game), Gurley returned to the limelight with a stellar showing in the Motor City. Working as the Rams' only healthy back (backup Malcolm Brown was lost to a shoulder injury in the first half), Gurley added his 18th and 19 touchdowns of the season with both scores coming in the second half. Gurley teased fantasy owners by purposely going down on the one-yard line on what should have been a walk-in touchdown with little time remaining (he pulled a similar stunt against the Packers earlier this year), but he saved fantasy owners a panic attack by scoring later in the drive. The win clinched L.A.'s second straight division title. The NFC-leading Rams will head to Chicago next week to face the Bears on Sunday Night Football. That game, of course, will be shown on NBC.
report: Todd Gurley rumbled to 132 yards and two touchdowns on 23 carries while adding three catches for 33 yards on five targets Sunday in the Rams’ Week 13 victory over the Lions.

impact: The All-World talent hit the ground on a non-contact injury and immediately pointed to his foot. Having been held out since Week 8 with a toe injury, it's likely Green's season is now done. He's officially been ruled out for the remainder of Week 13 against Denver.
report: A.J. Green (foot) was carted off Week 13 against the Broncos.

impact: It was Graham's best game in a long time; the 32-year-old tight end has recently battled thumb and knee injuries.  Graham will draw another plus matchup in Week 14 against the Falcons.  Despite his inconsistency, Graham remains a low-end TE1 play each week.
report: Jimmy Graham caught 8-of-11 targets for 50 yards in Green Bay's Week 13 loss to Arizona.

impact: Coming off a 90-yard game against the Packers, Gore's 67 yards rushing were his third most of the season. The ageless back is now averaging 4.54 yards per carry but has found the end zone just one time all year. He's a low-upside FLEX in the Dolphins' pop-gun offense.
report: Frank Gore rushed 14 times for 67 yards in the Dolphins' Week 12 loss to the Colts, adding a 10-yard reception.

impact: It was a wholly nondescript game from Gore. He did enter the medical tent to get his ankle looked at in the third quarter, but it did not affect his stat line. Still without a rushing touchdown this season, Gore will be a low-upside FLEX next week against the Patriots.
report: Frank Gore rushed eight times for 21 yards and hauled in his only target for 10 yards in the Dolphins' Week 13 win over the Bills.

impact: Gordon's five targets were his fewest in six games. They were a result of the Patriots going run heavy. Gordon has now cleared 70 yards in three of his past four games, though he has not caught more than five passes in the process. The WR2 should see plenty of Xavier Rhodes when the Patriots host the Vikings in Week 13.
report: Josh Gordon caught 5-of-5 targets for 70 yards in the Patriots' Week 12 win over the Jets.

impact: Gordon didn't see any looks from Tom Brady during the first half, but he came alive with 58 yards after the break with 48 of them coming on one drive. Brady found Gordon wide-open for a 24-yard touchdown, breaking a 10-10 tie with 0:35 remaining in the third quarter. Gordon's workload has taken a hit since Rob Gronkowski's return from back and ankle injuries, though the 27-year-old will still have his fair share of big games. He'll need to bring his A-game next week against Dolphins shutdown corner Xavien Howard.
report: Josh Gordon corralled three balls for 58 yards and a touchdown on three targets Sunday in New England’s Week 13 victory over the Vikings.

impact: Golladay nearly had a sixth grab for a late touchdown but could not quite get full extension. Golladay is lucky he got the numbers he did, as the Lions' offense was embarrassingly horizontal. Golladay has re-proven himself in Marvin Jones' (knee) absence, but Jones could be back for Week 13 against the Rams. Even if he is, Golladay will be an upside WR2/3 in a game where the Lions will have no choice but to go more vertical.
report: Kenny Golladay caught 5-of-8 targets for 90 yards in the Lions' Thanksgiving loss to the Bears.

impact: Two of his three grabs came before halftime. Even with shutdown corner Aqib Talib on a strict snap count in his return from ankle surgery, Golladay was unable to find daylight. Golladay nearly came down with an incredible touchdown during garbage time, but much to the dismay of fantasy owners, he couldn't keep both feet in bounds. The second-year receiver will have his work cut out for him going against shutdown corner Patrick Peterson next week in Arizona.
report: Kenny Golladay managed three catches for 50 yards on seven targets Sunday in the Lions’ Week 13 loss to the Rams.

impact: It was a quiet game for Godwin, who operates as a rotational receiver in the Bucs' deep passing game. Godwin is plenty capable of turning in big box-score games, but he doesn't always get enough opportunity to convert competing for targets with Mike Evans, Adam Humphries, DeSean Jackson, and Cameron Brate, among others.  Godwin will be a fringe WR3/flex in Week 13 against Carolina.
report: Chris Godwin caught 4-of-4 targets for 42 yards in the Bucs' Week 12 win.

impact: Godwin got half his yards on a wide open 40-plus yard catch and run. His TD came on a broken play in the red-zone. It’s the first touchdown for Godwin in last seven games. Godwin will be on the WR3 map if DeSean Jackson can’t return next week
report: Chris Godwin caught 5-of-6 targets for 101 yards and a touchdown in Week 13 against the Panthers.

impact: Gallup's brother committed suicide on Sunday, but he somehow was able to play today ahead of the funeral on Friday.  His six targets tied Ezekiel Elliott for second on the team.  This offense can really only support Zeke and Amari Cooper.
report: Michael Gallup caught 2-of-6 targets for 19 yards in the Cowboys' Week 12 win over the Redskins.

impact: The 76 yards were Gallup's second most of the season. The rookie should have had an even-bigger night, but Dak Prescott flat missed him on what would have been a guaranteed 55-yard touchdown. Gallup left Eli Apple in the dust with a double move. With some of the pressure removed, Gallup has actually been more productive since Amari Cooper's acquisition. He will have some low-end WR4 appeal for Week 13 against the Eagles.
report: Michael Gallup caught 5-of-7 targets for 76 yards in the Cowboys' Week 13 win over the Saints.

impact: It was the second week in a row Gabriel matched a season high with seven catches. Gabriel will lack WR3 upside for however long Mitchell Trubisky (shoulder) is sidelined. There does seem to be a decent chance that Trubisky is back for Week 13 against the Giants.
report: Taylor Gabriel caught 7-of-8 targets for 49 yards in the Bears' Week 12 win over the Lions.

impact: Gabriel lost a critical fumble inside his own 15-yard line to set up an Aldrick Rosas field goal to put the Giants up by 10 with less than two minutes to play.  The Bears were able to force overtime later, but Gabriel's day was one to forget.  Gabriel will be a big-play WR4 next week against the Rams.
report: Taylor Gabriel caught 3-of-7 targets for 17 yards in the Bears' Week 13 loss to the Giants.

impact: It's a step back after Gates blew up for 80 yards and a touchdown last week. Even in a plus matchup with the Steelers, Gates should be avoided as a Week 13 streaming option.
report: Antonio Gates caught one pass for 18 yards in the Chargers' Week 12 win over the Cardinals.

impact: The 28 yards from scrimmage were Ingram's fewest of the season. The Saints' offense was simply stuck in neutral against an inspired Cowboys defense. Mired in a three-game fantasy slump, Ingram will have an excellent chance at breaking it in Week 14 when the Saints take on the Bucs in Tampa Bay.
report: Mark Ingram rushed seven times for 27 yards in the Saints' Week 13 loss to the Cowboys, adding two receptions for one additional yard.

impact: Crowder was playing for the first time since Week 5.  He was the top slot man in this one, but Mark Sanchez threw for just 100 yards in relief of Colt McCoy (broken leg, 50 yards).  Crowder has no ceiling and a scary-low floor moving forward with Sanchez under center.  He doesn't need to be owned.
report: Jamison Crowder caught all four of his targets for 36 yards in the Redskins' Week 13 loss to the Eagles.

impact: The game was tied 13-13 late in the third quarter, but the Jets never got their run game in order, instead letting backup quarterback Josh McCown attempt 45 passes. Crowell won the touch and yardage battles with Elijah McGuire but got out-snapped 35-26 (via Pro Football Focus). Crowell will have a shot at positive game script in Week 13 against the Titans but is unlikely to have an RB2 day against a strong defense.
report: Isaiah Crowell rushed six times for 30 yards in the Jets' Week 12 loss to the Patriots, adding three receptions for 30 additional yards.

impact: He added four catches for  nine yards on five targets, finishing fourth on the team in looks from Josh McCown.  Crowell had been struggling badly for the better part of two months before this one.  The 21 carries marked a new season-high for Crowell and his 98 rushing yards were his most since Week 5.  Crowell should have a chance to get volume again next week against the Bills.
report: Isaiah Crowell rushed 21 times for 98 yards in the Jets' Week 13 loss to the Titans.

impact: Cousins had his way with an injury-ravaged Packers secondary, throwing just nine incompletions. He hit Dalvin Cook and Stefon Diggs for long touchdowns, with his final one coming on a red-zone strike to Adam Thielen in the third quarter. Cousins had been under some heat after a rough three-game stretch, so it's a needed bounceback. The Vikings get a matchup with the Patriots in Week 13.
report: Kirk Cousins completed 29-of-38 passes for 342 yards and three touchdowns in the Vikings' Week 12 win over the Packers.

impact: He was sacked twice for a loss of 18 yards. Coming off a stellar performance in last week's win over Green Bay, Cousins fell apart Sunday, averaging a dismal 4.6 yards per attempt in the loss to New England. Cousins delivered his lone touchdown on a five-yard strike to Adam Thielen with time winding down in the first half. His interceptions were both of the desperation variety. Cousins targeted Aldrick Robinson deep in the fourth quarter but couldn't connect as the ball deflected off Jonathan Jones before Duron Harmon collected it in the end zone. His second interception came on a pass intended for Thielen with only a few seconds remaining. Next week's game in Seattle will be a must-win for the Vikings, who sit at a lackluster 6-5-1 with four games left on the schedule.
report: Kirk Cousins completed 32-of-44 passes for 201 yards with a touchdown and two interceptions Sunday in the Vikings’ Week 13 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Crabtree gashed his former team for an eight-yard touchdown on a quick slant from Lamar Jackson early in the fourth quarter. That was his only catch of the second half. Crabtree is a familiar name to fantasy owners, but he's not the same player he was early in his career. With Baltimore turning to a run-first approach, fantasy owners shouldn't expect much from Crabtree down the stretch. He'll be tough to trust, even with a favorable matchup on tap against Atlanta in Week 13.
report: Michael Crabtree chipped in with three catches for 21 yards and a touchdown on six targets Sunday in the Ravens’ Week 12 win over the Raiders.

impact: Crabtree has seven catches for 64 yards since Lamar Jackson was inserted under center three weeks ago. The Ravens will have to open it up more against the Chiefs in Week 14, but Crabtree will still be hard to recommend as a WR4. Joe Flacco's return would further complicate matters, as it would not be as an every-snap starter.
report: Michael Crabtree caught 3-of-4 targets for 36 yards in the Ravens' Week 13 win over the Falcons.

impact: It was a relatively quiet week for Cooks, but he still reached an impressive milestone, going over 1,000 yards for the fourth time in his career. In doing so, Cooks became the first player in league history to top 1,000 yards receiving three straight years for three different teams. Cooks was going against Matt Patricia on Sunday (both former Patriots), which may explain why the Lions were able to contain him. Cooks and the Rams will be featured against the Bears on Sunday Night Football in Week 14.
report: Brandin Cooks corralled four-of-six targets for 62 yards Sunday in the Rams’ Week 13 win over Detroit.

impact: It was a rollercoaster afternoon for Cook, who committed an ugly first-half drop and also had a long catch negated by offensive pass interference. The Raiders' offense predictably struggled in a tough road game, though Cook salvaged the afternoon for his fantasy owners by hauling in a 16-yard touchdown strike from Derek Carr with around five minutes to go in the third quarter. Cook made a terrific adjustment on an under-thrown ball by Carr, though replay showed he may have been out at the one-yard line. The 31-year-old has already matched a career-high with five touchdowns this season. He'll look for No. 6 when the Raiders host Kansas City in Week 13.
report: Jared Cook pulled in two-of-five targets for 32 yards and a touchdown Sunday in the Raiders’ Week 12 loss to the Ravens.

impact: After struggling last week against the Jaguars, Conner was not able to get much going early in this one. He recorded just 24 yards on seven first-half carries, although he did add 19 yards on three catches. He started to get things going after the break, gaining 28 yards on five carries, but that momentum came to halt when he lost a fumble at the end of the third quarter. He did not touch the ball again until he was given a shot to redeem himself with under two minutes left in the game, but he was stuffed on second-and-goal. Ben Roethlisberger was intercepted on the next play. Conner has slowed down the last couple weeks, but he will still be a solid RB1 next week against the Chargers.
report: James Conner rushed 13 times for 53 yards and hauled in all four of his targets for 42 yards in the Steelers' Week 12 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Cook didn't do much on the ground, but he got the Vikings' scoring start on a screen he took for a 26-yard touchdown. It was his best receiving effort since Week 1. Cook was held in check last week, but he's had over 100 total yards or a touchdown in two of the last three games. He'll be an RB2 for a matchup with the Patriots in Week 13.
report: Dalvin Cook had 10 carries for 29 yards and caught three passes for 47 yards and a touchdown in the Vikings' Week 12 win over the Packers.

impact: Cook made things happen whenever he touched the ball, particularly in the first half when he picked up 73 yards on 10 touches. Unfortunately, he wasn't called on much with the Vikings playing from behind in the second half. Cook's eight catches represented a new career-high, though he averaged a lethargic 2.6 yards per reception with a long of only 10 yards. On the bright side, Cook out-touched backfield-mate Latavius Murray by a convincing 17-6 margin. Cook can be comfortably employed as an RB2 against the Seahawks in Week 14.
report: Dalvin Cook rolled to 84 yards on nine carries while supplying eight catches for 22 yards on 10 targets Sunday in the Vikings’ Week 13 loss to New England.

impact: Ito Smith was not any better. The Falcons barely bothered with the running game against the Ravens' elite defense. Coleman has just 18 touches for 34 yards over his past two games. He is averaging 4.01 yards per carry on the season. Barely even a FLEX in fantasy over the past month, Coleman will be a risky play for the first week of the fantasy playoffs in Green Bay.
report: Tevin Coleman rushed six times for eight yards in the Falcons' Week 13 loss to the Ravens, adding a three-yard reception.

impact: Cooper beat Quinton Dunbar for his first touchdown from 40 yards out then broke away from a weak Fabian Moreau tackle attempt for his monster 90-yard score.  Cooper has seen at least eight targets in 3-of-4 games with the Cowboys and has put together a 22-349-3 line for Dallas.  Cooper has been a legitimate WR2 with upside since the trade and gets New Orleans next Thursday.
report: Amari Cooper caught 8-of-9 targets for 180 yards and two touchdowns in the Cowboys' 31-23, Week 12 win over the Redskins on Thanksgiving.

impact: Cooper also lost a first half fumble where Marshon Lattimore kneed the ball out. The Cowboys are now 4-1 since Cooper's acquisition, with the wideout posting at least 75 yards three times in the process. He has added the desired new element to the Cowboys' offense. He will have a juicy Week 14 matchup against the Eagles' undermanned secondary.
report: Amari Cooper caught 8-of-8 targets for 75 yards in the Cowboys' Week 13 win over the Saints.

impact: Cole only played extensively because D.J. Chark was inactive due to injury.  Cole has been off the fantasy radar for several weeks.
report: Keelan Cole went catch-less on two targets in Week 12.

impact: Cole has lacked fantasy value for several weeks.
report: Keelan Cole caught 2-of-2 targets for 16 yards in Week 13.

impact: Cohen's missed connection was a should-have-been touchdown on a wheel route. Chase Daniel missed the throw. Daniel then atoned on a subsequent wheel route, finding Cohen for a 14-yard score in the fourth quarter. Cohen has just 166 yards from scrimmage over his past four games but has scored twice in the process. He will be in the RB2/FLEX mix for Week 13 against the Giants.
report: Tarik Cohen caught 7-of-8 targets for 45 yards and a touchdown in the Bears' Thanksgiving victory over the Lions, adding three rushes for 14 additional yards.

impact: Jordan Howard was the offense's focal point in the first half, rushing for 68 yards, but Howard had just eight yards after the break while Cohen simply took the game over for Chicago.  His 14 targets were five more than Allen Robinson for the team lead.  Cohen was called upon with the Bears down 27-20 on 4th-and-goal from the one-yard line with three seconds left in the fourth quarter to throw a one-yard touchdown to Anthony Miller and send the game to OT.  Cohen will be a borderline RB1/2 next week in a showdown at home against the Rams.
report: Tarik Cohen rushed eight times for 30 yards and caught 12-of-14 targets for 156 yards in the Bears' 30-27, Week 13 overtime loss to the Giants, adding a one-yard touchdown pass.

impact: Clement was the change-of-pace to Josh Adams, who had 22 carries and dropped his lone target.  This was one of Clement's better games of the season.  He's settled in behind Adams and doesn't have standalone fantasy value.
report: Corey Clement rushed five times for 45 yards and caught both of his targets for 31 yards in the Eagles' Week 12 win over the Giants.

impact: He now has 150 yards on 15 touches the last two weeks, solidifying himself as the pass-game complement to Josh Adams, who again went catch-less.  Darren Sproles returned to handle just four carries, turning them into 22 yards and a touchdown, but wasn't targeted in the pass game.  Clement is not a fantasy option but offers real-life value, though he's had a down year.
report: Corey Clement rushed five times for 27 yards and caught all three of his targets for 47 yards in the Eagles' Week 13 win over the Redskins.

impact: Cobb caught a flare pass in the second half for a 20-plus-yard gain, but it was negated by RT Jason Spriggs' holding penalty.  In a timeshare with Equanimeous St. Brown, Marquez Valdes-Scantling, and perhaps Jake Kumerow behind Davante Adams, Cobb will be tough to trust even as a WR4 in Week 14 versus Atlanta.
report: Randall Cobb caught 3-of-5 targets for 25 yards in the Packers' Week 13 loss to the Cardinals.

impact: This was Clay's first game since Week 9, and he probably wishes he had not returned, especially against his former team. After seeing just one target all game, Clay found himself wide open in the end zone on fourth down with time running out, but he dropped what would have been the game-winning touchdown. Josh Allen did not put enough on it as he scrambled around, but it was a catchable pass. Clay is not a fantasy option.
report: Charles Clay caught 1-of-2 targets for nine yards in the Bills' Week 13 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: Chubb got the day started with a 1-yard score on the ground on the opening drive of the game. He then added a 14-yard touchdown catch to put the Browns ahead 28-0 in which he ran a wheel route and pinned the ball to the back of the defender for his second score of the game. Chubb now has scored in four of his five games as a starter. He will enter Week 13 as a high-end RB2 on the road against the Texans.
report: Nick Chubb rushed 28 times for 84 yards with one touchdown while catching all three of his targets for 44 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 12 win over the Bengals.

impact: With the Browns falling behind by 23 points in the first half, Chubb received just 12 touches, his fewest in a game since taking over as the starting running back. Despite the circumstances of playing catchup, Chubb still managed to find the end zone for a 2-yard touchdown run in the second half and out-touched Duke Johnson 12-2 in the game. Chubb has worked his way into the top-portion of the weekly RB2 options and will once again be a starting option in Week 14 against the Panthers.
report: Nick Chubb rushed nine times for 31 yards and a touchdown while catching three passes for 41 yards in Sunday's Week 13 loss to the Texans.

impact: Carson opened Seattle’s second drive with a 16-yard run, but he was mostly bottled up early in this one. He also fumbled in the second quarter, but the ball ended up going out of bounds. It was a great break for Carson. Following that fumble, Russell Wilson marched the offense right down the field, and Carson capped the long drive with a one-yard score. He opened the second half with a 15-yard run in which he went flipping through the air after trying to hurdle the tackler, eventually landing on his feet and gaining a couple more yards, and opened the next drive with a 12-yard run. He was mostly bottled up from there, but Carson once again dominated the backfield work. The workhorse on a run-first offense, Carson will be a solid RB2 next week against the 49ers.
report: Chris Carson rushed 16 times for 55 yards and a touchdown in the Seahawks' Week 12 win over the Panthers.

impact: Carr was sacked three times for a loss of 12 yards. Playing one of the league's toughest defenses on the road with a depleted receiving corps, Carr's afternoon was doomed from the start. Carr was checked for a concussion late in the first half and also tweaked his ankle in the fourth quarter, though neither injury was serious. The five-year vet lost a costly fumble, which Terrell Suggs scooped up for a 43-yard touchdown with just under six minutes remaining in the fourth quarter. On a more positive note, Carr has now gone six straight games without throwing an interception. The Raiders could be in for another rough game when the 9-2 Chiefs visit in Week 13.
report: Derek Carr completed 16-of-34 passes for 194 yards and a touchdown Sunday in Oakland’s Week 12 loss to the Ravens.

impact: In the midst of a miserable season, Carr converted an excellent matchup. He locked onto top targets Jared Cook and Jordy Nelson and also managed to find Marcell Ateman and backup TE Lee Smith for scores. Carr could have had a bigger day had his running backs not killed three separate drives with fumbles. The good feeling is unlucky to last long, as the Steelers will provide a much stiffer test in Week 14.
report: Derek Carr completed 29-of-38 passes for 285 yards and three touchdowns in the Raiders' 40-33, Week 13 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Callaway's 62 yards were his most in a game since Week 2. He was a popular target of Baker Mayfield when on the move, with Mayfield finding him on a 13-yard score on the second drive of the game when Mayfield bought time moving to his left and then finding Callaway driving across the back of the end zone. Callaway has improved his efficiency over the past few weeks in a reduced role, catching 14-of-18 targets for 188 yards and two scores over his past four games. The Browns head to Houston in Week 13.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 4-of-5 targets for 62 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 12 win over the Bengals.

impact: Callaway had an adventurous series of plays in the third quarter, having a 77-yard touchdown reception called back due to a holding penalty and then two plays later, catching a pass in traffic down the field and then taking it 71 yards only to be stripped at the 1-yard line and lose the fumble. After sitting out all 2017, Callaway has shown positive signs over the back half of his rookie season. Over his past five games, Callaway has caught 17-of-24 targets for 272 yards and two touchdowns. He is still not a viable fantasy option when the Browns host the Panthers in Week 14.
report: Antonio Callaway caught 3-of-6 targets for 84 yards in Sunday's Week 13 loss to the Texans.

impact: His biggest play was a first-quarter gain that came directly in Richard Sherman's coverage for 42 yards, setting up Cameron Brate's six-yard touchdown.  Evans has now gone over 100 yards in consecutive games.  Week 13 opponent Carolina held Evans to 16 yards on ten targets in the teams' earlier-season meeting.  Evans will look to exact his revenge on James Bradberry in the rematch.
report: Mike Evans caught 6-of-8 targets for 116 yards in the Bucs' Week 12 win over the 49ers.

impact: Evans saw fewer targets than Adam Humphries and didn't have many red-zone looks. It's a disappointing game with DeSean Jackson sidelined. This breaks a two week stretch of at least 100 yards for Evans. Evans should rebound in blowup Week 14 spot against the Saints.
report: Mike Evans caught 4-of-6 targets for 48 yards in the Bucs' Week 13 win over the Panthers.

impact: After his 2-15 day on three targets against the Saints a week ago, Ertz rebounded in predictable fashion against a bad Giants defense.  The eight targets tied Golden Tate (4-30) for the team lead.  Ertz has easily been the best tight end in fantasy along with Travis Kelce and gets the Redskins in Week 13.
report: Zach Ertz caught 7-of-8 targets for 91 yards and one touchdown in the Eagles' 25-22, Week 12 win over the Giants.

impact: He was the best player on the field once again, leading the team in catches and targets.  Golden Tate and Jordan Matthews happened to be the red-zone beneficiaries in this one, however, catching short touchdowns from Carson Wentz.  Ertz did set the new single-season franchise record for catches and has four games to add to it.  He'll be a top-three TE1 next week at Dallas.
report: Zach Ertz caught 9-of-10 targets for 83 yards in the Eagles' Week 13 win over the Redskins.
