impact: He added five catches for 22 yards on six targets.  Elliott waltzed through a gaping hole untouched into the end zone for his 16-yard rushing score.  The Cowboys later bungled a first-and-goal from the four-yard line situation by not giving it to Elliott and then settling for a field goal.  Elliott has 643 yards and four touchdowns over his last four games since the bye, three resulting in Cowboys wins, who are now first in the NFC East.  Elliott will get the Saints next Thursday night.
report: Ezekiel Elliott rushed for 121 yards and one touchdown on 26 carries in the Cowboys' 31-23, Week 12 win over the Redskins on Thanksgiving.

impact: It was not an efficient night for Elliott against the Saints' elite run defense, but he made up for it with sheer volume. He already had 18 touches at halftime. Elliott's score was a perfectly-delivered 16-yarder on a screen. It was his third receiving touchdown of the season, which is a new career high. Elliott has now caught at least five passes in four-straight games. The workload monster will remain a top-four RB1 for Week 14 against the Eagles.
report: Ezekiel Elliott rushed 23 times for 76 yards in the Cowboys' Week 13 win over the Saints, adding six receptions for 60 additional yards and a touchdown.

impact: It's a monster game from Ekeler, though most of his rushing production came in the second half. He scored a goal-line TD after Melvin Gordon left in the third quarter. Ekeler wasn't limited by the next injury that cost him practice time this week. He would have plug-and-play RB2 value if Gordon misses time.
report: Austin Ekeler rushed five times for 35 yards and a touchdown and caught 10-of-11 targets for 68 yards in Week 12 against the Cardinals.

impact: Ekeler got the start with Melvin Gordon sidelined. He had just eight carries for one yard in the first half but found some success in the pass game. Ekeler was outplayed by Justin Jackson, who totaled 72 yards and a touchdown. Even if Gordon doesn't return next week, Ekeler figures to take a backseat to Jackson.
report: Austin Ekeler had 13 carries for 21 yards and caught 5-of-8 targets for 21 yards in Week 14 against the Steelers.

impact: Edmonds was out-touched by David Johnson 21 to 7, but Edmonds was more effective in scoring position with eight- and six-yard touchdown runs.  Johnson also blew an early-game blitz pickup to get Josh Rosen sacked, which may have contributed to Edmonds' increased playing time.  Edmonds still won't be a fantasy option when Arizona returns home to face the reeling Lions in Week 14.
report: Chase Edmonds rushed five times for 53 yards and two touchdowns and caught 2-of-2 targets for 13 yards in the Cardinals' Week 13 upset of Green Bay.

impact: For some reason, Ellington also added a two-yard rush. Ellington now has 12 catches on 16 targets in two games as a Lions. We suppose that will play in PPR for Week 13 against the Rams if Marvin Jones (knee) can't get cleared.
report: Bruce Ellington caught 6-of-7 targets for 28 yards in the Lions' Week 12 loss to the Bears.

impact: He also threw an incomplete pass. Working as the Lions' slot receiver—a role once occupied by target monster Golden Tate—Ellington again saw huge usage but did nothing with it. The fifth-year vet has logged 19 catches in three games since joining the Lions last month but somehow has just 115 yards to show for it. Ellington's volume keeps him in play as a cheap DFS lineup-filler, though he shouldn't be counted on in season-long leagues. The Lions are in Arizona next week.
report: Bruce Ellington absorbed seven-of-10 targets for 35 yards Sunday in the Lions’ Week 13 loss to Los Angeles.

impact: Edwards went ballistic against Oakland, bull-dozing his way to a new career-high in yards while Alex Collins (foot) watched in street clothes. Gus the Bus crushed it in the second half, blowing up for 65 yards on 15 carries after the break. Edwards had to be thinking end zone when Baltimore advanced to the Raiders' three-yard-line early in the fourth quarter, but a false start pushed the Ravens back five yards, costing the undrafted rookie a chance at a goal-line touchdown. He wasn't a factor in the passing game, ceding most of those opportunities to newcomer Ty Montgomery. The impressive rookie is closing in on must-start territory and will be employable as an RB2 next week in Atlanta, even if Collins returns from injury.
report: Gus Edwards rumbled to 118 yards on 23 carries Sunday in Baltimore’s Week 12 win over the Raiders.

impact: Edwards was not targeted in the passing game. Edwards, who entered the game battling an ankle issue, also limped off late but was never announced with an injury. Coach John Harbaugh did not mention it during his post-game presser. A returning Kenneth Dixon stole eight carries, but it remained Edwards' backfield. There is every reason to believe Edwards will remain a volume-based RB2 for next week's game against the Chiefs, though his lack of pass-catching prowess will make him a little more volatile in what could turn into a track meet.
report: Gus Edwards rushed 21 times for 82 yards in the Ravens' Week 13 win over the Falcons.

impact: Edelman started out wide open on his 21-yard touchdown but had to fight for the final few yards near the goal line. There was a scary moment in the first half where Edelman landed extremely hard on his right elbow/shoulder. He spent a few moments shaking it out on the field and did not appear to miss any plays. Edelman has now gone over 70 yards in four-straight games. He's a high-floor WR2.
report: Julian Edelman caught 4-of-5 targets for 84 yards and a touchdown in the Patriots' Week 12 win over the Jets.

impact: His afternoon included a pair of drops with both of them coming on crucial third downs. The 25 yards were a season-low for Edelman, though he made up for his lack of receiving success with a pair of long runs. The 10th-year slot man will look to redeem himself next week when the Patriots face Miami. He was suspended for the Patriots' first meeting with the Dolphins back in Week 4.
report: Julian Edelman collected three catches for 25 yards on eight targets while adding two carries for 35 yards Sunday in the Patriots’ Week 13 win over the Vikings.

impact: Coming off a zero-target game against the Titans, Ebron rebounded against the Dolphins' embarrassingly-bad tight end defense. The seven targets were by far the most he has drawn in four games since Jack Doyle's return. Doyle did also manage to find the end zone this afternoon. Although highly volatile, Ebron is Andrew Luck's go-to target in the red zone. Week 13 opponent Jacksonville has been bleeding tight end fantasy points.
report: Eric Ebron caught 5-of-7 targets for 45 yards and two touchdowns in the Colts' Week 12 win over the Dolphins.

impact: Unfortunately, Ebron also lost a fumble and nine yards on a rushing attempt to cost him nearly three fantasy points.  He was a PPR machine, though, pacing the Colts in targets and never coming off the field with Jack Doyle on IR and Mo Alie-Cox sidelined.  Next up is a Week 14 matchup with the Texans, who have been the weakest team in football in tight end pass coverage.
report: Eric Ebron caught 10-of-15 targets for 81 yards in the Colts' Week 13 loss to the Jaguars.

impact: He saw just three targets. Funchess played limited snaps but managed to find the end-zone after having an earlier touchdown called back. The Panthers didn't push Funchess in his first game back form a neck injury, but he should be back to his normal role for Week 14 against the Browns.
report: Devin Funchess caught a 10-yard touchdown in Week 13 against the Bucs.

impact: The clear No. 2 in the backfield, Freeman could not get anything going on his limited attempts in this one. He also lost the goal-line opportunity to Phillip Lindsay, who managed to score from two yards out. Freeman is just a handcuff at this point.
report: Royce Freeman rushed six times for 17 yards in the Broncos' Week 12 win over the Steelers.

impact: Don't let his touches fool you. Six of Freeman's 12 carries came during the team's final two possessions when they were leading by two scores. It was Phillip Lindsay who continued to pave the way to RB1 stardom, finishing with 19/157/2 on a team-high 19 carries. Lindsay's also out-touched Freeman 34-18 in the duo's last two games. Unless something drastic happens mid-week, Freeman is merely a handcuff at this point.
report: Royce Freeman rushed 12 times for 48 yards in the Broncos' Week 13 victory over the Bengals.

impact: They were his only two targets. Fitzgerald scored a 25-yard touchdown on the Cardinals opening drive and caught a five-yard pass on the final play of the game. After a slow start, he's now up to five touchdowns in the last five weeks. Fitzgerald will be a WR3 for Week 13 against the Packers.
report: Larry Fitzgerald caught two passes for 30 yards and a touchdown in Week 12 against the Chargers.

impact: It was a quiet game for Fitzgerald, who finally made his mark on a highlight-reel fourth-quarter 32-yard catch that set up Zane Gonzalez's game-winning 44-yard field goal.  Fitzgerald will be a better WR3 play in Week 14 against the Lions, who get smashed by slot receivers constantly.
report: Larry Fitzgerald caught 3-of-6 targets for 48 yards in the Cardinals' Week 13 upset of the Packers.

impact: Meet Marcell Ateman, the Raiders' new No. 1 receiver. The seventh-round rookie saw an exhausting 10 targets in Sunday's defeat, though obviously he wasn't able to take advantage of his monster usage. Ateman played three fewer snaps than teammate Jordy Nelson, but out-targeted him by a commanding 10-1 margin. His fantasy appeal is still limited by Oakland's stagnant offense, but at least he's getting volume. We'll see what kind of workload Ateman sees when the Raiders return home to face the Chiefs in Week 13.
report: Marcell Ateman delivered three catches for 16 yards on 10 targets Sunday in the Raiders’ Week 12 loss to the Ravens.

impact: It was the first score of the seventh-round rookie's career. Ateman nearly had a 32-yarder early in the third quarter but could not hook up with Derek Carr. Although he is playing heavy snaps, Ateman is not producing enough to gain WR5 consideration in re-draft leagues.
report: Marcell Ateman caught 2-of-4 targets for 16 yards and a touchdown in the Raiders' Week 13 loss to the Chiefs.

impact: Andrews made the most of his one target, producing the Ravens' longest play of the season with a 74-yard grab on a deep bomb from Lamar Jackson early in the second quarter. The third-round rookie has quietly emerged as Baltimore's top receiving tight end, though the former Oklahoma Sooner remains well off the fantasy radar. Andrews and the Ravens will take a two-game winning streak into next week's matchup with the struggling Falcons.
report: Mark Andrews converted his lone target for a 74-yard gain Sunday in the Ravens’ Week 12 victory over Oakland.

impact: The No. 86 overall pick has emerged as the top dog of the Ravens' pass-catching tight ends, but it is not translating to fantasy value. He will remain off the re-draft radar for the remainder of 2018.
report: Mark Andrews caught 3-of-3 targets for 47 yards in the Ravens' Week 13 win over the Falcons.

impact: Amendola ended up barely playing after injuring his knee early. He spent a ton of time in the medical tent before ultimately being cleared to return. Return he did not, however, as it appeared he was only available on an emergency basis. Amendola entered Week 12 battling a hamstring issue. He will be genuinely questionable for next Sunday's game against the Bills.
report: Danny Amendola caught 1-of-1 targets for 13 yards in the Dolphins' Week 12 loss to the Colts.

impact: Anderson was making just his second appearance since Week 7. He was supposedly going to be on a snap count, but Pro Football Focus charted him as taking the field for 48-of-64 plays. Anderson was the intended target on Josh McCown's arm punt interception. Anderson had good chemistry with McCown in 2018, but he will not be a viable WR3 if McCown makes another start in Week 13 against the Titans. He will offer big-play WR4 upside.
report: Robby Anderson caught 2-of-5 targets for 22 yards in the Jets' Week 12 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Anderson led the team in receiving on a day Josh McCown threw for just 128 scoreless yards.  Anderson has long been off the redraft map at wideout.
report: Robby Anderson caught 4-of-7 targets for 48 yards in the Jets' Week 13 loss to the Titans.

impact: The yards were a team high, but Allen saw fewer targets than Austin Ekeler. With Tyrell Williams not fully healthy, it's a slightly disappointing game from Allen, though he made a highlight-reel sideline catch in the end-zone for his TD. Allen will remain a high-end WR2 for a likely shootout with the Steelers in Week 13.
report: Keenan Allen caught seven passes for 72 yards and a touchdown in Week 12 against the Cardinals.

impact: He also caught a two-point conversion. Allen's touchdown came on a deflection off Steelers CB Joe Haden in the middle of the end-zone. It's the fourth straight week with a touchdown for Allen, who's now up to 996 yards on the season. Allen has another attackable matchup against the Bengals in Week 14.
report: Keenan Allen caught 14-of-19 targets for 148 yards and a touchdown in the Chargers' Week 13 win over the Steelers.

impact: Allen was far from perfect as a passer, but he hit Robert Foster for a 75-yard touchdown bomb and was dynamic on the ground, nearly scoring another touchdown late in the game during clock-killing mode.  Allen's week-to-week consistency has been all over the place in his rookie campaign, but he has certainly "flashed" when well protected and put in comfortable situations.  Allen will be a two-quarterback-league starter in Week 13 at Miami.
report: Josh Allen completed 8-of-19 passes for 160 yards and a touchdown and rushed 12 times for 100 yards and an additional score in the Bills' Week 12 win over the Jaguars.

impact: Following a slow start, Allen got the offense moving in the second quarter with his legs, a weapon he used to great effect each of the last two games, before escaping the pocket to the right and hitting Zay Jones at the back of the end zone for a 15-yard touchdown. He had Jones wide open in the end zone again on the first drive of the third quarter, but he threw behind him on what looked like a miscommunication. He made up for it with a great throw on the run in his own end zone to pick up a third down on the next drive, and he briefly gave Buffalo the lead by threading a pass to Jones for a 25-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter. Following a Dolphins score, Allen led what should have been a game-winning drive, but Charles Clay dropped an underthrown pass in the end zone to end the game. The rookie did have a bad interception in the second half – his other pick came on a Hail Mary just before halftime – but this was a solid performance. He will be a two-QB option next week.
report: Josh Allen completed 18-of-33 passes for 231 yards, two touchdowns, and two interceptions while rushing for 135 yards on nine carries in the Bills' Week 13 loss to the Dolphins.

impact: Even with Alex Collins (foot) absent, Allen was barely heard from, seeing the field on just one of the Ravens' 70 offensive snaps. Allen was used extensively as a receiving back early in the year, but that role is currently being filled by newcomer Ty Montgomery. With Gus Edwards, Collins and Montgomery all working ahead of him, Allen could end up being a healthy scratch when the Ravens travel to Atlanta for Week 13.
report: Javorius Allen rushed once for two yards Sunday in Baltimore’s Week 12 win over the Raiders.

impact: Agholor has been a non-factor the last two weeks with Golden Tate taking on a bigger role.  Agholor is not a fantasy option ahead of Week 13 vs. Washington.
report: Nelson Agholor caught his lone target for 12 yards in the Eagles' Week 12 win over the Giants.

impact: It was his best game in three weeks.  The eight targets were more than everyone besides Zach Ertz (10), and his 56 yards were more than Alshon Jeffery (3-31 on five targets), who flopped again.  Still, Agholor's production has been real spotty since the Golden Tate trade and isn't a fantasy play.
report: Nelson Agholor caught 4-of-8 targets for 56 yards in the Eagles' Week 13 win over the Redskins.

impact: Adams had a 52-yard touchdown run called back on the opening series due to a Jason Kelce holding penalty.  Adams then hurt his shoulder and missed the second series, going into halftime with four carries for four yards.  He dropped his lone target in the pass game after seeing six looks a week ago.  Adams got rolling after the break, however, as the Eagles overcame a 19-3 deficit.  Adams had some long runs in the second half and converted his goal-line carry for a one-yard score before then adding a two-point conversion.  Corey Clement pitched in 76 yards on seven touches.  Adams will be an RB2 next week against the Redskins in a must-win.
report: Josh Adams rushed 22 times for 84 yards and one touchdown in the Eagles' 25-22, Week 12 win over the Giants.

impact: NFL Network's Mike Garafolo has repeatedly reported Adams is "good to go," and Adams "got fist bumps" from GM Howie Roseman and coach Doug Pederson during Monday evening's pre-game warmup.  As a home-favorite running back with 20-plus touch upside, Adams is an upside RB2 against a sagging Washington defense.
report: Josh Adams (hip) will play on Monday Night Football against Washington.

impact: Adams was stonewalled on a pair of first-half carries on second- and fourth-and-goal from the two-yard line and then never got another chance to score in this one, with Jordan Matthews catching a short touchdown and Darren Sproles running one in from 14 yards out.  Adams' volume has been really nice of late, but he offers nothing in the pass game as a TD-or-bust RB2.
report: Josh Adams rushed 20 times for 85 yards in the Eagles' Week 13 win over the Redskins.

impact: Adams beat Vikings CB Xavier Rhodes in a one-on-one red-zone matchup for a 15-yard touchdown. He went without a target for a long stretch, but salvaged his night on the Packers' final drive. Adams went over 1,000 yards on the season and has at least 80 yards or a touchdown in every game. He gets a matchup with Cardinals CB Patrick Peterson in Week 13.
report: Davante Adams caught 5-of-8 targets for 69 yards and a touchdown in Week 12 against the Vikings.

impact: Albeit in a losing effort, Adams overcame yet another bad cornerback matchup, something he's made a habit of all season.  He was shadowed for the majority of the contest by Patrick Peterson, yet put on a clinic with an early 13-yard touchdown on a fourth-and-four play, and a 19-yard toe-tapping sideline catch in the fourth quarter to set up Aaron Jones' eight-yard TD.  One of Green Bay's precious few 2018 bright spots, Adams will remain a high-floor, high-upside WR1 when the Packers host the Falcons next.
report: Davante Adams caught 8-of-13 targets for 93 yards and a touchdown in Green Bay's Week 13 loss to Arizona.

impact: On one hand, Uzomah's 13 targets are a positive, but turning them into just 3.0 yards per target is disgusting. Uzomah has had lackluster results since forced into the starting lineup, catching 29 passes for 283 yards and two touchdowns on the season. Uzomah is a TE2 option at best in Week 13 against the Broncos.
report: C.J. Uzomah caught 6-of-13 targets for 39 yards in Sunday's Week 12 loss to the Browns.

impact: Per usual, Uzomah saw a lucrative number of targets but did absolutely nothing with them. He's somehow turned 20 targets into a bumbling 72 yards and no scores in the past two games. He'll stay a suck-it-up usage-based TE1 for those looking to stream next week against the Chargers.
report: C.J. Uzomah caught 5-of-7 targets for 33 yards in the Bengals' Week 13 loss to the Broncos.

impact: This was the worst game of the season for Rodgers, who was under countless pressures and took four sacks. The Packers' play calling continued to put them in bad spots, and Rodgers rarely had time to go through his progressions. Rodgers' only touchdown came on a timing route to Davante Adams in the first quarter. The Packers are out of playoff contention with the loss. Rodgers will look to rebound against the Cardinals in Week 13.
report: Aaron Rodgers completed 17-of-28 passes for 198 yards and a touchdown in Week 12 against the Vikings.

impact: He rushed three times for 20 yards and averaged an anemic 4.7 yards per attempt.  Rodgers took only one sack, but he faced consistent pressure from Arizona's underrated pass rush and got nothing going in the deep passing game.  Despite Rodgers dropping back to pass 51 times, the Packers didn't record a single 20-yard reception.  In a stumbling offense, Rodgers has been among fantasy football's biggest 2018 disappointments.  Even in a Week 14 home game versus Atlanta, Rodgers must be downgraded to a boom-bust QB1 throwing to day-three rookie receivers in an archaic offense with come-and-go pass protection.
report: Aaron Rodgers completed 31-of-50 passes for 233 yards and a touchdown in the Packers' Week 13 loss to Arizona.

impact: Sanu now has at least three catches in five-straight games but has not scored or cleared 75 yards in the process. He's producing as a standard "No. 3 receiver in a high-volume passing offense." He's a WR5 for fantasy purposes.
report: Mohamed Sanu caught 3-of-4 targets for 37 yards in the Falcons' Week 13 loss to the Ravens.

impact: He was the Jaguars' leading receiver in a game where Cody Kessler passed for just 150 yards, operating as a game-managing checkdown specialist.  Nevertheless, this was a reminder Yeldon has just as much fantasy value as Carlos Hyde if not more if Leonard Fournette misses any time going forward.  Yeldon out-touched Hyde 15 to 14 and outgained him 65 to 37.  Hyde also lost a fumble.  Fournette is due back for Week 14 at Tennessee.
report: T.J. Yeldon rushed eight times for 16 yards and caught 7-of-8 targets for 49 yards in the Jaguars' Week 13 win over the Colts.

impact: Ryan crushed between the 20's, averaging 8.0 YPA and completing 74.4% of his passes throughout the evening. The story of the night was still Atlanta's dreadful lack of urgency and play-calling as New Orleans' defense dominated with six sacks, five forced fumbles, and just 26 yards on the ground. To sum it all up, just know Ryan comically led the Falcons with 16 rushing yards. Atlanta's three lost fumbles in the red zone didn't help matters, either. Now sitting at 4-7, it wouldn't be shocking to hear OC Steve Sarkisian's name thrown around as a potential free agent at the end of the season. Despite his continued fantasy production, Ryan will be a mid-tier QB1 in Week 13 against Baltimore's nightmarish secondary.
report: Matt Ryan completed 35-of-47 passes for 377 yards, two touchdowns, and one interception in the Falcons' Week 12 loss to the Saints.

impact: Ryan also lost a fumble that was housed for a game-sealing, 12-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter. The Ravens blitzed on first down and Ryan was not expecting it. With zero running game and Julio Jones battling a hand injury, the Falcons could not sustain drives against the Ravens' elite defense. It was Ryan's worst showing since his miserable Week 1 in Philadelphia. He will have an excellent chance at bouncing back against the folding Packers in Week 14.
report: Matt Ryan completed 16-of-26 passes for 131 yards and a touchdown in the Falcons' 26-16, Week 13 loss to the Ravens.

impact: Jared Goff hung Woods out to dry on a first-half hospital ball as the wideout took a lick from Detroit cornerback Quandre Diggs. Luckily Woods bounced back, finding the end zone for his fifth touchdown of the year with 2:28 remaining in the second quarter. Woods hauled in a low throw from Goff while beating his man Darius Slay in coverage. Sunday's effort leaves Woods on the cusp of his first career 1,000-yard season. He'll look to reach that milestone against Chicago in Week 14.
report: Robert Woods snagged five-of-nine targets for 67 yards and a touchdown while adding 11 yards on two rushing attempts Sunday in L.A.’s Week 13 win over the Lions.

impact: He added seven carries for 24 yards.  Most importantly, Winston avoided turnovers in a high-efficiency effort, also taking just one sack and finding Adam Humphries (28 yards) and Cameron Brate (6) for scores.  Winston's ups and downs have been maddeningly frustrating all year, but this is the kind of performance he is capable of when on his game.  Winston will remain a high-upside Q1 play when Tampa Bay hosts a burnable Carolina defense next.
report: Jameis Winston completed 29-of-38 passes for 312 yards and two touchdowns in the Bucs' Week 12 win over the 49ers.

impact: Winston also led the Bucs with 48 yards rushing. It's the second straight turnover-free game from Winston, who's managed consecutive wins since retaking the starting job. Both of Winston's touchdowns were short red-zone throws to Adam Humphries and Chris Godwin. Winston get another great matchup in a likely Week 14 shootout with the Saints.
report: Jameis Winston completed 20-of-30 passes for 249 yards and two touchdowns in Week 13 against the Panthers.

impact: With the running game scuffling early, the Seahawks put the ball in Wilson’s hands on the third drive, and he quickly marched them down the field, although he did miss a wide-open Doug Baldwin in the end zone. Wilson did even better a couple drives later, leading a 75-yard touchdown march in which he accounted for 68 of them. After halftime, Wilson led another 80-yard touchdown drive, 54 of those coming on a long pass to David Moore, which he capped with a 12-yard strike to Tyler Lockett. His best throw of the afternoon was a 35-yard touchdown to Moore on 4th-and-three to tie the game late in the fourth quarter, and he found Lockett for a 43-yard gain to set up the game-winning field goal. Wilson still is not throwing much, but he has multiple touchdowns in all but one game this season. He will be a great option next week against the 49ers.
report: Russell Wilson completed 22-of-31 passes for 339 yards and two touchdowns in the Seahawks' Week 12 win over the Panthers.

impact: Wilson only threw six passes in the first half, but he made them count. The first found a wide open Jaron Brown for a 45-yard gain, and after a lifetime in the pocket, he found Brown again for a four-yard score to end that drive. He followed that up with a 52-yard touchdown to Tyler Lockett on the next drive, and he found Doug Baldwin from one yard out just before halftime. Wilson did not have much more to do in the second half, but he was able to tack on yet another score with an 18-yard strike to Brown in the fourth quarter. Wilson now has multiple touchdowns in all but one game this season and is easily on pace to set a new career-high in touchdowns. He will remain a solid QB1 next week against the Vikings on Monday night.
report: Russell Wilson completed 11-of-17 passes for 185 yards and four touchdowns in the Seahawks' Week 13 win over the 49ers.

impact: Williams caught both of Philip Rivers’ first half TDs. He didn't have a huge role despite Tyrell Williams playing injured but was a factor in the red-zone. Williams could be on the WR3 radar if Tyrell has a setback this week.
report: Mike Williams caught four passes for 25 yards and two touchdowns in Week 12 against the Cardinals.

impact: Williams' touch counts were 1, 1, and 3 over his previous three games, so to say this came out of nowhere would be an understatement.  Williams has been a black hole nearly all season, and Aaron Jones has been on absolute fire.  In the end, the Packers got exactly what they deserved in an embarrassing 20-17 home loss to a terrible Cardinals team.
report: Jamaal Williams rushed seven times for 13 yards and caught 4-of-4 targets for 14 yards in Green Bay's Week 13 loss to Arizona.

impact: Wilkins was held without a rush. That won't be the case in Week 13 if Marlon Mack is forced to sit with his concussion. If Mack is out, Wilkins will have FLEX appeal as a committee mate to Nyheim Hines.
report: Jordan Wilkins caught 3-of-3 targets for 32 yards in the Colts' Week 12 win over the Dolphins.

impact: The 73 yards rushing were a new season high by 29. Tom Brady completed a modest 20 passes as the Pats ran the ball 36 times, leading to White's quiet day through the air. White entered Week 12 having caught at least five passes in seven-straight games. The Vikings have done a solid job of limiting running back receiver production, but White should still bounce back across the board as an RB2 for Week 13.
report: James White rushed nine times for 73 yards in the Patriots' Week 12 win over the Jets, adding a five-yard reception.

impact: White had a phenomenal first half, coming down with five grabs for 80 yards before the break. On a day when Rob Gronkowski (3-26-0) and Julian Edelman (3-25-0) were non-existent, White filled the void, feasting off screens from Tom Brady. This was the fourth time White has led the Patriots in receiving yards this year. Next up are the Dolphins, who White demolished for 112 yards and two touchdowns back in Week 4.
report: James White carried the ball six times for 26 yards while snagging seven-of-nine targets for a team-leading 92 receiving yards Sunday in the Patriots’ Week 13 win over the Vikings.

impact: Westbrook has been the Jags' lone semi-consistent pass catcher, and he was one of the team's few bright spots in this disappointing loss.  His touchdown did come in what amounted to fourth-quarter garbage time, narrowing the deficit to 24-21 with Buffalo already up two scores.  Westbrook draws a plus Week 13 matchup against Indianapolis, where he will be a WR3/flex option.
report: Dede Westbrook rushed once for 43 yards and caught 3-of-4 targets for 44 yards and a touchdown in the Jaguars' Week 12 loss to Buffalo.

impact: He also rushed once for a loss of one.  As Cody Kessler threw for just 150 yards in the Jaguars' 6-0 upset of Indianapolis, no pass catchers on the team so much as cleared 50 yards.  All Jacksonville pass catchers will remain difficult to trust on Thursday Night Football against Tennessee.
report: Dede Westbrook caught 3-of-5 targets for 25 yards in the Jaguars' Week 13 win over Indianapolis.

impact: Wentz connected with Zach Ertz for a 15-yard touchdown in the second quarter to start the comeback from 19-3 down.  Wentz hasn't done much for fantasy owners the last two weeks against the Saints and Giants in cupcake spots.  He'll be a back-end QB1 next week against the Redskins after Dak Prescott just lit Washington up for his best game of the year on Thursday.
report: Carson Wentz completed 20-of-28 passes for 236 yards and one touchdown in the Eagles' Week 12 win over the Giants.

impact: This was as easy a win as they get in the NFL.  The Redskins were...wait for it...forced to turn to never-was and never-will-be Mark Sanchez at quarterback in this one after Colt McCoy broke his leg in the first half.  This was a game most were begging to just end.  Wentz's first touchdown was a short hookup to Golden Tate for the duo's first TD connection in four games.  The second passing score went to Wentz's BFF Jordan Matthews.  The 6-6 Eagles travel to Dallas for a must-win against the 7-5 Cowboys for the top spot in the NFC East next week.
report: Carson Wentz completed 27-of-39 passes for 306 yards, two touchdowns, and one interception in the Eagles' 28-13, Week 13 win over the Redskins.

impact: Watson's 70 rushing yards marked a new season-best, and he scored on the ground for the first time since Week 4.  His 24 attempts was also the sixth-straight game he's thrown the ball 25 times or fewer.  Watson needs the rushing output at that low passing volume for fantasy purposes, and he was able to get it tonight, scoring on a designed run from 15 yards away.  His two air scores were 12- and 10-yard connections with Demaryius Thomas.  Watson gets the Browns in Week 13.
report: Deshaun Watson completed 19-of-24 passes for 210 yards and two touchdowns in the Texans' 34-17, Week 12 win over the Titans on Monday night, adding 70 yards and a third touchdown on the ground.

impact: Watson added 30 yards rushing on seven attempts. He started the day off on fire, connecting on his first 11 passes of the game. He then went on to complete 17-of-22 passes in the first half for 191 yards, including an 11-yard touchdown to Jordan Thomas. With the Texans up 23-0 at the half, they took their foot off the gas and cruised the remainder of the game. Watson has now thrown for 239 yards or fewer in seven straight games, but has still offered upside with his legs and efficiency at times, making him an up and down fantasy option despite his strong play overall. The Texans will host a soft Colts defense in Week 14.
report: Deshaun Watson completed 22-of-31 passes for 224 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 13 win over the Browns.

impact: Rudolph didn't have a huge impact on the game, though he did contribute one highlight, pulling in a 23-yard catch over Patrick Chung with time winding down in the first half. It's been a frustrating season for the eighth-year tight end, who will take a nine-game touchdown drought into next week's action against Seattle. He's best viewed as a TE2 going forward.
report: Kyle Rudolph nabbed three catches for 38 yards on three targets Sunday in the Vikings’ Week 13 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Ross found the end zone for his third consecutive game, but once again his touchdown anchored his day. Ross has now secured 7-of-20 targets for 97 yards over the past three games with A.J. Green sidelined. While his touchdown streak is a positive to build on, Ross is still only a WR4 option in Week 13 against the Broncos.
report: John Ross caught 3-of-7 targets for 31 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 12 loss to the Browns.

impact: Even with A.J. Green (foot) being carted off mid-game, Ross wasn't able to overcome Jeff Driskel's inability to escape Denver's pass rush. With Green in and out of the lineup over the last four games, Ross has hauled in 9-of-20 targets for 110 yards. He's not a viable option in the fantasy playoffs.
report: John Ross vacuumed 2-of-3 targets for 13 yards in the Bengals' Week 13 loss to the Broncos Sunday.

impact: It was another dismal game from Rosen, who failed to move the offense outside of an opening drive touchdown. Rosen's pass attempts have been down since OC Byron Leftwich took over playing calling and he has the lowest completion percentage in the league. He'll be a low-end QB2 for Week 13 against Packers.
report: Josh Rosen completed 12-of-19 passes for 105 with a touchdown and an interception in Week 12 against the Chargers.

impact: One of his best plays was a 33-yard scramble.  The Cardinals' pass catchers struggle to get open and their offensive line is missing multiple starters, so weak box scores have become the norm for their rookie quarterback.  Rosen did make a handful of impressive throws, notably to "Trent Sherfield" for a 21-yard gain and Larry Fitzgerald for 32 yards on what amounted to Arizona's game-winning drive.  Rosen will remain a two-quarterback-league play only in Week 14 versus Detroit.
report: Josh Rosen completed 11-of-26 passes for 149 yards in the Cardinals' Week 13 win over the Packers.

impact: 29 of Robinson's yards came on a tough grab against sticky Darius Slay coverage, but backup quarterback Chase Daniel simply was not looking his way. Trying to avoid mistakes, Daniel was staying underneath. Robinson will be an upside WR3 for Week 13 against the Giants if Mitchell Trubisky (shoulder) can get cleared.
report: Allen Robinson caught 2-of-4 targets for 37 yards in the Bears' Week 12 win over the Lions.

impact: Robinson's big plays were a 30-yard grab off the helmet of CB B.W. Webb and then a catch on 4th-and-7 in traffic to extend the game late.  Robinson hasn't scored since his two-score Week 10.  He'll be a WR3 next week against the Rams.
report: Allen Robinson caught 5-of-9 targets for 79 yards in the Bears' Week 13 loss to the Giants.

impact: The bulk of his output came on a 44-yard catch on Oakland's opening drive of the second half. He was also on the receiving end of a 34-yard strike from Derek Carr, but that play was called back on offensive pass interference as Roberts appeared to push off his defender. The undrafted 27-year-old has never been a difference-maker, though injuries to Oakland's other pass-catchers have forced him into a larger-than-expected role this season. Even in deeper leagues, Roberts won't be a recommended play when the Raiders host Kansas City in Week 13.
report: Seth Roberts corralled two-of-three targets for a team-high 54 yards Sunday in the Raiders’ Week 12 loss to Baltimore.

impact: Pittsburgh moved the ball almost at will in the first half, but they just could not find the end zone. Their first drive ended with a blocked field goal, their second ended with a fumble at the goal line, and they needed a fake field goal to score just before halftime. Those miscues had nothing to do with Roethlisberger, who finished the first half with 221 yards. Ben’s best throw of the day came in the third quarter. Standing in his own end zone, Roethlisberger managed to find JuJu Smith-Schuster despite pressure in his face, and the receiver took it 97 yards for a touchdown. It was mostly downhill from there. Ben allowed the Broncos back into the game with an interception, another drive ended with a fumble, and he threw a terrible interception in the end zone to end the game. Despite giving the game away, Roethlisberger topped 450 yards for the second time this season. He will remain a solid QB1 despite a tough matchup against the Chargers on Sunday night.
report: Ben Roethlisberger completed 41-of-56 passes for 462 yards, a touchdown, and two interceptions in the Steelers' Week 12 loss to the Broncos.

impact: It’s another mixed game from Roethlisberger, who now has six interceptions over three weeks. The Steelers rolled the Chargers in the first half before blowing their lead in the final two quarters. Roethlisberger rallied for a tying touchdown late, but it wasn’t enough to avoid another loss. The Steelers are now just a half-game ahead of the Ravens in the AFC North. Roethlisberger gets a cupcake matchup with the Raiders in Week 14.
report: Ben Roethlisberger completed 29-of-45 passes for 281 yards with two touchdowns and an interception in the Steelers' Week 13 loss to the Chargers.

impact: Ridley appeared to score a fluky 14-yard touchdown on a batted ball in the fourth quarter, but the play was called back by penalty. The 22 yards were Ridley's fewest since Week 1. The Falcons simply could not get anything going against the Ravens' elite defense. A bounce back should be in order for Week 14 against the Packers.
report: Calvin Ridley caught 3-of-5 targets for 22 yards in the Falcons' Week 13 loss to the Ravens.

impact: Even with Oakland in catch-up mode in the second half, which is usually when Richard shines, the third-year receiving back was mostly a non-factor. That was probably to be expected playing on the road against one of the league's better defenses. Richard will hope for better results when the Chiefs come to town in Week 13. Fantasy owners can employ him as a PPR flex in that matchup.
report: Jalen Richard rushed for a yard on his lone carry Sunday while adding two catches for 15 yards on four targets Sunday in Oakland’s Week 12 loss to Ravens.

impact: The seven-catch performance was Riddick's third of the season. Even if Kerryon Johnson (knee) is cleared to return for Week 13, Riddick will have some PPR FLEX appeal against the Rams in a game where the Lions are going to have to throw more than they want to.
report: Theo Riddick caught 7-of-7 targets for 48 yards in the Lions' Thanksgiving loss to the Bears, adding two rushes for 12 additional yards.

impact: The eight carries for Riddick were his most since week 16 of last season, though obviously he didn't do much with them. Even with the Lions in catch-up mode late, which is generally when he thrives, Riddick failed to make his presence felt. Riddick did draw a red-zone target in Sunday's defeat, though Matthew Stafford was hit as he threw, resulting in an incompletion. The six-year vet will look to end his 12-game touchdown drought when the Lions visit Arizona in Week 14.
report: Theo Riddick produced 32 yards on eight carries while also totaling three grabs for 26 yards on four targets Sunday in the Lions’ Week 13 loss to the Rams.

impact: Rivers had a perfect first half, completing all 19 of his attempts for 187 yards and two TDs. He tied an NFL record with 25 consecutive completions in style on a four-yard score to Keenan Allen. Rivers could have had a bigger game but was rested early in the fourth quarter. He's now had multiple touchdown passes in every game this season. Rivers gets a matchup with the Steelers on Sunday night in Week 13.
report: Philip Rivers completed 28-of-29 passes for 259 yards and three touchdowns in Week 12 against the Cardinals.

impact: Rivers stayed hot after throwing 25 straight completions last week. He hit Travis Benjamin on a 46-yard bomb for his first touchdown, and later found Keenan Allen on a pass that was deflected in the end-zone. Rivers has shed his turnover-prone ways this year, throwing for 3,418 yards and a 28:6 TD/INT ratio through 12 games. He'll be a top-five quarterback play against Cincinnati's barely-there secondary in Week 14.
report: Philip Rivers completed 26-of-36 passes for 299 yards and two touchdowns in the Chargers' Week 13 win over the Steelers.

impact: Reed was nowhere to be found for much of the first half, catching his lone target for seven yards.  He was a tad more involved after the break, but the Redskins were simply horrible as a team and did nothing of note besides get their heads beat into the dirt.  Reed will be tough to trust with Mark Sanchez under center.
report: Jordan Reed caught 4-of-5 targets for 21 yards in the Redskins' Week 13 loss to the Eagles.

impact: He had only two targets. There wasn't much opportunity for Valdes-Scantling on a night Aaron Rodgers threw for only 198 yards. Valdes-Scantling is in the midst of a bad two-game stretch, but still has value as the No. 2 receiver on the Packers. He'll try to rebound in a Week 13 matchup with the Cardinals.
report: Marquez Valdes-Scantling caught one pass for three yards in Week 12 against the Vikings.

impact: Valdes-Scantling had an early drop, and the rest of his missed targets were off-the-mark throws from Aaron Rodgers on a day where Green Bay didn't complete a single 20-plus-yard pass.  Valdes-Scantling's usage has been all over the map lately.  He will be a boom-bust WR4 play in Week 14 against the Falcons.
report: Marquez Valdes-Scantling caught 2-of-7 targets for 19 yards in the Packers' Week 13 loss to Arizona.

impact: Sutton was held without a catch in the first quarter, but he made a great grab with a defender on his back early in the second. Unfortunately, that was it for the rookie despite three more targets, one of which he dropped, in the second half. Sutton has not seen the big target boost most expected following the Demaryius Thomas trade, but this was his first really bad fantasy game. He is worth keeping around for a great matchup against the Bengals next week.
report: Courtland Sutton hauled in 1-of-4 targets for 14 yards in the Broncos' Week 12 win over the Steelers.

impact: The story of Sutton's season had been drops, overthrown targets, and downfield DPIs. It all finally came out in the wash Sunday as he maneuvered his burly 6'3", 218-pound frame for several deep receptions, including a 30-yard jump-ball that hit pay dirt. Despite having an extremely volatile floor, Sutton's boom-or-bust style of play is tolerable if he continues seeing a team-high share of targets. Unfortunately, he'll be a dicey option in Week 14 on the outside against the Niners and stud corner Richard Sherman.
report: Courtland Sutton hauled in 4-of-7 targets for a season-high 85 yards and one score in the Broncos' Week 13 win over the Bengals.

impact: Switzer’s career-high was just 32 yards heading into Sunday, but he was a big part of the game plan early in this one. He recorded 57 yards on four catches in the first half including a 24-yard gain just before halftime to help set up Pittsburgh’s first touchdown. Things obviously slowed down in the second half, and it seems unlikely he is able to carve out a real role behind Antonio Brown and JuJu Smith-Schuster. Still, he is a name to watch in deeper PPR leagues.
report: Ryan Switzer hauled in 6-of-8 targets for 67 yards in the Steelers' Week 12 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Stills has been held to one catch in four of his past five games. The sixth-year pro deserves better than this, but he is safely droppable in coach Adam Gase's conservative offense.
report: Kenny Stills caught 1-of-4 targets for six yards in the Dolphins' Week 12 loss to the Colts.

impact: Despite complaining about his target total during the week, Stills was on his way to another disappointing game heading into the fourth quarter. He saved his best for last, however. With the Dolphins down, Stills made a great play on the ball to turn what probably should have been a Ryan Tannehill interception into the game-winning touchdown. If Danny Amendola sits out again next week, Stills will be a WR4 option against the Patriots.
report: Kenny Stills hauled in 4-of-6 targets for 37 yards and a touchdown in the Dolphins' Week 13 win over the Bills.

impact: He went from starter to backup in Randall Cobb's (hamstring) return.
report: Equanimeous St. Brown missed his lone target in Green Bay's Week 13 loss.

impact: Missing Marvin Jones and Kerryon Johnson, the Lions played unwatchable football, running a horizontal offense that treated Stafford like Sam Darnold. Of course, Stafford uncorked two awful picks, the first of which was housed for a touchdown by Eddie Jackson. Forced into a "hot" throw, Stafford never saw Jackson, who was jumping the route all the way. Stafford's second interception was essentially a game ender to a confused Michael Roberts in the end zone. Playing genuinely bad football for the Lions' retrograde offense, Stafford is barely even a QB2 right now.
report: Matthew Stafford completed 28-of-38 passes for 236 yards, zero touchdowns and two interceptions in the Lions' 23-16 Thanksgiving loss to the Bears.

impact: Stafford was sacked four times for 37 yards and was also charged with a lost fumble. This was probably as much as fantasy owners could have hoped for given the Lions' concerning lack of offensive weaponry (their leading receiver on Sunday was blocking tight end Levine Toilolo). Stafford's lone touchdown came on a trick play where he threw to offensive lineman Taylor Decker, who was announced as an eligible receiver. Aaron Donald was a thorn in his side all day, dropping him for two sacks while also forcing a fumble, which the Rams recovered deep in Detroit territory. Stafford will aim to get back on track next week when the Lions travel to Arizona for Week 14.
report: Matthew Stafford completed 20-of-33 passes for 245 yards with a touchdown and an interception while also tacking on a two-yard carry Sunday in the Lions’ Week 13 loss to Los Angeles.

impact: He wasn't targeted in the pass game with Corey Clement keeping those duties.  Sproles scored from 14 yards out as he walked into the end zone on a perfectly-blocked play.  It was the 35-year-old's first game since Week 1 due to hamstring issues.  Sproles won't be a fantasy option the last four weeks.
report: Darren Sproles rushed four times for 22 yards and one touchdown in the Eagles' Week 13 win over the Redskins.

impact: Lamar Jackson completed just 12 passes, so there simply was not any volume for the Ravens' passing attack. Snead now has just six catches in three games with Jackson under center. Snead won't be a recommended WR5 even if Joe Flacco returns for Week 14. There are simply too many better options with bye weeks over.
report: Willie Snead caught 1-of-3 targets for eight yards in the Ravens' Week 13 win over the Falcons.

impact: Thompson played his first game since Week 8 and did nothing of note.  He reclaimed pass-game work but made zero plays.  It's been a season to forget for Thompson.  He's off the fantasy radar until further notice.
report: Chris Thompson rushed three times for three yards and caught 3-of-5 targets for 18 yards in the Redskins' blowout loss to the Eagles in Week 13.

impact: His 38 yards were a season-low mark. Thomas' team-high six targets were encouraging, but Brees ultimately attempted only 22 passes as the Saints rolled to an easy win behind a dominating defensive effort. Thomas has admittedly cooled off of late due in part to New Orleans simply routing teams out of the gates the past three weeks. Assuming their upcoming Thursday night showdown against Dallas' surging offense stays competitive, Thomas should return to being a strong WR1 in Week 13.
report: Michael Thomas caught 4-of-6 targets for 38 yards in the Saints' Week 12 destruction of the Falcons.

impact: Thomas was also drawing penalties left and right, but that does not show up in the box score for fantasy owners. Although he's in the midst of a monster fantasy campaign, Thomas has cleared 100 yards in just 3-of-12 contests. He's hit the century mark once since September. He has a safe, even floor but ceiling has been unpredictable. Thomas does have a circle-the-calendar Week 14 matchup with the Bucs. Thomas ripped Tampa to shreds for 16/180/1 in Week 1.
report: Michael Thomas caught 5-of-8 targets for 40 yards in the Saints' Week 13 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: His 11-yard touchdown was the lone offensive touchdown for the Texans on the day and the fourth touchdown that Thomas has scored on the season. The rookie tight end  has stepped up as one of the team's top red zone options over the past five weeks, but is still a touchdown dependent fantasy option, catching more than two passes in just two games on the season. The Texans host the Colts in Week 14.
report: Jordan Thomas caught all three of his targets for 32 yards and a touchdown in Sunday's Week 13 win over the Browns.

impact: The touchdowns were Thomas' first two with the Texans in his third game with the team.  It was a much-needed breakout for the veteran after combining for three catches and 61 scoreless yards on four targets across his first two games.  Thomas scored from 12 yards out in the first quarter, beating Adoree Jackson, and added a 10-yard score in the fourth quarter to put the game out of reach.  Thomas' volume is still real low, but he'll be a WR3 next week vs. Cleveland.
report: Demaryius Thomas caught 4-of-5 targets for 38 yards and two touchdowns in the Texans' 34-17, Week 12 win over the Titans on Monday night.

impact: Even with Keke Coutee sidelined, Thomas still only managed four targets Sunday, which was third on the team. In four games with the Texans, Thomas has received just 13 total targets, catching 10 for 131 yards and two touchdowns. Thomas is not a viable fantasy option to close the season.
report: Demaryius Thomas caught 3-of-4 targets for 32 yards in Sunday's Week 13 win over the Browns.

impact: Taylor had been sidelined since getting hurt in Week 9 and immediately came back to notch a 100-yard game.  Taylor beat Morris Claiborne for a 55-yard grab down the left side.  Marcus Mariota actually missed Taylor earlier in the game for what should have been a long touchdown after Taylor got wide open behind the defense.  Taylor will be a WR5 next week against Jacksonville.
report: Taywan Taylor caught 3-of-5 targets for 104 yards in the Titans' Week 13 win over the Jets.

impact: Thielen was invisible for much of the first half, delivering his first catch of the game on a five-yard touchdown strike from Kirk Cousins with 15 ticks remaining in the second quarter. He was slightly more involved in the second half, though Jason McCourty did a nice job defending him. Thielen was the intended target on the second of Cousins' two interceptions. This wasn't one of Thielen's better performances, though he still boasts a monster 98-1,166-9 receiving line for the season. Those are WR1 numbers. He'll try to bounce back against the Seahawks in Week 14.
report: Adam Thielen registered five grabs for 28 yards and a touchdown on 10 targets Sunday in the Vikings’ Week 13 loss to the Patriots.

impact: Making his first start since Week 5, Tannehill added three rushes for 14 additional yards. The good news is that Tannehill's 33-yard first quarter strike to Kenyan Drake was the Dolphins' first offensive touchdown in 27 possessions. The bad news is, coach Adam Gase treated Tannehill like he was Sam Darnold in crunch time, calling unimaginative, horizontal plays as the Dolphins watched a 24-14 lead disappear. Tannehill's second score was a 74-yard jump ball against CB Pierre Desir where Leonte Carroo did most of the work. Although better than Brock Osweiler, Tannehill is one of the league's most limited regular starters. He will struggle for QB2 value in Week 13 against the Bills.
report: Ryan Tannehill completed 17-of-25 passes for 204 yards and two touchdowns in the Dolphins' 27-24, Week 12 loss to the Colts.

impact: Despite taking some big hits, Tannehill started out this game hot, completing 4-of-5 passes for 43 yards and a touchdown on the opening drive. He mostly struggled the rest of the first half, but he was able to take advantage of a Bills turnover just before the break, finding Kenyan Drake in the flat for a three-yard score. Miami’s offense did absolutely nothing in the third quarter, and Tannehill followed up a Josh Allen interception with one of his own. He quickly bounced back, however, leading a touchdown drive to give Miami the lead. He capped that march with a dangerous throw to the back of the end zone, but Kenny Stills bailed him out with a great play. This was not a great game from Tannehill, but he did enough for the win. He will be a weak two-quarterback league option next week against the Patriots.
report: Ryan Tannehill completed 16-of-24 passes for 137 yards, three touchdowns, and an interception in the Dolphins' Week 13 win over the Bills.

impact: The eight targets tied Zach Ertz for the team lead, but Ertz did far more with his at 7-91-1.  Tate had a brutal drop as well.  Tate has seen 16 targets over the last two games but isn't doing anything downfield or breaking big plays.  Tate will be a low-end WR3/4 next week against the Redskins.
report: Golden Tate caught 4-of-8 targets for 30 yards in the Eagles' Week 12 win over the Giants.

impact: It was easily Tate's best game with the team after totaling 97 scoreless yards on 20 targets his first three contests since the trade.  Tate's score was a scramble effort by Carson Wentz, who barely snuck the ball pass the diving cornerback in the corner of the end zone from a few yards away.  The Redskins just offered zero resistance in this one.  Tate has been getting heavy usage at the expense of Alshon Jeffery and Nelson Agholor.  Tate will be a WR3 in Dallas next week.
report: Golden Tate caught all seven of his targets for 85 yards and one touchdown in the Eagles' 28-13, Week 13 win over the Redskins on Monday night.

impact: Yikes. That is going to leave a mark if you forced Smith into your lineup for the final week of the fantasy regular season. There wasn't much Smith could do against a swarming Cowboys defense on an evening where Drew Brees completed just 18 passes for 127 yards. Smith and the entire Saints offense has a perfect Week 14 bounce-back spot in the Bucs.
report: Tre'Quan Smith was held without a catch on one target in the Saints' Week 13 loss to the Cowboys.

impact: Smith-Schuster found his inner Jarvis Landry early in this one. He recorded eight catches on nine targets in the first half, but he managed just 39 yards on those grabs. All of that changed in a flash in the third quarter. With the Steelers backed up against their own goal line, Smith-Schuster got loose down the sideline, Ben Roethlisberger was able to find him despite taking a hit, and the receiver out-ran everyone for a 97-yard touchdown. Amazingly, it is the second 97-yard catch of Smith-Schuster’s career, both the longest passing plays in Steelers’ history, and he also scored a 96-yard kickoff return last season. Smith-Schuster did not pack it in after that grab. With the game on the line late in the fourth, Smith-Schuster caught two 19-yard passes to help get the Steelers in position for the win -- a Roethlisberger interception ended the comeback. Smith-Schuster faces a tough matchup next week against the Chargers, but he will remain a high-end WR2.
report: JuJu Smith-Schuster hauled in 13-of-17 targets for 189 yards and a touchdown in the Steelers' Week 12 loss to the Broncos.

impact: Smith out-touched Tevin Coleman 8-7. One of his carries was a thundering stuff on an early fourth down. The Falcons' running game has been bordering on nonfunctional for some time now. Smith will be off the fantasy radar for Week 14 against the Packers.
report: Ito Smith rushed seven times for 22 yards in the Falcons' Week 13 loss to the Ravens, "adding" a zero-yard reception.

impact: Smith caught his first target for a gain on two then was left completely uncovered in the middle of the field, caught a short pass and ran virtually untouched straight up the middle for a 61-yard score in the first quarter.  He curiously wasn't heard from again.  Smith has seen his role increased in recent weeks with Taywan Taylor (foot) out, but he's still very unreliable as a TE2.
report: Jonnu Smith caught both of his targets for 63 yards and a touchdown in the Titans' Week 12 loss to the Texans.

impact: The TE2 will get the Jaguars next week.  He went 1-9 on two targets against them in Week 3.  Smith has touchdowns here and there, but they're unpredictable.
report: Jonnu Smith caught 2-of-3 targets for 29 yards in the Titans' Week 13 win over the Jets.

impact: The five targets were a three-game high but Shepard continues to do very little on the stat sheet.  The 34 yards were actually the most he's had in that span.  Shepard has devolved into a WR4 ahead of Week 13 against Chicago.
report: Sterling Shepard caught 3-of-5 targets for 34 yards in the Giants' Week 12 loss to the Eagles.

impact: This has become the new normal for Shepard in this broken passing offense.  Saquon Barkley and Odell Beckham are the only players this scheme can support heading into a Week 14 division game at the Redskins.
report: Sterling Shepard caught 4-of-6 targets for 28 yards in the Giants' Week 13 win over the Bears.

impact: He had just two targets. Seals-Jones continued to have a low-volume role despite Chad Williams missing another game. He's droppable in fantasy leagues.
report: Ricky Seals-Jones caught one pass for five yards in Week 12 against the Chargers.

impact: Seals-Jones has been too inefficient this season for fantasy usefulness.
report: Ricky Seals-Jones caught 1-of-3 targets for 10 yards in Week 13.

impact: Samuel did not do anything early in this game, but he announced his presence by gaining 25 yards on a well-designed end around midway through the second quarter to help set up his seven-yard touchdown catch two plays later. He was limited to just one catch the rest of the way as D.J. Moore and Christian McCaffrey dominated targets, but Samuel has consistently flashed his playmaking ability when given a chance this season.
report: Curtis Samuel rushed once for 25 yards and hauled in both of his targets for 17 yards and a touchdown in the Panthers' Week 12 loss to the Seahawks.

impact: The 11 targets were a season high. Samuel also led the Panthers in receiving with Greg Olsen (foot) leaving early and Devin Funchess not playing full snaps. Samuel would be in line for a larger role if Olsen misses time.
report: Curtis Samuel caught 6-of-11 targets for 88 yards in Week 13 against the Bucs.

impact: Sanders was the focus of the passing game against his former team, recording six targets in the first half. He did not do much with the work, but he was just a hair away from a long catch early in the second quarter. His fortunes changed in the second half. Following a Steelers interception, Case Keenum found Sanders for a 38-yard catch and then hit him again the very next play for a five-yard score. The score was Sanders’ first since Week 7 and just his fourth of the season. He will be a decent bet to add to that total in a great matchup against the Bengals next week.
report: Emmanuel Sanders hauled in 7-of-12 targets for 86 yards and a touchdown in the Broncos' Week 12 win over the Steelers.

impact: With Courtland Sutton bullying his coverage (and, in turn, hogging targets) on the outside, Sanders fell victim to low volume as the Broncos laid waste to the Bengals behind Phillip Lindsay's 19/157/2 breakout day. There's nothing to see here considering Case Keenum only threw the ball 21 times Sunday. Sanders will be a tremendous bounce-back candidate (and DFS buy-low option) as he'll likely avoid Richard Sherman by staying in the slot against the Niners in Week 14.
report: Emmanuel Sanders caught 4-of-6 targets for 19 yards in the Broncos' Week 13 win over the Bengals.
